""#if _HLSL \n\nstruct VS_OUTPUT { \n  float4 vTex : TEXCOORD0; \n  float4 vPos : SV_Position; \n#if !_PSSL \n  float4 vPosXRight : NV_X_RIGHT;  \n  uint4 vViewportMask : NV_VIEWPORT_MASK;  \n#endif \n}; \n  const uniform float4 c_avMapAdj[2] : register(c0); \n  VS_OUTPUT main( float4 vInPos : TEXCOORD0) { \n  VS_OUTPUT o; \n#ifdef INV_Z \n  o.vPos = float4( vInPos.xy, 0.99999f,1); \n#else \n  o.vPos = float4( vInPos.xy, 0.00001f,1); \n#endif \n#if !_PSSL \n  o.vPosXRight = o.vPos; \n  o.vViewportMask = 0x00020001; \n#endif \n  o.vTex.xy = vInPos.zw *c_avMapAdj[0].xy +c_avMapAdj[0].zw; \n  o.vTex.zw = vInPos.zw *c_avMapAdj[1].xy +c_avMapAdj[1].zw; \n  return o; \n} \n\n#elif _GLSL \n\n  #define c_avMapAdj c_avVexUniformsF \n  layout (location=0) in  float4 i_vAttr0; \n  layout (location=0) out float4 vTexCoords; \n\nvoid main(void) \n{ \n#ifdef INV_Z \n  gl_Position = float4( i_vAttr0.xy, 0.99999f,1); \n#else \n  gl_Position = float4( i_vAttr0.xy, 0.00001f,1); \n#endif \n  vTexCoords.xy = i_vAttr0.zw *c_avMapAdj[0].xy +c_avMapAdj[0].zw; \n  vTexCoords.zw = i_vAttr0.zw *c_avMapAdj[1].xy +c_avMapAdj[1].zw; \n} \n#undef c_avMapAdj \n\n#endif \n""

""#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/AmdShaderIntrinsics.hs> \ncbuffer CBVREye :register(b1) {float2 sc_fVREyeMV :packoffset(c0);} \n#define sc_fVREye sc_fVREyeMV.x \n#define sc_fMultiview sc_fVREyeMV.y \nstatic float g_fVRViewport = 0.0f; \ninline float GetVREye() { \n  return sc_fMultiview ? g_fVRViewport : sc_fVREye; \n} \n\ninline void SetVRViewport(uint iViewportIndex) { \n  g_fVRViewport = (sc_fMultiview > 0.0f && sc_fMultiview < 1.01f) ? AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_GetViewportIndex() : iViewportIndex; \n} \n\ninline float2 MultiviewUVConditional(float2 vUV, float fMultiview) { \n  float4 vMad = (sc_fMultiview * fMultiview > 0.0f) ? float4(0.5f, 1.0f, 0.5f * GetVREye(), 0.0f) : float4(1.0f, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f); \n  return vUV * vMad.xy + vMad.zw; \n} \ninline float2 MultiviewCoordConditional(float2 vCoord, float2 vSize, float fMultiview) { \n  vCoord.x += (sc_fMultiview * fMultiview > 0.0f) ? GetVREye() * vSize.x : 0.0f; \n  return vCoord; \n} \n""
""#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs> \n\n#if _HLSL \n\nstruct VS_OUTPUT { \n  float4 vPos : POSITION;  \n#if !_PSSL \n  float4 vPosXRight : NV_X_RIGHT;  \n  uint4 vViewportMask : NV_VIEWPORT_MASK;  \n#endif \n}; \n  const uniform float2 c_vMisc : register(c0); \n\n  VS_OUTPUT main( float3 vInPos : TEXCOORD0) { \n  VS_OUTPUT o; \n  o.vPos.x = (c_vMisc.y>=0.0f) ? vInPos.z : vInPos.x; \n  o.vPos.y = vInPos.y; \n  o.vPos.z = c_vMisc.x; \n  o.vPos.w = 1.0f; \n\n#if !_PSSL \n\n  o.vPosXRight.x = vInPos.z; \n  o.vPosXRight.yzw = o.vPos.yzw; \n\n  o.vPos.x = VRSelectPosX_VS( o.vPos.x, o.vPosXRight.x); \n  o.vViewportMask = 0x00020001; \n\n#endif \n\n  return o; \n} \n\n#elif _GLSL \n\n  #define c_vMisc c_avVexUniformsF[0] \n  layout (location=0) in float3 i_vAttr0; \n\nvoid main(void) \n{ \n  gl_Position.x = (c_vMisc.y>=0.0f) ? i_vAttr0.z : i_vAttr0.x; \n  gl_Position.y = i_vAttr0.y; \n  gl_Position.z = c_vMisc.x; \n  gl_Position.w = 1.0f; \n\n  gl_Position.x = VRSelectPosX_VS( gl_Position.x, i_vAttr0.z); \n} \n#undef c_vMisc \n\n#endif \n""
""#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs> \n\n#if _HLSL \n\nstruct VS_OUTPUT { \n  float4 vPos : SV_Position; \n#if !_PSSL \n  float4 vPosXRight : NV_X_RIGHT; \n  uint4 vViewportMask : NV_VIEWPORT_MASK; \n#endif \n}; \n\n  const uniform float4x4 c_mModel : register(c0); \n  const uniform float4x4 c_mViewProjLeft : register(c4); \n  const uniform float4   c_vStretch : register(c8); \n  const uniform float4   c_vOffset  : register(c9); \n  const uniform float4   c_vViewProjRightX : register(c10); \n\n  VS_OUTPUT main( float4 vInPos : TEXCOORD0) \n{ \n  VS_OUTPUT o; \n  float4 vPosObj = vInPos *c_vStretch + c_vOffset; \n  float4x4 mMVPLeft = mul( c_mModel, c_mViewProjLeft); \n  o.vPos = mul( vPosObj, mMVPLeft); \n#if !_PSSL \n  float4x4 mMVPRight = mul( c_mModel, VRRightMatrix( c_mViewProjLeft, c_vViewProjRightX)); \n  o.vPosXRight = mul( vPosObj, mMVPRight); \n  o.vPos.x = VRSelectPosX_VS( o.vPos.x, o.vPosXRight.x); \n  o.vViewportMask = 0x00020001; \n#endif \n  return o; \n} \n\n#elif _GLSL \n\n  float4x4 c_mModel = float4x4( c_avVexUniformsF[0], c_avVexUniformsF[1], c_avVexUniformsF[2], c_avVexUniformsF[3]); \n  float4x4 c_mViewProjLeft = float4x4( c_avVexUniformsF[4], c_avVexUniformsF[5], c_avVexUniformsF[6], c_avVexUniformsF[7]); \n  float4   c_vStretch= c_avVexUniformsF[8]; \n  float4   c_vOffset = c_avVexUniformsF[9]; \n  float4   c_vViewProjRightX = c_avVexUniformsF[10]; \n\n  layout (location=0) in float4 i_vAttr0; \n\nvoid main(void) \n{ \n  float4 vPosObj = i_vAttr0 *c_vStretch + c_vOffset; \n  float4x4 mMVPLeft = mul( c_mModel, c_mViewProjLeft); \n  gl_Position = mul( vPosObj, mMVPLeft); \n  float4x4 mMVPRight = mul( c_mModel, VRRightMatrix( c_mViewProjLeft, c_vViewProjRightX)); \n  float4 vPosXRight = mul( vPosObj, mMVPRight); \n  gl_Position.x = VRSelectPosX_VS( gl_Position.x, vPosXRight.x); \n} \n\n#endif \n""
""#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs> \n\n#if _HLSL \n\nTexture2D t_sTex : register(t0); SamplerState s_tTex : register(s0); \nuniform float4 c_vColMul : register(c0); \nstruct PS_INPUT { \n  float2 vTex : TEXCOORD0; \n  float4 vPos : SV_Position; \n  #if _HLSL==1 && !_PSSL \n    uint iViewport : SV_ViewportArrayIndex; \n  #endif \n}; \nfloat4 main( PS_INPUT i) : SV_Target { \n\n#if _PSSL \n  return c_vColMul * t_sTex.Sample( s_tTex, i.vTex) ; \n#else \n  SetVRViewport(i.iViewport); \n  return c_vColMul * t_sTex.Sample( s_tTex, MultiviewUV(i.vTex)); \n#endif \n} \n\n#elif _GLSL \n\n  float4 c_vColMul = c_avPixUniformsF[0]; \n  layout (location=0) in float4 vTexCoords; \n  #if _GLSL_METAL \n    layout (binding=0) uniform sampler2D t_sTex; \n    out vec4 _glPixOut; \n  #else \n    layout (set=1, binding=0) uniform sampler2D t_sTex; \n    layout (location=0) out vec4 _glPixOut; \n  #endif \n//_Sreg2D( t_sTex, s_tTex, 0); \n\nvoid main(void) \n{ \n  _glPixOut = c_vColMul * texSample2D( t_sTex, void, vTexCoords.xy); \n} \n\n#endif \n""

""#pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default PS_OUTPUT_TYPE) \n\nConstantBuffer cbPix : register(b2) { \n  float4 c_vcolClear: packoffset(c0); \n}; \nfloat4 main(void) : S_TARGET_OUTPUT0 { \n  return c_vcolClear; \n}; \n""
""#pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default PS_OUTPUT_TYPE) \n\nMS_Texture2D<float4> t_sTexMS: register(t15); \nTexture2D<int2> t_sFMask : register(t16); \n\nfloat4 main( float2 vInTex : TEXCOORD0) : S_TARGET_OUTPUT0 \n{ \n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, 0); \n#if BILINEAR_FILTER \n  int4 ivCoords = int4( vInTex.xyxy+ float4( -0.5f,-0.5f, 0.5f,0.5f)); \n#endif \n  int2 viFMask = t_sFMask.Load( int3( vInTex,0)).xy; \n  int iSampleIdx; \n\n  for( int iSampleNum=0; iSampleNum<SUB_SAMPLES; iSampleNum++) { \n\n    float4 vSubSample; \n    if( iSampleNum < 8) { \n      iSampleIdx = (viFMask.x >>(iSampleNum*4)) & 15; \n    } else { \n      iSampleIdx = (viFMask.y >>((iSampleNum-8)*4)) & 15; \n    } \n    #if BILINEAR_FILTER \n      vSubSample  = t_sTexMS.Load( ivCoords.xy, iSampleIdx); // UL \n      vSubSample += t_sTexMS.Load( ivCoords.xw, iSampleIdx); // DL \n      vSubSample += t_sTexMS.Load( ivCoords.zw, iSampleIdx); // DR \n      vSubSample += t_sTexMS.Load( ivCoords.zy, iSampleIdx); // UR \n      vSubSample *= 0.25f; \n    #else \n      vSubSample = t_sTexMS.Load( int2( vInTex), iSampleIdx); \n    #endif \n    vOutColor += vSubSample; \n  } \n  vOutColor /= SUB_SAMPLES; \n  return vOutColor; \n}; \n""
""#pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default PS_OUTPUT_TYPE) \n\nuniform Texture2D    t_sTex : register(t15); \nuniform SamplerState s_tSam : register(s15); \n\nfloat4 main( float2 vInTex : TEXCOORD0) : S_TARGET_OUTPUT0 \n{ \n  return t_sTex.Sample( s_tSam, vInTex); \n}; \n""
""#pragma warning(disable:3557) // (loop only executes for 1 iteration(s), forcing loop to unroll) \n#pragma warning(disable:3582) // (texture access must have literal offset and multisample index, forcing loop to unroll) \nTexture2DMS<float4,SUB_SAMPLES> t_tTexture: register(t0); \nstruct PS_INPUT { \n  float2 vTex : TEXCOORD0; \n}; \nfloat4 main( PS_INPUT i) : SV_Target { \n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, 0); \n  float2 vTex = i.vTex; \n#if BILINEAR_FILTER \n  float4 vCoords = vTex.xyxy+ float4( -0.495f,-0.495f, 0.495f,0.495f); \n#endif \n  for( int iSample=0; iSample<SUB_SAMPLES; iSample++) { \n    float4 vSubSample; \n    #if BILINEAR_FILTER \n      vSubSample  = t_tTexture.Load( vCoords.xy, iSample); // UL \n      vSubSample += t_tTexture.Load( vCoords.xw, iSample); // DL \n      vSubSample += t_tTexture.Load( vCoords.zw, iSample); // DR \n      vSubSample += t_tTexture.Load( vCoords.zy, iSample); // UR \n      vSubSample *= 0.25f; \n    #else \n      vSubSample = t_tTexture.Load( vTex, iSample); \n    #endif \n    vOutColor += vSubSample; \n  } \n  vOutColor /= SUB_SAMPLES; \n  return vOutColor; \n}; \n""

""#version""
""#version: compilation for SPIR-V does not support the compatibility profile""
""#version: compute shaders require es profile with version 310 or above, or non-es profile with version 420 or above""
""#version: Desktop shaders for OpenGL SPIR-V require version 330 or higher""
""#version: Desktop shaders for Vulkan SPIR-V require version 140 or higher""
""#version: ES shaders for OpenGL SPIR-V are not supported""
""#version: ES shaders for Vulkan SPIR-V require version 310 or higher""
""#version: geometry shaders require es profile with version 310 or non-es profile with version 150 or above""
""#version: only version 300, 310, and 320 support the es profile""
""#version: statement must appear first in es-profile shader; before comments or newlines""
""#version: tessellation shaders require es profile with version 310 or non-es profile with version 150 or above""
""#version: versions 300, 310, and 320 require specifying the 'es' profile""
""#version: versions 300, 310, and 320 support only the es profile""
""#version: versions before 150 do not allow a profile token""

""-- Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved.\n\n-- Create a table which associates timer event filter with timer events (their ids)\nlsch_timerEventsTable = {}\n\n-- Table which associates a table with some coroutine\n-- this table is weak in relation to keys so no unnecessary references\n-- to coroutines are made\nlsch_coroutineParamsTable = {}\nsetmetatable(lsch_coroutineParamsTable, {__mode=\"k\"})\n\n-- Runs given function in new coroutine (which is resumed immediately)\nfunction RunInNewCoroutine(func, coroutineParams, ...)\n  -- create the coroutine for given function\n  local co = coroutine.create(func)\n  \n  -- if coroutine params are provided\n  if coroutineParams ~= nil then\n    -- use the same params for new coroutine\n    lsch_coroutineParamsTable[co] = coroutineParams\n    -- add coroutine to list of breakable coroutine in the coroutine params\n    table.insert(coroutineParams.breakableCoroutines, co)\n  end\n  \n  -- start the coroutine with given params\n  lschResumeCoroutine(co, ...)\nend\n\n-- Array of signaled filters (those whose events were signaled).\nlsch_signaledFiltersArray = {}\n  \n-- Clears signaled filters array\nfunction lschClearSignaledFilters()\n  -- remove all elements from the signaled filters array (in reverse since it is more efficient)\n  local ctSignaledFilters = #lsch_signaledFiltersArray\n  for i = 1, ctSignaledFilters do \n    table.remove(lsch_signaledFiltersArray)\n  end\nend\n\n-- Use to mark filter as signaled.\nfunction lschFilterSignaled(filter, event)\n  -- insert filter and his event at the end of signaled filters array\n  table.insert(lsch_signaledFiltersArray, {filter, event})\nend\n\n-- Processes (executes 'OnSignaled' function) all filters in signaled filters array.\nfunction lschProcessSignaledFilters()\n  -- while there are still filters to process\n  while true do\n    -- get first filter-event pair from array of signaled filters\n    local filterAndEvent = lsch_signaledFiltersArray[1]\n    -- stop processing if there are no more filters\n    if filterAndEvent == nil then break end\n    -- run 'OnSignaled' function for this filter passing the event as argument\n    filterAndEvent[1]:OnSignaled(filterAndEvent[2])\n    -- remove processed filter-event pair from the array\n    table.remove(lsch_signaledFiltersArray, 1)\n  end\nend\n\n-- Registers a filter for delay (in seconds)\nfunction lschRegisterForDelayEvent(filter, delay)\n  -- filter must be a non nil table\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\", \n    \"lschRegisterForDelayEvent - invalid filter; filter should be a table!\")\n  -- delay must be a number\n  assert(type(delay) == \"number\",\n    \"lschRegisterForDelayEvent - invalid delay; delay should be a number (of seconds)!\")\n  \n  -- register delay event with scheduler (also set whether it is repeating or not)\n  local delayEventId = lschRegisterDelayEvent(delay)\n  -- associate filter with delay event id\n  lsch_timerEventsTable[delayEventId] = filter;\n  return delayEventId\nend\n\n-- Create global table which holds information about events and all those who wait for them\n-- lsch_eventTable[object][event] is a table whose values are filters (which receive notifications about signaled events)\n-- object is a handle to some object and event is a string name of the event\n-- event table is a weak table (for keys) so that it doesn't unnecessarily hold references to objects (which would prevent\n-- garbage collection)\nlsch_eventTable = {}\nsetmetatable(lsch_eventTable, {__mode = \"k\"})\n\n-- With this function a filter is registered for specified event on the specified object\n-- object (optional) is handle to the object and event is a string name of the event\nfunction lschRegisterForEvent(filter, event, object)\n  -- filter must be a table\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and filter.isValid,\n    \"lschRegisterForEvent - invalid filter; filter should be a table!\")\n  -- event must be a string\n  assert(type(event) == \"string\" and event ~= \"\",\n    \"lschRegisterForEvent - invalid event specifier; event should be specified by a non-empty string!\")\n  -- place where filter will be inserted\n  local filtersTable = nil\n  \n  -- if object is not specified (event is not bound to an object)\n  if object == nil then\n    -- create table for filters for this event if it doesn't exist\n    if lsch_eventTable[event] == nil then      \n      lsch_eventTable[event] = {}\n    end\n    -- this is where our filter will be stored\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[event]\n  -- else, if there are no existing entries for requested object\n  elseif lsch_eventTable[object] == nil then\n    -- create filters table for object and event\n    lsch_eventTable[object] = {}\n    lsch_eventTable[object][event] = {}\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[object][event]\n  -- else, if there are no existing entries for requested event\n  elseif lsch_eventTable[object][event] == nil then\n    -- create filters table for that event\n    lsch_eventTable[object][event] = {}\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[object][event]\n  -- else, filters table for that object and event already exits\n  else\n    -- use existing filters table for given object and event\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[object][event]\n  end\n  \n  -- store the filter as a key in filters table\n  filtersTable[filter] = true;\n  -- notify the object that script event has been registered for it\n  if object ~= nil then\n    object:OnScriptEventRegistered(event)\n  end\nend\n\n-- With this function a filter is unregistered from specified event on the specified object\n-- object (optional) is handle to the object and event is a string name of the event\nfunction lschUnregisterFromEvent(filter, event, object)\n  -- filter must be a table\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and filter.isValid,\n    \"lschUnregisterFromEvent - invalid filter; filter should be a table!\")\n  -- event must be a string\n  assert(type(event) == \"string\" and event ~= \"\",\n    \"lschUnregisterFromEvent - invalid event specifier; event should be specified by a non-empty string!\")\n  -- place where filter should be inserted\n  local filtersTable = nil\n  \n  -- if object is not specified (event is not bound to an object)\n  if object == nil then\n    -- there is no table for this event - bail (filter is not registered at all)\n    if lsch_eventTable[event] == nil then return end\n    -- this is where our filter should be stored\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[event]\n  -- else, if there are no existing entries for requested object\n  elseif lsch_eventTable[object] == nil then\n    -- there is no table for this object\n    -- bail (event is not registered at all)\n    return\n  -- else, if there are no existing entries for requested event\n  elseif lsch_eventTable[object][event] == nil then\n    -- bail (filter is not registered at all)\n    return\n  -- else, filters table for that object and event already exits\n  else\n    -- use existing filters table for given object and event\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[object][event]\n  end\n  \n  -- remove the filter from registered filters table\n  filtersTable[filter] = nil;\n  -- see if there are no more filters registered for this event\n  -- if filtersTable is empty - we need to remove the associated event\n  if next(filtersTable) == nil then \n    -- if object is not set then we remove the event directly from the lsch_eventTable\n    if object == nil then \n      lsch_eventTable[event] = nil\n    -- else, we remove the event for given object\n    else \n      lsch_eventTable[object][event] = nil \n      -- if there are no more events for given object\n      if next(lsch_eventTable[object]) == nil then\n        -- remove the event table entry for this object\n        lsch_eventTable[object] = nil\n      end\n    end\n  end\nend\n\n-- Checks whether any filter is registered for specified event on an (optional) object.\n-- This function is necessary in order to avoid the overhead related to sending events and creating event objects.\nfunction lschIsEventNeeded(object, idEvent)\n  -- if object is not set\n  if object == nil then\n    -- check whether anything is registered for an event with the specified id\n    return lsch_eventTable[idEvent] ~= nil\n  -- else, object is set\n  else\n    -- check whether anything is registered for that object and event\n    return lsch_eventTable[object] ~= nil and lsch_eventTable[object][idEvent] ~= nil\n  end\nend\n\n-- signals given event on given (optional) object\n-- there are two valid forms for calling this function:\n-- 1: SignalEvent(\"EventName\"[, <optional event param>]) - signals the event \"EventName\" which is not bound to any object\n-- 2: SignalEvent(<object>, \"EventName\"[, <optional event param>]]) - signals the event \"EventName\" on given object (table)\nfunction SignalEvent(param1, param2, param3)\n  local idEvent = nil\n  local object = nil\n  local eventParams = nil\n  \n  -- if first parameter is a string\n  if type(param1) == \"string\" then\n    -- first parameter is the event id\n    idEvent = param1\n    assert(idEvent ~= \"\", \"SignalEvent called with invalid event name!\")\n    -- second parameter contains event parameters\n    eventParams = param2\n  -- else, if first parameter is the object\n  elseif type(param1) == \"table\" then\n    -- first parameter is the object\n    object = param1\n    -- second parameter must be the event id\n    idEvent = param2\n    assert(type(idEvent) == \"string\" and idEvent ~= \"\", \"SignalEvent called on object, but with invalid event name!\")\n    -- third parameter could be the event params (if any)\n    eventParams = param3\n  -- else, there was an error\n  else\n    assert(false, \"SignalEvent called with invalid parameters!\")\n  end\n  \n  -- table of filters for given event and object\n  local filtersTable = nil\n  -- if object is nil\n  if object == nil then\n    -- if no one is waiting for that event\n    if lsch_eventTable[idEvent] == nil then\n      -- no filters to signal - return\n      return\n    end\n    -- set filters table\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[idEvent]\n  -- else, if no one is waiting for that event on that object\n  elseif lsch_eventTable[object] == nil or lsch_eventTable[object][idEvent] == nil then\n    -- no filters to signal - return\n    return\n  else\n    -- set filters table\n    filtersTable = lsch_eventTable[object][idEvent]\n  end\n  \n  -- go through all filters\n  for filter in pairs(filtersTable) do\n    -- if lambda function is not set, or is set and accepted\n    if filter.lambda == nil or filter.lambda(eventParams or true) then\n      -- signal event for filter (passing it the event params)\n      lschFilterSignaled(filter, eventParams or true)\n      -- if filter should not be repeated - it should be removed (so it doesn't get signaled again)\n      if not filter.shouldRepeat then filtersTable[filter] = nil end\n    end\n  end\n  -- see if there are no more filters registered for this event\n  -- if filtersTable is empty - we need to remove the associated event\n  if next(filtersTable) == nil then \n    -- if object is not set then we remove the event directly from the lsch_eventTable\n    if object == nil then \n      lsch_eventTable[idEvent] = nil\n    -- else, we remove the event for given object\n    else \n      lsch_eventTable[object][idEvent] = nil \n      -- if there are no more events for given object\n      if next(lsch_eventTable[object]) == nil then\n        -- remove the event table entry for this object\n        lsch_eventTable[object] = nil\n      end\n    end\n  end\nend\n\n-- Runs given function in new coroutine.\n-- New coroutine is executed immediately and is scheduled in case that it yields\nfunction RunAsync(func)\n  assert(type(func) == \"function\",\n    \"RunAsync shold receive a function as argument!\")\n  -- run function in new coroutine with possible coroutine params for currently running coroutine\n  RunInNewCoroutine(func, lsch_coroutineParamsTable[coroutine.running()])\nend\n\n-- Adopts the event filter created by syntactic sugar so it becomes a valid event filter\nfunction Event(filter, lambda)\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and filter.isValid == false,\n    \"Invalid event passed to Event function\")\n  -- check for common error of using Event with group variable\n  assert(#filter == 0, \"Group events passed to Event, use Events instead!\")\n  -- assign provided lambda filter function (may be nil)\n  assert(lambda == nil or type(lambda) == \"function\", \n    \"If a second argument is passed to Event(), it must be a function!\")\n  filter.lambda = lambda \n  -- mark the filter as valid\n  filter.isValid = true\n  -- return the filter\n  return filter\nend\n\n-- Adopts the array of event objects created by syntactic sugar (for waiting on events on a group variable)\n-- so that it can be used inside All or Any\nfunction Events(filterArray)\n  assert(type(filterArray) == \"table\" and #filterArray > 0 and filterArray.isValid == false, \n    \"Invalid group events passed to Events function!\")\n  \n  -- mark each individual filter as valid\n  for _, filter in ipairs(filterArray) do\n    assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and filter.isValid == false, \"Invalid group events passed to Events function!\")\n    filter.isValid = true\n  end\n  \n  -- mark the array of filters as valid\n  filterArray.isValid = true\n  return filterArray\nend\n\n-- metatable used for filters generated by CustomEvent function\nlocal customEventFilterMetatable = {\n  __index = {\n    -- registration function (called when filter is registered)\n    Register = function(self)\n        -- register for event on object\n      lschRegisterForEvent(self, self.idEvent, self.object)\n    end,\n    -- unregistration function (called when filter is deregistered)\n    Unregister = function(self)\n      -- unregister for event on object\n      lschUnregisterFromEvent(self, self.idEvent, self.object)\n    end,\n    -- SetRepeating function (called to mark the filter as repeating)\n    SetRepeating = function(self)\n      self.shouldRepeat = true\n    end,\n    -- this marks the event as valid\n    isValid = true\n  }\n}\n\n-- Creates waiting for custom event filter\nfunction CustomEvent(param1, param2)\n  local eventId = nil\n  local eventObject = nil\n  \n  -- if first param is a string\n  if type(param1) == \"string\" then\n    -- first parameter represents the event name\n    eventId = param1\n    assert(eventId ~= \"\", \"CustomEvent function should receive a non empty event name!\");\n    -- check that there is no second parameter\n    assert(param2 == nil, \"When first parameter to CustomEvent function is event name then there should not be a second parameter!\")\n  -- else if first param is a table (object)\n  elseif type(param1) == \"table\" then\n    -- first parameter is the event object\n    eventObject = param1\n    -- second parameter is the event name\n    eventId = param2\n    assert(eventId ~= \"\", \"CustomEvent function should receive a non empty event name!\");\n  else\n    assert(false, \"Invalid parameters provided to CustomEvent function!\")\n  end\n  \n  -- create filter table\n  local filter = {\n    -- store event id (so it can be used for deregistration)(also so we don't use the upvalue which causes problems to pluto)\n    idEvent = eventId,\n    -- store object (so it can be used for deregistration)(also so we don't use the upvalue which causes problems to pluto)\n    object = eventObject\n  }\n\n  -- set the metatable that makes the filter valid (and with required functions)\n  setmetatable(filter, customEventFilterMetatable)\n  \n  -- return filter table\n  return filter;\nend\n\n\n-- metatable used for filters generated by Delay function\nlocal delayFilterMetatable = {\n  __index = {\n    -- registration function (called when filter is registered)\n    Register = function(self)\n      -- register for delay and remember delay id so we can used that id with unregistration\n      self.delayId = lschRegisterForDelayEvent(self, self.seconds)\n    end,\n    -- unregistration function (called when filter is deregistered)\n    Unregister = function(self)\n        -- unregister from delay using the delay id\n        lschUnregisterDelayEvent(self.delayId)\n    end,\n    -- SetRepeating function (called to mark the filter as repeating)\n    SetRepeating = function(self)\n      self.shouldRepeat = true\n    end,\n    -- this marks the event as valid\n    isValid = true\n  }\n}\n\n-- Creates waiting for delay filter\nfunction Delay(delayInSeconds)\n  -- delay should be specified by a number greater than zero\n  assert(type(delayInSeconds) == \"number\" and delayInSeconds > 0,\n    \"Delay should be specified using a number of seconds!\")\n  -- create filter table\n  local filter = {\n    -- Registration function (called when filter is registered)\n    -- store number of seconds (so we don't use the upvalue which causes problems to pluto)\n    seconds = delayInSeconds,\n  }\n  \n  -- set the metatable that makes the filter valid (and with required functions)\n  setmetatable(filter, delayFilterMetatable);\n  \n  -- return filter table\n  return filter;  \nend\n\n\n-- metatable used by filters created by the Times function\nlocal timesFilterMetatable = {\n  __index = {\n    -- Registration function (called when filter is registered)\n    Register = function(self)\n      -- check that this filter has his 'OnSignaled' function set\n      assert(type(self.OnSignaled) == \"function\", \"Times function - OnSignaled function not provided\")\n    \n      -- set contained filter's owner filter to this filter\n      self.containedFilter.ownerFilter = self\n    \n      -- contained filter's OnSignaled function should call this filter's Evaluate function\n      function self.containedFilter:OnSignaled(event)\n        self.ownerFilter:Evaluate(event)  \n      end\n    \n      -- set contained filter as repeating (so it will be signaled multiple times)\n      self.containedFilter:SetRepeating()\n        \n      -- register contained filter\n      assert(type(self.containedFilter.Register) == \"function\",\n          \"Times function - invalid filter provided (missing 'Register' function)!\")\n      self.containedFilter:Register()\n    end,\n  \n    -- Unregistration function (called when filter is unregistered)\n    Unregister = function(self)\n      -- call Unregistration function on contained filter\n      assert(type(self.containedFilter.Unregister) == \"function\", \n        \"Times function - invalid filter provided (missing 'Unregister' function)!\")\n      self.containedFilter:Unregister()\n    end,\n  \n    -- Evaluate function (called on each step so that filter can evaluate itself)\n    Evaluate = function(self, containedFilterIndex, event)\n      -- reduce the number of times that are left for this filter to be signaled\n      self.numberOfTimesLeftToBeSignaled = self.numberOfTimesLeftToBeSignaled - 1\n    \n      -- if contained filter was signaled the required number of times\n      if self.numberOfTimesLeftToBeSignaled == 0 then\n        -- see if this filter is a repeating filter\n        if self.shouldRepeat then\n          -- initialize the number of times left to be signaled\n          self.numberOfTimesLeftToBeSignaled = self.numberOfTimesToBeSignaled\n        else\n          -- this is not a repeating filter - unregister the contained filter\n          self.containedFilter:Unregister()\n        end\n      \n        -- signal this filter\n        self:OnSignaled(true)\n      end\n    end,\n  \n    -- SetRepeating function (called to mark the filter as repeating)\n    SetRepeating = function(self)\n      -- mark this filter as repeating\n      self.shouldRepeat = true\n    end,\n  \n    -- mark the filter as valid\n    isValid = true\n  }\n}\n\n\n-- Adjusts the input filter so that the resulting filter is signaled \n-- when input filter is signaled the specified number of times.\nfunction Times(numberOfTimes, inputFilter)\n  assert(type(numberOfTimes) == \"number\" and numberOfTimes > 1, \"Times function should be called with a number greater than 1 as first argument!\")\n  assert(type(inputFilter) == \"table\" and inputFilter.isValid, \"Times function should be called with filter table as second argument!\")\n  \n  local filter = {\n    -- store input filter\n    containedFilter = inputFilter,\n    -- initialize the number of times left to be signaled\n    numberOfTimesLeftToBeSignaled = numberOfTimes,\n    -- remember the number of times the filter needed to signal the filter\n    numberOfTimesToBeSignaled = numberOfTimes\n  }\n\n  -- set metatable in order to make the filter valid\n  setmetatable(filter, timesFilterMetatable)\n  \n  -- return the filter\n  return filter\nend\n\n-- helper function which returns the last non nil element of an array\nfunction _GetLastNonNilArrayElement(array)\n  local lastNonNilIndex = 0\n  while array[lastNonNilIndex + 1] ~= nil do\n    lastNonNilIndex = lastNonNilIndex + 1\n  end\n  return lastNonNilIndex\nend\n\n\n-- OnSignaled function set to contained filters in All filter\nlocal function All_ContainedFilter_OnSignaled(self, event)\n  self.ownerFilter:Evaluate(self.containedIndex, event) \nend\n\n-- metatable for filters created by the Any funciton\nlocal allFilterMetatable = {\n  __index = {\n    -- Registration function (called when filter is registered)\n    Register = function(self)\n      -- check that this filter has his 'OnSignaled' function set\n      assert(type(self.OnSignaled) == \"function\", \"All(...), ('OnSignaled' function not provided)\")\n      -- register all contained filters\n      for i = 1, self.containedFiltersCount do\n        local containedFilter = self.filters[i]\n        -- filter should be a table and it should have a 'Register' function\n        assert(type(containedFilter) == \"table\" and containedFilter.isValid,\n          \"All(...), invalid filter provided!\")\n        assert(type(containedFilter.Register) == \"function\",\n          \"All(...), invalid filter provided (missing 'Register' function)!\")\n        -- let contained filter remember it's index and the filter it is contained in\n        -- (this was needed because pluto library has problems with upvalues and coroutines\n        containedFilter.containedIndex = i\n        containedFilter.ownerFilter = self\n        -- contained filter's 'OnSignaled' should call 'Evaluate' function of this composite filter with his contained index\n        containedFilter.OnSignaled = All_ContainedFilter_OnSignaled\n        -- register contained filter\n        containedFilter:Register()\n      end\n    end,\n  \n    -- Unregistration function (called when filter is unregistered)\n    Unregister = function(self)\n      -- call Unregistration function for all contained filters\n      for i = 1, self.containedFiltersCount do\n        local containedFilter = self.filters[i]\n        assert(type(containedFilter.Unregister) == \"function\", \n          \"All(...), invalid filter provided (missing 'Unregister' function)!\")\n        containedFilter:Unregister()\n      end\n    end,\n  \n    -- Evaluate function (called on each step so that filter can evaluate itself)\n    Evaluate = function(self, containedFilterIndex, event)\n      -- bail if this filter's event is already set (all contained filters were fulfilled)\n      if _GetLastNonNilArrayElement(self.all) == self.containedFiltersCount then return end\n      -- set the event for contained filter\n      self.all[containedFilterIndex] = event\n    \n      -- if all contained filters have signaled their events\n      if _GetLastNonNilArrayElement(self.all) == self.containedFiltersCount then\n        -- mark this filter as signaled\n        lschFilterSignaled(self, {all=self.all})\n        -- clear the signaled filters array\n        self.all = {}\n      end\n    end,\n  \n    -- SetRepeating function (called to mark the filter as repeating)\n    SetRepeating = function(self)\n      -- call SetRepeating function for all contained filters\n      for i = 1, self.containedFiltersCount do\n        local containedFilter = self.filters[i]\n        assert(type(containedFilter.SetRepeating) == \"function\", \n          \"All(...), invalid filter provided (missing 'SetRepeating' function)!\")\n        containedFilter:SetRepeating()\n      end \n    end,\n    -- this marks the filter as valid\n    isValid = true,\n  }\n}\n\n-- Composite filter which is signaled when all its contained filters are signaled.\nfunction All(...)\n  local inputFilters  \n  -- if there is only one argument\n  if #arg == 1 then\n    -- first and only argument is a table of input filters\n    inputFilters = arg[1]\n    assert(type(inputFilters) == \"table\" and inputFilters.isValid == true and #inputFilters > 0,\n      \"All(...) received invalid group of events!\");\n  else\n    -- arguments represent filters\n    inputFilters = arg\n    -- there should be at least two filters\n    assert(#inputFilters > 1, \"All(...) should be called with at least two filters as arguments!\")\n  end\n  \n  local filter = {\n    -- array of contained filters\n    filters = inputFilters,\n    -- array of events which correspond to contained filters (event at index i corresponds to filter i)\n    all = {},\n    -- count of contained filters (so we don't use the upvalue which causes problems to pluto)\n    containedFiltersCount = #inputFilters,\n  }\n  \n  -- set the metatable \n  setmetatable(filter, allFilterMetatable)\n  \n  -- return filter table\n  return filter;\nend\n\n\n-- function set as OnSignaled member function to filters contained in Any filter\nlocal function AnyFilter_ContainedFilter_OnSignaled(self, event)\n  -- when contained filter gets signaled it should signal this filter and set the apropriate event at its index\n  -- if filter in which contained filter is contained should not be signaled again\n  if not self.ownerFilter.shouldNotSignalAgain then\n    -- signal the filter in which we are contained (also mark the signaled payload and signaled index in Any filter for easier retrieval)\n    lschFilterSignaled(self.ownerFilter, {any = {[self.containedIndex]=event, signaled = event, signaledIndex = self.containedIndex}})\n    -- if the filter in which we are contained should not be repeated\n    if not self.ownerFilter.shouldRepeat then\n      -- unregister the filter we are contained in\n      self.ownerFilter:Unregister()          \n      -- don't allow the filter in which we are contained to be signaled again\n      self.ownerFilter.shouldNotSignalAgain = true\n    end\n  end\nend\n\n-- metatable for filters created by the Any function\nlocal anyFilterMetatable = {\n  __index = {\n    -- Registration function (called when filter is registered)\n    Register = function(self)\n      -- check that this filter has his 'OnSignaled' function set\n      assert(type(self.OnSignaled) == \"function\", \"Any(...), ('OnSignaled' function not provided)\")\n      -- register all contained filters\n      for i = 1, self.containedFiltersCount do\n        local containedFilter = self.filters[i]\n        -- filter should be a table and it should have a 'Register' function\n        assert(type(containedFilter) == \"table\" and containedFilter.isValid and type(containedFilter.Register) == \"function\",\n          \"Any(...), invalid filter provided!\")\n        assert(type(containedFilter.Register) == \"function\",\n          \"Any(...), invalid filter provided (missing 'Register' function)!\")\n       \n        -- let contained filter remember it's index and the filter it is contained in\n        -- (this was needed because pluto library has problems with upvalues and coroutines\n        containedFilter.containedIndex = i\n        containedFilter.ownerFilter = self\n        -- when contained filter gets signaled it should signal this filter and set the apropriate event at its index\n        containedFilter.OnSignaled = AnyFilter_ContainedFilter_OnSignaled\n        -- register contained filter\n        containedFilter:Register()\n      end\n    end,\n    -- Unregistration function (called when filter is unregistered)\n    Unregister = function(self)\n      -- call Unregistration function for all contained filters\n      for i = 1, self.containedFiltersCount do\n        local containedFilter = self.filters[i]\n        assert(type(containedFilter.Unregister) == \"function\", \n          \"Any(...), invalid filter provided (missing 'Unregister' function)!\")\n        containedFilter:Unregister()\n      end\n    end,\n    -- SetRepeating function (called to mark the filter as repeating)\n    SetRepeating = function(self)\n      -- set this filter's repeating flag\n      self.shouldRepeat = true\n      -- call SetRepeating function for all contained filters\n      for i = 1, self.containedFiltersCount do\n        local containedFilter = self.filters[i]\n        assert(type(containedFilter.SetRepeating) == \"function\", \n          \"Any(...), invalid filter provided (missing 'SetRepeating' function)!\")\n        containedFilter:SetRepeating()\n      end\n    end,\n    -- mark the filter as valid\n    isValid = true,\n  }\n}\n\n-- Composite filter which is signaled when one of its contained filters are signaled.\nfunction Any(...)\n  local inputFilters  \n  -- if there is only one argument\n  if #arg == 1 then\n    -- first and only argument is a table of input filters\n    inputFilters = arg[1]\n    assert(type(inputFilters) == \"table\" and inputFilters.isValid == true and #inputFilters > 0,\n      \"Any(...) received invalid group of events!\");\n  -- there were more arguments\n  else\n    -- arguments represent filters\n    inputFilters = arg\n    -- there should be at least two filters\n    assert(#inputFilters > 1, \"Any(...) should be called with at least two filters as arguments!\")\n  end\n\n  local filter = {\n    -- array of contained filters\n    filters = inputFilters,\n    -- count of contained filters (so we don't use the upvalue which causes problems to pluto)\n    containedFiltersCount = #inputFilters\n  }\n  \n  -- set metatable that makes the filter valid\n  setmetatable(filter, anyFilterMetatable)\n  \n  -- return filter table\n  return filter;\nend\n\n\n-- OnSignaled function set to filters used in Wait expression\nlocal function Filter_In_Wait_OnSignaled(self, event)\n  -- set 'OnSignaled' function to resume this coroutine\n  self.receivedEvent = event\n  lschResumeCoroutine(self.coThis)\nend\n\n-- Function for waiting on some wait expression\nfunction Wait(filter)\n  -- if 'filter' is a boolean false\n  if type(filter) == \"boolean\" and filter == false then\n    -- we should not wait at all (like when trying to wait on latent functions which turned \n    -- out not to be latent at all)\n    return\n  end\n  -- filter must be a table which has a 'Register' function\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and type(filter.Register) == \"function\" and filter.isValid,\n    \"Wait was provided with invalid filter!\");\n  -- filter should not be marked as repeating (by OnEvery construct)\n  assert(not filter.shouldRepeat, \"OnEvery construct should not be used with 'Wait' construct!\")\n  -- set 'OnSignaled' function to resume this coroutine\n  filter.coThis = coroutine.running()\n  filter.OnSignaled = Filter_In_Wait_OnSignaled\n  -- call filter registration function\n  filter:Register()\n  -- yield (until resumed)\n  coroutine.yield()\n  -- unregister filter\n  filter:Unregister()\n  -- return filter's event (so it can be used by waiting code)\n  return filter.receivedEvent\nend\n\n-- Function which makes the couroutine block forever - same as coroutine.yield\nWaitForever = coroutine.yield\n\n-- Function used to adjust filters which are used in RunHandled construct.\nfunction On(filter)\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and filter.isValid, \"Invalid filter parameter given to On function!\")\n  -- check common error that happens when using Events without All or Any\n  if #filter > 0 then\n    assert(type(filter.Register) == \"function\", \"Invalid filter parameter given to On function! Did you forget to use All or Any?\")\n  end\n  -- mark the filter as ready for runhandled\n  filter.readyForRunHandled = true\n  -- return modified filter\n  return filter\nend\n\n-- Adjusts the input filter for use in RunHandled construct so that the filter is marked as repeating.\n-- OnEvery filter adapter should only be used with filters found in 'RunHandled' construct.\nfunction OnEvery(filter)\n  -- filter should be a table\n  assert(type(filter) == \"table\" and filter.isValid, \"Invalid filter parameter given to OnEvery function!\")\n  -- check common error that happens when using Events without All or Any\n  if #filter > 0 then\n    assert(type(filter.Register) == \"function\", \"Invalid filter parameter given to OnEvery function! Did you forget to use All or Any?\")\n  end\n  -- mark filter as repeating by calling the 'SetRepeating' function\n  filter:SetRepeating()\n  -- mark the filter as ready for runhandled\n  filter.readyForRunHandled = true\n  -- return modified filter\n  return filter\nend\n\n\n-- OnSignaled function set to handler filters in RunHandled construct\nlocal function RunHandled_HandlerFilter_OnSignaled(self, event)\n  -- run handler function in new coroutine with event given as parameter\n  RunInNewCoroutine(self.handlerFunc, self.coroutineParams, event)\nend\n\n-- Runs given function.\n-- Takes one or more handlers as optional parameters. One handler is of form {filter, func}\n-- where filter is a filter table (produced with Event, CustomEvent, Delay or similar) and func is a function\n-- which is called when filter event is signaled.\nfunction RunHandled(func, ...)\n  -- func must be a function\n  assert(type(func) == \"function\", \"First argument to RunHandled must be a function!\")\n  local ctArgs = #arg\n  -- there should be at least one handler\n  assert(ctArgs > 0, \"RunHandled should have at least one handler filter handler function pair!\")\n  -- there should be even number of arguments (because handler filter should come with handler function)\n  assert(ctArgs % 2 == 0, \"invalid handler arguments to RunHandled!\")\n  \n  local currentCoroutineParams = lsch_coroutineParamsTable[coroutine.running()]\n  \n  -- HANDLER REGISTRATION --\n  -- go through all optional arguments\n  for i = 1, ctArgs, 2 do\n    -- each pair of optional arguments is a handler-filter pair\n    local handlerFilter = arg[i]\n    local handlerFunc = arg[i + 1]\n    \n    -- index of the handler filter\n    local handlerIndex = mthCeilF(i/2)\n    \n    -- handlerFilter must be a table and handlerFunc must be a function\n    assert(type(handlerFilter) == \"table\" and type(handlerFunc) == \"function\",\n      \"RunHandled - handler \" .. handlerIndex .. \" is invalid!\")\n    assert(handlerFilter.readyForRunHandled, \n      \"Invalid handler filter (\" .. handlerIndex .. \") passed to RunHandled! (Did you forget to use On or OnEvery?)\")\n    -- register handler:\n    -- store the handler function in handler filter table (so it is not stored in upvalue with which pluto has problems)\n    handlerFilter.handlerFunc = handlerFunc;\n    handlerFilter.coroutineParams = currentCoroutineParams\n    -- when handler filter gets signaled - it will call the handler function\n    handlerFilter.OnSignaled = RunHandled_HandlerFilter_OnSignaled\n    -- call filter's registration function\n    handlerFilter:Register()\n  end\n  -- run handled function\n  func()\n  -- HANDLER UNREGISTRATION -- \n  -- go through all optional arguments\n  for i = 1, ctArgs, 2 do\n    -- each optional argument is a handler and first element is the handler filter\n    local handlerFilter = arg[i]\n    -- (no need to check the handler filter now since they were all checked upon registration)\n    -- check that handler filter has a valid 'Unregister' function\n    assert(type(handlerFilter.Unregister) == \"function\",\n      \"RunHandled - handler \" .. i .. \" is invalid (missing 'Deregister' function)!\")\n    -- call handler filter's 'Unregister' function\n    handlerFilter:Unregister()\n  end\nend\n\n\n-- OnSignaled function set to handler filters in BreakableRunHandled construct\nlocal function BreakableRunHandled_handlerFilter_OnSignaled(self, event)\n  -- run handler function in new coroutine, with given coroutine params and\n  -- with event given as parameter\n  RunInNewCoroutine(self.handlerFunc, self.coroutineParams, event)\nend\n\nlocal function dummyOnScriptEventRegistered()\nend\n\n-- Same as RunHandled, except that it is possible to break the execution\n-- of the handled function and all of its handlers.\nfunction BreakableRunHandled(func, ...)\n  -- func must be a function\n  assert(type(func) == \"function\", \"First argument to BreakableRunHandled must be a function!\")\n  local ctArgs = #arg\n  -- there should be at least one handler\n  assert(ctArgs > 0, \"BreakableRunHandled should have at least one handler filter handler function pair!\")\n  -- there should be even number of arguments (because handler filter should come with handler function)\n  assert(ctArgs % 2 == 0, \"invalid handler arguments to BreakableRunHandled!\")\n  \n  -- create coroutine which will execute the handled function\n  -- put it in a special table which contains breakable coroutines\n  -- and signal an event on that table after function is finished\n  -- (so code after BreakableRunHandled continues)\n  -- since this table is registered as event object, it should have the 'OnScriptEventRegistered' function so it doesn't cause crashes (all other objects have this function)\n  local breakableCoroutines = {OnScriptEventRegistered = dummyOnScriptEventRegistered}\n  -- this table should have weak values so references to\n  -- coroutines are not artificially kept\n  setmetatable(breakableCoroutines, {__mode = \"v\"})\n  \n  local handledCoroutine = coroutine.create(\n    function()\n      -- run handled function\n      func()\n      -- signal the event that breakable runhandled has finished (and was not breaked)\n      SignalEvent(breakableCoroutines, \"HandledFinished\", false)\n    end\n  )\n  breakableCoroutines[1] = handledCoroutine\n  -- setup coroutine params which will be used for all handlers and child coroutines\n  local coroutineParams = {breakableCoroutines = breakableCoroutines}\n  -- register coroutine params in coroutine params table for handled coroutine\n  lsch_coroutineParamsTable[handledCoroutine] = coroutineParams;\n  \n  -- HANDLER REGISTRATION --\n  -- go through all optional arguments\n  for i = 1, ctArgs, 2 do\n    -- each pair of optional arguments is a handler-filter pair\n    local handlerFilter = arg[i]\n    local handlerFunc = arg[i + 1]\n    \n    -- index of the handler filter\n    local handlerIndex = mthCeilF(i/2)\n    \n    -- handlerFilter must be a table and handlerFunc must be a function\n    assert(type(handlerFilter) == \"table\" and type(handlerFunc) == \"function\",\n      \"BreakableRunHandled - handler \" .. handlerIndex .. \" is invalid!\")\n    assert(handlerFilter.readyForRunHandled, \n      \"Invalid handler filter (\" .. handlerIndex .. \") passed to BreakableRunHandled! (Did you forget to use On or OnEvery?)\")\n    -- register handler:\n    -- store the handler function in handler filter table (so it is not stored in upvalue with which pluto has problems)\n    handlerFilter.handlerFunc = handlerFunc;\n    handlerFilter.coroutineParams = coroutineParams\n    -- when handler filter gets signaled - it will call the handler function\n    handlerFilter.OnSignaled = BreakableRunHandled_handlerFilter_OnSignaled\n    -- call filter's registration function\n    handlerFilter:Register()\n  end\n  \n  -- start the handled coroutine\n  lschResumeCoroutine(handledCoroutine)\n  \n  -- do not continue until event signaling that handled coroutine is finished is signaled\n  -- accept result saying whether handled was breaked or not\n  local handledBreaked = Wait(CustomEvent(breakableCoroutines, \"HandledFinished\"))\n  \n  -- if handled function was breaked\n  if handledBreaked then\n    -- unregister all filters waiting to resume handled coroutine\n    -- or any of its child coroutines\n    for _, co in ipairs(breakableCoroutines) do\n      -- unregister all evens for current coroutine\n      for k, v in pairs(lsch_eventTable) do\n        if type(k) == \"string\" then\n          local found = false\n          for k1, _ in pairs(v) do\n            if k1.coThis == co then\n              v[k1] = nil\n              found = true\n              break\n            end\n          end\n          if found then\n           break\n          end\n        else\n          for k1, v1 in pairs(v) do\n            local found = false\n            for k2, _ in pairs(v1) do\n              if k2.coThis == co then\n                v1[k2] = nil\n                found = true\n                break\n              end\n            end\n            if found then\n             break\n            end\n          end\n        end\n      end\n      -- unregister all timer events for current coroutine\n      for k, v in pairs(lsch_timerEventsTable) do\n        if v.coThis == co then\n          lsch_timerEventsTable[k] = nil\n          break\n        end\n      end\n    end\n  end\n  -- HANDLER UNREGISTRATION -- \n  -- go through all optional arguments\n  for i = 1, ctArgs, 2 do\n    -- each optional argument is a handler and first element is the handler filter\n    local handlerFilter = arg[i]\n    -- (no need to check the handler filter now since they were all checked upon registration)\n    -- check that handler filter has a valid 'Unregister' function\n    assert(type(handlerFilter.Unregister) == \"function\",\n      \"BreakableRunHandled - handler \" .. i .. \" is invalid (missing 'Deregister' function)!\")\n    -- call handler filter's 'Unregister' function\n    handlerFilter:Unregister()\n  end\n  -- return whether handled function has sucessfully finished or was breaked\n  return not handledBreaked\nend\n\n-- Used to break breakable runhandled.\nfunction BreakRunHandled()\n  local coThis = coroutine.running()\n  local coroutineParams = lsch_coroutineParamsTable[coThis]\n  assert(coroutineParams ~= nil, \"Executing BreakRunHandled outside of BreakableRunHandled!\")\n  local breakableCoroutines = coroutineParams.breakableCoroutines\n  assert(breakableCoroutines[1] ~= coThis, \"Executing BreakRunHandled in handled function!\")\n  -- signal event that handled function has finished but with break\n  SignalEvent(breakableCoroutines, \"HandledFinished\", true)\nend\n\n\n\n-- Helpers -----------------------------------------------------\n\n-- Calls the specified function with given optional variable number of parameters on each member of the group\nfunction CallOnGroup(group, functionName, ...)\n assert(type(group) == \"table\" and type(functionName) == \"string\")\n for _, groupMember in pairs(group) do\n   groupMember[functionName](groupMember, ...)\n end\nend \n\n-- Replacement for the standard lua \"ipairs\" function. Needed because \"ipairs\" returns a C function\n-- which cannot be persisted by pluto library.\nfunction _iter_lua(a, i)\n  i = i + 1\n  local v = rawget(a, i)\n  if v ~= nil then\n    return i, v\n  end\nend\n    \nfunction _ipairs_lua(a)\n  assert(type(a) == \"table\", \"bad argument #1 to 'ipairs' (table expected, got \" .. type(a) .. \")\")\n  return _iter_lua, a, 0\nend\n\n-- Replacement for the standard lua \"pairs\" function. Needed because \"pairs\" returns a C function\n-- which cannot be persisted by pluto library.\nfunction _next_lua(t, k)\n  return next(t, k)\nend\n\nfunction _pairs_lua(t)\n  assert(type(t) == \"table\", \"bad argument #1 to 'pairs' (table expected, got \" .. type(t) .. \")\")\n  return _next_lua, t, nil\nend\n\n-- accepts a string and returns it, used only to specify dependencies in lua scripts (parsed by SECmd)\nfunction Depfile(f)\n  return f\nend\n""

""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Terrain/Shaders/TerrainElevationSamplingCommon.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vNodeMad, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vLevelAndSamplesPerMeter, 1);\n_CregF(float4, c_vInputElevPixUVmad, 2);\n_CregF(float4, c_vEditElevUVmad, 3);\n\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float4, vInPos, 0);\n  _inReg(float2, fInData, 1); // x = alpha, y = alpha interpolation correction factor\n  _inReg(float, fInTransCoeff, 2);\nVS_IN_END\n\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg(float4, vInputElevPixEditElevUV, 0);\n  _outReg(float, fAlpha, 1);\n  _outReg(float, fInterpolationFactor, 2);\n  _outReg(float, fPow, 3);\nVS_OUT_END\n\nVS_ENTRY(TerrainRoadElevationDownsamplingVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4(VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vNodeMad.xy + c_vNodeMad.zw, 0, 1);\n  VS_OUT(vInputElevPixEditElevUV).xy = VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vInputElevPixUVmad.xy + c_vInputElevPixUVmad.zw;\n#if HAS_EDITED_DATA\n  VS_OUT(vInputElevPixEditElevUV).zw = VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vEditElevUVmad.xy + c_vEditElevUVmad.zw;\n#else\n  VS_OUT(vInputElevPixEditElevUV).zw = float2(0, 0);\n#endif\n  VS_OUT(fAlpha) = VS_IN(fInData.x);\n  VS_OUT(fInterpolationFactor) = VS_IN(fInData.y);\n  VS_OUT(fPow) = c_vLevelAndSamplesPerMeter.z * VS_IN(fInTransCoeff);\n  //VS_OUT(fPow) = pow(2, c_vLevelAndSamplesPerMeter.x - 8.5) * VS_IN(fInTransWidth) * VS_IN(fInData).y;\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n_Sreg2D(t_sInputElevationmap2D, s_tInputElevationmap2D, 0);\n#if HAS_EDITED_DATA\n_SregAry2D(t_sEditElevMap, s_tEditElevMap, 1);\n#endif\n\n// .xy = size, .zw = 1 / size\n_CregF(float4, c_vElevationSamplingConsts, 0);\nstatic float c_fEditElevSlice = c_vElevationSamplingConsts.x;\nstatic float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize = c_vElevationSamplingConsts.zw;\n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float4, vInputElevPixEditElevUV, 0);\n  _inReg(float, fAlpha, 1);\n  _inReg(float, fInterpolationFactor, 2);\n  _inReg(float, fPow, 3);\nPS_IN_END\n\nPS_ENTRY(TerrainRoadElevationDownsamplingPS)\n{\n  float4 vOutColor;\n#if HAS_EDITED_DATA\n  float2 vEditElevUV = PS_IN(vInputElevPixEditElevUV).zw;\n  float fEditElev = texSample2D(t_sEditElevMap, s_tEditElevMap, float3(vEditElevUV, c_fEditElevSlice)).r;\n  if (fEditElev > -1000000.f) {\n    vOutColor = EncodeElevationmapSample(fEditElev, 0.0f);\n    PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n  }\n#endif\n  float fElevation;\n  float2 vPixCoords = PS_IN(vInputElevPixEditElevUV).xy;\n\n  float2 vFrac = frac(vPixCoords - 0.5f);\n  // this will hit pixel centers (coordinates ending with .5)\n  float2 vCenter = vPixCoords - vFrac;\n  \n#if !APPROX_BICUBIC\n  if (vFrac.x > 0.01f || vFrac.y > 0.01f) {\n#endif\n    float3 fElevGrad = GetInterpolatedElevation(t_sInputElevationmap2D, s_tInputElevationmap2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vCenter, vFrac);\n    fElevation = fElevGrad.x;\n#if !APPROX_BICUBIC\n  } else {\n    fElevation = GetSimpleElevationSample(t_sInputElevationmap2D, s_tInputElevationmap2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, PS_IN(vInputElevPixLodCoords).xy).x;\n  }\n#endif\n\n  float fOutAlpha = 0.0f;\n  float fCorrectedAlpha = PS_IN(fAlpha) / PS_IN(fInterpolationFactor);\n  float fPow = PS_IN(fPow) / PS_IN(fInterpolationFactor);\n\n  fOutAlpha = max((fCorrectedAlpha - 1) * fPow + 1, 0);\n\n  vOutColor = EncodeElevationmapSample(fElevation, fOutAlpha);\n  PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Terrain/Shaders/TerrainHelpers.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vNodeMad, 0);\n_CregF(float2, c_vUVStretch, 2);\n_CregF(float4, c_vMainMaterialsUVMad, 3);\n\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float4, vInPos, 0);\n  _inReg(float4, vInData, 1); // x=alpha, y=width, zw=texUV\nVS_IN_END\n\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg(float4, vVtxData, 0);\n  _outReg(float2, vMainMaterialCoords, 2);\nVS_OUT_END\n\nVS_ENTRY(TerrainRoadGlossVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4(VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vNodeMad.xy + c_vNodeMad.zw, 0, 1);\n  VS_OUT(vVtxData).xy = VS_IN(vInData).xy;\n  VS_OUT(vVtxData).zw = VS_IN(vInData).zw * c_vUVStretch.xy;\n  VS_OUT(vMainMaterialCoords) = VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vMainMaterialsUVMad.xy + c_vMainMaterialsUVMad.zw;\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - 1 - c_iFirstMainMaterial;\n  if (iMainVariation < 0 || iMainVariation >= c_ctMainMaterialCount) {\n    clip(-1);\n  }\n  int iArraySlice = GetMaterialSlice(iMainVariation);\n  float4 vGloss = texLod2D(t_sGlossmap, s_tGlossmap, float3(PS_IN(vVtxData).zw, iArraySlice), c_fMipmap);\n\n  vGloss.argb *= float4(GetMaterialBaseSpec(iMainVariation), GetMaterialCoatSpec(iMainVariation), GetMaterialCoatMask(iMainVariation), GetMaterialDetAtt(iMainVariation));\n\n  PS_OUT(vGloss);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vNodeMad, 0);\n\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float3, vInPos, 0);\n  _inReg(float, fOrthoDist, 1);\n  _inReg(float2, vInHorDis, 2);\nVS_IN_END\n\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg(float3, vHorDisOrthoDist, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\nVS_ENTRY(TerrainWallHorDisVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4(VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vNodeMad.xy + c_vNodeMad.zw, 0, 1);\n  VS_OUT(vHorDisOrthoDist) = float3(VS_IN(vInHorDis), VS_IN(fOrthoDist));\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vQuadSize, 0);\n\nstatic float c_fQuadSize = c_vQuadSize.x;\n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float3, vHorDisOrthoDist, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\nPS_ENTRY(TerrainWallHorDisPS)\n{\n  float2 vHorDis = PS_IN(vHorDisOrthoDist).xy;\n  float fOrthoDist = PS_IN(vHorDisOrthoDist).z;\n\n  if (fOrthoDist > 1.42 * c_fQuadSize) {\n    vHorDis = float2(0, 0);\n  }\n\n  float4 vOutColor = float4(vHorDis, 0, 1);\n  PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vNodeMad, 0);\n\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float3, vInPos, 0);\n  _inReg(float, fOrthoDist, 1);\nVS_IN_END\n\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n_outReg(float2, fElevOrthoDist, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\nVS_ENTRY(TerrainWallElevationVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4(VS_IN(vInPos).xz * c_vNodeMad.xy + c_vNodeMad.zw, 0, 1);\n  VS_OUT(fElevOrthoDist) = float2(VS_IN(vInPos).y, VS_IN(fOrthoDist));\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vQuadSize, 0);\n\nstatic float c_fQuadSize = c_vQuadSize.x;\n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float2, fElevOrthoDist, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\nPS_ENTRY(TerrainWallElevationPS)\n{\n  float fElevation = PS_IN(fElevOrthoDist).x;\n  float fOrthoDist = PS_IN(fElevOrthoDist).y;\n\n  if (fOrthoDist > 2 * 1.42 * c_fQuadSize) {\n    clip(-1);\n  }\n\n  float4 vOutColor = float4(fElevation, 0, 0, 1);\n  PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n_Sreg2D(t_sInputFrame2D, s_tInputFrame2D, 0);\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vColor, 0);\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vContrast_Brightness_Gamma, 1);\n#define c_fContrast (c_vContrast_Brightness_Gamma.x)\n#define c_fBrightness (c_vContrast_Brightness_Gamma.y)\n#define c_fGamma (c_vContrast_Brightness_Gamma.z)\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vChromaKey_PixelSize, 2);\n#define c_vChromaKey (c_vChromaKey_PixelSize.xy)\n#define c_vPixelSize (c_vChromaKey_PixelSize.zw)\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vKeyRGB, 3);\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vSimilarity_Smoothness_Spill, 4);\n#define c_fSimilarity (c_vSimilarity_Smoothness_Spill.x)\n#define c_fSmoothness (c_vSimilarity_Smoothness_Spill.y)\n#define c_fSpill (c_vSimilarity_Smoothness_Spill.z)\n\nstatic float4x4 g_mYUV = float4x4(\n    float4(0.182586, -0.100644,  0.439216, 0.000000),\n    float4(0.614231, -0.338572,  -0.398942, 0.000000),\n    float4(0.062007, 0.439216, -0.040274, 0.000000),\n    float4(0.062745, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.000000)\n  );\n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float2, vUV, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\nfloat4 GetInputColor(float2 vUV)\n{\n\treturn texSample2D(t_sInputFrame2D, s_tInputFrame2D, vUV);\n}\n\nfloat ChromaDistance(float3 vCol)\n{\n\tfloat4 vYUV = mul(float4(vCol.rgb, 1.0), g_mYUV);\n\treturn distance(c_vChromaKey, vYUV.yz);\n}\n\n// Calculates the average chroma distance in area of 3x3 pixels around the provided UV coordinate\nfloat CalculateAverageChromaDistance(float3 vColSample, float2 vUV)\n{\n\tfloat fDistanceSum = ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV-c_vPixelSize).rgb);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV-float2(0.0, c_vPixelSize.y)).rgb);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV+float2(c_vPixelSize.x, -c_vPixelSize.y)).rgb);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV-float2(c_vPixelSize.x, 0.0)).rgb);\n  fDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(vColSample);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV+float2(c_vPixelSize.x, 0.0)).rgb);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV-float2(c_vPixelSize.x, -c_vPixelSize.y)).rgb);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV+float2(0.0, c_vPixelSize.y)).rgb);\n\tfDistanceSum += ChromaDistance(GetInputColor(vUV+c_vPixelSize).rgb);\n\treturn fDistanceSum/9.0;\n}\n\nfloat4 ChromaKeying(float4 vColSample, float2 vUV)\n{\n\tfloat fMaskBase = CalculateAverageChromaDistance(vColSample.rgb, vUV) - c_fSimilarity;\n\tfloat fMask = pow(saturate(fMaskBase/c_fSmoothness), 1.5);\n\tvColSample.a *= fMask;\n\n\tfloat fDesat = saturate((vColSample.r * 0.2126 + vColSample.g * 0.7152 + vColSample.b * 0.0722));\n\tfloat fSpill = pow(saturate(fMaskBase/c_fSpill), 1.5);\n\tvColSample.rgb = float3(fDesat, fDesat, fDesat) * (1.0 - fSpill) + vColSample.rgb * fSpill;\n\n  return vColSample;\n}\n\nPS_ENTRY(ChromaKeyPS)\n{\n  float4 vInColor = GetInputColor(PS_IN(vUV))*c_vColor;\n\n  float4 vOutColor = ChromaKeying(vInColor, PS_IN(vUV));\n  \n  // modifying the output for gama, contrast and brightness\n  vOutColor.rgb = pow(vOutColor.rgb, float3(c_fGamma, c_fGamma, c_fGamma)) * c_fContrast;\n  vOutColor.rgb += c_fBrightness;\n  PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n_Sreg2D(t_sInputFrame2D, s_tInputFrame2D, 0);\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vInputOutputSize, 0);\nstatic float2 c_vInputSize = c_vInputOutputSize.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vOutputSize = c_vInputOutputSize.zw;\n_CregM44F(c_mColorMatrix, 1);\n_CregF(float2, c_vPeriod_Y, 5);\n_CregF(float2, c_vPeriod_U, 6);\n_CregF(float2, c_vPeriod_V, 7);\n_CregF(float4, c_vMAD_Y, 8);\n_CregF(float4, c_vMAD_U, 9);\n_CregF(float4, c_vMAD_V, 10);\n_CregF(float2, c_vPortraitUpsideDown, 11);\n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float2, vUV, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\nfloat3 ConvertYUVToRGB(float3 vYUV)\n{\n  float4 vRGBX = mul( float4(vYUV,1.0f), c_mColorMatrix);\n  return saturate( vRGBX.rgb);\n}\n\nfloat3 GetSamplingCoords(float2 vPix, float2 vPixPeriod, float4 vPixMAD)\n{\n  float2 vAdjustedPix = floor(vPix / vPixPeriod);\n  float fAdjustedWidth = c_vOutputSize.x / vPixPeriod.x;\n  float fAdjustedPixIndex = floor(vAdjustedPix.y * fAdjustedWidth + vAdjustedPix.x + 0.5f);\n  fAdjustedPixIndex = round(fAdjustedPixIndex * vPixMAD.x + vPixMAD.z) + 0.5f;\n  \n  float3 vPixSampling;\n  int2 ivAdjPixInputSize = int2( fAdjustedPixIndex, c_vInputSize.x);\n  vPixSampling.x = _tcast( float, (ivAdjPixInputSize.x % ivAdjPixInputSize.y));\n  vPixSampling.y = _tcast( float, (ivAdjPixInputSize.x / ivAdjPixInputSize.y));\n  \n  vPixSampling.y = vPixSampling.y * vPixMAD.y + vPixMAD.w;\n  vPixSampling += 0.5f;\n  \n  int iPixSamplingX = _tcast( int, vPixSampling.x);\n  vPixSampling.z = _tcast( float, (iPixSamplingX % 4));\n  vPixSampling.x = _tcast( float, (iPixSamplingX / 4)) +0.5f;\n\n  vPixSampling.x /= c_vInputSize.x * 0.25f;\n  vPixSampling.y /= c_vInputSize.y;\n  return vPixSampling;\n}\n\nfloat SampleInputFrame(float3 vUVComponent)\n{\n  float4 vSample = texSample2D(t_sInputFrame2D, s_tInputFrame2D, vUVComponent.xy);\n  int iComponent = _tcast( int, vUVComponent.z);\n  return vSample.bgra[iComponent];\n}\n\nfloat3 GetYUV(float2 vUV)\n{\n  float2 vPixOut = vUV * c_vOutputSize;\n  float3 vUV_Y = GetSamplingCoords(vPixOut, c_vPeriod_Y, c_vMAD_Y);\n  float3 vUV_U = GetSamplingCoords(vPixOut, c_vPeriod_U, c_vMAD_U);\n  float3 vUV_V = GetSamplingCoords(vPixOut, c_vPeriod_V, c_vMAD_V);\n\n  float3 vYUV;\n  vYUV.x = SampleInputFrame(vUV_Y);\n  vYUV.y = SampleInputFrame(vUV_U);\n  vYUV.z = SampleInputFrame(vUV_V);\n  return vYUV;\n}\n\nPS_ENTRY(VideoFormatConversionPS)\n{\n  float2 vUV;\n  // swap coordinates in portrait mode\n  if (c_vPortraitUpsideDown.x > 0.5f) {\n    vUV.xy = PS_IN(vUV).yx;\n    // mirror image if source is upside down\n    if (c_vPortraitUpsideDown.y > 0.5f) {\n      vUV.y = 1.0f - vUV.y;\n    }\n  } else {\n    vUV.xy = PS_IN(vUV).xy;\n  }\n  \n  float3 vYUV = GetYUV(vUV);\n  \n  float4 vOutColor;\n  vOutColor.rgb = ConvertYUVToRGB(vYUV);\n  vOutColor.a = 1.0f;\n  PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// AmbientOcclusionShader.psh\n\n// (Special thanx goes to nVidia's Morgan McGuire, Michael Mara and David Luebke for Scalable Ambient Obscurance method!)\n\n\n// handy macros\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// (use optimized code)\n#define OPTIMIZE 1\n// (use scalable SSAO)\n#define USE_SAO 1\n\n// if SSAO samples are not specified\n#ifndef SSAO_SAMPLES\n  // not valid!\n  #define SSAO_SAMPLES 1\n#endif\n\n// sampling pixel distance, fall-off and darkness\n_CregF( float4, c_vRadOffBiasDith, 0);\nstatic float c_fDistance    = c_vRadOffBiasDith.x;\nstatic float c_fFallOffStep = c_vRadOffBiasDith.y;\nstatic float c_fDepthOffset = c_vRadOffBiasDith.z;\nstatic float c_fDithering   = c_vRadOffBiasDith.w;\n\n// Z-buffer scale and offset\n_CregF( float2, c_vDepthScaler, 1);\nstatic float c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepthScaler.x;\nstatic float c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepthScaler.y;\n\n// projective frustum params\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumLeftZ, 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumRightZ,3);\nstatic float4 g_vFrustumZ;\n\n// rendering canvas size (width and height)\n_CregF( float4, c_vScreenSizes, 4);\nstatic float2 c_vScreenSize  = c_vScreenSizes.xy;\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize= c_vScreenSizes.zw;\n// depth buffer size (width and height)\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepthSizes, 5);\nstatic float2 c_vDepthSize   = c_vDepthSizes.xy;\nstatic float2 c_v1oDepthSize = c_vDepthSizes.zw;\n\n// SSAO radius modulation data\n_CregF( float4, c_vSceneRadiusModulation, 6);\nstatic float c_fFocusDistance   = c_vSceneRadiusModulation.x;     // efx_fOcclusionRadiusMinStretchDistance\nstatic float c_f1oFocusDistance = c_vSceneRadiusModulation.y;     // 1.0f / efx_fOcclusionRadiusMinStretchDistance\nstatic float c_fMaxStretch      = c_vSceneRadiusModulation.z;     // efx_fOcclusionRadiusMaxStretch - 1.0f\nstatic float c_f1oStretchRange  = c_vSceneRadiusModulation.w;     // 1.0f / (efx_fOcclusionRadiusMaxStretchDistance - efx_fOcclusionRadiusMinStretchDistance)\n\n_CregF( float3, c_vMiscModulation, 7);\nstatic float c_fWeaponRadiusMultiplier = c_vMiscModulation.x;   // efx_fOcclusionRadiusWeaponStretch\nstatic float c_fStrength = c_vMiscModulation.y;\nstatic float c_fFOVAdjust = c_vMiscModulation.z;\n\n#if _HLSL\n\n  // sphere sampling points\n  const uniform float3 c_avSpherePoints[ SSAO_SAMPLES] : register(c8);\n\n  // get one sphere point\n  static inline float3 _getSpherePoint( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avSpherePoints[ iIndex];\n  }\n#elif _GLSL\n\n  // get one sphere point\n  static inline float3 _getSpherePoint( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avUniformsF[ iIndex+8].xyz;\n  }\n#endif\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n#ifdef run_AmbientOcclusionPS\n\n\n// scene depth (normalized distance in meters)\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 0);\n// random texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sRandom, s_tRandom, 1);\n\n\n// (some constants to keep GLSL happy)\nstatic const float4 _c_vZero4f = float4(0,0,0,0);\nstatic const float4 _c_vOne4f  = float4(1,1,1,1);\n\n\n// return depth sampled from specified tex coords\ninline float GetOneDepth( const float2 vTexCoords)\n{\n  // read depth from texture, and restore depth range\n  float fDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( vTexCoords)).r;\n  return DECODE_DEPTH(fDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;  // == -fDepth\n}\n\n\n// return 4 depths sampled from specified tex coords (.x=left, .y=right, .z=up, .w=down)\ninline float4 GetFourDepths( float4 vTexCoordsLR, float4 vTexCoordsUD)\n{\n  // read depth from texture, and restore depth range\n  float4 vDepths;\n  vTexCoordsLR = MultiviewUV2( vTexCoordsLR);\n  vTexCoordsUD = MultiviewUV2( vTexCoordsUD);\n  vDepths.x = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoordsLR.xy, 0.0f).r;\n  vDepths.y = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoordsLR.zw, 0.0f).r;\n  vDepths.z = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoordsUD.xy, 0.0f).r;\n  vDepths.w = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoordsUD.zw, 0.0f).r;\n  return DECODE_DEPTH(vDepths) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n}\n\n\n// reconstruct pixel position in clip-space, based on uv coords\ninline float2 GetClipPosition( in float2 vScreenCoord)\n{\n  // convert coord to clip space\n  return vScreenCoord *float2(2,-2) +float2(-1,1);\n}\n\n// calculate pixel position in view-space, based on clip coords and view space (linear) depth\ninline float3 CalcViewPosition( in float3 vClipCoord)\n{\n  vClipCoord.xy = -vClipCoord.z* (vClipCoord.xy+ g_vFrustumZ.yw) /g_vFrustumZ.xz;\n  return vClipCoord;\n}\n\n\n// reconstruct pixel position in view-space, based on uv coords and view space (linear) depth\ninline float3 GetViewPosition( in float3 vCoord)\n{         \n  // convert coord to clip space\n  vCoord.xy = GetClipPosition( vCoord.xy);\n  // and then to view space\n  return CalcViewPosition( vCoord);\n}\n\n\n// reconstruct per-pixel normal in view-space, based on pixel uv coords and pixel view-space position\ninline float3 GetNormal( const float2 vTexCoords, const float3 vViewPos)\n{\n  // We calculate the normal in the direction of minimum depth difference,\n  // in order to avoid crossing object boundaries.\n\n#if OPTIMIZE\n\n  // Determine tex coords of four nearest neighbour samples.\n  float4 vTexCoordsLR = vTexCoords.xyxy +float4( -c_v1oDepthSize.x, 0, c_v1oDepthSize.x, 0);\n  float4 vTexCoordsUD = vTexCoords.xyxy +float4( 0, -c_v1oDepthSize.y, 0, c_v1oDepthSize.y);\n\n  // Sample all four positions and calculate delta from pivot.\n  float4 vDepths = GetFourDepths( vTexCoordsLR, vTexCoordsUD);\n  float4 vDepthDeltas = abs( vDepths - vViewPos.z); \n\n  // We are assuming positive direction in both x and y axis.\n  // Pack all data into a float4: uv coords, linear view-space depth, direction multiplier. \n  float4 vMinTexCoordsDepthX  = float4( vTexCoordsLR.xy, vDepths.x,-1);\n  float4 vMinTexCoordsDepthX1 = float4( vTexCoordsLR.zw, vDepths.y, 1);\n  float4 vMinTexCoordsDepthY  = float4( vTexCoordsUD.xy, vDepths.z,-1);\n  float4 vMinTexCoordsDepthY1 = float4( vTexCoordsUD.xw, vDepths.w, 1);\n\n  // Test the depth difference in opposite direction and select the minimum.\n  vMinTexCoordsDepthX = (vDepthDeltas.x<vDepthDeltas.y) ? vMinTexCoordsDepthX : vMinTexCoordsDepthX1;\n  vMinTexCoordsDepthY = (vDepthDeltas.z<vDepthDeltas.w) ? vMinTexCoordsDepthY : vMinTexCoordsDepthY1;\n\n  // Reconstruct view-space 3D position of selected samples.\n  float3 vSampleH = GetViewPosition( vMinTexCoordsDepthX.xyz);\n  float3 vSampleV = GetViewPosition( vMinTexCoordsDepthY.xyz);\n\n  // Based on sampling direction, determine component vectors of the normal.\n  vSampleH -= vViewPos;\n  vSampleH *= vMinTexCoordsDepthX.w;\n\n  vSampleV -= vViewPos;\n  vSampleV *= vMinTexCoordsDepthY.w;\n\n#else // OPTIMIZE\n\n  // Determine tex coords of four nearest neighbour samples.\n  float2 vTexCoordsRight = vTexCoords+ float2( c_v1oDepthSize.x, 0);\n  float2 vTexCoordsLeft  = vTexCoords- float2( c_v1oDepthSize.x, 0);\n  float2 vTexCoordsDown  = vTexCoords+ float2( 0, c_v1oDepthSize.y);\n  float2 vTexCoordsUp    = vTexCoords- float2( 0, c_v1oDepthSize.y);\n\n  // Sample all four positions.\n  float fDepthRight = GetOneDepth( vTexCoordsRight);\n  float fDepthLeft  = GetOneDepth( vTexCoordsLeft);\n  float fDepthDown  = GetOneDepth( vTexCoordsDown);\n  float fDepthUp    = GetOneDepth( vTexCoordsUp);\n\n  // Toggle variables that indicate swapping the sampling direction.\n  float bLeft = 0.0f;\n  float bUp = 0.0f;\n\n  // We are assuming positive direction in both x and y axis.\n  float fMinDepthX = fDepthRight;\n  float2 vMinTexCoordsX = vTexCoordsRight;\n  float fMinDepthY = fDepthDown;\n  float2 vMinTexCoordsY = vTexCoordsDown;\n   \n  // Test the depth difference in opposite direction and select the minimum.\n  if( abs( fDepthLeft-vViewPos.z) < abs( fMinDepthX-vViewPos.z)) {\n    fMinDepthX = fDepthLeft;\n    vMinTexCoordsX = vTexCoordsLeft;\n    bLeft = 1.0f;\n  } \n  if( abs( fDepthUp-vViewPos.z) < abs( fMinDepthY-vViewPos.z)) {\n    fMinDepthY = fDepthUp;\n    vMinTexCoordsY = vTexCoordsUp;\n    bUp = 1.0f;\n  }   \n\n  // reconstruct view-space 3D position of selected samples\n  float3 vSampleH = GetViewPosition( float3( vMinTexCoordsX, fMinDepthX));\n  float3 vSampleV = GetViewPosition( float3( vMinTexCoordsY, fMinDepthY));\n\n  // Based on sampling direction, determine component vectors of the normal.\n  if( bLeft == 1.0f) {\n    vSampleH = vViewPos - vSampleH; \n  } else {\n    vSampleH = vSampleH - vViewPos;\n  }\n  if( bUp == 1.0f) {\n    vSampleV = vViewPos - vSampleV;\n  } else {\n    vSampleV = vSampleV - vViewPos;\n  }\n#endif // OPTIMIZE\n\n  // Compute the normal.\n  return normalize( cross( vSampleV, vSampleH));\n} \n\n\n// return a random 3D normal (sampled from a look-up texture)\ninline float3 GetRandom3( in float2 vTexCoords)\n{\n  vTexCoords *= c_vScreenSize / 4.0f;  // (random texture is fixed to 4x4 texels)\n  float3 vNormal = texSample2D( t_sRandom, s_tRandom, vTexCoords).xyz *2.0f -1.0f;\n  return vNormal * c_fDithering;  // (already normalized!)\n}\n\n\n// -------------------------------------------------\n// Hemisphere based ambient occlusion. (USEFUL ONE!)\n// -------------------------------------------------\n\n// Screen-space ambient occlusion\nPS_ENTRY( AmbientOcclusionPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustumZ = VRSelect( c_vFrustumLeftZ, c_vFrustumRightZ);\n  \n  // get pivot texture coordinates (offseted a bit by scaling factor)\n  float2 vInTexCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy);\n  /*\n  // make sure that we sample direct center of pivot pixel, \n  // otherwise nasty artefacts may occur when computing normal\n  // (THIS IS NOT TRUE! THIS CODE ACTUALLY PRODUCES A LOT OF ARTEFACTS!)\n  vInTexCoords = vInTexCoords *c_vDepthSize +0.5f;\n  vInTexCoords -= frac( vInTexCoords);\n  vInTexCoords += 0.5f;\n  vInTexCoords *= c_v1oDepthSize;\n  //*/\n  // sample pivot depth and calc linear depth\n  float3 vPivotClipPos; // (.z == pivot depth)\n  float fRawPivotDepth = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( vInTexCoords), 0.0f).r;\n  vPivotClipPos.z = DECODE_DEPTH(fRawPivotDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  #define fPivotDepth vPivotClipPos.z\n \n  // ignore background pixels\n  float fOcclusion = 0.0f;\n  if( fRawPivotDepth < 0.95f) {\n\n    // reconstruct pivot (current pixel) position and normal in view space\n    vPivotClipPos.xy = GetClipPosition( vInTexCoords);\n    float3 vPivotViewPos= CalcViewPosition( vPivotClipPos);\n    float3 vPivotNormal = GetNormal( vInTexCoords, vPivotViewPos);\n\n    // offset the pivot in the direction of the normal, to remove z-fighting issues\n    // the amount of offseting is determined by the pivot's current depth\n    // (far away pixels require large offsets, near ones little to no offset)\n    vPivotViewPos -= vPivotNormal * fPivotDepth * c_fDepthOffset;\n\n    // random normal for kernel rotation\n    float3 vRandom = GetRandom3( vInTexCoords);\n    \n    // number of discarded samples\n    float fOutSamples = 0.0f;\n\n    // Compute SSAO radius multiplier.
