We want:\n    // - smaller radius for close-ups (to prevent a huge performance drop, due to sampling a very large area of screen; bonus: capture small surface details)\n    // - larger radius for distant objects (practicaly free, due to still small screen-space sampling area; more noticable and visually pleasing AO shadows for distant occluders)\n            \n    // for pixels futher away than focus distance, lerp the multiplier between 1.0f and max stretch factor, based on pixel depth\n    float fSceneRadiusMultiplier = c_fMaxStretch * saturate((-fPivotDepth - c_fFocusDistance) * c_f1oStretchRange) + 1.0f;\n    // for pixels closer than focus distance, lerp the multiplier between 0.0f and 1.0f, based on pixel depth\n    fSceneRadiusMultiplier *= saturate(-fPivotDepth * c_f1oFocusDistance); \n\n    // select proper multiplier for scene / first person weapon rendering\n    float fRadiusMultiplier = (fRawPivotDepth<0.0f) ? c_fWeaponRadiusMultiplier : fSceneRadiusMultiplier;\n    // Scale AO radius by FOV adjustment factor (wide FOV allows for a wide radius, narrow FOV requires a narrow radius).\n    // Note: weapon radius is adjusted by scene FOV factor. This produces errors because weapon renders in its own FOV. \n    // The correct solution would be to use different projection matrices for reconstructing samples' view space positions, \n    // depending on whether sampled depth is negative (weapon) or positive (scene). However, this would add complexity and \n    // was deemed unnecessary.\n    fRadiusMultiplier *= c_fFOVAdjust;\n\n    // determine the scaled radius falloff step\n    float fFallOffStep = c_fFallOffStep * fRadiusMultiplier;\n\n    // determine if pivot depth is positive (scene pixels have positive depth, weapon pixels have negative depth)\n    float fPivotDepthPositive = step( 0.0f, fRawPivotDepth);\n               \n    // gather occlusion contribution from each sample\n    float fSampleDistance = c_fDistance * fRadiusMultiplier;\n    float2 vClipSample;\n    float fDepthMip;\n  #if !USE_SAO\n    fDepthMip = 0.0f;\n  #endif\n  #if !_PSSL\n    _unroll\n  #endif\n    for( int iSample=0; iSample<SSAO_SAMPLES; iSample++) {\n      \n      // rotate the sampling kernel by reflecting against a random plane (defined by random normal)\n      float3 vOffsetView = reflect( _getSpherePoint( iSample), vRandom) * fSampleDistance;\n      \n      // samples falling outside the pivot's hemisphere are wasted, \n      // so flip them to achieve better sampling density\n      // (must ensure that sampling sphere points the shader gets do not overlap when flipped!)\n    #if OPTIMIZE\n      float fOffsetNormal = dot( vOffsetView, vPivotNormal);\n      vOffsetView = (fOffsetNormal>=0.0f) ? vOffsetView : -vOffsetView;\n    #else\n      if( dot( vOffsetView, vPivotNormal) < 0.0f) {\n        vOffsetView = -vOffsetView;\n      }\n    #endif\n\n      // the sample in view space\n      float3 vSample = vPivotViewPos + vOffsetView;\n          \n      // project sample into clip space\n      vClipSample = (vSample.xy/-vSample.z) *g_vFrustumZ.xz -g_vFrustumZ.yw;\n\n      // if using scalable SSAO\n    #if USE_SAO\n\n      // calculate distance from pivot\n      float2 vSampleDist = abs( vClipSample-vPivotClipPos.xy);\n      vSampleDist *= c_vScreenSize;\n      float fSampleDist = max( vSampleDist.x, vSampleDist.y);\n      // and choose mipmap in distance buffer\n      fDepthMip = log2( fSampleDist) *0.5f;\n\t    fDepthMip = clamp( fDepthMip-2.0f, 0.0f, 3.0f);\n\n    #endif // SAO\n\n      // fetch sample's depth and compute depth delta\n      vClipSample = vClipSample *float2(0.5f,-0.5f) +float2(0.5f,0.5f);\n      float fRawSampleDepth = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( vClipSample), fDepthMip).r;\n      float fSampleDepth = DECODE_DEPTH(fRawSampleDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n      float fDepthDelta = fSampleDepth - vSample.z;\n\n      // in case we've passed a depth threshold we reject the sample to reduce white and black halos\n\n      // white halos are a result of zero-occlusion on a surface that would otherwise be (self)occluded,\n      // black halos are a result of full occlusion on a surface that is too far away to be occluded\n\n      // only positive depth deltas contribute to occlusion\n      // (negative depth delta occurs with samples behind the current pixel - such samples are not occluders)\n\n      // contribution to occlusion is determined by the distance from occluder to ocludee, but we \n      // optimize it away, and just use a binary contribution for every sample (0 or 1)\n\n    #if OPTIMIZE\n\n      // determine if sample is rejected\n\n      // if depth sample is a lot nearer than sphere point\n      float fSkipSample = step( fSampleDistance*2.0f, fDepthDelta);\n      /*\n      // if sample lies outside of screen area (sample depth is zero)\n      float fSkipOutside = (fSampleDepth==0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f;\n      fSkipSample += fSkipOutside;\n      //*/\n      // if pivot belongs to scene and sample belongs to weapon\n      // (pivot depth sign is positive and sample depth sign is negative)\n      // Warning - the opposite case must not be rejected!\n      // When pivot belongs to the weapon and lies on the edge between weapon and scene, most of the samples it gathers belong to the scene.\n      // Therefore, most samples do not occlude it, and it is mostly white. However, if we reject such samples (because their depth has different sign),\n      // what remains are a few samples taken from the weapon (which occlude the pivot), and thus we get (wrongly) very high occlusion, causing a dark\n      // outline around the weapon.\n      float fSkipSign = fPivotDepthPositive * step( fRawSampleDepth, 0.0f);\n      fSkipSample += fSkipSign;\n\n      // clamp fSkipSample to 0 or 1\n      fSkipSample = saturate( fSkipSample);\n      \n      // increase rejected samples count\n      fOutSamples += fSkipSample;\n      \n      // increase occlusion value if sample is not rejected and depth delta is positive\n      float fOccFactor = (fDepthDelta>=0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f;\n      fOcclusion += (1.0f-fSkipSample) * fOccFactor;\n\n    #else // !OPTIMIZE\n              \n      // if depth sample is a lot nearer than sphere point, \n      // or sample lies outside of screen area (sample depth is zero), \n      // or pivot belongs to scene and sample belongs to weapon (pivot depth is positive and sample depth is negative)   \n      if( fDepthDelta>(fSampleDistance*2) || fSampleDepth==0.0f || (fRawPivotDepth>0.0f && fRawSampleDepth<0.0f)) {\n        // do not take it into account\n        fOutSamples += 1.0f;\n      // only positive depth deltas contribute to occlusion\n      } else if( fDepthDelta > 0.0f) {\n        // (negative depth delta occurs with samples behind the current pixel - such samples are not occluders)\n        fOcclusion += 1.0f;\n      }\n\n    #endif // OPTIMIZE\n      \n      // next distances over falloffs\n      fSampleDistance -= fFallOffStep;\n    }\n\n    // average occlusion from all contributing samples\n    fOcclusion /= max( float(SSAO_SAMPLES)-fOutSamples, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT);\n  }\n\n  // compute visibility factor\n  float fVisibility = 1.0f- saturate( fOcclusion *c_fStrength);\n\n  // enhance occlusion a bit\n  fVisibility *= fVisibility;\n\n  // and output it\n  PS_OUT( float4( 0,0,0, fVisibility));\n}\n\n#else // !run_AmbientOcclusionPS\n\n// AO buffer\n_Sreg2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, 2);\n\n#endif\n#ifdef run_MinFilterPS\n\n\n// Minimum filter\nPS_ENTRY( MinFilterPS)\n{   \n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  float fMinimum;\n  float4 vSamples[2];\n  float4 vSampleCoords;\n  \n  // gather samples from upper row\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4(-1,-1, 0,-1);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  vSamples[0].x = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // left\n  vSamples[0].y = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // center\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4( 1,-1, -1,0);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  vSamples[0].z = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // right\n  // gather samples from middle row\n  vSamples[0].w = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // left\n  fMinimum      = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).a; // center\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4( 1,0, -1,1);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  vSamples[1].x = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // right\n  // gather samples from lower row\n  vSamples[1].y = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // left\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4( 0,1, 1,1);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  vSamples[1].z = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // center\n  vSamples[1].w = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // right\n\n  // find minimum of it all \n  vSamples[0].xy = min( vSamples[0].xy, vSamples[0].zw);\n  vSamples[0].zw = min( vSamples[1].xy, vSamples[1].zw);\n  vSamples[0].xy = min( vSamples[0].xy, vSamples[0].zw);\n  vSamples[0].x  = min( vSamples[0].x,  vSamples[0].y);\n  fMinimum = min( fMinimum, vSamples[0].x);\n\n  // and output that to alpha channel\n  PS_OUT( float4( 0,0,0, fMinimum));\n}\n\n#endif // run_MinFilterPS\n#ifdef run_MedianFilterPS\n\n\n#define s2(a, b)\t\tfTemp = a; a = min(a, b); b = max(fTemp, b);\n#define mn3(a, b, c)\t\ts2(a, b); s2(a, c);\n#define mx3(a, b, c)\t\ts2(b, c); s2(a, c);\n\n#define mnmx3(a, b, c)\t\tmx3(a, b, c); s2(a, b);                                   // 3 exchanges\n#define mnmx4(a, b, c, d)\ts2(a, b); s2(c, d); s2(a, c); s2(b, d);                   // 4 exchanges\n#define mnmx5(a, b, c, d, e)\ts2(a, b); s2(c, d); mn3(a, c, e); mx3(b, d, e);           // 6 exchanges\n#define mnmx6(a, b, c, d, e, f) s2(a, d); s2(b, e); s2(c, f); mn3(a, b, c); mx3(d, e, f); // 7 exchanges\n\n// Median filter\nPS_ENTRY( MedianFilterPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  float4 vSampleCoords;\n  float fSamples[9];\n\n  // gather samples from upper row\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4(-1,-1, 0,-1);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  fSamples[0] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // left\n  fSamples[1] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // center\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4( 1,-1, -1,0);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  fSamples[2] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // right\n  // gather samples from middle row\n  fSamples[3] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // left\n  fSamples[4] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).a; // center\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4( 1,0, -1,1);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  fSamples[5] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // right\n  // gather samples from lower row\n  fSamples[6] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // left\n  vSampleCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy)+ c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy *float4( 0,1, 1,1);\n  vSampleCoords = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoords); \n  fSamples[7] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.xy).a;      // center\n  fSamples[8] = texSample2D( t_sAO, s_tAO, vSampleCoords.zw).a;      // right\n\n  float fTemp = 0.0f;\n\n  // starting with a subset of size 6, remove the min and max each time\n  mnmx6(fSamples[0], fSamples[1], fSamples[2], fSamples[3], fSamples[4], fSamples[5]);\n  mnmx5(fSamples[1], fSamples[2], fSamples[3], fSamples[4], fSamples[6]);\n  mnmx4(fSamples[2], fSamples[3], fSamples[4], fSamples[7]);\n  mnmx3(fSamples[3], fSamples[4], fSamples[8]);\n\n  // return result\n  PS_OUT( float4( 0,0,0, fSamples[4]));\n}\n\n#endif // run_MedianFilterPS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// AmbientShadowShader.sh\n\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n\n// input to VS\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float3, vClipCoordLeft, 0);\n  _outReg( float3, vClipCoordRight, 1);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// rendering ambi-shadows\nVS_ENTRY( AmbientShadowVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // vertex pos to clip space\n  float4 vClipPosLeft = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  float4 vClipPosRight = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n  VS_OUT_POS = vClipPosLeft;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = vClipPosRight;\n\n  // projective coord\n#if _GLSL && !_GLSL_METAL\n  // (need to flip coord because of flipped texture RT)\n  vClipPosLeft.y = -vClipPosLeft.y;\n  vClipPosRight.y = -vClipPosRight.y;\n#endif\n  VS_OUT( vClipCoordLeft) = vClipPosLeft.xyw;\n  VS_OUT( vClipCoordRight) = vClipPosRight.xyw;\n\n  // and go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// depth texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 0);\n\n// reciprocal of depth texture dimensions\n_CregF( float4, c_vScreenSizeDepth, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_vScreenSizeDepth.xy;\nstatic float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vScreenSizeDepth.z;\nstatic float  c_f1oDepthRange = c_vScreenSizeDepth.w;\n// frustum perspective ratios\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumLeft, 1);\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumRight, 2);\nstatic float4 g_vFrustum;\n// ambient shadow position in view space\n_CregF( float4, c_vShadowPosViewDistLeft, 3);\n_CregF( float4, c_vShadowPosViewDistRight, 4);\nstatic float4 g_vShadowPosViewDist;\n#define g_vShadowPosView g_vShadowPosViewDist.xyz\n#define g_f1oMaxDist g_vShadowPosViewDist.w // 1/falloff\n// shadow factor (1=full..0=none)\n_CregF( float3, c_vDepthShadow, 5);\nstatic float2 c_vDepthMapping = c_vDepthShadow.xy;\nstatic float  c_fShadowFactor = c_vDepthShadow.z;\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float3, vClipCoordLeft, 0);\n  _inReg( float3, vClipCoordRight, 1);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// distance shadow main function\nPS_ENTRY( AmbientShadowPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustum = VRSelect(c_vFrustumLeft, c_vFrustumRight);\n  g_vShadowPosViewDist = VRSelect(c_vShadowPosViewDistLeft, c_vShadowPosViewDistRight);\n  \n  // calc projective coords (-1 - +1 range)\n  float3 vClipCoord = VRSelect(PS_IN(vClipCoordLeft), PS_IN(vClipCoordRight));\n  float2 vProjCoord = vClipCoord.xy / vClipCoord.z;\n  // calc texture coords (0 - 1 range)\n  float2 vTexCoord = vProjCoord *float2(0.5f,-0.5f) +0.5f;\n  // readjust for sub-portion\n  vTexCoord *= c_vDepthMapping;\n\n  // sample depth texture and restore depth range (also converts to meters!)\n  float fTexDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV(vTexCoord)).r;\n  fTexDepth = abs( fTexDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // and then to view space\n  float3 vPixView;\n  vPixView.xy = -fTexDepth* (vProjCoord +g_vFrustum.yw) *g_vFrustum.xz;\n  vPixView.z  =  fTexDepth;\n\n  // calc distance from center\n  float3 vDistView = vPixView - g_vShadowPosView;\n  float fDist = length( vDistView) +0.001f; // (add to avoid div by zero)\n  // normalize distance by falloff\n  float fDistN = saturate( fDist *g_f1oMaxDist);\n  // quadratic fall-off looks better\n  fDistN *= fDistN;\n  // attenuate a bit (or not?!)\n  float fResult = (1.0f- fDistN) *0.75f;\n\n  // apply global fading factor\n  fResult *= c_fShadowFactor;\n  float4 vOutColor = _tcast( float4, fResult);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ArchitectureShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/RGBEConversion.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ParallaxMapping.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse1,   s_tDiffuse1, 0);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n  _Sreg2D( t_sNormalMap1, s_tNormalMap1, 1);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  _Sreg2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, 2);\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse2, s_tDiffuse2, 3);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  _Sreg2D( t_sNormalMap2, s_tNormalMap2, 4);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n  _Sreg2D( t_sLightMap,  s_tLightMap, 5);\n#endif\n_Sreg2D( t_sShade, s_tShade, 6);\n#ifndef BAKING\n  _Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc,s_tIllumAmbOcc, 7);\n#endif\n_Sreg2D( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, 8);\n#if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2) || defined(DOUBLE_PARALLAX)\n  _Sreg2D( t_sHeightMap2, s_tHeightMap2, 9);\n#endif\n\n// depth range and booleans\n_CregF( float4, c_v1oScreenSizeBools, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_v1oScreenSizeBools.xy;\n// baking? \n#ifdef BAKING\n  // in RGBE or LDR?\n  static float c_fBakeRGBE = c_v1oScreenSizeBools.z;\n  static float c_fBakeGamma= c_v1oScreenSizeBools.w;\n#endif\n\n// normal map strengths\n_CregF( float2, c_vNormStrengths, 1);\nstatic float c_fNorMap1Strength = c_vNormStrengths.x;\nstatic float c_fNorMap2Strength = c_vNormStrengths.y;\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbs, 2);\n\n// offset mapping UV-map ratio\n// (math: height & norm UV-map / other UV-map)\n_CregF( float4, c_vNor1ShdOfsRatio,  3);\n_CregF( float2, c_vDiffuse1OfsRatio, 4);\n_CregF( float4, c_vDif2Nor2OfsRatio, 5);\n  // (bump mapping uses const reg c8!)\n  // (parallax mapping uses const reg c9!)\n\n\n// global vars\nstatic float3 g_vNormalAbs;\nstatic float4 g_vDiffuse;\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs,    0);\n  _inReg( float4, vDiff1LMapUV,  1);\n  _inReg( float4, vNorm1ShadeUV, 2);\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskDiff2UV,  3);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  _inReg( float2, vNorm2UV, 4);\n#endif\n#if defined(HAS_PARALLAX) || defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT)\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n    // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n    _inReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 5);\n  #else\n    _inReg( float3, vNormalAbs,  5);\n  #endif\n#endif\n  _inReg( float3, vDiffuseColor, 8);\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n\n// lambert lighting\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  float fNdotL = saturate( dot( g_vNormalAbs, vLightDirAbs));\n  return g_vDiffuse.rgb * fNdotL;\n}\n\n\n// arch\nPS_ENTRY( ArchitecturePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // if has 2nd layer\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  // fetch mask texel\n  float fMask = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, PS_IN( vMaskDiff2UV.xy)).a;\n  // if not\n#else\n  // default the mask texel\n  float fMask = 0.0f;\n#endif\n  float3 vOffsetAmbDepth;\n\n  // prepare inputs for offseting\n  float4 vNorm1ShadeOfsUV = PS_IN( vNorm1ShadeUV);\n  float4 vDiff1Diff2OfsUV;\n  vDiff1Diff2OfsUV.xy = PS_IN( vDiff1LMapUV.xy);\n  #ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n    vDiff1Diff2OfsUV.zw = PS_IN( vMaskDiff2UV.zw);\n  #endif\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n    float2 vNorm2OfsUV = PS_IN( vNorm2UV);\n  #endif\n\n  // if rendering with parallax mapping                                      \n  #if !defined(BAKING) && defined(HAS_PARALLAX) && defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1)\n\n    // calc view pixel-distance(^2!) and direction\n    float3 vViewDirAbs = c_vViewPosAbs.xyz - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz);\n    float fPixDist2 = dot( vViewDirAbs, vViewDirAbs);\n    vViewDirAbs *= rsqrt( fPixDist2); // ==normalize\n    // transform view direction to tangent space\n    float3 vViewDirTan = _mulT( PS_IN( mTanToAbs), vViewDirAbs);  // (already normalized!)\n\n    // calc offset of texture coords\n    #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n      // double height maps\n      vOffsetAmbDepth = GetMappingOffset2( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, t_sHeightMap2, s_tHeightMap2,\n        vNorm1ShadeOfsUV.xy, vNorm2OfsUV, fMask, 1.0f, vViewDirTan, fPixDist2).xyz;\n    #else\n      // single height map\n      vOffsetAmbDepth = GetMappingOffset( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, vNorm1ShadeOfsUV.xy, 1.0f-fMask, vViewDirTan, fPixDist2).xyz;\n      vOffsetAmbDepth.z = lerp( vOffsetAmbDepth.z, 1.0f, fMask);\n    #endif\n    // apply offset to texture coords\n    vDiff1Diff2OfsUV.xy += vOffsetAmbDepth.xy * c_vDiffuse1OfsRatio.xy;\n    vNorm1ShadeOfsUV += vOffsetAmbDepth.xyxy * c_vNor1ShdOfsRatio;\n    #ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n      vDiff1Diff2OfsUV.zw += vOffsetAmbDepth.xy * c_vDif2Nor2OfsRatio.xy;\n      #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n        vNorm2OfsUV += vOffsetAmbDepth.xy * c_vDif2Nor2OfsRatio.zw;\n      #endif\n    #endif\n\n  // if no parallaxing\n  #else\n\n    // just sample height texture and if has normal-map 2\n    vOffsetAmbDepth.z = texSample2D( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, vNorm1ShadeOfsUV.xy).g;\n    #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n      // combine it with height-map 2\n      float fAmbDepth2 = texSample2D( t_sHeightMap2, s_tHeightMap2, vNorm2OfsUV).g;\n      vOffsetAmbDepth.z = lerp( vOffsetAmbDepth.z, fAmbDepth2, fMask); \n    #endif\n\n  #endif\n\n  // cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n\n  // fetch pixel from diffuse 1 texture\n  g_vDiffuse = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse1, s_tDiffuse1, vDiff1Diff2OfsUV.xy);\n  LinearSpace( g_vDiffuse.rgb);\n\n  // if has 1st normal-map\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n  // fetch it (tangent space)\n  float4 vNormalTan = texSample2D( t_sNormalMap1, s_tNormalMap1, vNorm1ShadeOfsUV.xy);\n  vNormalTan.xy = nor2D( vNormalTan) *c_fNorMap1Strength;\n#endif\n\n  // if has 2nd layer\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n\n  // fetch overlay diffuse texture\n  float3 vDiffuse2 = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse2, s_tDiffuse2, vDiff1Diff2OfsUV.zw).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( vDiffuse2);\n  // blend two layers through mask alpha channel\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = lerp( g_vDiffuse.rgb, vDiffuse2, _tcast(float3,fMask));\n\n  // if has 1st normal-map\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n    // and attenuate underlay normal-map by mask texture\n    vNormalTan.xy *= 1.0f-fMask;\n  #endif\n\n  // if has 2nd normal-map\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n    // fetch and lerp with underlaying normal-map\n    float4 vNormal2 = texSample2D( t_sNormalMap2, s_tNormalMap2, vNorm2OfsUV);\n    vNormalTan.xy  += nor2D( vNormal2) *c_fNorMap2Strength *fMask;\n  #endif\n#endif  // HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n\n  // fetch pixel from shade texture and modulate diffuse texture\n  float3 vShade = texSample2D( t_sShade, s_tShade, vNorm1ShadeOfsUV.zw).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( vShade);\n  // (2.0 in linear space = 2^2.2)\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb *= vShade *LINEAR_2; \n\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n\n  // construct Z of normal vector and \n  vNormalTan.z = CalcNormalZ( vNormalTan.xy);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n    // transform normal from tangent to absolute space\n    g_vNormalAbs = _mulT( vNormalTan.xyz, PS_IN( mTanToAbs));\n  #else\n    // or just use vertex normal\n    g_vNormalAbs = PS_IN( vNormalAbs);\n  #endif\n  // (re)normalize (vertex or pixel) normal\n  g_vNormalAbs = normalize( g_vNormalAbs);\n\n#endif // HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n\n  // force opaque alpha\n  // (needed for expanding edges when baking!)\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n\n  // if not baking\n#ifndef BAKING\n\n  // sample fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos());\n\n  // if baking\n#else  \n  // no FLAO texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n\n#endif // FLAO\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // sample HDR lightmap\n  float3 vLightMap = SampleRGBE( t_sLightMap, s_tLightMap, PS_IN( vDiff1LMapUV.zw));\n  // and modulate it by diffuse color\n  vLightMap *= PS_IN( vDiffuseColor);\n\n  // also modulate by ambient occlusion\n  vLightMap *= vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // and add illumination (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vLightMap += vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // apply ambient light map (could also be thought as total light solution for fully baked static lights)\n  vOutColor.rgb = g_vDiffuse.rgb * vLightMap;\n\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n    // fake light direction for ambient normal-map\n    vOutColor.rgb *= CalcFakeLightModulator( vNormalTan.xyz);\n  #endif\n\n#else  // HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // apply (shadowed) distant light\n  float3 vDistColor = DistantLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs));\n  // and add to final color (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vDistColor *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // spot (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += SpotLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // omni (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += OmniLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#endif  // LIGHTS\n\n  // apply depth attenuation from height map\n  vOutColor.rgb *= GetDepthOcclusion( vOffsetAmbDepth.z);\n\n  // if baking\n#ifdef BAKING\n\n  // in LDR\n  if( c_fBakeGamma != 0.0f) {\n\n    // apply gamma\n    vOutColor.rgb = pow( vOutColor.rgb, _tcast(float3,0.4545f));\n  }\n  // in RGBE\n  if( c_fBakeRGBE != 0.0f) {\n\n    // convert output\n    vOutColor.rgba = PackRGBE( vOutColor.rgb);\n  }\n#endif // BAKING\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ArchitectureShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// transformation to clip, absolute or view space\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n// spherical harmonics calculation\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/SphericalHarmonics.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// object to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 35);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n\n// mapping matrices for the used textures\n  _CregM42F( c_mDiffuse1Mapping, 7);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n  _CregF( float4, c_vNormal1Mapping, 9);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  _CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping,     10);\n  _CregM42F( c_mDiffuse2Mapping, 12);\n#endif\n  // (SPH calc uses const regs c14-c22!)\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  _CregF( float4, c_vNormal2Mapping, 23);\n#endif\n  _CregF( float4, c_vLightMapping, 24);\n  _CregM42F( c_mShadeMapping, 25);\n\n// ambient modulator\n_CregF( float, c_fAmbientModulator, 27);\n\n// mapping masks for UV coords (select UV-map or XY, YZ or XY plane)\n_CregF( float3, c_vDif1MappingMask, 28);\n_CregF( float3, c_vNor1MappingMask, 29);\n_CregF( float3, c_vMaskMappingMask, 30);\n_CregF( float3, c_vDif2MappingMask, 31);\n_CregF( float3, c_vNor2MappingMask, 32);\n_CregF( float3, c_vShadMappingMask, 33);\n// normal and tangent signed/unsigned masks\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorTanMask, 34);\n// (c_vObjToClipRightX uses const reg c35!)\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition,  0);\n  _inReg( float4, vDiffuse1UV,1);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n  _inReg( float2, vNorMap1UV, 2);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,    3);\n  _inReg( float4, vDiffuse2UV,4);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  _inReg( float2, vNorMap2UV, 5);\n#endif\n  _inReg( float2, vLightUV, 6);\n  _inReg( float4, vShadeUV, 7);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,  8);\n  _inReg( float4, vTangent, 9);\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  _inReg( float4x3, mInstObjToAbs, 10);\n  _inReg( float4, vLightMapping, 13);\n#else\n  #ifdef BAKING\n    _inReg( float4, vBakePos, 10); // (required for lighting since baker uses uv coords as positions)\n  #endif\n  #ifdef HAS_BONES\n    _inReg( float4, vIndices, 11); // (matrix indices)\n    _inReg( float4, vWeights, 12); // (blend weights)\n  #endif\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs,    0);\n  _outReg( float4, vDiff1LMapUV,  1);\n  _outReg( float4, vNorm1ShadeUV, 2);\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  _outReg( float4, vMaskDiff2UV,  3);\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  _outReg( float2, vNorm2UV, 4);\n#endif\n#ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n    // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n    _outReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 5);\n  #else\n    _outReg( float3, vNormalAbs,  5);\n  #endif\n#endif\n  _outReg( float3, vDiffuseColor, 8);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( ArchitectureVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n#ifdef BAKING\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vBakePos);\n#else\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#endif\n  // expand normal (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorTanMask.yyyx);\n\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  #define i_mInstObjToAbs VS_IN( mInstObjToAbs)\n#endif\n\n// if needs tangents or spherical harmonics lighting calc\n#if defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS) || defined(HAS_SPHARMONICS)\n\n  // (have object to absolute space rotation matrix)\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot;\n\n  // if needs tangents and has normal-map\n  #if defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS) && defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1)\n\n    // if using planar mapping\n    float3x3 mOutTanToAbs;\n    if( c_vNor1MappingMask.z > 0.0f) {\n\n      // transform normal from object to absolute space\n    #ifdef INSTANCING\n      // (use instanced location matrix)\n      mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n    #else\n      // (use fixed location matrix)\n      mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n      #ifdef HAS_BONES\n        // (with skinning, if needed)\n        vPos.xyz = SkinVertexNor( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor);\n      #endif\n    #endif\n      // fix stretching\n      FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n\n      // normal to absolute space\n      float3 vNorAbs = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRot);\n      // and construct tangent to object space plane matrix\n      mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToAbsPlaneMatrix( vNorAbs, c_vNor1MappingMask.x);\n\n    // if using UV-mapping\n    } else {\n\n      // expand tangent (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n      float4 vTan = ExpandTangent( VS_IN( vTangent), c_vNorTanMask.wwwz);\n    #ifdef INSTANCING\n      // (use instanced location matrix)\n      mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n    #else\n      // (use fixed location matrix)\n      mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n      #ifdef HAS_BONES\n        // (with skinning, if needed)\n        vPos.xyz = SkinVertexTan( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor, vTan.xyz);\n      #endif\n    #endif\n      // construct tangent to object space transformation matrix\n      mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToObjMatrix( vNor, vTan);\n    #if _GLSL\n      mObjToAbsRot = transpose( mObjToAbsRot);\n    #endif\n      // fix stretching\n      FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n\n      // move tangents from object to absolute space\n      mOutTanToAbs = _mulT( mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRot);\n    }\n    // (re)normalize rotation matrix\n    VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = NormalizeRotation( mOutTanToAbs);\n\n  // if no tangents nor normal-map\n  #else \n\n    // if has instancing\n    #ifdef INSTANCING\n      // (use instanced location matrix)\n      mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n    // if no instancing\n    #else\n      // (use fixed location matrix)\n      mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n      #ifdef HAS_BONES\n        // (with skinning, if needed)\n        vPos.xyz = SkinVertexNor( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor);\n      #endif\n    #endif\n    // fix stretching\n    FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n    // transform normal to absolute space\n    float3 vOutNorAbs = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRot);\n    #if defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS)\n      // and send it to pixel shader\n      VS_OUT( vNormalAbs) = vOutNorAbs;\n    #endif\n  #endif // NEEDS_TANGENTS && HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n\n#endif // NEEDS_TANGENTS || HAS_SPHARMONICS\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n\n  // combine model and view-proj matrices first (obj-to-clip here is infact abs-to-clip matrix!)\n  float4x4 mObjToAbs4 =\n  #if _GLSL\n    float4x4( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n  #elif _HLSL\n  { float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[0], 0),\n    float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[1], 0),\n    float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[2], 0),\n    float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[3], 1) };\n  #endif\n  float4x4 mMVPLeft = mul( mObjToAbs4, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  float4x4 mMVPRight = mul( mObjToAbs4, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n  // to project to clip space\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, mMVPLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, mMVPRight);\n  // and also transform to absolute space\n  vPos.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, i_mInstObjToAbs);\n\n#elif defined(BAKING)\n\n  // baking, project pos coords directly\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n#else\n\n  // w/o instancing, project directly from object to clip space\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n#endif\n\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  // (for instancing, position is already in absolute space!)\n  vOutVexPosAbs = vPos;\n#else\n  // (non-instancing, position is in object space)\n  vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToAbs);\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n#endif\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n\n  // mapping masks\n  float4 vInShadeUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vShadeUV.xy),    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vShadMappingMask); \n  float4 vInDiff1UV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vDiffuse1UV.xy), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vDif1MappingMask); \n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2                                \n  float4 vInMaskUV  = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vMaskUV.xy),     vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vMaskMappingMask); \n  float4 vInDiff2UV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vDiffuse2UV.xy), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vDif2MappingMask); \n#endif                                              \n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1                             \n  float2 vInNorMap1UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vNorMap1UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vNor1MappingMask); \n#endif                                              \n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  float2 vInNorMap2UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vNorMap2UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vNor2MappingMask); \n#endif\n\n  // combine mapping coordinates\n  VS_OUT( vDiff1LMapUV.xy) = mulM42F( vInDiff1UV, c_mDiffuse1Mapping);\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  VS_OUT( vDiff1LMapUV.zw) = VS_IN( vLightUV.xy) *VS_IN( vLightMapping.xy) +VS_IN( vLightMapping.zw);\n#else\n  VS_OUT( vDiff1LMapUV.zw) = VS_IN( vLightUV.xy) *c_vLightMapping.xy +c_vLightMapping.zw;\n#endif\n\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1\n  VS_OUT( vNorm1ShadeUV.xy) = vInNorMap1UV *c_vNormal1Mapping.xy +c_vNormal1Mapping.zw;\n#else\n  VS_OUT( vNorm1ShadeUV.xy) = _tcast( float2, 0);\n#endif\n  VS_OUT( vNorm1ShadeUV.zw) = mulM42F( vInShadeUV, c_mShadeMapping); \n\n#ifdef HAS_DIFFUSE_2\n  VS_OUT( vMaskDiff2UV.xy) = mulM42F( vInMaskUV,  c_mMaskMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vMaskDiff2UV.zw) = mulM42F( vInDiff2UV, c_mDiffuse2Mapping); \n#endif\n\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP_2\n  VS_OUT( vNorm2UV.xy) = vInNorMap2UV *c_vNormal2Mapping.xy +c_vNormal2Mapping.zw;\n#endif\n\n  // if has spherical harmonics coefficients\n#ifdef HAS_SPHARMONICS\n\n  // calc SHCs\n  #if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP_1) && defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS)\n    // (from tan-to-abs matrix)\n    VS_OUT( vDiffuseColor) = CalcSHLight( mOutTanToAbs[2]);\n  #else\n    // from vertex normal abs\n    VS_OUT( vDiffuseColor) = CalcSHLight( vOutNorAbs);\n  #endif\n\n  // if no spherical harmonics\n#else \n\n  // just use ambient modulator\n  VS_OUT( vDiffuseColor) = _tcast( float3, c_fAmbientModulator);\n\n#endif // HAS_SPHARMONICS\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// BlurShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// bluree texture dimensions x/texW, y/texH\n_CregF( float4, c_vMapping, 0);\n// bluree pix size (.xy), and stretched pix size (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vPixSize, 1);\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n#if POINT_SAMPLING\n  #if STRETCHING\n    // 4x4 nearest\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords0, 0);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords1, 1);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords2, 2);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords3, 3);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords4, 4);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords5, 5);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords6, 6);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords7, 7);\n  #else\n    // 3x3 nearest\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords0, 0);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords1, 1);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords2, 2);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords3, 3);\n    _outReg( float4, vTexCoords4, 4);\n  #endif\n#else\n  // 3x3 or 4x4 bilinear\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords0, 0);\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords1, 1);\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// blur vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( BlurVS)\n{ \n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // vpos from texcoords\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( VS_IN( vInPos.xy), 0,1); \n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n\n  // central coord\n  float2 vTexCoord = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vMapping.xy +c_vMapping.zw;\n\n  // sampling positions\n#if STRETCHING\n\n  #if POINT_SAMPLING\n\n    vTexCoord.xy -= c_vPixSize.zw *1.0f;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 0,0\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 0,1\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 0,2\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 0,3\n\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.y;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords3.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 1,3\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords3.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 1,2\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords2.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 1,1\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords2.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 1,0\n\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.y;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords4.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 2,0\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords4.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 2,1\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords5.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 2,2\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords5.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 2,3\n\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.y;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords7.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 3,3\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords7.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 3,2\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords6.zw) = vTexCoord;  // 3,1\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords6.xy) = vTexCoord;  // 3,0\n\n  #else // BILINEAR\n\n    vTexCoord.xy -= c_vPixSize.zw *0.5f;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.xy) = vTexCoord;  // upper-left\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.z;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.zw) = vTexCoord;  // upper-right\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.w;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.zw) = vTexCoord;  // lower-right\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.z;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.xy) = vTexCoord;  // lower-left\n\n  #endif  // SAMPLING\n\n#else // NO STRETCHING\n\n  #if POINT_SAMPLING\n\n    vTexCoord.xy -= c_vPixSize.xy *1.0f;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.xy) = vTexCoord;  // upper-left\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.zw) = vTexCoord;  // upper-middle\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.xy) = vTexCoord;  // upper-right\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.y;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords2.zw) = vTexCoord;  // middle-right\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords2.xy) = vTexCoord;  // middle\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.zw) = vTexCoord;  // middle-left\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.y;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords3.xy) = vTexCoord;  // lower-left\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords3.zw) = vTexCoord;  // lower-middle\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords4.xy) = vTexCoord;  // lower-right\n    // (rest)\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords4.zw) = _tcast(float2,0);\n\n  #else // BILINEAR\n\n    vTexCoord.xy -= c_vPixSize.xy *0.5f;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.xy) = vTexCoord;  // upper-left\n    vTexCoord.x += c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords0.zw) = vTexCoord;  // upper-right\n    vTexCoord.y += c_vPixSize.y;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.zw) = vTexCoord;  // lower-right\n    vTexCoord.x -= c_vPixSize.x;\n    VS_OUT( vTexCoords1.xy) = vTexCoord;  // lower-left\n\n  #endif  // SAMPLING\n\n#endif  // STRETCHING\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n#ifdef _PSSL\n  // (need more precision for output, when blurring 16-bit integer RTs)\n  #pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default FMT_32_ABGR)\n#endif\n                     \n// texture to blur\n_Sreg2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, 0);\n\n// coord clamp edges (.xy=min, .zw=max)\n_CregF( float4, c_vEdges, 0);\n\n// PS output\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n#if POINT_SAMPLING\n  #if STRETCHING\n    // 4x4 nearest\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords0, 0);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords1, 1);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords2, 2);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords3, 3);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords4, 4);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords5, 5);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords6, 6);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords7, 7);\n  #else\n    // 3x3 nearest\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords0, 0);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords1, 1);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords2, 2);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords3, 3);\n    _inReg( float4, vTexCoords4, 4);\n  #endif\n#else\n  // 3x3 or 4x4 bilinear\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords0, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords1, 1);\n#endif\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// blur pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( BlurPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // (result and temp for tex coords clamping)\n  float4 vBlurred, vClampedCoord;\n  \n  float4 vMultiviewMAD = MultiviewMAD();\n\n#if POINT_SAMPLING\n\n#if STRETCHING\n\n    // 4x4\n    const float c_fWeight = 1.0f / 16.0f;\n\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords0), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred  = texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords1), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords2), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords3), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords4), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords5), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords6), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords7), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n\n  #else // NO STRETCHING\n\n    // 3x3\n    const float c_fCornerWeight = 3.0f / 40.0f;\n    const float c_fBorderWeight = 5.0f / 40.0f;\n    const float c_fCenterWeight = 8.0f / 40.0f;\n\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords0), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred  = texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fCornerWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fBorderWeight;\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords1), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fCornerWeight;\n\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fBorderWeight;\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords2), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fCenterWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fBorderWeight;\n\n    vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords3), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fCornerWeight;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fBorderWeight;\n    vClampedCoord.xy = clamp( vClampedCoord.xy, c_vEdges.xy, c_vEdges.zw) * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw;\n    vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fCornerWeight;\n\n  #endif  // STRETCHING\n\n#else // BILINEAR\n\n  // 2x2\n  const float c_fWeight = 1.0f / 4.0f;\n\n  vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords0), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n  vBlurred  = texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n  vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n\n  vClampedCoord = clamp( PS_IN( vTexCoords1), c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw) * vMultiviewMAD.xyxy + vMultiviewMAD.zwzw;\n  vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.xy) *c_fWeight;\n  vBlurred += texSample2D( t_sBluree, s_tBluree, vClampedCoord.zw) *c_fWeight;\n\n#endif  // SAMPLING\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vBlurred);\n\n  // and the result is...\n  PS_OUT( vBlurred);\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ColorConvShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0);\n\n// pixel input is vertex output\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( ColorConvPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample soource texture and clamp\n  float3 vTexel = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).rgb;\n  vTexel = min( vTexel, _tcast(float3,32767)); // (1<<15)-1\n\n  // find the maximum channel\n  float fMaxCh = max( max( vTexel.r, vTexel.g), vTexel.b);\n  // add a bias to prevent division by zero and bring denormalized numbers into proper range\n  fMaxCh += 1.0f / 131072.0f; // (1<<17)\n\n  // determine the exponent\n  float fLog2, fExp2;\n  fLog2 = log2( fMaxCh);\n  fExp2 = ceil( fLog2*8.0f *255.0f/256.0f +128.0f);\n  fExp2 = max(  fExp2/255.0f, 0.0f);\n\n  // pack it all into the resulting color\n  float4 vOutColor;   // (final output)\n  vOutColor.rgb = vTexel / exp2( fExp2*32.0f-16.0f);\n  vOutColor.a   = fExp2;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// CrumbsBaker.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix for rendering\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProj, 0); \n// and for transforming depth\n_CregM44F( c_mClipSpace, 4); \n\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float2, vClipDepth, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( BakeCrumbsVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // get positions for rendering and depth transform\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProj);\n  float4 vClipPos = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mClipSpace);\n  // (normalize depth Z coord to 0-1 range!)\n  VS_OUT( vClipDepth) = vClipPos.zw *float2( 0.5f, 1) +float2( 0.5f, 0);\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// pixel input(s)\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float2, vClipDepth, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( BakeCrumbsPS)\n{\n  // final output\n  float fDepth = PS_IN( vClipDepth.x) / PS_IN( vClipDepth.y); // ==Z/W\n  PS_OUT( float4( fDepth, fDepth, fDepth, 1));\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// DefaultShaders.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProjLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vModelViewProjRightX, 4);\n\n// color constants: colormask(mul op), colormask(add op), gamma correction, exposure\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskGammaExp, 5);\nstatic float2 c_vColorMask = c_vMaskGammaExp.xy;\nstatic float  c_fGamma     = c_vMaskGammaExp.z;\nstatic float  c_fExposure  = c_vMaskGammaExp.w;\n// texture coordinates UV stretch (.xy) and offset (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vTextureMapping, 6);\n// constant color\n_CregF( float4, c_vConstColor, 7);\n\n\n// input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition,  0);  // vertex position in object space\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,    1);  // vertex normal\n  _inReg( float4, vColorMap,  2);  // vertex color\n  _inReg( float2, vTextureUV, 3);  // vertex texture 2D coordinates\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices,   4);  // vertex bone indices\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,   5);  // vertex bone blend weights\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vColor,     0); // vertex color modulated by constant color and gamma correction\n  _outReg( float2, vTexCoords, 1); // texture coordinates modified by stretch and offset\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n\n// default vertex shader with optional skinning\nVS_ENTRY( DefaultVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // get input position\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  // object-space position skinned by bones' matrices (if needed)\n  vPos.xyz = SkinVertexPos( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos);\n#endif\n  // clip space position\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mModelViewProjLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mModelViewProjLeft, c_vModelViewProjRightX));\n\n  // texture coordinates modified by stretch and offset\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords) = VS_IN( vTextureUV) * c_vTextureMapping.xy + c_vTextureMapping.zw;\n  // apply color mask to color map\n  float4 vOutColor = VS_IN( vColorMap);\n  vOutColor = vOutColor *c_vColorMask.xxxx +c_vColorMask.yyyy;\n  // modulate color with constant color\n  vOutColor *= c_vConstColor;\n  // apply gamma correction to color\n  float3 vGamma = float3( c_fGamma,c_fGamma,c_fGamma);\n  vOutColor.rgb = pow( vOutColor.rgb, vGamma);  \n  // modulate color with exposure correction\n  // (includes HDR output normalization factor!)\n  vOutColor.rgb *= c_fExposure;\n  VS_OUT( vColor) = vOutColor;\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, 0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, 1);\n\n// flag indicator that bound texture is in RGBE format and must be unpacked\n// and HDR input denormalization value\n_CregF( float, c_fUnpackRGBE, 0);\n// depth range\n_CregF( float4, c_vScreenSizeDepth, 1);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_vScreenSizeDepth.xy;\nstatic float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vScreenSizeDepth.z;\nstatic float  c_fDepthRange   = c_vScreenSizeDepth.w;\n\n// VS output = PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vColor,     0);\n  _inReg( float2, vTexCoords, 1);\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// default shader's pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( DefaultPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // for a start, out color = vertex interpolated color\n  float4 vOutColor = PS_IN( vColor);\n\n  // modulate by ambient occlusion and add illumination\n  float2 vIllumAmbOccCoords = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), c_v1oScreenSize);\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, MultiviewUV(vIllumAmbOccCoords));\n  vOutColor.rgb *= vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n  // (attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights)\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  vOutColor.rgb += vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // sample texture\n  float4 vUnpacked;\n  float4 vTexture = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, PS_IN( vTexCoords));\n  // unpack it (from RGBE)\n  vUnpacked.rgb = vTexture.rgb * exp2( vTexture.a *32.0f -16.0f);\n  vUnpacked.a = 1.0f;\n\n  // and based on texture format choose whether unpacked on LDR texture color is used\n  vOutColor *= (c_fUnpackRGBE>=0.0f) ? vUnpacked : vTexture;\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// DepthShadowShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// object to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vToClipRightX, 4);\n\n// object to abs space transformation matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 5);\n\n// constants\n_CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping, 8);      // mask texture mapping adjustments\n_CregF( float4, c_vModelViewZ, 10);  // 3rd row (Z) of model-view matrix\n_CregM42F( c_mMask2Mapping, 11);\n\n_CregM44F( c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft, 13);\n\n// vertex input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,   1);\n#if USE_MASK2\n  _inReg( float4, vMask2UV,  2);\n#endif\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  _inReg( float4x3, mInstObjToAbs, 3);\n#elif defined(HAS_BONES)\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices, 3);  // matrix indices\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights, 4);  // blend weights\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// vertex output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // tex coords, depth value and alpha keying multiplier\n  _outReg( float4, vUV_Z_AMul, 0); \n#ifdef APPLY_HAZE\n  // vertex position in absolute space\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1); \n#endif\n#if USE_MASK2\n  _outReg( float4, v2ndMaskUV, 2); \n#endif\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  _outReg( float4, vClipSpacePos, 3);\n  _outReg( float4, vPreviousClipSpacePos, 4);\n#endif\n#if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n  _outReg( float4, vModelSpacePos, 5);\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( DepthShadowVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // get position\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  float4 vOutPosPreviousClipLeft = float4( 0,0,0,0 );\n  float4 vCachedPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#endif\n\n#ifndef INSTANCING\n\n  #ifdef HAS_BONES\n    // do skinning for position (if any)\n    vPos.xyz = SkinVertexPos( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos);\n  #endif\n\n  #ifdef RENDER_SHADOW\n    // object to absolute space\n    vPos.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToAbs);\n  #endif\n  #if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  vCachedPos = vPos;\n  #endif\n  // then from object or absolute to clip space\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix( c_mToClipLeft, c_vToClipRightX));\n\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  // from previous frame object or absolute to clip space\n  vOutPosPreviousClipLeft = mul( vPos, c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft);\n#endif\n\n#else // INSTANCING\n\n  #define i_mInstObjToAbs VS_IN( mInstObjToAbs)\n\n  #ifndef RENDER_SHADOW\n\n    // then combine model and view-proj matrices first (obj-to-clip here is infact abs-to-clip matrix!)\n    float4x4 mObjToAbs4 =\n    #if _GLSL\n      float4x4( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n    #elif _HLSL\n    { float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[0], 0),\n      float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[1], 0),\n      float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[2], 0),\n      float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[3], 1) };\n    #endif\n    float4x4 mMVPLeft = mul( mObjToAbs4, c_mToClipLeft);\n    float4x4 mMVPRight= mul( mObjToAbs4, VRRightMatrix( c_mToClipLeft, c_vToClipRightX));\n    // to project to clip space\n    VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, mMVPLeft);\n    VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, mMVPRight);\n\n  #if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n    // from previous frame object or absolute to clip space\n    vOutPosPreviousClipLeft = mul( vPos, mul( mObjToAbs4, c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft));\n  #endif\n\n    // now project object to abs space\n    vPos.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, i_mInstObjToAbs);\n\n  #else // SHADOW\n\n    // first project object to abs space\n    vPos.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, i_mInstObjToAbs);\n\n    // and then to clip space\n    VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mToClipLeft);\n    VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix( c_mToClipLeft, c_vToClipRightX));\n\n  #endif // SHADOW\n#endif // INSTANCING\n\n  // output depth value from Z (in meters, will be normalized later)\n  // (we cannot output W here, because of ortho projection used by distant light which has W=1)\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.z) = dot( vPos, c_vModelViewZ);\n\n  // 1st mask texcoords\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vMaskUV),  c_mMaskMapping); // (4-component dot product)\n#if USE_MASK2\n  // 2nd mask texcoords\n  VS_OUT( v2ndMaskUV.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vMask2UV), c_mMask2Mapping);\n  VS_OUT( v2ndMaskUV.zw) = _tcast(float2, 0.0f);\n#endif\n\n  // set default alpha keying multiplier\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.a) = 1.0f; // default depth shader doesn't use alpha key multiplier (fade)\n\n  // if using haze\n#ifdef APPLY_HAZE\n\n  // but w/o instancing\n  #ifndef INSTANCING\n    // transform vertex position from object to absolute space now\n    // (for instancing, it's already in absolute space!)\n    vPos.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToAbs);\n  #endif\n  // and output it to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vPos;\n#endif\n\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  VS_OUT( vClipSpacePos) = VS_OUT_POS;\n  VS_OUT( vPreviousClipSpacePos) = vOutPosPreviousClipLeft;\n#endif\n\n#if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n  VS_OUT( vModelSpacePos) = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#endif\n\n  // ok, go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// fog/haze calculation functions\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n\n#define USE_MASK1 (USE_MASK1_TEX2D || USE_MASK1_TEXARRAY)\n#define USE_MASK2 (USE_MASK2_TEX2D || USE_MASK2_TEXARRAY)\n#define USE_MASK (USE_MASK1 || USE_MASK2)\n\n#define DIFFUSION (DIFFUSION_NOISE_TEX || DIFFUSION_SCREEN_POS)\n\n#ifdef _PSSL\n\n  // if rendering depth\n  #ifndef RENDER_SHADOW\n    // without haze\n    #ifndef APPLY_HAZE\n      // nor split-depth\n      #ifndef SPLIT_DEPTH\n        // then using only 1-channel output\n        #pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default FMT_32_R)\n      // if has split-depth\n      #else\n        // then using 2-channels output\n        #pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default FMT_32_GR)\n      #endif\n    #endif\n  // if rendering shadow\n  #else\n    // then using only 1-channel output\n    #pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default FMT_32_R)\n  #endif\n\n#endif // _PSSL\n\n\n#if USE_MASK\n  #if USE_MASK1_TEX2D\n    // mask texture \n    _Sreg2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, 0);\n  #elif USE_MASK1_TEXARRAY\n    // mask array texture \n    _SregAry2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, 0);\n  #endif\n#if USE_MASK2\n  #if USE_MASK2_TEX2D\n    // mask texture \n    _Sreg2D( t_s2ndMask, s_t2ndMask, 1);\n  #elif USE_MASK2_TEXARRAY\n    // mask array texture \n    _SregAry2D( t_s2ndMask, s_t2ndMask, 1);\n  #endif\n#endif\n#endif // USE_MASK\n#if DIFFUSION_NOISE_TEX\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDiffusion, s_tDiffusion, 2);\n#endif\n\n// mask and depth range\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskRange, 0);\nstatic float c_fMaskTreshold = c_vMaskRange.x;\nstatic float c_fStartSpan    = c_vMaskRange.y;\nstatic float c_f1oRangeSpan  = c_vMaskRange.z;\nstatic float c_fRangeSign    = c_vMaskRange.w;\n// alpha range and split depth factors\n_CregF( float4, c_vAlphaRangeDiv, 1);\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange= c_vAlphaRangeDiv.xy;\nstatic float  c_fSplitMul  = c_vAlphaRangeDiv.z;\nstatic float  c_fSplitDiv  = c_vAlphaRangeDiv.w;\n// viewer position and split depth exponent\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsExp, 2);\nstatic float3 c_vViewPosAbs= c_vViewPosAbsExp.xyz;\nstatic float  c_fSplitExp  = c_vViewPosAbsExp.w;\n_CregF( float4, c_vDissolveMap, 3);\n_CregF( float4, c_fFadeFactorsSlice, 4);\nstatic float c_fFadeFactor = c_fFadeFactorsSlice.x; // (signed,  -1 - 1)\nstatic float c_fLerpFactor = c_fFadeFactorsSlice.y;\nstatic float c_fBaseArraySlice1 = c_fFadeFactorsSlice.z;\nstatic float c_fBaseArraySlice2 = c_fFadeFactorsSlice.w;\n_CregF( float2, c_vViewportSizeInPixels, 5);\n\n// (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n\n// pixel input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // tex coords, depth value and alpha keying multiplier\n  _inReg( float4, vUV_Z_AMul, 0); \n#ifdef APPLY_HAZE\n  // pixel position in absolute space\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);\n#endif\n#if USE_MASK2\n  _inReg( float4, v2ndMaskUV, 2); \n#endif\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  _inReg( float4, vClipSpacePos, 3);\n  _inReg( float4, vPreviousClipSpacePos, 4);\n#endif\n#if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n  _inReg( float4, vModelSpacePos, 5);\n#endif\n#if DIFFUSION\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n#endif\nPS_IN_END\n\n#if USE_HASH_ALPHA\nfloat hash( float2 v )\n{\n  return frac( 1.0e4 * sin( 17.0f * v.x + 0.1f * v.y ) * ( 0.1f + abs( sin( 13.0f * v.y + v.x ))) );\n}\n\nfloat hash3D( float3 v )\n{\n  return hash( float2( hash( v.xy ), v.z ) );\n}\n\nfloat HashAlpha( const in float3 vObjCoord, const float fHashScale )\n{\n  // Find the discretized derivatives of our coordinates\n  float fMaxDeriv = max( length( ddx( vObjCoord.xyz ) ), length( ddy( vObjCoord.xyz ) ) );\n  float fPixScale = 1.0f / (fHashScale * fMaxDeriv);\n\n  // Find two nearest log-discretized noise scales\n  float2 vPixScales = float2( exp2( floor( log2(fPixScale))),\n                             exp2( ceil( log2(fPixScale))));\n\n  // Compute alpha thresholds at our two noise scales\n  float2 vAlpha = float2( hash3D( floor( vPixScales.x*vObjCoord.xyz)),\n                         hash3D( floor( vPixScales.y*vObjCoord.xyz)));\n\n  // Factor to interpolate with\n  float fLerpFactor = frac( log2(fPixScale) );\n\n  // Interpolate alpha threshold from noise at two scales\n  float x = ( 1 - fLerpFactor) * vAlpha.x + fLerpFactor*vAlpha.y;\n\n  // Pass into CDF to compute uniformly distrib threshold\n  float a = min( fLerpFactor, 1-fLerpFactor );\n  float3 vCases = float3( x*x/(2*a*(1-a)),\n                     (x-0.5*a)/(1-a),\n                     1.0-((1-x)*(1-x)/(2*a*(1-a))) );\n\n  // Find our final, uniformly distributed alpha threshold\n  float fAlphaR = (x < (1-a)) ?\n    ((x<a) ? vCases.x : vCases.y ) :\n    vCases.z;\n\n  // Avoids fAlphaR == 0. Could also do fAlphaR=1-fAlphaR\n  fAlphaR = clamp( fAlphaR, 1.0e-6, 1.0 );\n\n  return fAlphaR;\n}\n#endif\n\n// pixel shader\n#ifdef RENDER_SHADOW\n  PS_ENTRY_NOOUT( DepthShadowPS)\n#else\n  PS_ENTRY( DepthShadowPS)\n#endif\n{  \n  // prepare array slice indices\n  float fArraySlice1 = c_fBaseArraySlice1;\n  float fArraySlice2 = c_fBaseArraySlice2;\n#if USE_MASK2_TEXARRAY\n  fArraySlice1 += round(PS_IN(v2ndMaskUV).z - frac(PS_IN(v2ndMaskUV).z));\n  fArraySlice2 += round(PS_IN(v2ndMaskUV).w);  \n#endif\n\n#if DIFFUSION\n\n  // get screen raster coordinates\n  float2 vRasterPos = PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy);\n  // adjust by object position\n  vRasterPos -= c_vDissolveMap.zw;\n\n  // do dithering with it\n  float2 vClipTreshold;\n  #if DIFFUSION_NOISE_TEX\n    // (via noise texture)\n    vRasterPos *= c_vDissolveMap.xy;\n    vClipTreshold.x = texSample2D( t_sDiffusion, s_tDiffusion, vRasterPos).r;\n  #elif DIFFUSION_SCREEN_POS\n    // (or directly from screen position)\n    vClipTreshold.x = dot( vRasterPos, float2( 12.9898f,78.233f));\n    vClipTreshold.x = sin( vClipTreshold.x *0.001f);\n    vClipTreshold.x = frac(vClipTreshold.x *43758.5453f);\n  #endif\n\n  // convert diffusion (noise) to signed values\n  vClipTreshold.y = vClipTreshold.x *2.0f -1.0f;\n\n  // apply fading to diffusion\n  vClipTreshold.xy += _tcast(float2,c_fFadeFactor);\n\n#endif // DIFFUSION\n\n// if rendering shadow\n#if defined(RENDER_SHADOW)\n  \n  // (shadows don't use color buffer, only depth)\n  float fOutAlpha = 0.0f; // this assignment is only temporary until CShaderVariations class can handle dependant flags\n\n#else\n\n   // (result)\n  float4 vDepth = _tcast(float4, 0.0f); // this assignment is only temporary until CShaderVariations class can handle dependant flags\n  #define fOutAlpha vDepth.a\n\n#endif\n\n// if using alpha-testing\n#if USE_MASK\n\n  #if USE_MASK1_TEX2D\n    // sample mask texture (mask is in alpha channel)\n    fOutAlpha = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy)).a;\n  #elif USE_MASK1_TEXARRAY\n    // sample mask array texture (mask is in alpha channel)    \n    float3 vMaskCoords = float3( PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy), fArraySlice1);\n    fOutAlpha = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, vMaskCoords).a;\n  #endif\n\n  // if has 2nd mask also\n  #if USE_MASK2_TEX2D\n    // modulate depth alpha with 2nd mask alpha channel\n    float fOutAlpha2 = texSample2D( t_s2ndMask, s_t2ndMask, PS_IN( v2ndMaskUV).xy).a;\n  #elif USE_MASK2_TEXARRAY\n    // modulate depth alpha with 2nd mask alpha channel\n    float3 vMask2Coords = float3( PS_IN( v2ndMaskUV).xy, fArraySlice2);\n    float fOutAlpha2 = texSample2D( t_s2ndMask, s_t2ndMask, vMask2Coords).a;\n  #endif\n\n  // blend the two masks\n  #if USE_MASK2          \n    #if BLEND_MASK_ALPHA\n      float fBlendFactor = frac(PS_IN(v2ndMaskUV).z);\n      fOutAlpha = lerp(fOutAlpha, fOutAlpha2, fBlendFactor);      \n    #else\n      fOutAlpha *= fOutAlpha2;      \n    #endif\n  #endif\n\n  // apply alpha keying vertex multiplier\n  fOutAlpha *= PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.a); // +0.001f;\n\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  fOutAlpha = saturate( fOutAlpha *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n\n  #if DIFFUSION\n    // mix in unsigned diffusion\n    fOutAlpha *= vClipTreshold.x;\n  #endif\n  // discard pixel if mask is lower than treshold\n#if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n  clip( fOutAlpha - HashAlpha( PS_IN( vModelSpacePos.xyz), 1.0f ) );\n#else\n  clip( fOutAlpha - c_fMaskTreshold);\n#endif\n\n// if no alpha-testing but has diffusion\n#elif DIFFUSION\n\n  // clip at treshold\n  clip( vClipTreshold.y);\n\n  // alpha is unsigned diffusion then\n  fOutAlpha = saturate( vClipTreshold.x);\n\n// if no alpha-testing nor diffusion\n#elif !defined(RENDER_SHADOW)\n\n  // alpha is opaque then\n  fOutAlpha = 1.0f;\n\n#endif // USE_MASK\n\n// now, if applying haze\n#ifdef APPLY_HAZE\n\n  // calculate haze amount now\n  float fPixViewDist = length( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz) - c_vViewPosAbs);\n  vDepth.b = CalcHazeAmount( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.y), fPixViewDist);\n\n// if no haze\n#elif !defined(RENDER_SHADOW)\n\n  // no output for it\n  vDepth.b = 0.0f;\n\n#endif\n\n// if not rendering shadow\n#ifndef RENDER_SHADOW\n\n  // adjust depth range (so we can flatten everything out of this range;\n  // nearer object than this will have 0 value and therefore always cast shadow,\n  // while farther objects will have 1, and will never cast shadow)\n  vDepth.r = PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.z) *c_f1oRangeSpan +c_fStartSpan;\n  // clamp depth to 0 to 1 range\n  vDepth.r = saturate( vDepth.r);\n  \n  // encode depth value for storing\n  vDepth.r = ENCODE_DEPTH( vDepth.r);\n  \n  // if splitting depth output to multiple components\n  #ifdef SPLIT_DEPTH\n  \n    // gain extra precision\n    vDepth.r = pow( vDepth.r, c_fSplitExp);\n    // apply sign\n    vDepth.r *= c_fRangeSign;\n\n    // split depth from one 32bit float to two 10 or 16bit float components\n    // (we cannot use exponent and mantisa splitting approach here, because it'll\n    //  provoke errors when resolving AA that's done with simple linear interpolation!)\n    vDepth.g = frac( vDepth.r *c_fSplitMul);\n    vDepth.r-= vDepth.g *c_fSplitDiv;\n\n  // if no splitting of depth\n  #else\n\n    // apply sign\n    vDepth.r *= c_fRangeSign;\n    // (G channel is empty)\n    vDepth.g = 0.0f;\n\n  #endif\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vDepth);\n\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  float4 vVelocity = ( PS_IN( vClipSpacePos) / PS_IN( vClipSpacePos).w ) - ( PS_IN( vPreviousClipSpacePos) / PS_IN( vPreviousClipSpacePos).w );\n  vVelocity.xy *= c_vViewportSizeInPixels.xy * 0.5f;\n  vDepth = float4( vDepth.r, vVelocity.xy, 1 );\n#endif\n\n  // all done\n  PS_OUT( vDepth);\n\n#endif // !RENDER_SHADOW\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ExpandEdges.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// converting to/from RGBE\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/RGBEConversion.hs>\n\n\n// expandee texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0);\n\n// step to move one pixel right (.x) and down (.y)\n_CregF( float2, c_vPixStep, 0);  \n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoord, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n\n\n\n// MAIN\nPS_ENTRY( ExpandEdgesPS)\n{\n  // sample central pixel\n  float2 vTex11 = PS_IN( vTexCoord.xy);\n  float4 vOutCol = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vTex11, 0.0f);\n\n  // and if hasn't already been rendered\n  if( !_any4( vOutCol)) { \n\n    float fSamples = 0.0f;\n\n    // sample surrounding pixels\n    float2 vUV00 = vTex11- c_vPixStep*float2(-1,-1);\n    float4 vCol00 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV00, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol00.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol00);\n    vCol00.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol00)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;                      \n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV01 = vTex11- c_vPixStep*float2(0,-1);\n    float4 vCol01 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV01, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol01.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol01);\n    vCol01.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol01)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;                      \n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV02 = vTex11+ c_vPixStep*float2(1,-1);\n    float4 vCol02 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV02, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol02.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol02);\n    vCol02.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol02)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;                      \n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV10 = vTex11- c_vPixStep*float2(-1,0);\n    float4 vCol10 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV10, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol10.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol10);\n    vCol10.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol10)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;                      \n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV12 = vTex11+ c_vPixStep*float2(1,0);\n    float4 vCol12 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV12, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol12.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol12);\n    vCol12.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol12)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;                      \n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV20 = vTex11- c_vPixStep*float2(-1,1);\n    float4 vCol20 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV20, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol20.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol20);\n    vCol20.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol20)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;                      \n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV21 = vTex11+ c_vPixStep*float2(0,1);\n    float4 vCol21 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV21, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol21.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol21);\n    vCol21.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol21)) {                      \n      fSamples += 1.0f;\n    }                                      \n                                           \n    float2 vUV22 = vTex11+ c_vPixStep*float2(1,1);\n    float4 vCol22 = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vUV22, 0.0f);\n  #ifdef RGBE_IN                               \n    vCol22.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vCol22);\n    vCol22.a = 0.0f; \n  #endif                                     \n    if( _any4( vCol22)) {\n      fSamples += 1.0f;\n    }\n    // if sourounding pixels are not empty\n    if( fSamples > 0.0f) {\n\n      // average (some of) them\n      vOutCol = (vCol00+vCol01+vCol02 + vCol10+vCol12 + vCol20+vCol21+vCol22) / fSamples;\n    }\n  }\n#ifdef RGBE_OUT\n  vOutCol = PackRGBE( vOutCol.rgb);\n#endif\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// FastLightShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADERS\n\n\n// input to both VSes\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n\n#ifdef run_FastLightVS\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float3, vClipCoordLeft, 0);\n  _outReg( float3, vClipCoordRight, 1);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// rendering fast-lights\nVS_ENTRY( FastLightVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // vertex pos to clip space\n  float4 vOutPosLeft = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  float4 vOutPosRight = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n  VS_OUT_POS = vOutPosLeft;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = vOutPosRight;\n\n  // projective coord\n#if _GLSL && !_GLSL_METAL\n  // (need to flip coord because of flipped texture RT)\n  vOutPosLeft.y = -vOutPosLeft.y; \n  vOutPosRight.y = -vOutPosRight.y; \n#endif\n  VS_OUT( vClipCoordLeft) = vOutPosLeft.xyw;\n  VS_OUT( vClipCoordRight) = vOutPosRight.xyw;\n\n  // and go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_FastLightVS\n#ifdef run_FixEdgesVS\n\n\n// mapping texel size and pixel offset\n_CregF( float4, c_vMapAdj,  0);\n_CregF( float2, c_vPixSize, 1);\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN \n  // sampling positions\n  _outReg( float2, vTexMid, 0);  // middle\n  _outReg( float4, vTexMUD, 1);  // middle-up, middle-down\n  _outReg( float4, vTexMLR, 2);  // middle-left, middle-right\n  _outReg( float4, vTexULR, 3);  // up-left, up-right\n  _outReg( float4, vTexDLR, 4);  // down-left, down-right\nVS_OUT_END_VR \n\n\n// fix AA edges\nVS_ENTRY( FixEdgesVS)\n{ \n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( VS_IN( vInPos.xy), 0,1); \n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n\n  // calculate sampling positions\n  float2 vOutTexMid = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vMapAdj.xy +c_vMapAdj.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vTexMUD.xy) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2( 0,-1);\n  VS_OUT( vTexMUD.zw) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2( 0,+1);\n  VS_OUT( vTexMLR.xy) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2(-1, 0);\n  VS_OUT( vTexMLR.zw) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2(+1, 0);\n  VS_OUT( vTexULR.xy) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2(-1,-1);\n  VS_OUT( vTexULR.zw) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2(+1,-1);\n  VS_OUT( vTexDLR.xy) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2(-1,+1);\n  VS_OUT( vTexDLR.zw) = vOutTexMid+ c_vPixSize *float2(+1,+1);\n  VS_OUT( vTexMid) = vOutTexMid;\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_FixEdgesVS\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADERS\n\n#ifdef run_FastLightPS\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 0);\n\n#ifdef HAS_PROJECTOR\n\n  #ifndef TYPE_SPOT\n    // cube projector\n    _SregCUBE( t_sProjector, s_tProjector, 1);\n  #else\n    // or 2D projector\n    _Sreg2D( t_sProjector, s_tProjector, 1);\n  #endif\n\n  // shadow source offset (.xyz) and RGB mask (.w, 0/1)\n  _CregF( float4, c_vShadowOffsetMask, 9);\n  static float3 c_vShadowOffset    = c_vShadowOffsetMask.xyz;\n  static float  c_fShadowColorMask = c_vShadowOffsetMask.w;\n  // view to absoute space rotation matrix (w/o stretching!)\n  _CregM33F( c_mViewToObj, 10);\n\n#endif\n\n// light illumination color\n_CregF( float4, c_vColIllum, 0);\n// reciprocal of depth texture dimensions\n_CregF( float4, c_vScreenSizeDepth, 1);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_vScreenSizeDepth.xy;\nstatic float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vScreenSizeDepth.z;\nstatic float  c_f1oDepthRange = c_vScreenSizeDepth.w;\n// frustum perspective ratios\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumLeft, 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumRight, 3);\nstatic float4 g_vFrustum;\n// light position in view  space\n_CregF( float4, c_vLightPosViewDistLeft, 4);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLightPosViewDistRight, 5);\nstatic float4 g_vLightPosViewDist;\n#define g_vLightPosView g_vLightPosViewDist.xyz\n#define g_fMaxDistance
