g_vLightPosViewDist.w // falloff\n// max distance (fall-off) and smoothing factors\n_CregF( float4, c_vSmoothDist, 6);\nstatic float c_fSmoothing  = c_vSmoothDist.x;\nstatic float c_f1oMaxDist  = c_vSmoothDist.y; // 1/falloff\nstatic float c_f1oMaxDist2 = c_vSmoothDist.z; // ^2\nstatic float c_f1oShdDist  = c_vSmoothDist.w; // 1/min_shadow_dist\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepthMapCones, 7);\nstatic float2 c_vDepthMapping = c_vDepthMapCones.xy;\nstatic float  c_f1oConeRange  = c_vDepthMapCones.z;\nstatic float  c_fOuterCone    = c_vDepthMapCones.w;\n// light normal in view  space\n_CregF( float4, c_vLightDirSoft, 8);\nstatic float3 c_vLightDirView = c_vLightDirSoft.xyz;\nstatic float  c_f1oSoftRatio  = c_vLightDirSoft.w;\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float3, vClipCoordLeft, 0);\n  _inReg( float3, vClipCoordRight, 1);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// distance lighting main function\nPS_ENTRY( FastLightPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustum = VRSelect(c_vFrustumLeft, c_vFrustumRight);\n  g_vLightPosViewDist = VRSelect(c_vLightPosViewDistLeft, c_vLightPosViewDistRight);\n\n  // calc projective coords (-1 - +1 range)\n  float3 vClipCoord = VRSelect(PS_IN(vClipCoordLeft), PS_IN(vClipCoordRight));\n  float2 vProjCoord = vClipCoord.xy / vClipCoord.z;\n  // calc texture coords (0-1 range)\n  float2 vTexCoord = vProjCoord *float2(0.5f,-0.5f) +0.5f;\n  // adjust for sub-portion\n  vTexCoord *= c_vDepthMapping;\n\n#if 0 // EXPERIMENT - fixing resolved depth issues (no luck)\n\n  // sample depth texture \n  float4 vTexCoords4 = vTexCoord.xyxy + c_v1oScreenSize.xyxy*float4(-1.0f,-1.0f,1.0f,1.0f);\n  vTexCoords4 = MultiviewUV2( vTexCoords4); \n\n  float4 vTexDepth;\n  vTexDepth.x = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoords4.xy).r;\n  vTexDepth.y = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoords4.zy).r;\n  vTexDepth.z = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoords4.xw).r;\n  vTexDepth.w = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoords4.zw).r;\n\n  vTexDepth = abs( vTexDepth);\n  vTexDepth.xy = max( vTexDepth.xy, vTexDepth.zw);\n  float fTexDepth = max( vTexDepth.x, vTexDepth.y);\n\n#else\n\n  float fTexDepth = abs( texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( vTexCoord)).r);\n\n#endif\n\n  float3 vPixView;\n\n  // restore depth range (also converts to meters!)\n  vPixView.z = fTexDepth *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;  \n  // and reconstruct view-space coordinates\n  vPixView.xy = -vPixView.z* (vProjCoord +g_vFrustum.yw) *g_vFrustum.xz;\n\n  // calc distance from center\n  float3 vDistView = vPixView - g_vLightPosView;\n  float fDist2 = dot( vDistView, vDistView) +0.001f; // (add to avoid div by zero)\n  float f1oDist = rsqrt( fDist2);  \n  float fDist = 1.0f / f1oDist; \n  // normalize distance by falloff\n  float fDistN = saturate( fDist *c_f1oMaxDist);\n\n#if 0\n\n  // (original code)\n\n  // mix quadratic and linear distance attenuations\n  float fScaleLin = 1- fDistN;\n  float fScale = fScaleLin / fDist2;\n  // lerp with linear attenuation\n  fScale = lerp( fScale, fScaleLin, c_fSmoothing);\n  // degamma linear attenuation\n  fScale = lerp( fScale, fScale*fScale, c_fSmoothing);\n\n#else // 1\n\n  #ifndef FALLOFF_QUAD_ONLY\n    // linear (or mixed) falloff\n    float fScaleLin = 1.0f- fDistN;\n    // degamma linear attenuation\n    fScaleLin *= fScaleLin;\n  #endif\n  #ifndef FALLOFF_LIN_ONLY\n    // quadratic (or mixed) falloff\n    // (first, quadratic = mix hyperbolic and parabolic distance attenuations with smooth-step)\n    float f1oDist2 = max( 1.0f/fDist2, c_f1oMaxDist2); \n    float fScale = f1oDist2 - (c_f1oMaxDist2* (3.0f-2.0f*fDistN));\n  #else\n    // linear falloff only\n    float fScale = fScaleLin;\n  #endif\n  // if mixed linear and quadratic falloffs\n  #if !defined(FALLOFF_QUAD_ONLY) && !defined(FALLOFF_LIN_ONLY)\n    // lerp with linear attenuation\n    fScale = lerp( fScale, fScaleLin, c_fSmoothing);\n  #endif\n\n#endif // 0/1\n\n  // if this fast-light is of spot type\n  #ifdef TYPE_SPOT\n    // apply cone attenuation       \n    float3 vPixDirView = -vDistView * f1oDist; // =normalize()\n    float fAngleCos = dot( vPixDirView, -c_vLightDirView);\n    fScale *= saturate( c_fOuterCone- fAngleCos*c_f1oConeRange);\n  #endif\n\n  // apply to color (adjusted by HDR output normalization value!)\n  float3 vOutColor = c_vColIllum.rgb * fScale;\n\n  // if has projector texture\n#ifdef HAS_PROJECTOR\n\n  // calc attenuated shadow offset\n  float3 vShadowOffset = c_vShadowOffset * max( fDist*c_f1oShdDist-1.0f, 0.0f);\n  // transform direction from view to object space\n  float3 vDistObj = mul( vDistView, c_mViewToObj);\n\n  #ifndef TYPE_SPOT\n\n    // flip north and south faces\n    vDistObj.z = -vDistObj.z; \n    // apply attenuated shadow offset\n    vDistObj += vShadowOffset;\n    // sample projector texture as cube\n    float4 vtexProj = texSampleCube( t_sProjector, s_tProjector, vDistObj);\n\n  #else // TYPE_SPOT\n\n    // apply attenuated shadow offset\n    vDistObj += vShadowOffset;\n    // X & Y coords to projective space\n    // (Z is in normalized meters)\n    vDistObj.xy /= vDistObj.z;\n    // adjust by soft ratio (outer cone)\n    vDistObj.xy *= c_f1oSoftRatio;\n    // normalize to texture coord (0-1 range)\n    vDistObj.xy = vDistObj.xy *0.5f +0.5f;\n    float4 vtexProj = texSample2D( t_sProjector, s_tProjector, vDistObj.xy);\n\n  #endif // TYPE_SPOT\n\n  // apply shadow attenuation by distance^2 (or ^3?)\n  float fShadowAttenuation = fDistN * fDistN; // *fDistN;\n  vtexProj.rgb = lerp( vtexProj.rgb, _tcast(float3,1), fShadowAttenuation);\n  // mask out RGB channels (if unused) and modulate color by it\n  vOutColor *= saturate( vtexProj.rgb + c_fShadowColorMask);\n\n  // if projector has depth info in alpha channel\n  #ifdef PROJECTOR_DEPTH\n\n    // absolute of Z (depth) is \"default\" distance\n    vDistObj = abs( vDistObj);\n    fDist = vDistObj.z;\n    #ifndef TYPE_SPOT\n      // but for cube maps, find linear (not radial!) distance (less z-fighting artefacts this way)\n      fDist = max( max( vDistObj.x, vDistObj.y), fDist);\n    #endif\n    // normalize it by max distance (to get into alpha range)\n    fDist = saturate( fDist *c_f1oMaxDist);\n    // slope-scaled z-bias w/ constant offset is needed\n    vtexProj.a += min( fwidth( vPixView.z), fTexDepth) /8.0f +fTexDepth*8.0f;  \n    // unlit pixel if further away than depth from alpha\n    vOutColor *= step( fDist, vtexProj.a);\n\n  #endif // PROJECTOR_DEPTH\n#endif // HAS_PROJECTOR\n  \n  // alpha has to be 0 in order to remain unchanged, since this output is applied with ADD blending mode\n  // (also, we wan't to avoid possible ROP-performance issue when disabling writing to RT's alpha channel)\n  float4 vOutRes = float4( vOutColor, 0);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutRes);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutRes.rgb = clamp( vOutRes.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutRes);\n}\n\n#endif // run_FastLightPS\n#ifdef run_FixEdgesPS\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, 1);\n\n// max coordinates for sampling source\n_CregF( float4, c_vSampleRect, 0);\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // sampling positions\n  _inReg( float2, vTexMid, 0);  // middle\n  _inReg( float4, vTexMUD, 1);  // middle-up, middle-down\n  _inReg( float4, vTexMLR, 2);  // middle-left, middle-right\n  _inReg( float4, vTexULR, 3);  // up-left, up-right\n  _inReg( float4, vTexDLR, 4);  // down-left, down-right\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// fix wrong edges that were messed up by multi-sampled anti-aliasing\nPS_ENTRY( FixEdgesPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample fast-lights\n  float3 avTex[9];  // (luminance in alpha)\n  float2 vInTexMid = PS_IN( vTexMid.xy);\n  float4 vInTexMUD = PS_IN( vTexMUD);\n  float4 vInTexMLR = PS_IN( vTexMLR);\n  float4 vInTexULR = PS_IN( vTexULR);\n  float4 vInTexDLR = PS_IN( vTexDLR);\n  float2 vMVTexMid = MultiviewUV(  vInTexMid);\n  float4 vMVTexMUD = MultiviewUV2( vInTexMUD);\n  float4 vMVTexMLR = MultiviewUV2( vInTexMLR);\n  float4 vMVTexULR = MultiviewUV2( vInTexULR);\n  float4 vMVTexDLR = MultiviewUV2( vInTexDLR);\n\n  avTex[0] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexMid.xy).rgb;  // middle\n  avTex[1] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexMUD.xy).rgb;  // top\n  avTex[2] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexMUD.zw).rgb;  // bottom\n  avTex[3] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexMLR.xy).rgb;  // left\n  avTex[4] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexMLR.zw).rgb;  // right\n  avTex[5] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexULR.xy).rgb;  // top-left\n  avTex[6] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexULR.zw).rgb;  // top-right\n  avTex[7] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexDLR.xy).rgb;  // bottom-left\n  avTex[8] = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, vMVTexDLR.zw).rgb;  // bottom-right\n\n#if 0 // EXPERIMENT - fixing resolved depth issues (no luck)\n\n  #if 0\n\n    avTex[0] = min( avTex[0], avTex[1]);\n    avTex[1] = min( avTex[2], avTex[3]);\n    avTex[2] = min( avTex[4], avTex[5]);\n    avTex[3] = min( avTex[6], avTex[7]);\n\n    avTex[0] = min( avTex[0], avTex[8]);\n    avTex[1] = min( avTex[1], avTex[2]);\n    avTex[2] = min( avTex[2], avTex[3]);\n\n    avTex[1] = min( avTex[1], avTex[2]);\n\n    avTex[0] = min( avTex[0], avTex[1]);\n\n  #else\n\n    const float3 LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS = float3( 0.2125f, 0.7154f, 0.0721f);\n\n    float4 avLumas[2];\n    avLumas[0].x = dot( avTex[1], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[0].y = dot( avTex[2], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[0].z = dot( avTex[3], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[0].w = dot( avTex[4], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[1].x = dot( avTex[5], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[1].y = dot( avTex[6], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[1].z = dot( avTex[7], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n    avLumas[1].w = dot( avTex[8], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n\n    avLumas[0].xy = max( avLumas[0].xy, avLumas[0].zw);\n    avLumas[0].zw = max( avLumas[1].xy, avLumas[1].zw);\n    //vLumas.x  = min( vLumas.x,  vLumas.y);\n\n    float fLumaPivot;\n    fLumaPivot = dot( avTex[0], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS) *0.9f;\n    if( fLumaPivot > avLumas[0].x) {\n\n      avTex[0]  = avTex[1] *0.5f;\n      avTex[0] += avTex[2] *0.5f;\n    }\n    fLumaPivot = dot( avTex[0], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS) *0.9f;\n    if( fLumaPivot > avLumas[0].y) {\n\n      avTex[0]  = avTex[3] *0.5f;\n      avTex[0] += avTex[4] *0.5f;\n    }\n    fLumaPivot = dot( avTex[0], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS) *0.9f;\n    if( fLumaPivot > avLumas[0].z) {\n\n      avTex[0]  = avTex[5] *0.5f;\n      avTex[0] += avTex[6] *0.5f;\n    }\n    fLumaPivot = dot( avTex[0], LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS) *0.9f;\n    if( fLumaPivot > avLumas[0].w) {\n\n      avTex[0]  = avTex[7] *0.5f;\n      avTex[0] += avTex[8] *0.5f;\n    }\n\n  #endif\n\n  PS_OUT( float4( avTex[0], 1));\n\n#else // 0/1\n\n  // find luminances\n  float2 vLum0Bak0;\n  float4 avLum8[2], avLumBak8[2];\n  float3 vLumWeights = float3( 0.3f, 0.6f, 0.1f);\n  vLum0Bak0.x = vLum0Bak0.y = dot( avTex[0].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[0].x = dot( avTex[1].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[0].y = dot( avTex[2].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[0].z = dot( avTex[3].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[0].w = dot( avTex[4].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[1].x = dot( avTex[5].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[1].y = dot( avTex[6].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[1].z = dot( avTex[7].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLum8[1].w = dot( avTex[8].rgb, vLumWeights);\n  avLumBak8[0] = avLum8[0];\n  avLumBak8[1] = avLum8[1];\n\n  // do median filter (sorting)\n  float t;\n\n#define sort2( a, b)  t=a; a=min(a,b); b=max(t,b);\n\n#define min3( a, b, c)  sort2( a, b); sort2( a, c);\n#define max3( a, b, c)  sort2( b, c); sort2( a, c);\n             \n#define sort3( a, b, c)          max3( a, b, c); sort2( a, b);                                                     // 3 exchanges\n#define sort4( a, b, c, d)       sort2( a, b);   sort2( c, d);  sort2( a, c);    sort2( b, d);                     // 4 exchanges\n#define sort5( a, b, c, d, e)    sort2( a, b);   sort2( c, d);  min3( a, c, e);  max3( b, d, e);                   // 6 exchanges\n#define sort6( a, b, c, d, e, f) sort2( a, d);   sort2( b, e);  sort2( c, f);    min3( a, b, c);  max3( d, e, f);  // 7 exchanges\n\n  // starting with a subset of size 6, remove the min and max each time\n  sort6( vLum0Bak0.x, avLum8[0].x, avLum8[0].y, avLum8[0].z, avLum8[0].w, avLum8[1].x);\n  sort5( avLum8[0].x, avLum8[0].y, avLum8[0].z, avLum8[0].w, avLum8[1].y);\n  sort4( avLum8[0].y, avLum8[0].z, avLum8[0].w, avLum8[1].z);\n  sort3( avLum8[0].z, avLum8[0].w, avLum8[1].w);\n  vLum0Bak0.x = avLum8[0].w;\n\n  // check if this luminance is very similar to center (middle) sample\n  float2 vMedCoords = vInTexMid;\n  float2 vRatio = vLum0Bak0 +0.0001f;\n  float fDeltaM = abs( vRatio.x/vRatio.y -1.0f);\n  if( fDeltaM > 0.1f) {\n\n    // if not, find tex-coords this luminance belongs to and use it\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[0].x==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexMUD.xy : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[0].y==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexMUD.zw : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[0].z==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexMLR.xy : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[0].w==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexMLR.zw : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[1].x==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexULR.xy : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[1].y==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexULR.zw : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[1].z==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexDLR.xy : vMedCoords;\n    vMedCoords = (avLumBak8[1].w==vLum0Bak0.x) ? vInTexDLR.zw : vMedCoords;\n  }\n  // clamp found tex-coord to be inside drawport area\n  vMedCoords = clamp( vMedCoords, c_vSampleRect.xy, c_vSampleRect.zw);\n  // and sample from there\n  float4 vOutColor = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, MultiviewUV( vMedCoords));\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n\n#endif // 0/1\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_FixEdgesPS\n#ifdef run_FlatFillPS\n\n\n// fill color\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolFill, 0);\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\n// (altho unused, needs to be here for proper PS input definition!)\nPS_IN_BEGIN\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( FlatFillPS)\n{\n  PS_OUT( c_vcolFill);\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_FlatFillPS\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// FatLineShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProjLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vModelViewProjRightX, 4);\n\n// adjustment for projection matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mProjRenAdjLeft, 5);\n_CregF( float4, c_vProjRenAdjRightX, 9);\n\n// normal signed/unsigned masks and line width\n_CregF( float3, c_vNorMaskLineWidth, 10);\nstatic float2 c_vNorMask  = c_vNorMaskLineWidth.xy;\nstatic float  c_fLineWidth= c_vNorMaskLineWidth.z;\n\n\n// input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition,  0);  // vertex position in object space\n  _inReg( float4, vPosPivot,  1);  // vertex pivot position\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,    2);  // vertex normal\n  _inReg( float2, vTextureUV, 3);  // texture 2D coordinates\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type input to tex-col pixel shader!)\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0); // texture coordinates\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// the vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( FatLineVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  float4x4 mModelViewProjRight = VRRightMatrix(c_mModelViewProjLeft, c_vModelViewProjRightX);\n  \n  float3 vPivorNor = normalize( VS_IN( vPosition.xyz) - VS_IN( vPosPivot.xyz));\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorMask.yyyx);\n  float3 vLineNor = cross( vPivorNor, vNor);\n  float3 vUpNormClip = float3( 0,0,-1);\n  \n  float4 vPivotPosClipLeft = mul( VS_IN( vPosPivot), c_mModelViewProjLeft);\n  float4 vLineNorClipLeft = mul( float4(vLineNor,0), c_mModelViewProjLeft);\n  float3 vVexDirClipLeft = cross( vUpNormClip, vLineNorClipLeft.xyz);\n  vVexDirClipLeft.xy = normalize( vVexDirClipLeft.xy);\n  vPivotPosClipLeft.xy += vVexDirClipLeft.xy * vPivotPosClipLeft.z *c_fLineWidth;\n\n  float4 vPivotPosClipRight = mul( VS_IN( vPosPivot), mModelViewProjRight);  \n  float4 vLineNorClipRight = mul( float4(vLineNor,0), mModelViewProjRight);\n  float3 vVexDirClipRight = cross( vUpNormClip, vLineNorClipRight.xyz);\n  vVexDirClipRight.xy = normalize( vVexDirClipRight.xy);\n  vPivotPosClipRight.xy += vVexDirClipRight.xy * vPivotPosClipRight.z *c_fLineWidth;  \n  \n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPivotPosClipLeft, c_mProjRenAdjLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPivotPosClipRight, VRRightMatrix(c_mProjRenAdjLeft, c_vProjRenAdjRightX));\n\n  // texture coordinates modified by stretch and offset\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords) = VS_IN( vTextureUV.xyxy);\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// FlareShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProjLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vModelViewProjRightX, 4);\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos,   0);\n  _inReg( float2, vInTexUV, 1);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float2, vTexUV, 0);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( FlareVS)\n{\n  // output\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProjLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), VRRightMatrix( c_mModelViewProjLeft, c_vModelViewProjRightX));\n  VS_OUT( vTexUV) = VS_IN( vInTexUV);\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// 2D texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sTex2D, s_tTex2D, 0);\n_CregF( float3, c_vcolModulator, 0);\n\n// PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float2, vTexUV, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( FlarePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // sample 2D texture\n  float3 vOutColor = texSample2D( t_sTex2D, s_tTex2D, PS_IN( vTexUV)).rgb;\n  // modulate by constant color\n  vOutColor *= c_vcolModulator;\n\n  // discard pixel if color is (almost) black\n  float fOutLuma = dot( vOutColor, _tcast(float3,1));\n  clip( fOutLuma-0.001f);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( float4( vOutColor, 1.0f));\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// FuseColorChannelsShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n#ifdef _PSSL\n  // (need more precision for output)\n  #pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default FMT_32_R)\n#endif\n\n\n// texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0);\n\n// fusion weights (exponent in .w)\n_CregF( float4, c_vWeightsExp, 0);\n\n// pixel input is vertex output\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( FuseChannelsPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample soource texture and clamp\n  float4 vTexel = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)));\n  // combine components back into a single value\n  vTexel.r = dot( vTexel.rgb, c_vWeightsExp.xyz); \n  // keep sign\n  float fSign = sign( vTexel.r);\n  // apply \"(de)compression\" exponent\n  vTexel.r = pow( abs( vTexel.r), c_vWeightsExp.w);\n  // and sign\n  vTexel.r *= fSign;\n  PS_OUT( vTexel.rrrr);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// GlitchShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n\n_Sreg2D( t_sSrc,   s_tSrc,   0); // source (to displace)\n_Sreg2D( t_sDisp1, s_tDisp1, 1); // 1st displacement map\n_Sreg2D( t_sMask,  s_tMask,  2); // mask for 1st displacement map\n_Sreg2D( t_sDisp2, s_tDisp2, 3); // 2nd displacement map\n\n// source texture's coordinates clamping edges (.xy=min, .zw=max)\n_CregF( float4, c_vEdges, 0);\n// mapping factors for source texture\n// 2D rectangle mapping constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vRectMapping, 1);\n// 1st and 2nd displacements' strengths (by channels)\n_CregF( float3, c_vDisp1Strength, 2);\n_CregF( float3, c_vDisp2Strength, 3);\n// fading factors (color, alpha, 1/edge)\n_CregF( float3, c_vFadeFactors, 4);\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vSrcExpCoords, 0);  // .xy=inner, .zw=outer\n  _inReg( float4, vDisplsCoords, 1);\n  _inReg( float2, vMaskCoord,    2);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// begin one light pass\nPS_ENTRY( GlitchPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample mask texture\n  float3 vMask = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, PS_IN( vMaskCoord)).rgb;\n\n  // and displacement maps\n  float3 vDisp1 = texSample2D( t_sDisp1, s_tDisp1, PS_IN( vDisplsCoords.xy)).rgb;\n  float3 vDisp2 = texSample2D( t_sDisp2, s_tDisp2, PS_IN( vDisplsCoords.zw)).rgb;\n  vDisp1 = vDisp1 *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vDisp2 = vDisp2 *2.0f -1.0f;\n\n  // attenuate 1st displacement by mask\n  vDisp1 *= vMask; \n\n  // apply strengths to RGB channels\n  float3 vDispR = vDisp1 * c_vDisp1Strength.r;\n  float3 vDispG = vDisp1 * c_vDisp1Strength.g;\n  float3 vDispB = vDisp1 * c_vDisp1Strength.b;\n  float3 vDisp2R= vDisp2 * c_vDisp2Strength.r;\n  float3 vDisp2G= vDisp2 * c_vDisp2Strength.g;\n  float3 vDisp2B= vDisp2 * c_vDisp2Strength.b;\n\n  // combine displacements\n  vDispR += vDisp2R;\n  vDispG += vDisp2G;\n  vDispB += vDisp2B;\n\n  // convert Z offset to size-relative\n  float2 vDispRZ2 = _tcast(float2,1.0f)- vDispR.zz *float2(1.0f,0.5f);\n  float2 vDispGZ2 = _tcast(float2,1.0f)- vDispG.zz *float2(1.0f,0.5f);\n  float2 vDispBZ2 = _tcast(float2,1.0f)- vDispB.zz *float2(1.0f,0.5f);\n  vDispR.z = (vDispR.z<0.0f) ? vDispRZ2.x : vDispRZ2.y;\n  vDispG.z = (vDispG.z<0.0f) ? vDispGZ2.x : vDispGZ2.y;\n  vDispB.z = (vDispB.z<0.0f) ? vDispBZ2.x : vDispBZ2.y;\n\n  // get source texture coordinates\n  float2 vSrcCoordR = PS_IN( vSrcExpCoords).xy;\n  float2 vSrcCoordG = vSrcCoordR;\n  float2 vSrcCoordB = vSrcCoordR;\n\n  // apply Z offset to source texture's XY coords\n  vSrcCoordR = vSrcCoordR *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vSrcCoordG = vSrcCoordG *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vSrcCoordB = vSrcCoordB *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vSrcCoordR*= vDispR.z;\n  vSrcCoordG*= vDispG.z;\n  vSrcCoordB*= vDispB.z;\n  vSrcCoordR = vSrcCoordR *0.5f +0.5f;\n  vSrcCoordG = vSrcCoordG *0.5f +0.5f;\n  vSrcCoordB = vSrcCoordB *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // apply XY offsets to source texture's XY coords\n  vSrcCoordR += vDispR.xy;\n  vSrcCoordG += vDispG.xy;\n  vSrcCoordB += vDispB.xy;\n\n  // clamp coordinates to inner rect edges\n  vSrcCoordR = saturate( vSrcCoordR);\n  vSrcCoordG = saturate( vSrcCoordG);\n  vSrcCoordB = saturate( vSrcCoordB);\n\n  // calculate edge fading factors \n  float2 vEdgeFading; // (at %20!)\n  float2 vExpCoords = PS_IN( vSrcExpCoords).zw;\n  vEdgeFading  = saturate( (vExpCoords-0.0f) *c_vFadeFactors.zz);\n  vEdgeFading *= saturate( (1.0f-vExpCoords) *c_vFadeFactors.zz);\n\n  // convert coordinates to used inner area bounds\n  vSrcCoordR.xy = vSrcCoordR.xy *c_vRectMapping.xy +c_vRectMapping.zw; \n  vSrcCoordG.xy = vSrcCoordG.xy *c_vRectMapping.xy +c_vRectMapping.zw; \n  vSrcCoordB.xy = vSrcCoordB.xy *c_vRectMapping.xy +c_vRectMapping.zw; \n\n  // (no need for this, we already clamped by saturate!)\n  // clamp them to edges of that area \n//vSrcCoordR.xy = clamp( vSrcCoordR.xy, c_vEdges.xy, c_vEdges.zw);\n//vSrcCoordG.xy = clamp( vSrcCoordG.xy, c_vEdges.xy, c_vEdges.zw);\n//vSrcCoordG.xy = clamp( vSrcCoordB.xy, c_vEdges.xy, c_vEdges.zw);\n\n  // sample source texture channels\n  float2 vRA = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, MultiviewUV(vSrcCoordR.xy)).ra;\n  float2 vGA = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, MultiviewUV(vSrcCoordG.xy)).ga;\n  float2 vBA = texSample2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, MultiviewUV(vSrcCoordB.xy)).ba;\n\n  // combine them\n  float4 vOutCol;\n  vOutCol.rgb = float3( vRA.x, vGA.x, vBA.x);\n  // average alpha\n  vOutCol.a = saturate( (vRA.y + vGA.y + vBA.y) * 0.33334f);\n\n  // apply fading factors\n  vOutCol *= c_vFadeFactors.xxxy;\n  // along with edge fading\n  vOutCol.a *= vEdgeFading.x * vEdgeFading.y;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// GlitchShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// depth of rectangle (in clip space!)\n_CregF( float3, c_vRectDepth,  0); \n_CregF( float4, c_vSrcMapping, 1); \n// mapping factors\n_CregM42F( c_mDisp1Mapping, 2);\n_CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping,  4);\n_CregM42F( c_mDisp2Mapping, 6);\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type input to tex-col pixel shader!)\n  _outReg( float4, vSrcExpCoords, 0);  // .xy=inner, .zw=outer\n  _outReg( float4, vDisplsCoords, 1);\n  _outReg( float2, vMaskCoord,    2);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( GlitchVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  float4 vInTex, vOutPos;\n\n  // construct position in clip-space\n  float2 vInPos = VS_IN( vPosition.xy);\n  vOutPos.xy = vInPos;\n  vOutPos.z = c_vRectDepth.x / c_vRectDepth.y;\n  vOutPos.w = 1.0f;\n  VS_OUT_POS = vOutPos * -c_vRectDepth.z;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n\n  // pass mapping coordinates to pixel shader\n  vInTex.xy = VS_IN( vPosition.zw);\n  vInTex.zw = float2( 0.0f, 1.0f);\n  VS_OUT( vSrcExpCoords.xy) = vInTex.xy *c_vSrcMapping.xy +c_vSrcMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vSrcExpCoords.zw) = vInTex.xy;\n  VS_OUT( vDisplsCoords.xy) = mulM42F( vInTex, c_mDisp1Mapping);\n  VS_OUT( vDisplsCoords.zw) = mulM42F( vInTex, c_mDisp2Mapping);\n  VS_OUT( vMaskCoord)       = mulM42F( vInTex, c_mMaskMapping);\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// GrassShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeBlend.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse,     s_tDiffuse,     0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, 1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sSpecMask,    s_tSpecMask,    2);\n\n// for screen coords sampling and HDR output normalization value\n_CregF( float3, c_vScreenSizeFace, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_vScreenSizeFace.xy;\nstatic float  c_fFacingness   = c_vScreenSizeFace.z;\n// alpha range adjustment (for transparency AA, if any)\n_CregF( float2, c_vAlphaRange, 1);\n// mask for usage of FLAO texture values\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskFLAO, 2);\n// viewer position\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPix, 3);\n// specularity color and power\n_CregF( float4, c_vSpecularity, 4);\nstatic float3 c_vSpecColor = c_vSpecularity.rgb;\nstatic float  c_fSpecPower = c_vSpecularity.w;\n  // (fog/haze use const reg c5-c7!)\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (name of 1st two members must match names of depth/shadow pass pixel shaders!)\n  _inReg( float4, vUV_Z_AMul, 0);   // tex coordinates (.xy only!)\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);\n  _inReg( float4, vVexNorAbsFog,  2);  // .w=fog amount\n  _inReg( float4, vVexColDiffuse, 3);\n  _inReg( float4, vVexColLitHaze, 4);  // .w=haze amount\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\n  _inFacReg;\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// global vars\nstatic float4 g_vDiffuse;\nstatic float3 g_vNorAbs;\nstatic float2 g_vTexCoord;\n#ifdef HAS_SPECULARITY\n  static float3 g_vPosAbs;\n#endif\n\n\n// apply shading\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  // compute dot product of light dir with normal\n  float fNdotL = saturate( dot( g_vNorAbs, vLightDirAbs));\n  float3 vLighting = g_vDiffuse.rgb;\n\n#ifdef HAS_SPECULARITY\n\n  // calculate view direction vector\n  float3 vViewDir = normalize( c_vViewPosAbsPix.xyz - g_vPosAbs);\n\n  // calculate specularity\n  float fSpecularityFactor = PhongSpecularity( g_vNorAbs, vViewDir, vLightDirAbs, c_fSpecPower);\n  \n  // modulate it by mask\n  float fSpecMask = texSample2D( t_sSpecMask, s_tSpecMask, g_vTexCoord).r;\n  fSpecularityFactor *= fSpecMask;\n\n  // and add it over light color\n  vLighting += c_vSpecColor * fSpecularityFactor;\n\n#endif\n\n  // apply diffuse to lighting\n  vLighting *= fNdotL;\n  return vLighting;\n}\n\n\n// screen rendering shader\nPS_ENTRY( GrassPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // fetch normal, position in absolute space and UV tex coords for specular mask texture\n  g_vNorAbs = PS_IN( vVexNorAbsFog.xyz);\n  g_vTexCoord = PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy);\n#ifdef HAS_SPECULARITY\n  g_vPosAbs = PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz);\n#endif\n  // cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n  // adjust facing sign\n  float fInPolyFace = PS_FACE * c_fFacingness;\n  // and eventually flip (for 2-sided lighting)\n  g_vNorAbs = FlipNormal( g_vNorAbs, fInPolyFace);\n\n  // fetch LDR diffuse texture and bias it\n  g_vDiffuse = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, g_vTexCoord);\n  LinearSpace( g_vDiffuse.rgb);\n  // compensate for the fact that grass texture is centered around gray\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb *= LINEAR_2; // (2.0 in linear space = 2^2.2)\n  g_vDiffuse *= PS_IN( vVexColDiffuse);\n\n  // (will apply dynamic light in here)\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, g_vDiffuse.a);\n\n  // sample fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos());\n  vIllumAmbOccSample = vIllumAmbOccSample *c_vMaskFLAO.xxxz +c_vMaskFLAO.yyyw;\n\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // start from vertex lighting\n  vOutColor.rgb = PS_IN( vVexColLitHaze.xyz);\n  // modulate by ambient occlusion\n  vOutColor.rgb *= vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // and add illumination (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // modulate all that by diffuse color\n  vOutColor.rgb *= g_vDiffuse.rgb;\n\n#else  // HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // do complete per-pixel distant light (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += DistantLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) * vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // per-pixel spot light (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += SpotLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // per-pixel omni light (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += OmniLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#endif\n\n  // if has fog and/or haze\n#ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  float2 vFozeAmount = float2( PS_IN( vVexNorAbsFog.w), PS_IN( vVexColLitHaze.w));\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, vFozeAmount);\n#endif\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// GrassShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Shockwave.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// world to clip space matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mAbsToClipLeft, 0);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n// object to view (eye) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToView, 7);\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n// view to absolute space transformation matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mViewToAbs, 14);\n\n// input colors masks\n_CregF( float3, c_vInputColorMasks, 17);\nstatic float c_fInputAmbientMul = c_vInputColorMasks.x;\nstatic float c_fInputDiffuseMul = c_vInputColorMasks.y;\nstatic float c_fInputDiffuseAdd = c_vInputColorMasks.z;\n// viewer position\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbs, 18);\n// sway params\n_CregF( float4, c_vSwayParams, 19);\nstatic float c_fSwayStrength = c_vSwayParams.x;\nstatic float c_fMinFrequency = c_vSwayParams.y;\nstatic float c_fMaxFrequency = c_vSwayParams.z;\nstatic float c_fTime         = c_vSwayParams.w;\n// 3rd row (Z) of view matrix, for depth and shadow casting\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewZ, 20);\n// fade in/out distances\n_CregF( float4, c_vFadeDistances, 21);\nstatic float c_f1oFadeOutRange   = c_vFadeDistances.x;\nstatic float c_fFadeOutEndoRange = c_vFadeDistances.y;\nstatic float c_fFadeInStartoRange= c_vFadeDistances.z;\nstatic float c_f1oFadeInRange    = c_vFadeDistances.w;\n_CregF( float4, c_vHeightFadeDistSwavesAMul, 22);\nstatic float c_f1oHeightFadeOutRange  = c_vHeightFadeDistSwavesAMul.x;\nstatic float c_fHeightFadeOutEndoRange= c_vHeightFadeDistSwavesAMul.y;\nstatic float c_fShockwavesCount       = c_vHeightFadeDistSwavesAMul.z;\nstatic float c_fAlphaMul              = c_vHeightFadeDistSwavesAMul.w;\n\n// mask for normal and tangents\n// (up constant vector, signed or unsigned inputs)\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorMaskBool, 23);\nstatic float3 c_vNorMask = c_vNorMaskBool.xyz;\n// flag that indicate that polygons should be rendered in face-forward mode\nstatic float c_fFaceForward = c_vNorMaskBool.w;\n\n// multiply-add for texture coords\n_CregF( float4, c_vUVmad, 24);\n\n// other VR eye projection X row\n_CregF(float4, c_vAbsToClipRightX, 25);\nstatic float4x4 g_mAbsToClip;\n\n// ambient color\n_CregF( float3, c_vColAmbient, 26);\n\n_CregM44F( c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft, 27);\n\n\n// object to absolute space transformation matrix\nstatic float4x3 g_mObjToAbs;\nstatic float g_fAlphaMul;\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition,     0);\n  _inReg( float2, vDiffuseUV,    1);\n  _inReg( float4, vDiffuseColor, 2);\n  _inReg( float4, vLightColor,   3);\n  _inReg( float4, vSwayBias,     4);\n  _inReg( float4, vPivotPosObj,  5);\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal, 6);\n#endif\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  _inReg( float4x3, mInstObjToAbs, 7);\n  _inReg( float, vAMul, 10);\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (name of 1st two members must match names of depth/shadow pass vertex shaders!)\n  _outReg( float4, vUV_Z_AMul, 0); // tex coordinates, z value and alpha keying multiplier\n#ifdef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n  #ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n    _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);\n  #endif\n  #ifdef GENERATE_MVECS\n    _outReg( float4, vClipSpacePos, 3);\n    _outReg( float4, vPreviousClipSpacePos, 4);\n  #endif\n  #if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n    _outReg( float4, vModelSpacePos, 5);\n  #endif\n#else\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);\n  _outReg( float4, vVexNorAbsFog,  2);  // .w=fog amount\n  _outReg( float4, vVexColDiffuse, 3);\n  _outReg( float4, vVexColLitHaze, 4);  // .w=haze amount\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// global vars\nstatic float3 g_vPixNormalAbs;\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( GrassVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  g_mObjToAbs = VS_IN( mInstObjToAbs);\n  g_fAlphaMul = VS_IN( vAMul);\n#else\n  g_mObjToAbs = c_mObjToAbs;\n  g_fAlphaMul = c_fAlphaMul;\n#endif\n\n  // apply grass swaying\n  float4 vObjPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  float fPhase = vObjPos.x + vObjPos.z *3.1f;\n  float fFrequency = lerp( c_fMinFrequency, c_fMaxFrequency, frac(vObjPos.x*3.3f+vObjPos.z*1.56f));\n  float fWavesMoveSpeed = c_fTime*0.5f;\n  float fSwayWaves = (sin( vObjPos.x+fWavesMoveSpeed) + cos( vObjPos.z+fWavesMoveSpeed)) *0.3f +1.0f;\n  float fSwayBias = VS_IN( vSwayBias).x;\n  vObjPos.xz += sin( c_fTime*fFrequency +fPhase) *fSwayBias *c_fSwayStrength *fSwayWaves;\n\n  // transform position into absolute space\n  float3 vPivotPosAbs = mulM43F( VS_IN( vPivotPosObj), g_mObjToAbs);\n\n  // copy diffuse mapping coordinates\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.xy) = VS_IN( vDiffuseUV) * c_vUVmad.xy + c_vUVmad.zw;\n\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n\n  // get normal (or just up vector, depends on mask)\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorMask.xyxz);\n\n  // transform normal from object to absolute space\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( g_mObjToAbs);\n  float3 vNorAbs = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRot);\n  // and (re)normalize it\n  // (cannot use \"normalize()\" here because of weird issue with SPIR-V compiled code and NV GPU; Vulkan pipeline state object creation puke an error!)\n  vNorAbs /= length( vNorAbs);\n  VS_OUT( vVexNorAbsFog.xyz) = vNorAbs;\n\n  // unpack light color and pass it to the pixel program\n  float4 vVexLightColor = VS_IN( vLightColor);\n  VS_OUT( vVexColLitHaze.xyz) = UnpackRGBE( vVexLightColor) *c_fInputAmbientMul +c_vColAmbient;\n\n  // compensate diffuse for the crumbs baker random gradient\n  // and convert floor diffuse texture into linear space\n  float4 vVexDiffuseColor = VS_IN( vDiffuseColor);\n  // apply overbrighting (\"shade\" mode)\n  vVexDiffuseColor.rgb *= 2.0f;\n  // convert to linear space (fast!)\n  vVexDiffuseColor.rgb *= vVexDiffuseColor.rgb;\n  // mask out or not\n  VS_OUT( vVexColDiffuse.rgb) = vVexDiffuseColor.rgb *c_fInputDiffuseMul +c_fInputDiffuseAdd;\n\n#endif\n\n  // calculate pivot distance\n  float fPivotDistance = length( c_vViewPosAbs.xyz - vPivotPosAbs);\n  float fNegHeightDiff = vPivotPosAbs.y - c_vViewPosAbs.y;\n  \n  // calculate fade factors\n  float fFadeOut = saturate(-fPivotDistance *c_f1oFadeOutRange+c_fFadeOutEndoRange);\n  float fFadeIn  = saturate( fPivotDistance *c_f1oFadeInRange -c_fFadeInStartoRange);\n  float fHeightFade = saturate( fNegHeightDiff *c_f1oHeightFadeOutRange +c_fHeightFadeOutEndoRange);\n\n  // pass alpha keying multiplier to the pixel program (used by depth prepass/shadow shader)\n  float fOutAMul = fFadeOut * fFadeIn * fHeightFade;\n  fOutAMul *= g_fAlphaMul;\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.a) = fOutAMul;\n\n  // select \"normal\" or pivot coordinates (if completly faded out)\n  float4 vObjPosFinal = (fOutAMul>0.0f) ? vObjPos : VS_IN( vPivotPosObj);\n\n  // position in absolute space\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n\n  // if face forward\n  if( c_fFaceForward != 0.0f) {\n\n    // VIEWER FACING\n\n    // get vertex position in abs space\n    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vObjPosFinal, g_mObjToAbs);\n\n    float3 vAbsPivDir = vPivotPosAbs - c_vViewPosAbs.xyz;\n\n    // determine basis vectors for viewer facing orientation\n    float3 vRight = normalize(float3(-vAbsPivDir.z, 0, vAbsPivDir.x));\n    float3 vForward = normalize(-vAbsPivDir);\n    float3 vUp = cross(vForward, vRight);\n\n    // note 1: this matrix is not orthonormal, because vRight and vForward are not necessarily orthogonal\n    // note 2: there is an edge case if pivot and viewer both lie on the plane x=0, in which case vUp is nul\n    float3x3 mObjPivToViewerFacing = float3x3(vRight, vUp, vForward);\n    \n    // determine offset vector from pivot to vertex in object space\n    float3 vPivToVexObj = vObjPosFinal.xyz - VS_IN( vPivotPosObj).xyz;\n    // we have to use the magnitude of the offset vector in absolute space,\n    // because that preserves the stretch from obj-to-abs matrix\n    float fPivToVexAbsLen = length( vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - vPivotPosAbs);\n    vPivToVexObj = normalize( vPivToVexObj) *fPivToVexAbsLen;\n    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = _mulT( vPivToVexObj, mObjPivToViewerFacing) + vPivotPosAbs;\n\n  // if not face-forward\n  } else {\n\n    // vertex pos to abs space\n    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vObjPosFinal, g_mObjToAbs);\n  }\n\n#if !defined(DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS) || defined(APPLY_FOZE)\n\n  // (out with vertex position in absolute space)\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n\n#endif\n\n  // output depth\n  // (we must output depth *after* face-forward calculations!)\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.z) = dot( vOutVexPosAbs, c_vViewZ);\n  \n  // and there are some shockwaves\n  if( c_fShockwavesCount > 0.0f) {\n\n    // apply shockwave effects (if any)\n    ApplyShockwavesAbs( c_fShockwavesCount, vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, vPivotPosAbs.xyz, 100.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n  }\n  // calc clip-space pixel position\n  float4 vOutPosClipLeft = mul( vOutVexPosAbs, c_mAbsToClipLeft);\n  float4 vOutPosClipRight = mul( vOutVexPosAbs, VRRightMatrix(c_mAbsToClipLeft, c_vAbsToClipRightX));\n\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n\n  // apply fading onto alpha channel (for translucent models)\n  VS_OUT( vVexColDiffuse.a) = fOutAMul;\n\n  #ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n    // calculate fog and haze amount\n    float fViewDistance = length( vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - c_vViewPosAbs.xyz);\n    VS_OUT( vVexNorAbsFog.w)  = CalcFogAmount( vOutVexPosAbs, c_vViewPosAbs, fViewDistance);\n    VS_OUT( vVexColLitHaze.w) = CalcHazeAmount( vOutVexPosAbs.y, fViewDistance);\n  #else\n    // no fog nor haze\n    VS_OUT( vVexNorAbsFog.w)  = 0.0f;\n    VS_OUT( vVexColLitHaze.w) = 0.0f;\n  #endif\n\n#else\n  #ifdef GENERATE_MVECS\n    VS_OUT( vClipSpacePos ) = vOutPosClipLeft;\n    VS_OUT( vPreviousClipSpacePos ) = mul( vOutVexPosAbs, c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft );\n  #endif\n  #if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n    VS_OUT( vModelSpacePos ) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n  #endif\n#endif // !DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n\n  // output clip-space position\n  VS_OUT_POS = vOutPosClipLeft;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = vOutPosClipRight;\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// GridOverlayShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n \n// input texture of world\n_Sreg2D(t_sInputWorldFrame2D, s_tInputWorldFrame2D, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vMaskPositionRadiusExp, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vOverlayOpacity, 1);\nstatic float2 c_vMaskPosition = c_vMaskPositionRadiusExp.xy;\nstatic float c_fRadius = c_vMaskPositionRadiusExp.z;\nstatic float c_fExponent = c_vMaskPositionRadiusExp.w;\nstatic float c_fOpacityCoef = c_vOverlayOpacity.x;\n\n// PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float2, vUV, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\nfloat Distance(float2 v1, float2 v2)\n{\n  float2 vd = v1 - v2;\n  return sqrt(vd.x * vd.x + vd.y * vd.y);\n}\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY(GridOverlayShaderPS)\n{\n  // get vertex color\n  float4 vOutColor = float4(1, 0, 0, 0.9);\n  // sample 2D texture\n  float4 vTexture = texSample2D(t_sInputWorldFrame2D, s_tInputWorldFrame2D, PS_IN(vUV));\n  \n  float fDist = Distance(PS_IN(vUV).xy, c_vMaskPosition);\n\n  if(fDist <= c_fRadius){\n    float fCoef = fDist / c_fRadius;\n    float fSmoothing = pow(fCoef, c_fExponent);\n    vTexture.a = 1 - fSmoothing;\n  }else{\n    vTexture.a = 0;\n  }\n\n  vTexture.a = lerp(1, vTexture.a, c_fOpacityCoef);\n\n  vOutColor = vTexture; \n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT(vOutColor);\n}\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// HeatShimmerShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n// 2D rectangle mapping constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepthMapping, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vBumpsMapping, 1);\n// depth of rectangle (in clip space!)\n_CregF( float, c_fRectDepth, 2); \n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n// input to VS\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // (rectangle map)\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( HeatShimmerVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // construct position in clip-space\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( VS_IN( vInPos.xy), c_fRectDepth, 1);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n\n  // and pass mapping coordinates to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.xy) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vDepthMapping.xy +c_vDepthMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.zw) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vBumpsMapping.xy +c_vBumpsMapping.zw;\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sRefr,  s_tRefr,  0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sBumps, s_tBumps, 1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 2);\n\n// strength and depth offset\n_CregF( float4, c_vBumpDepthRect, 0);\nstatic float  c_fBumpPower = c_vBumpDepthRect.x; \nstatic float  c_fDepthOfs  = c_vBumpDepthRect.y; \nstatic float2 c_vRectEdges = c_vBumpDepthRect.zw;\n\n// Z-buffer scale, offset and mapping\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepth, 1);\nstatic float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepth.x;\nstatic float  c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepth.y;\nstatic float2 c_vDepthMapping = c_vDepth.zw;\n\n// projective frustum params\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumZL, 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumZR, 3);\n\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\nstatic float4 g_vFrustumZ;\n\n\n// begin one light pass\nPS_ENTRY( HeatShimmerPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustumZ = VRSelect( c_vFrustumZL, c_vFrustumZR);\n\n  // reconstruct pixel position\n  float4 vPixView, vRefr;\n  vPixView.xy= PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) * c_vDepthMapping;\n  float fPixZ = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV(vPixView.xy)).r;\n  fPixZ = abs( fPixZ);\n\n  // discard if background pixel\n  clip( 0.95f-fPixZ);\n\n  // apply depth-range and to view space with it\n  vPixView.z  = fPixZ *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  vPixView.xy = vPixView.xy *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vPixView.yw = float2( -vPixView.y, 1);\n  vPixView.xy = -vPixView.z* (vPixView.xy *g_vFrustumZ.xz +g_vFrustumZ.yw);\n\n  // calc distance from viewer\n  const float4 vViewPosView = float4( 0,0,0,1);\n  float fPixViewDist = max( length( vPixView.xyz) -c_fDepthOfs, 0.0f);\n\n  // determine bumps' power\n  float fBumps = c_fBumpPower;\n  fBumps *= CalcFogAmount( vPixView, vViewPosView, fPixViewDist);\n  // sample and \"unpack\" bumps\n  float4 vTexBump= texSample2D( t_sBumps, s_tBumps, PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw));\n  float2 vOffset = nor2D( vTexBump) *fBumps;\n\n  // sample depth at offset\n  vPixView.xy = (PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + vOffset) * c_vDepthMapping;\n  vPixView.z = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV(vPixView.xy)).r;\n  vPixView.z = abs( vPixView.z);\n\n  // and discard is offseted depth is nearer than original\n  clip( vPixView.z/fPixZ -0.1f);\n  \n  // calculate offseted refraction coordinates\n  float2 vRefrCoord = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + vOffset*c_vRectEdges;\n  vRefrCoord = min( vRefrCoord, c_vRectEdges);\n  // sample refraction texture\n  vRefr.rgb = texSample2D( t_sRefr, s_tRefr, MultiviewUV(vRefrCoord)).rgb;\n  vRefr.a = 1.0f;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vRefr);\n\n  // output refraction\n//vRefr.gb *= 0.75f;\n  PS_OUT( vRefr);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// HeightShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProj, 0); \n\n// vertex input(s)\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// vertex output(s)\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vClipPos, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( HeightVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // get position\n  float4 vPos = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProj);\n  // output all\n  VS_OUT_POS = VS_OUT( vClipPos) = vPos;\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// pixel input(s)\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vClipPos, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( HeightPS)\n{\n  // final output\n  float fDepth = 1.0f- (PS_IN( vClipPos.z) / PS_IN( vClipPos.w));\n  PS_OUT( float4( fDepth,fDepth,fDepth, 1));\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// HighlightShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sSrcHL, s_tSrcHL, 0);\n\n// coord clamp edges (.xy=min, .zw=max)\n_CregF( float4, c_vEdges, 0);\n// pixel size\n_CregF( float2, c_v1oPixSize, 1);\n\n// color component weights be used for luminance calculations (in RGB order)\nstatic const float3 LUM_WEIGHTS = float3( 0.2125f, 0.7154f, 0.0721f);\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// begin one light pass\nPS_ENTRY( OutlinePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // calc sample coords\n  float4 vTexCoordsLR = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy) +c_v1oPixSize.xyxy *float4(-1, 0, 1,-0); // left, right\n  float4 vTexCoordsUD = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy) +c_v1oPixSize.xyxy *float4( 0,-1, 0, 1); // up, downcenter\n  // clamp to edges\n  vTexCoordsLR = clamp( vTexCoordsLR, c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw);\n  vTexCoordsUD = clamp( vTexCoordsUD, c_vEdges.xyxy, c_vEdges.zwzw);\n  vTexCoordsLR = MultiviewUV2( vTexCoordsLR);\n  vTexCoordsUD = MultiviewUV2( vTexCoordsUD);\n\n  // sample texels\n  float4 vColA, vEdgesL, vEdgesA;\n  float2 vResLumA; // (luminosity,alpha);\n\n  // center\n  vColA = texSample2D( t_sSrcHL, s_tSrcHL, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)));\n  vResLumA = float2( dot( vColA.rgb, LUM_WEIGHTS), vColA.a);\n\n  // left\n  vColA = texSample2D( t_sSrcHL, s_tSrcHL, vTexCoordsLR.xy);\n  vEdgesL.x = dot( vColA.rgb, LUM_WEIGHTS);\n  vEdgesA.x = vColA.a;\n  // right\n  vColA = texSample2D( t_sSrcHL, s_tSrcHL, vTexCoordsLR.zw);\n  vEdgesL.y = dot( vColA.rgb, LUM_WEIGHTS);\n  vEdgesA.y = vColA.a;\n  // up\n  vColA = texSample2D( t_sSrcHL, s_tSrcHL, vTexCoordsUD.xy);\n  vEdgesL.z = dot( vColA.rgb, LUM_WEIGHTS);\n  vEdgesA.z = vColA.a;\n  // down\n  vColA = texSample2D( t_sSrcHL, s_tSrcHL, vTexCoordsUD.zw);\n  vEdgesL.w = dot( vColA.rgb, LUM_WEIGHTS);\n  vEdgesA.w = vColA.a;\n\n  // calc differences from center\n  vEdgesL -= vResLumA.x;\n  vEdgesA -= vResLumA.y;\n  // (separate for luminosity and alpha)\n  vResLumA.x = dot( abs( vEdgesL), _tcast(float4,1));\n  vResLumA.y = dot( abs( vEdgesA), _tcast(float4,1));\n\n  // if not all the same, output 1, otherwise 0\n//vResLumA.xy = step( _tcast(float2,0.01f), vResLumA.xy); // (1% tolerance; OLD VERSION)\n  vResLumA.xy = abs( vResLumA.xy);\n  vColA = vResLumA.xxxy;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vColA);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vColA);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// HighlightShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type input to tex-col pixel shader!)\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n#ifdef run_OutlineVS\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n// mapping constants\n_CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping, 5);\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,   1);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices,  2); // (matrix indices)\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,  3); // (blend weights)\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( OutlineVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // get input position\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  // skin position only (if has bones)\n  vPos.xyz = SkinVertexPos( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos);\n#endif\n\n  // and transform it to clip-space\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // transform mask texture mapping coordinates\n  // (4-component dot product: Z is 0, W is offset; cannot use Z for offset\n  //  since 2D vectors will be expanded to X,Y,0,1, and we need 1 for dot product)\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vMaskUV), c_mMaskMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.zw) = float2(0,0);\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#elif defined(run_Rect3DVS)\n\n\n// 2D rectangle mapping constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vRectMapping, 0);\n// depth of rectangle (in clip space!)\n_CregF( float3, c_vRectDepth, 1); \n// position mapping constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vPosMapping, 2);\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( Rect3DVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // construct position in clip-space\n  float2 vInPos = VS_IN( vPosition.xy);\n#if _HLSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  vInPos.y = -vInPos.y;\n#endif\n  vInPos = vInPos *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // (taking in account \"sub-drawport\"!)\n  vInPos = vInPos *c_vPosMapping.xy +c_vPosMapping.zw;\n  vInPos = vInPos *2.0f -1.0f;\n#if _HLSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  vInPos.y = -vInPos.y;\n#endif\n  float4 vOutPos;\n  vOutPos.xy = vInPos;\n  vOutPos.z = c_vRectDepth.x / c_vRectDepth.y;\n  vOutPos.w = 1.0f;\n  VS_OUT_POS = vOutPos * -c_vRectDepth.z;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n  // and pass mapping coordinates to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.xy) = VS_IN( vPosition.zw) *c_vRectMapping.xy +c_vRectMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.zw) = float2(0,0);\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(run_OverlayVS)\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n// mapping constants\n_CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping, 5);\n// extrusion max distance\n_CregF( float, c_fThickness, 7); \n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,   1);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices,  2);   // (matrix indices)\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,  3);   // (blend weights)\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( OverlayVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // get input position\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  // skin position only (if has bones)\n  vPos.xyz = SkinVertexPos( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos);\n#endif\n\n  // position to clip-space \n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // transform mask texture mapping coordinates\n  // (4-component dot product: Z is 0, W is offset; cannot use Z for offset\n  //  since 2D vectors will be expanded to X,Y,0,1, and we need 1 for dot product)\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vMaskUV), c_mMaskMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.zw) = float2(0,0);\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// MultiLayerShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/RGBEConversion.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ParallaxMapping.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sMask,     s_tMask,     0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sLightMap, s_tLightMap, 1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sShade,    s_tShade,    2);\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse1, s_tDiffuse1, 3);\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse2, s_tDiffuse2, 4);\n#if LAYERS>2\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse3, s_tDiffuse3, 5);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>3\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse4, s_tDiffuse4, 6);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>4\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse5, s_tDiffuse5, 7);\n#endif\n_Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, 8);\n_Sreg2D( t_sNormap1, s_tNormap1, 9);\n_Sreg2D( t_sNormap2, s_tNormap2, 10);\n#if LAYERS>2\n  _Sreg2D( t_sNormap3, s_tNormap3, 11);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>3\n  _Sreg2D( t_sNormap4, s_tNormap4, 12);\n#endif\n_Sreg2D( t_sNormap5, s_tNormap5, 13);\n#define t_sHeightMap t_sNormap5\n#define s_tHeightMap s_tNormap5\n\n// depth range\n_CregF( float4, c_v1oScreenAmbient, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize  = c_v1oScreenAmbient.xy;\nstatic float  c_fAmbiModulator = c_v1oScreenAmbient.z;\nstatic float  c_fMaskedSSAO    = c_v1oScreenAmbient.w;\n\n// viewer position in absolute space and HDR output normalization value\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbs, 1);\n// power of shade texture and 1st bump bias\n_CregF( float4, c_vDetailBumpBool, 2);\nstatic float c_fDetailPower = c_vDetailBumpBool.x;\nstatic float c_fLayer1Bumps = c_vDetailBumpBool.y;\n#ifdef BAKING\n  // baking? in RGBE? and/or gamma space?\n  static float c_fBakeRGBE = c_vDetailBumpBool.z;\n  static float c_fBakeGamma= c_vDetailBumpBool.w;\n#endif\n// bump biases for overlayers\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayerBumps, 3);\nstatic float c_fLayer2Bumps = c_vLayerBumps.x;\nstatic float c_fLayer3Bumps = c_vLayerBumps.y;\nstatic float c_fLayer4Bumps = c_vLayerBumps.z;\nstatic float c_fLayer5Bumps = c_vLayerBumps.w;\n\n// fading ratio and base layer max distance\n_CregF( float3, c_vLayer5DistFade, 4);\nstatic float c_fFadeRatio    = c_vLayer5DistFade.x;\nstatic float c_fLayer5Dist   = c_vLayer5DistFade.y;\nstatic float c_f1oLayer5Fade = c_vLayer5DistFade.z; // (1.0 / max_distance * fade)\n\n// max distances for overlayers (.r=2nd, .g=3rd, .b=4th, .a=5th)\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayerDistances, 5);\n// 1.0 / (max_distance * fade)\n_CregF( float4, c_v1oLayerFades, 6);\n\n// offset mapping UV-map ratio\n// (math: height & norm UV-map / other UV-map)\n_CregF( float4, c_vDif1OfsRatio, 7);\n  // (bump mapping uses const reg c8!)\n  // (parallax mapping uses const reg c9!)\n\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs,      0);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskLightUV,    1);\n  _inReg( float4, vShadeLayer1UV,  2);\n  _inReg( float4, vLayer2Layer3UV, 3);\n  _inReg( float4, vBumps1Bumps2UV, 4);\n#if LAYERS>2\n  _inReg( float4, vBumps3Bumps4UV, 5);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>3\n  _inReg( float4, vLayer4Layer5UV, 6);\n#endif\n#if defined(HAS_PARALLAX) || defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT)\n  _inReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 7);\n#endif\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// list of static variables used in program\nstatic float3 g_vNormalAbs;\nstatic float4 g_vDiffuse;\n\n\n// lambert\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  float fNdotL = saturate( dot( g_vNormalAbs, vLightDirAbs));\n  return g_vDiffuse.rgb * fNdotL;\n}\n\n\n// main pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( MultiLayerPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // calculate view distance(^2)\n  float3 vViewDirAbs = c_vViewPosAbs.xyz - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  float fPixDist2 = dot( vViewDirAbs, vViewDirAbs);\n  // and cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n\n  // first, sample mask texture\n  float4 vMask = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, PS_IN( vMaskLightUV.xy));\n\n  // now, if rendering with parallax mapping\n  float4 vLayer1Bumps1UV = float4( PS_IN( vShadeLayer1UV.zw), PS_IN( vBumps1Bumps2UV.xy));\n  #if !defined(BAKING) && defined(HAS_PARALLAX)\n\n    // calc view direction (i.e. normalize)\n    vViewDirAbs *= rsqrt( fPixDist2); // ==normalize\n    // transform view direction to tangent space\n    float3 vViewDirTan = _mulT( PS_IN( mTanToAbs), vViewDirAbs);\n    float fScaler;\n    #if LAYERS>4\n      fScaler = dot( vMask.rgba, _tcast(float4,1));\n    #elif LAYERS>3\n      fScaler = dot( vMask.rgb, _tcast(float3,1));\n    #elif LAYERS>2\n      fScaler = dot( vMask.rg, _tcast(float2,1));\n    #else\n      fScaler = vMask.r;\n    #endif\n    fScaler = saturate( 1.0f- fScaler);\n\n    // apply offset to texture coords\n    float3 vOffsetAmbDepth = GetMappingOffset( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, vLayer1Bumps1UV.zw, fScaler, vViewDirTan, fPixDist2).xyz;\n    vLayer1Bumps1UV.xy += vOffsetAmbDepth.xy * c_vDif1OfsRatio.xy;\n    vLayer1Bumps1UV.zw += vOffsetAmbDepth.xy;\n    vOffsetAmbDepth.z = lerp( 1.0f, vOffsetAmbDepth.z, fScaler);\n\n  #endif\n\n  // calculate view distance\n  float fPixDist = sqrt( fPixDist2);\n\n  // calculate distance attenuation factors\n  /* formulae:\n       a = sat( (max-dist) / (max-min));\n       min = max * (1-ratio) = max - max*ratio ->\n       a = sat( (max-dist) / (max - max + max*ratio)) \n    -> a = sat( (max-dist) / (max*ratio)) */\n\n  // fetch 1st layer diffuse texture\n  g_vDiffuse = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse1, s_tDiffuse1, vLayer1Bumps1UV.xy);\n  LinearSpace( g_vDiffuse.rgb);\n\n  // calc distance faders for overlay\n  float4 vLayersFade = saturate( (c_vLayerDistances-fPixDist) *c_v1oLayerFades);\n  // apply mask to overlays' faders\n  vLayersFade.gba *= vMask.rgb;\n\n  // prepare for layers\n  float4 vOverlay, vOverNor;\n  float3 vNormalTan;\n\n  // lerp diffuse texture to gray by distance \n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = lerp( _tcast(float3,0.5f), g_vDiffuse.rgb, vLayersFade.r);\n  // fetch 1st layer normal-map texture and attenuate bumps\n  vOverNor = texSample2D( t_sNormap1, s_tNormap1, vLayer1Bumps1UV.zw);\n  vNormalTan.xy = nor2D( vOverNor) *c_fLayer1Bumps *vLayersFade.r;\n\n  // fetch diffuse \n  vOverlay = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse2, s_tDiffuse2, PS_IN( vLayer2Layer3UV.xy));\n  LinearSpace( vOverlay.rgb);\n  vOverlay.a *= vLayersFade.g;\n  // and normal from 2nd layer \n  vOverNor = texSample2D( t_sNormap2, s_tNormap2, PS_IN( vBumps1Bumps2UV.zw));\n  vOverNor.xy = nor2D( vOverNor) *c_fLayer2Bumps;\n  // and blend those with 1st layer\n  vNormalTan.xy  = lerp( vNormalTan.xy,  vOverNor.xy,  vOverlay.aa);\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = lerp( g_vDiffuse.rgb, vOverlay.rgb, vOverlay.aaa);\n\n#if LAYERS>2\n\n  // fetch diffuse\n  vOverlay = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse3, s_tDiffuse3, PS_IN( vLayer2Layer3UV.zw));\n  LinearSpace( vOverlay.rgb);\n  vOverlay.a *= vLayersFade.b;\n  // with normal from 3rd layer\n  vOverNor = texSample2D( t_sNormap3, s_tNormap3, PS_IN( vBumps3Bumps4UV.xy));\n  vOverNor.xy = nor2D( vOverNor) *c_fLayer3Bumps;\n\n  // and blend those in\n  vNormalTan.xy  = lerp( vNormalTan.xy,  vOverNor.xy,  vOverlay.aa);\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = lerp( g_vDiffuse.rgb, vOverlay.rgb, vOverlay.aaa);\n\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>3\n\n  // fetch diffuse\n  vOverlay = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse4, s_tDiffuse4, PS_IN( vLayer4Layer5UV.xy));\n  LinearSpace( vOverlay.rgb);\n  vOverlay.a *= vLayersFade.a;\n  // with normal from 4th layer\n  vOverNor = texSample2D( t_sNormap4, s_tNormap4, PS_IN( vBumps3Bumps4UV.zw));\n  vOverNor.xy = nor2D( vOverNor) *c_fLayer4Bumps;\n\n  // and blend those in\n  vNormalTan.xy  = lerp( vNormalTan.xy,  vOverNor.xy,  vOverlay.aa);\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = lerp( g_vDiffuse.rgb, vOverlay.rgb, vOverlay.aaa);\n\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>4\n\n  // calc fading factor\n  vLayersFade.r = saturate( (c_fLayer5Dist-fPixDist) *c_f1oLayer5Fade);\n  vLayersFade.r*= vMask.a;\n\n  // fetch diffuse \n  vOverlay = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse5, s_tDiffuse5, PS_IN( vLayer4Layer5UV.zw));\n  LinearSpace( vOverlay.rgb);\n  vOverlay.a *= vLayersFade.r;\n  // with normal from 5th layer\n  vOverNor = texSample2D( t_sNormap5, s_tNormap5, PS_IN( vLayer4Layer5UV.zw));\n  vOverNor.xy = nor2D( vOverNor) *c_fLayer5Bumps;\n\n  // and blend those in\n  vNormalTan.xy  = lerp( vNormalTan.xy,  vOverNor.xy,  vOverlay.aa);\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = lerp( g_vDiffuse.rgb, vOverlay.rgb, vOverlay.aaa);\n\n#endif\n\n  // convert diffuse to gamma space\n  // (since \"blending\"-mode with shade-mask has to be done in gamma space)\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = sqrt( g_vDiffuse.rgb);\n\n  // fetch pixel from shade texture (in gamma space!)\n  float3 vShade = texSample2D( t_sShade, s_tShade, PS_IN( vShadeLayer1UV.xy)).rgb;\n  // mix it with diffuse color (in gamma space, yes!)\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb = max( _tcast(float3,0), vShade+ (g_vDiffuse.rgb-0.5f) *c_fDetailPower);\n\n  // convert diffuse texture back to linear space \n  g_vDiffuse.rgb *= g_vDiffuse.rgb;  \n\n  // construct Z of normal vector\n  vNormalTan.z = CalcNormalZ( vNormalTan.xy);\n\n#ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n\n  // transform normal from tangent to absolute space \n  g_vNormalAbs = _mulT( vNormalTan, PS_IN( mTanToAbs));\n  // and renormalize\n  g_vNormalAbs = normalize( g_vNormalAbs);\n\n#endif\n\n  // (final result)\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n\n  // if not baking\n#ifndef BAKING\n\n  // sample fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos());\n  // mask out SSAO usage (if needed)\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = saturate( vIllumAmbOccSample.a+c_fMaskedSSAO);\n  \n  // if baking\n#else  \n\n  // no FLAO texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // sample HDR lightmap\n  vOutColor.rgb = SampleRGBE( t_sLightMap, s_tLightMap, PS_IN( vMaskLightUV.zw));\n  // apply ambient modulator and ambient occlusion\n  vOutColor.rgb *= c_fAmbiModulator * vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // and add illumination (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // modulate by diffuse color (texture)\n  vOutColor *= g_vDiffuse;\n\n  // fake light direction for ambient normal-map\n  vOutColor.rgb *= CalcFakeLightModulator( vNormalTan);\n\n#else // HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // apply (shadowed) distant light\n  float3 vDistColor = DistantLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs));\n  // add to final color (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vDistColor *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // spot (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += SpotLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // omni (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += OmniLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#endif  // LIGHTS\n#if !defined(BAKING) && defined(HAS_PARALLAX)\n\n  // apply depth attenuation from height map\n  vOutColor.rgb *= GetDepthOcclusion( vOffsetAmbDepth.z);\n#endif\n\n  // if baking\n#ifdef BAKING\n\n  // in LDR\n  if( c_fBakeGamma != 0.0f) {\n\n    // apply gamma\n    vOutColor.rgb = pow( vOutColor.rgb, _tcast(float3,0.4545f));\n  }\n  // in RGBE\n  if( c_fBakeRGBE != 0.0f) {\n\n    // convert output\n    vOutColor.rgba = PackRGBE( vOutColor.rgb);\n  }\n#endif // BAKING\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// MultiLayerShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// transformation to clip, absolute or view space\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 24);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n\n// mapping matrices\n_CregM42F( c_mShadeMapping, 7);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLightMapping,  9);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayer1Mapping, 10);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayer2Mapping, 11);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayer3Mapping, 12);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayer4Mapping, 13);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLayer5Mapping, 14);\n\n// mapping masks for UV coords (select UV-map or XY, YZ or XY plane)\n_CregF( float3, c_vLayer1MappingMask, 15);\n_CregF( float3, c_vLayer2MappingMask, 16);\n_CregF( float3, c_vLayer3MappingMask, 17);\n_CregF( float3, c_vLayer4MappingMask, 18);\n_CregF( float3, c_vLayer5MappingMask, 19);\n_CregF( float3, c_vMaskMappingMask,   20);\n_CregF( float3, c_vShadeMappingMask,  21);\n\n// relative stretching factor for normal-maps\n_CregF( float4, c_vBumpsStretch, 22);\n// normal and tangent signed/unsigned masks\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorTanMask, 23);\n// (c_vObjToClipRightX uses const reg c24!)\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vTangent,  2);\n\n  _inReg( float2, vMaskUV,   3);\n  _inReg( float2, vLightUV,  4);\n  _inReg( float4, vShadeUV,  5);\n\n  _inReg( float2, vLayer1UV, 6);\n  _inReg( float2, vLayer2UV, 7);\n#if LAYERS>2\n  _inReg( float2, vLayer3UV, 8);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>3\n  _inReg( float2, vLayer4UV, 9);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>4\n  _inReg( float2, vLayer5UV, 10);\n#endif\n#ifdef BAKING\n  _inReg( float4, vBakePos,  11); // (required for lighting since baker uses uv coords as positions)\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs,      0);\n  _outReg( float4, vMaskLightUV,    1);\n  _outReg( float4, vShadeLayer1UV,  2);\n  _outReg( float4, vLayer2Layer3UV, 3);\n  _outReg( float4, vBumps1Bumps2UV, 4);\n#if LAYERS>2\n  _outReg( float4, vBumps3Bumps4UV, 5);\n#endif\n#if LAYERS>3\n  _outReg( float4, vLayer4Layer5UV, 6);\n#endif\n#ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n  _outReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 7);\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( MultiLayerVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // calc clip-space pixel position\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n#ifdef BAKING\n  // calc UV-space pixel position\n  vOutVexPosAbs = float4( mulM43F( VS_IN( vBakePos), c_mObjToAbs), 1);\n#else\n  // calc abs-space pixel position\n  vOutVexPosAbs = float4( mulM43F( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToAbs), 1);\n#endif\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n\n  // mapping masks\n  float4 vInShadeUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vShadeUV.xy), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vShadeMappingMask); \n  float2 vInLayer1UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vLayer1UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vLayer1MappingMask); \n  float2 vInLayer2UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vLayer2UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vLayer2MappingMask); \n#if LAYERS>2                                 \n  float2 vInLayer3UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vLayer3UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vLayer3MappingMask); \n#endif                                       \n#if LAYERS>3                                 \n  float2 vInLayer4UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vLayer4UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vLayer4MappingMask); \n#endif                                       \n#if LAYERS>4                                 \n  float2 vInLayer5UV = SelectUV( VS_IN( vLayer5UV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vLayer5MappingMask); \n#endif\n\n  // combine mapping coordinates\n  VS_OUT( vMaskLightUV.xy) = SelectUV( VS_IN( vMaskUV), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vMaskMappingMask); \n  VS_OUT( vMaskLightUV.zw) = VS_IN( vLightUV.xy) *c_vLightMapping.xy +c_vLightMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vShadeLayer1UV.xy) = mulM42F( vInShadeUV, c_mShadeMapping); \n\n  // 1st layer and shade\n  float2 vOutLayer1UV = vInLayer1UV *c_vLayer1Mapping.xy +c_vLayer1Mapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vShadeLayer1UV.zw) = vOutLayer1UV;\n\n  // 2nd and 3rd layers\n  float4 vOutLayer2Layer3UV;\n  vOutLayer2Layer3UV.xy = vInLayer2UV *c_vLayer2Mapping.xy +c_vLayer2Mapping.zw; \n#if LAYERS>2\n  // layer 3\n  vOutLayer2Layer3UV.zw = vInLayer3UV *c_vLayer3Mapping.xy +c_vLayer3Mapping.zw; \n#else\n  vOutLayer2Layer3UV.zw = float2(0,0);\n#endif\n  VS_OUT( vLayer2Layer3UV) = vOutLayer2Layer3UV;\n\n#if LAYERS>3\n  // layer 4\n  float2 vOutLayer4UV = vInLayer4UV *c_vLayer4Mapping.xy +c_vLayer4Mapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vLayer4Layer5UV.xy) = vOutLayer4UV;\n  #if LAYERS>4\n    // layer 5\n    VS_OUT( vLayer4Layer5UV.zw) = vInLayer5UV *c_vLayer5Mapping.xy +c_vLayer5Mapping.zw; \n  #else \n    VS_OUT( vLayer4Layer5UV.zw) = float2(0,0); \n  #endif\n#endif\n\n  // calc normal-map texture coordinates (relative to diffuse coords)\n  VS_OUT( vBumps1Bumps2UV.xy) = vOutLayer1UV *c_vBumpsStretch.xx;\n  VS_OUT( vBumps1Bumps2UV.zw) = vOutLayer2Layer3UV.xy *c_vBumpsStretch.yy;\n#if LAYERS>2\n  // for layer 3\n  VS_OUT( vBumps3Bumps4UV.xy) = vOutLayer2Layer3UV.zw *c_vBumpsStretch.zz;\n  #if LAYERS>3\n    // and 4\n    VS_OUT( vBumps3Bumps4UV.zw) = vOutLayer4UV *c_vBumpsStretch.ww;\n  #else\n    // (if any)\n    VS_OUT( vBumps3Bumps4UV.zw) = float2(0,0);\n  #endif\n#endif \n\n#ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n\n  // expand normal (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorTanMask.yyyx);\n\n  // if using planar mapping\n  float3x3 mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRot;\n  if( c_vLayer1MappingMask.z > 0.0f) {\n\n    // fix stretching on object-to-absolute space rotation matrix\n    mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n    FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n    // transform normal from object to absolute space\n    float3 vNorAbs = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRot);\n    // and construct tangent to object space plane matrix\n    mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToAbsPlaneMatrix( vNorAbs, c_vLayer1MappingMask.x);\n\n  // if using UV-mapping\n  } else {\n\n    // expand tangent (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n    float4 vTan = ExpandTangent( VS_IN( vTangent), c_vNorTanMask.wwwz);\n\n    // construct tangent to object space transformation matrix\n    mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToObjMatrix( vNor, vTan);\n    // and move tangents from object to absolute space\n    mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n  #if _GLSL\n    mObjToAbsRot = transpose( mObjToAbsRot);\n  #endif\n    // fix stretching\n    FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n\n    // move tangents from object to absolute space\n    mOutTanToAbs = _mulT( mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRot);\n  }\n  // (re)normalize rotation matrix\n  VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = NormalizeRotation( mOutTanToAbs);\n\n#endif // NEEDS_TANGENTS\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// MultiTexShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProj, 0);\n// constant color\n_CregF( float4, c_vConstColor, 4);\n\n// input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\n  _inReg( float2, vTexUV1,   1);\n  _inReg( float2, vTexUV2,   2);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vTexUVs, 0);\n  _outReg( float4, vColor,  1);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( MultiTexVS)\n{\n  // output\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProj);\n  VS_OUT( vTexUVs) = float4( VS_IN( vTexUV1), VS_IN( vTexUV2));\n  VS_OUT( vColor) =  c_vConstColor;\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse,  s_tDiffuse,  0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sModulate, s_tModulate, 1);\n\n// pixel input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexUVs, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vColor,  1);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( MultiTexPS)\n{\n  // sample textures\n  float4 vDiffuse  = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse,  s_tDiffuse,  PS_IN( vTexUVs.xy));\n  float4 vModulate = texSample2D( t_sModulate, s_tModulate, PS_IN( vTexUVs.zw));\n  vModulate.rgb *= 2.0f; // (shade blending mode!)\n  // result = modulate textures and with constant color\n  float4 vOutColor = vDiffuse * vModulate * PS_IN( vColor);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// NormalMapShader.sh\n\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// vertex constants\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClip, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vDifMapping, 4);\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorMapping, 5);\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorMask,    6);\n_CregF( float4, c_vTanMask,    7);\n\n// VS in\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos,   0);\n  _inReg( float4, vInNor,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vInTan,   2);\n  _inReg( float2, vInDifUV, 3);\n  _inReg( float2, vInNorUV, 4);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices, 5);\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights, 6);\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS out\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4,  vDifNorUV, 0);\n  _outReg( float3x3,mTanToObj, 1);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// texture metrix vertex program\nVS_ENTRY( normapVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // texture and normal map coordinates\n  VS_OUT( vDifNorUV.xy) = VS_IN( vInDifUV) *c_vDifMapping.xy +c_vDifMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vDifNorUV.zw) = VS_IN( vInNorUV) *c_vNorMapping.xy +c_vNorMapping.zw;\n\n  // normal and tangent in object space\n  float4 vPosObj = VS_IN( vInPos);\n  float3 vNorObj = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vInNor), c_vNorMask.xyxz);\n  float4 vTanObj = ExpandTangent(VS_IN( vInTan), c_vTanMask.xyxz);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  vPosObj.xyz = SkinVertexTan( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPosObj, vNorObj, vTanObj.xyz);\n#endif\n\n  // model->absolute->view->clip space transformation\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPosObj, c_mObjToClip);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n\n  VS_OUT( mTanToObj) = MakeTanToObjMatrix( vNorObj, vTanObj);\n\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // -
