- - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse,s_tDiffuse,0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sNorMap, s_tNorMap, 1);\n\n// pixel constants\n_CregM33F( c_mObjToAbs, 0);\n_CregF( float3, c_fFacingAlpha, 3);\nstatic float  c_fFacingness = c_fFacingAlpha.x;\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange = c_fFacingAlpha.yz;\n\n\n// PS in\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4,  vDifNorUV, 0);\n  _inReg( float3x3,mTanToObj, 1);\n  _inFacReg;\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// texture metrix pixel program\nPS_ENTRY( normapPS)\n{\n  float3 vNorTan;\n  float4 vNorTex = texSample2D( t_sNorMap, s_tNorMap, PS_IN( vDifNorUV.zw));\n  vNorTan = nor3D( vNorTex);\n\n  float3 vNorObj = _mulT( vNorTan, PS_IN( mTanToObj));\n  \n  //float fInPolyFace = PS_FACE * c_fFacingness;\n  //vNorObj = FlipNormal( vNorObj, fInPolyFace);\n  \n  float4 vOutNor;\n  vOutNor.xyz = mul( vNorObj, c_mObjToAbs); \n  vOutNor.xyz = normalize( vOutNor.xyz);  \n\n  vOutNor.xyz = vOutNor.xyz *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // sample and compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutNor.a = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, PS_IN( vDifNorUV.xy)).a;\n  vOutNor.a = saturate( vOutNor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n\n  PS_OUT( vOutNor);\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// OpaqueFozeShader.sh\n\n// disable if-check for fog and haze calculation\n// (those will be rendered for sure here!)\n#define NO_FOG_CHECK  1\n#define NO_HAZE_CHECK 1\n#define NO_ATMOSPHERICS_CHECK 1\n\n// handy macros\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n// fog/haze calculation functions\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Atmospherics.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADERS\n\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n\n#ifdef run_FogVS\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// fog vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( FogVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // vertex pos to clip space\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), VRRightMatrix( c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // and go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_FogVS\n#ifdef run_HazeVS\n\n\n// 2D rectangle mapping constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vDistMapping, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vClipMapping, 1);\n// depth of rectangle (in clip space!)\n_CregF( float, c_fRectDepth, 2); \n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type input to tex-col pixel shader!)\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // (rectangle map)\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( HazeVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // construct position in clip-space\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( VS_IN( vInPos.xy), c_fRectDepth, 1);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n  // and pass mapping coordinates to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.xy) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vDistMapping.xy +c_vDistMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.zw) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vClipMapping.xy +c_vClipMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_HazeVS\n#ifdef run_AtmosphericsVS\n\n\n// 2D rectangle mapping constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vDistMapping, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vClipMapping, 1);\n// depth of rectangle (in clip space!)\n_CregF( float, c_fRectDepth, 2); \n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type input to tex-col pixel shader!)\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // (rectangle map)\n  _outReg( float4, vTexCoordsClip, 1);  // (rectangle map)\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( AtmosphericsVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // construct position in clip-space\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( VS_IN( vInPos.xy), c_fRectDepth, 1);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n  // and pass mapping coordinates to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.xy) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vDistMapping.xy +c_vDistMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords.zw) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vClipMapping.xy +c_vClipMapping.zw;\n  VS_OUT( vTexCoordsClip ) = VS_IN( vInPos );\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_AtmosphericsVS\n\n                           \n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADERS\n\n\n// scene depth (normalized distance in meters)\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 0);\n\n// Z-buffer scale and offset\n_CregF( float3, c_vDepthScalerOfs, 0);\nstatic float c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepthScalerOfs.x;\nstatic float c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepthScalerOfs.y;\nstatic float c_fDepthOfs     = c_vDepthScalerOfs.z; \n// projective frustum params\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumZL, 1);\n_CregF( float4, c_vFrustumZR, 2);\n// canvas size (width and height)\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepthMapping, 3);\nstatic float2 c_v1oDepthMapping = c_vDepthMapping.xy;\nstatic float2 c_v1oDepthPixSize = c_vDepthMapping.zw;\n\n// view to absolute Y-coord transformation vector\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewToAbsY, 4);\n// fog or haze color\n_CregF( float4, c_vColFoze, 5);\n\nstatic float4 g_vFrustumZ;\n\n\n#ifdef run_HazePS\n\n\n// rectangle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// transform pixel from clip to view space and calculate distance (.x) and height (.y)\nstatic inline float2 CalcHeightDistance( in float4 vPos)\n{\n  // reconstruct center pixel position in view space\n  vPos.xy = -vPos.z* (vPos.xy *g_vFrustumZ.xz +g_vFrustumZ.yw);\n  // calc distances from viewer\n  float2 vOut;\n  vOut.x = max( length( vPos) -c_fDepthOfs, 0.0f);\n  // transform Y pixel coord from view to absolute space\n  vOut.y = dot( vPos, c_vViewToAbsY); \n  return vOut;\n}\n\n\n// screen-space haze calculation\nPS_ENTRY( HazePS) \n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustumZ = VRSelect( c_vFrustumZL, c_vFrustumZR);\n\n  // sample pixel depth and reconstruct linear depth\n  float4 vPixClip;  // (right in here!)\n  vPixClip.z = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).r;\n  vPixClip.z = DECODE_DEPTH( vPixClip.z) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  vPixClip.z = max( vPixClip.z, -9000.0f);\n  vPixClip.w = 1.0f;\n\n  // calculate pixel position in clip space \n  vPixClip.xy = PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw);\n  // and its height (in absolute space) and distance from viewer\n  float2 vPixDistAbsY = CalcHeightDistance( vPixClip);\n\n  // calculate haze amount and attenuate color and alpha by it\n  float fHazer = CalcHazeAmount( vPixDistAbsY.y, vPixDistAbsY.x);\n  float4 vHazeColor = c_vColFoze * fHazer;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vHazeColor);\n\n  // return haze color and strength (in alpha channel)\n  PS_OUT( vHazeColor);\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_HazePS\n\n#ifdef run_AtmosphericsPS\n// camera data\n_CregF( float4, c_vCamera, 18);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewRight, 19);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewUp, 20);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewFront, 21);\n_CregF( float4, c_vInvPixelSize, 22);\n\nstatic float g_fCameraHeightFromSeaLevel = c_vCamera.x;\nstatic float g_fHalfFOV = c_vCamera.y;\n\n// rectangle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoordsClip, 1);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\nfloat GetPixelDepth( float2 uv, out float fRawPivotDepth )\n{\n  float fPixClip = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( uv)).r;\n  fRawPivotDepth = fPixClip;\n  fPixClip = DECODE_DEPTH( fPixClip) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  //fPixClip = max( fPixClip, -9000.0f);\n  return abs( fPixClip );\n}\n\n// screen-space atmospherics calculation\nPS_ENTRY_2OUTS( AtmosphericsPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustumZ = VRSelect( c_vFrustumZL, c_vFrustumZR);\n\n  // sample pixel depth and reconstruct linear depth\n  float4 vPixClip;  // (right in here!)\n  vPixClip.z = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).r;\n  float fRawPivotDepth = vPixClip.z;\n  vPixClip.z = DECODE_DEPTH( vPixClip.z) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  //vPixClip.z = max( vPixClip.z, -9000.0f);\n  vPixClip.w = 1.0f;\n\n  float fPixelUpRaw;\n  float fPixelUp = GetPixelDepth( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + float2( 0, -c_vInvPixelSize.y ), fPixelUpRaw );\n\n  float fPixelDownRaw;\n  float fPixelDown = GetPixelDepth( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + float2( 0, c_vInvPixelSize.y ), fPixelDownRaw );\n\n  float fPixelLeftRaw;\n  float fPixelLeft = GetPixelDepth( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + float2( -c_vInvPixelSize.x, 0 ), fPixelLeftRaw );\n\n  float fPixelRightRaw;\n  float fPixelRight = GetPixelDepth( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + float2( c_vInvPixelSize.x, 0 ), fPixelRightRaw );\n\n  // calculate pixel position in clip space \n  vPixClip.xy = PS_IN( vTexCoordsClip.xy);\n\n  // gets direction vector over given point...\n  const float fAspect = (g_vFrustumZ.x / g_vFrustumZ.z);\n  float3 vDirection = normalize( c_vViewRight.xyz * vPixClip.x * tan( g_fHalfFOV ) + c_vViewUp.xyz * vPixClip.y * tan( g_fHalfFOV ) / fAspect - c_vViewFront.xyz );\n\n  float4 vScatteringColor, vScatteringAttenuation;\n  vScatteringColor.a = 0.0f;\n  vScatteringAttenuation.a = 1.0f;\n\n  float fMinDistance = abs( vPixClip.z );\n  if( fPixelUpRaw < 0.95f )\n    fMinDistance = min( fMinDistance, fPixelUp );\n  if( fPixelDownRaw < 0.95f )\n    fMinDistance = min( fMinDistance, fPixelDown );\n  if( fPixelLeftRaw < 0.95f )\n    fMinDistance = min( fMinDistance, fPixelLeft );\n  if( fPixelRightRaw < 0.95f )\n    fMinDistance = min( fMinDistance, fPixelRight );\n\n  const float fAtmosphereAlpha = 1 - saturate( vDirection.y / c_fBlendFactor );\n  float fst = lerp( fMinDistance, -1.0f, step( 0.95f, fRawPivotDepth ) );\n  AtmosphericScattering( float3( 0, g_fCameraHeightFromSeaLevel, 0 ),\n    vDirection, vScatteringColor.rgb, vScatteringAttenuation.rgb, fst, fAtmosphereAlpha );\n\n  if( fRawPivotDepth < 0.95f )\n  {\n    // terrain or models (foreground)\n  }\n  else\n  {\n    // atmosphere (background)\n    vScatteringColor.rgb *= fAtmosphereAlpha;\n    vScatteringAttenuation.rgb = lerp( _tcast(float3,1), vScatteringAttenuation.rgb, fAtmosphereAlpha);\n  }\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vScatteringColor );\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vScatteringAttenuation );\n\n  // return haze color and strength (in alpha channel)\n  PS_2OUTS( vScatteringColor, vScatteringAttenuation);\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_AtmosphericsPS\n\n#ifdef run_BlendHazePS\n\n\n// haze amount\n_Sreg2D( t_sHazeAmount, s_tHazeAmount, 1);\n\n// rectangle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// screen-space haze calculation\nPS_ENTRY( BlendHazePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample haze strength\n  float fHazer = texSample2D( t_sHazeAmount, s_tHazeAmount, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).b;\n  // and attenuate color and alpha by it\n  float4 vHazeColor = c_vColFoze * fHazer;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vHazeColor);\n\n  // return haze color and strength (in alpha channel)\n  PS_OUT( vHazeColor);\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_BlendHazePS\n#ifdef run_FogPS\n\n\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// screen-space fog calculation\nPS_ENTRY( FogPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vFrustumZ = VRSelect( c_vFrustumZL, c_vFrustumZR);\n\n  // convert screen coordinates to texture UV space\n  float2 vTexCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize( c_v1oDepthPixSize));\n  // sample pixel depth and reconstruct linear depth\n  float fPixelDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vTexCoord).r;\n  fPixelDepth = DECODE_DEPTH( fPixelDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  float4 vPixView;\n\n  // calc projection coords from those (adjusted for mapping!)\n  vTexCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), c_v1oDepthPixSize);\n  float2 vProjCoord = frac( vTexCoord) * c_v1oDepthMapping;\n  vProjCoord = vProjCoord *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vProjCoord.y = -vProjCoord.y;\n\n  // reconstruct current pixel position in view space\n  vPixView = float4( vProjCoord.xy, fPixelDepth, 1);\n  vPixView.xy = -vPixView.z* (vPixView.xy *g_vFrustumZ.xz +g_vFrustumZ.yw);\n\n  // calc distance from viewer\n  const float4 vViewPosView = float4( 0,0,0,1);\n  float fPixViewDist = length( vPixView.xyz);\n\n  // calc fog amount and attenuate color and alpha by it\n  float fFogger = CalcFogAmount( vPixView, vViewPosView, fPixViewDist);\n  float4 vFogColor = c_vColFoze * fFogger;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vFogColor);\n\n  // return fog color and strength (in alpha channel)\n  PS_OUT( vFogColor);\n}\n\n#endif // run_FogPS\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n\n// don't override foze checks anymore\n#undef NO_FOG_CHECK\n#undef NO_HAZE_CHECK\n#undef NO_ATMOSPHERICS_CHECK\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PlainShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeBlend.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, 0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 1);\n\n// reciprocal of depth texture dimenstions\n_CregF( float4, c_vScreenSizeDepth, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_vScreenSizeDepth.xy;\nstatic float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vScreenSizeDepth.z;\nstatic float  c_f1oDepthRange = c_vScreenSizeDepth.w;\n\n// lerp destination color dependant on the blend type\n_CregF( float4, c_vLerpDestMask, 1);\nstatic float4 c_vLerpDest = c_vLerpDestMask.xxxy;\nstatic float4 c_vLerpMask = c_vLerpDestMask.zzzw;\n// soft particle's softness factor -> 0 = sharp\n_CregF( float4, c_vAlphaSoftness, 2);\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange = c_vAlphaSoftness.xy;\nstatic float2 c_v1oSoftness = c_vAlphaSoftness.zw;\n// near clip plane\n_CregF( float, c_fNearClipPlane, 3);\n  // (fog/haze use const reg c5-c7!)\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vBaseUVFoze,    0);   // .z=fog, .w=haze amount\n  _inReg( float4, vNormalAbsDist, 1);   // .w=distance from viewer\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbsDepth,2);   // .w=oPos depth\n  _inReg( float4, vVexIllumDist,  3);   // .w=1/vertex-pivot distance\n  _inReg( float4, vVexDiffuse,    4);\n#ifdef TEX_LERP\n  _inReg( float4, vBaseUV2LerpZ,  5);  // .w=absoulte of normal Z in view space\n#else\n  _inReg( float,  fVexNorViewZ,   5);\n#endif\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// global var(s)\nstatic float3 g_vNormalAbs;\n\n\n// apply depth fading\ninline float4 DepthFade( const float4 vColor, const float4 vScreenPosDist, const float fNorViewZ)\n{\n  // sample depth texture (map to 0-1 range)\n  float fTexDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vScreenPosDist.xy).r;\n  // restore depth range\n  fTexDepth = abs( fTexDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // formula for determinig the pixel's alpha fade: A = DS * NS\n  // (DS = depth softness, NS = near softness)\n  float2 vSoftness;\n  vSoftness.x = fTexDepth - vScreenPosDist.z;\n  vSoftness.y = vScreenPosDist.z - c_fNearClipPlane;\n  vSoftness   = saturate( vSoftness *c_v1oSoftness *vScreenPosDist.w);\n  float fAlphaFader = 1.0f- (vSoftness.x * vSoftness.y);\n\n  // also apply normal softness (squared!)\n  fAlphaFader = lerp( 1.0f, fAlphaFader, saturate( fNorViewZ*fNorViewZ));\n\n  // and finaly, apply blending\n  return lerp( vColor, c_vLerpDest, c_vLerpMask*fAlphaFader);\n}\n\n\n// lambert\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  // simple as it is!\n  float fLightness = saturate( dot( g_vNormalAbs, vLightDirAbs));\n  return _tcast( float3, fLightness);\n}\n\n\n// MAIN RENDERING PASS\n\nPS_ENTRY( PlainPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // get interpolated normal\n  g_vNormalAbs = PS_IN( vNormalAbsDist.xyz);  // renormalized?\n  // and cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n\n  // final result starts with vertex color\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( PS_IN( vVexIllumDist.rgb), 1);\n\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // do complete per-pixel distant light\n  float4 vPixPosAbs = float4( PS_IN( vVexPosAbsDepth.xyz), 1.0f);\n  vOutColor.rgb += DistantLight( vPixPosAbs);\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // spot\n  float4 vPixPosAbs = float4( PS_IN( vVexPosAbsDepth.xyz), 1.0f);\n  vOutColor.rgb += SpotLight( vPixPosAbs);\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // omni\n  float4 vPixPosAbs = float4( PS_IN( vVexPosAbsDepth.xyz), 1.0f);\n  vOutColor.rgb += OmniLight( vPixPosAbs);\n\n#endif // LIGHTS\n\n  // sample diffuse texture \n  float4 vDiffuse = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, PS_IN( vBaseUVFoze.xy));\n  LinearSpace( vDiffuse.rgb);\n#ifdef TEX_LERP\n  // sample 2nd diffuse texture \n  float4 vDiff2 = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, PS_IN( vBaseUV2LerpZ.xy));\n  LinearSpace( vDiff2.rgb);\n  // and lerp between them\n  vDiffuse = lerp( vDiffuse, vDiff2, PS_IN( vBaseUV2LerpZ.z));\n#endif\n  // and vertex color\n  vDiffuse *= PS_IN( vVexDiffuse);\n\n  // modulate lighting by diffuse\n  vOutColor *= vDiffuse;\n\n  // and apply depth fading\n  float4 vScreenPosDist = float4( GetRasterClipPos(), PS_IN( vVexPosAbsDepth.w), PS_IN( vVexIllumDist.w));\n  #ifdef TEX_LERP\n    float fNorZ = PS_IN( vBaseUV2LerpZ.w); \n  #else\n    float fNorZ = PS_IN( fVexNorViewZ); \n  #endif\n  vOutColor = DepthFade( vOutColor, vScreenPosDist, fNorZ);\n\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, PS_IN( vBaseUVFoze.zw));\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PlainShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// world to clip space matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mAbsToClipLeft, 0);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n// object to view (eye) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToView, 7);\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n// view to absolute space transformation matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mViewToAbs, 14);\n\n// color and illum map arrays masks and relative pivots\n_CregF( float4, c_vColorIllumPivotMasks, 17);\nstatic float2 c_vColorMapMask = c_vColorIllumPivotMasks.xy; // (0,1 or 1,0)\nstatic float  c_fIllumMapMask = c_vColorIllumPivotMasks.z;  // (0 or 1)\nstatic float  c_fRelPivots    = c_vColorIllumPivotMasks.w;  // (0 or 1)\n\n// model stretch\n_CregF( float3, c_vStretchNorLerp, 18);\nstatic float2 c_vStretch = c_vStretchNorLerp.xy;\nstatic float  c_fNorLerp = c_vStretchNorLerp.z;\n\n// mask for constant normals (0001 for vertex or xyz1 for constant)\n_CregF( float4, c_vNormalMask, 19);\n// viewer position\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbs, 20);\n\n// constant color for ambient (includes illumination!)\n_CregF( float4, c_vColAmbientBool, 21);\nstatic float3 c_vColAmbient = c_vColAmbientBool.xyz;\n// polygons should be rendered in face-forward mode?\nstatic float c_fFaceForward = c_vColAmbientBool.w;\n\n// constant diffuse color\n_CregF( float4, c_vColDiffuse, 22);\n// object-to-view rotation matrix 3rd row (Z)\n_CregF( float3, c_vObjToViewRotZ, 23);\n// diffuse mapping constant\n_CregM42F( c_mDiffuseMapping, 24);\n// other VR eye projection X row\n_CregF( float4, c_vAbsToClipRightX, 26);\n\n// (shadow is in c32-c49!)\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vPosPivot, 1);\n  _inReg( float4, vDiffuseUV,2);\n  _inReg( float4, vColorMap, 3);\n  _inReg( float4, vIllumMap, 4);  // RGBE!\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   5);\n#ifdef TEX_LERP\n  _inReg( float4, vDiffUV2,  6);\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vBaseUVFoze,    0);   // .z=fog, .w=haze amount\n  _outReg( float4, vNormalAbsDist, 1);   // .w=distance from viewer\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbsDepth,2);   // .w=oPos depth\n  _outReg( float4, vVexIllumDist,  3);   // .w=1/vertex-pivot distance\n  _outReg( float4, vVexDiffuse,    4);\n#ifdef TEX_LERP\n  _outReg( float4, vBaseUV2LerpZ,  5);\n#else\n  _outReg( float,  fVexNorViewZ,   5);\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( PlainVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // use input normal or up-normal\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNormalMask.xyzw);\n\n  // pivot position in absolute space\n  float4 vInPivot = VS_IN( vPosPivot) + VS_IN( vPosition) *c_fRelPivots;\n  float3 vPivotPosAbs = mulM43F( vInPivot, c_mObjToAbs);\n\n  // if face-forward mode\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n  if( c_fFaceForward != 0.0f) {\n\n    // calc pivot pos in view space\n    float3 vPosInView = mulM43F( vInPivot, c_mObjToView);\n\n    // offset pivot pos by face-forward vectors\n    float3 vSize = VS_IN( vPosition.xyz) - vInPivot.xyz;\n    float2 vStretch = vSize.xy * c_vStretch;\n    vPosInView.xy += vStretch;\n    /* WAS:\n    const float3 vSize  = VS_IN( vPosition.xyz) - vInPivot.xyz;\n    const float3 vUp    = float3(0,1,0);\n    const float3 vRight = float3(1,0,0);\n    vPosInView +=    vUp*vSize.y * c_vStretch.y;\n    vPosInView += vRight*vSize.x * c_vStretch.x;\n    */\n\n    // http://mathworld.wolfram.com/RodriguesRotationFormula.html\n    // get both pivot and vertex pos in abs space\n    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( float4( vPosInView,1), c_mViewToAbs);\n\n    // get billboard rotation matrix\n    float3 vPosDeltaDir = vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - vPivotPosAbs;\n    float3 vAxis = cross( vSize, vPosDeltaDir);\n    float fCos = dot( vSize, vPosDeltaDir);\n    float fSin = length( vAxis);\n    vAxis /= fSin;\n    float f1mCos = 1.0f - fCos;\n    float3x3 mRotation = float3x3(\n               fCos+ vAxis.x*vAxis.x*f1mCos, -vAxis.z*fSin+ vAxis.x*vAxis.y*f1mCos,  vAxis.y*fSin+ vAxis.x*vAxis.z*f1mCos,\n       vAxis.z*fSin+ vAxis.x*vAxis.y*f1mCos,          fCos+ vAxis.y*vAxis.y*f1mCos, -vAxis.x*fSin+ vAxis.y*vAxis.z*f1mCos,\n      -vAxis.y*fSin+ vAxis.x*vAxis.z*f1mCos,  vAxis.x*fSin+ vAxis.y*vAxis.z*f1mCos,          fCos+ vAxis.z*vAxis.z*f1mCos);\n    // rotate normal in same direction billboard is facing\n    vNor = mul( mRotation, vNor);\n\n  // regular position otherwise\n  } else {\n\n    // vertex position to absolute space\n    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToAbs);\n  }\n\n  // (output vertex position in absolute space)\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbsDepth.xyz) = vOutVexPosAbs.xyz;\n\n  // calc pixel position in abs space\n  float4 vOutPosLeft = mul( vOutVexPosAbs, c_mAbsToClipLeft);\n  float4 vOutPosRight = mul( vOutVexPosAbs, VRRightMatrix(c_mAbsToClipLeft, c_vAbsToClipRightX));\n  VS_OUT_POS = vOutPosLeft;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = vOutPosRight;\n  // and transform normal to absolute space, also\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n  VS_OUT( vNormalAbsDist.xyz) = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRot);\n\n  // first (or only) diffuse texture UV coords\n  VS_OUT( vBaseUVFoze.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vDiffuseUV), c_mDiffuseMapping);\n  // current pixel's W value for depth comparison (smoothness)\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbsDepth.w) = vOutPosLeft.w;\n\n  // calculate (and attenuate) normal Z in view space\n  float fNorViewZ = dot( vNor, c_vObjToViewRotZ);\n  fNorViewZ = lerp( abs( fNorViewZ), 1.0f, c_fNorLerp);\n\n#ifdef TEX_LERP\n  // output 2nd UV coords (along with lerp factor!)\n  VS_OUT( vBaseUV2LerpZ.xy) = mulM42F( float4( VS_IN( vDiffUV2.xy),0,1), c_mDiffuseMapping);\n  VS_OUT( vBaseUV2LerpZ.z)  = VS_IN( vDiffUV2.z);\n  // and squeeze normal Z in, also\n  VS_OUT( vBaseUV2LerpZ.w) = fNorViewZ;\n#else\n  VS_OUT( fVexNorViewZ) = fNorViewZ;\n#endif\n\n  // fetch color map array (if bound)\n  float4 vOutVexDiffuse = VS_IN( vColorMap);\n  vOutVexDiffuse = vOutVexDiffuse *c_vColorMapMask.xxxx +c_vColorMapMask.yyyy;\n  // modulate by constant diffuse color\n  vOutVexDiffuse *= c_vColDiffuse;\n  // convert to linear space\n  vOutVexDiffuse.rgb *= vOutVexDiffuse.rgb;\n  // and output to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vVexDiffuse) = vOutVexDiffuse;\n\n  // fetch illumination map array (if bound) and add ambient to it\n  float4 vVexIllum = VS_IN( vIllumMap);\n  VS_OUT( vVexIllumDist.rgb) = UnpackRGBE( vVexIllum) *c_fIllumMapMask +c_vColAmbient;\n\n  // calculate fog and haze amount\n  float3 vVexDist = vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - c_vViewPosAbs.xyz;\n  float fOutNorAbsDist = length( vVexDist); // (via precached vertex-viewer distance)\n  VS_OUT( vBaseUVFoze.z) = CalcFogAmount( vOutVexPosAbs, c_vViewPosAbs, fOutNorAbsDist);\n  VS_OUT( vBaseUVFoze.w) = CalcHazeAmount( vOutVexPosAbs.y, fOutNorAbsDist);\n  VS_OUT( vNormalAbsDist.w) = fOutNorAbsDist;\n\n  // calc vertex-pivot distance\n  float fVtxPvtDist = length( vPivotPosAbs - vOutVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  VS_OUT( vVexIllumDist.w) = 1.0f / lerp( 1.0f, fVtxPvtDist, min( fVtxPvtDist, 1.0f));\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PostProcessingEffects.psh\n\n\n// handy macros\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// if blur samples are not defined\n#ifndef BLUR_SAMPLES\n  // no blurring\n  #define BLUR_SAMPLES 1\n#endif\n\n// original texture (destination)\n_Sreg2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, 0);   \n\n// various constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vSampleStep,  0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vBlurFactors, 1);\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolModulate, 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vSampleRect,  3);\n_CregF( float3, c_vDepthRangeMultiview,  4);\nstatic float c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepthRangeMultiview.x;\nstatic float c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepthRangeMultiview.y;\nstatic float c_fOriginalMultiview = c_vDepthRangeMultiview.z;\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy), bloom (.zw)\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n// (to keep GLSL happy)\nstatic const float g_fBlurSamples = float(BLUR_SAMPLES);\n\n\n// get randomize factor based on coords\ninline float Randomizer( in float2 vCoords)\n{\n//vCoords = floor( vCoords*256) / 256;\n  float fFactor = dot( vCoords, float2( 12.9898f,78.233f));\n  fFactor = sin( fFactor);\n  fFactor = frac( fFactor *43758.5453f);\n  return fFactor;\n}\n\n\n// --- GAUSSIAN BLUR\n\n\n#ifdef run_GaussianBlurPS\n\n\n// gaussian factors\nstatic float c_f1o2Dev2      = c_vBlurFactors.x;\nstatic float c_f1oSqrtPiDev  = c_vBlurFactors.y; // (normalization already inside!)\n\n\n// calc gaussian factor from a distance\ninline float CalcGaussianFactor( const float fDist, const float fDevAdj)\n{\n  // f = (e^(-x^2 / (2d^2)) / sqrt( PI*2d^2)\n  return exp( fDist*fDist *fDevAdj); // (w/o *c_f1oSqrtPiDev, will divide after accumulation!)\n}\n\n// calc two gaussian factor from two distances\ninline float2 CalcGaussianFactors( const float2 vDist, const float fDevAdj)\n{\n  // f = (e^(-x^2 / (2d^2)) / sqrt( PI*2d^2)\n  return exp( vDist*vDist *fDevAdj); // (w/o *c_f1oSqrtPiDev, will divide after accumulation!)\n}\n\n\n/// Performs a gaussian blur on the source.\nPS_ENTRY( GaussianBlurPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample center pixel (will be weighted after accumulation)\n  float4 vMultiviewMAD = MultiviewMAD(c_fOriginalMultiview);\n  float4 vTotalCol = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw);\n  vTotalCol = min( vTotalCol, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  float4 vSample; \n\n#ifdef BILINEAR_GAUSSIAN \n  \n  // prepare for loop\n  float2 vDistances = float2( 1, 2);\n  float2 vPixelCoord = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy);\n\n  // loop thru pixels\n  _unroll while( vDistances.x < g_fBlurSamples) {\n\n    // calculate two gaussian factors for two sample pairs\n    float2 vFactors = CalcGaussianFactors( vDistances, c_f1o2Dev2);\n\n    // calculate sampling coordinate for bilinear\n    float fBothFactors = vFactors.x + vFactors.y;\n    vFactors.y /= fBothFactors;\n    // and incorporate sample distance from center pixel into it\n    vFactors.y += vDistances.x;\n\n    // generate coordinates of next sample pairs\n    float4 vSampleCoordRL = vPixelCoord.xyxy+ c_vSampleStep.xyxy* float4( vFactors.yy, -vFactors.yy);\n    // clamp those coordinates\n    vSampleCoordRL = clamp( vSampleCoordRL, c_vSampleRect.xyxy, c_vSampleRect.zwzw);\n\n    // sample X-axis or Y-axis surrounding pixels\n    vSample  = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordRL.xy * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw);\n    vSample += texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordRL.zw * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw);\n    vSample  = min( vSample, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n    // add them to total attenuated by gaussian factor\n    vTotalCol += vSample *fBothFactors; \n\n    // move to next two outer sample pairs\n    vDistances += 2.0f;\n  }\n  // and not blurred entirely\n#ifdef MORE_SAMPLES\n\n  // loop thru rest of pixels\n  float4 vSampleCoordLR;\n  while( vDistances.x < c_vSampleStep.z)  {\n\n    // calculate two gaussian factors for two sample pairs\n    float2 vFactors = CalcGaussianFactors( vDistances, c_f1o2Dev2);\n\n    // calculate sampling coordinate for bilinear\n    float fBothFactors = vFactors.x + vFactors.y;\n    vFactors.y /= fBothFactors;\n    // and incorporate sample distance from center pixel into it\n    vFactors.y += vDistances.x;\n\n    // generate coordinates of next sample pairs\n    vSampleCoordLR = vPixelCoord.xyxy+ c_vSampleStep.xyxy *float4( vFactors.yy,-vFactors.yy);\n    // clamp those coordinates\n    vSampleCoordLR = clamp( vSampleCoordLR, c_vSampleRect.xyxy, c_vSampleRect.zwzw);\n\n    // sample X-axis or Y-axis surrounding pixels\n    vSample  = texLod2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordLR.xy * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw, 0.0f);\n    vSample += texLod2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordLR.zw * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw, 0.0f);\n    vSample  = min( vSample, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n    // add them to total attenuated by gaussian factor\n    vTotalCol += vSample *fBothFactors;\n\n    // move to next two outer sample pairs\n    vDistances += 2.0f;\n  }\n#endif // MORE_SAMPLES\n\n#else // BILINEAR_GAUSSIAN\n\n  // prepare for loop\n  float4 vCoordRL = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy);  // R=.xy, L=.zw\n  float4 vSampleStepRL = c_vSampleStep.xyxy *float4( 1,1,-1,-1);\n  float fDistance = 1.0f;\n\n  // loop thru pixels\n  _unroll while( fDistance <= g_fBlurSamples) {\n\n    // generate coordinates of next sample pairs\n    vCoordRL += vSampleStepRL;\n    // clamp those coordinates\n    vCoordRL = clamp( vCoordRL, c_vSampleRect.xyxy, c_vSampleRect.zwzw);\n\n    // sample X-axis or Y-axis surrounding pixels\n    vSample  = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vCoordRL.xy * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw);\n    vSample += texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vCoordRL.zw * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw);\n    vSample  = min( vSample, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n    // add them to total attenuated by gaussian factor\n    vTotalCol += vSample * CalcGaussianFactor( fDistance, c_f1o2Dev2);\n\n    // move to outer sample pairs\n    fDistance += 1.0f;\n  }\n  // and not blurred entirely\n#ifdef MORE_SAMPLES\n\n  // loop thru rest of pixels\n  while( fDistance <= c_vSampleStep.z)  {\n\n    // generate coordinates of next sample pairs\n    vCoordRL += vSampleStepRL;\n    // clamp those coordinates\n    vCoordRL = clamp( vCoordRL, c_vSampleRect.xyxy, c_vSampleRect.zwzw);\n\n    // sample X-axis or Y-axis surrounding pixels\n    vSample  = texLod2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vCoordRL.xy * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw, 0.0f);\n    vSample += texLod2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vCoordRL.zw * vMultiviewMAD.xy + vMultiviewMAD.zw, 0.0f);\n    vSample  = min( vSample, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n    // add them to total attenuated by gaussian factor\n    vTotalCol += vSample * CalcGaussianFactor( fDistance, c_f1o2Dev2);\n\n    // move to outer sample pairs\n    fDistance++;\n  }\n#endif // MORE_SAMPLES\n  \n#endif // BILINEAR_GAUSSIAN\n\n  // do final average\n  vTotalCol *= c_f1oSqrtPiDev;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vTotalCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vTotalCol);\n}\n\n#else // run_GaussianBlurPS\n\n// depth info for depth blur effect\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 1);   \n\n#endif\n\n\n\n// --- DEPTH OF FIELD\n\n\n// some constants for DoF\n#define MAX_DEVIATION 5.0f  // i.e. blur radius\n#define MAX_KERNEL_SIZE 10 // == MAX_DEVIATION*2\nstatic const float c_fSqrt2PI = 2.5f; // == sqrt(2.0f*PI)\n\n// DoF factors\nstatic float c_fFocalDist    = c_vBlurFactors.x;\nstatic float c_fApertureSize = c_vBlurFactors.y;\n\n\n/// Calculate normalized gaussian factor at given offset, for given standard deviation. \n/** The normalization makes the integral of this function over the entire domain equal unity. */\ninline float NormalizedGaussianFactor( const float fX, const float fDev)\n{\n  // phi(x, t) = exp(-x^2/(2*t^2)) / (t*sqrt(2*pi))\n  return exp( -(fX*fX) / (2.0f*fDev*fDev)) / (fDev*c_fSqrt2PI);\n}\n\n// (vectorized version)\ninline float2 NormalizedGaussianFactor2( const float fX, const float2 vDev)\n{\n  return exp( -(fX*fX) / (2.0f*vDev*vDev)) / (vDev*c_fSqrt2PI);\n}\n\n\n/// Convert object distance to the circle-of-confusion radius to be used by gaussian blur.\ninline float CocRadius( float fZ)\n{\n  // calculate the circle of confusion radius in pixels\n  float fCocR = c_fApertureSize * (1.0f-c_fFocalDist/fZ);\n  // make sure it doesn't overflow the maximum blur kernel\n  return clamp( fCocR, -MAX_DEVIATION, MAX_DEVIATION);\n}\n\n// (vectorized version)\ninline float4 CocRadius4( float4 vZ)\n{\n  // calculate the circle of confusion radius in pixels\n  float4 vCocR = c_fApertureSize * (1.0f-c_fFocalDist/vZ);\n  // make sure it doesn't overflow the maximum blur kernel\n  return clamp( vCocR, -MAX_DEVIATION, MAX_DEVIATION);\n}\n\n#ifdef run_DepthDownsamplePS\n\n\n/// Performs a distance blur on the source.\nPS_ENTRY( DepthDownsamplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // (circle of confusion)\n  float fCocR;\n\n#if 1\n\n  // sample pixel depths\n  float4 vPixDepths;\n\n  // 4 of them, one-by-one\n  float4 vDepthCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords.zwzw)+ c_vSampleStep.xyxy*float4(-0.5f,-0.5f, 0.5f,0.5f);\n  vDepthCoords = MultiviewUV2( vDepthCoords);\n  vPixDepths.x = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoords.xy).r;\n  vPixDepths.y = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoords.zy).r;\n  vPixDepths.z = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoords.xw).r;\n  vPixDepths.w = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoords.zw).r;\n\n  // and \"unpack\" those depths\n  vPixDepths = abs( vPixDepths) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // calculate circle-of-confusions\n  float4 vCocRs = CocRadius4( vPixDepths);\n  // and find maxumum (average is no good when sign is different)\n  vCocRs.xy = max( vCocRs.xy, vCocRs.zw);\n  fCocR = max( vCocRs.x, vCocRs.y);\n\n#else // 0\n\n  float fPixDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw))).r;\n  fPixDepth = abs( fPixDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  fCocR = CocRadius( fPixDepth);\n\n#endif // 1/0\n\n  // sample center pixel\n  float4 vCentral;\n  vCentral.rgb = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy))).rgb;\n\n  // store (signed!) circle-of-confusion in alpha\n  fCocR = (fCocR/MAX_DEVIATION) *0.5f +0.5f;\n  vCentral.a = saturate( fCocR);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vCentral);\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_DepthDownsamplePS\n#ifdef run_DepthBlendPS\n\n\n/// Performs a distance blur on the source.\nPS_ENTRY( DepthBlendPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // fetch downsampled texel\n  float4 vInTexCoords = MultiviewUV2( PS_IN( vTexCoords));\n  float4 vDownsampled = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vInTexCoords.xy);\n#if 1\n  // calculate circle-of-confusion\n  float fPixDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vInTexCoords.zw).r;\n  fPixDepth = abs( fPixDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n  float fCocR = CocRadius( fPixDepth);\n  vDownsampled.a = abs( fCocR);\n#else // 0\n  // unpack circle-of-confusion stored in alpha\n  // (not quite good because of aliasing artefacts on the depth edges!)\n  vDownsampled.a = abs( vDownsampled.a *2.0f -1.0f);\n  vDownsampled.a *= MAX_DEVIATION;\n#endif // 1/0\n  vDownsampled.a = saturate( vDownsampled.a);\n  PS_OUT( vDownsampled);\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_DepthBlendPS\n#ifdef run_DepthBlurPS\n\n\n/// Performs a distance blur on the source.\nPS_ENTRY( DepthBlurPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // sample center pixel (clamped to HDR max value)\n  float4 vTotalColor = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)));\n\n//return vTotalColor;\n\n  // get circle-of-confusion\n  float4 vCocRs; //.xy = sample, .z=pivot, .w=pivot_abs_clamped\n  vCocRs.z = (vTotalColor.a *2.0f -1.0f) *MAX_DEVIATION;\n  vCocRs.w = max( abs( vCocRs.z), 0.001f);\n\n  // and calculate weight from it\n  float fTotalWeight = 1.0f / (vCocRs.w * c_fSqrt2PI);\n\n  // prepare for loop\n  float4 vSampleStepRL = c_vSampleStep.xyxy *float4( 1,1,-1,-1);\n  float4 vTexCoordsRL = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xyxy);  // R=.xy, L=.zw\n\n  // apply weight to it and accumulate for total\n  vTotalColor.rgb *= fTotalWeight;\n\n  // loop thru surrounding pixels\n#ifndef DOF_EARLY_OUT\n  _unroll for( int iSample=1; iSample<MAX_KERNEL_SIZE; iSample++) {\n#else\n  int iSample = 1;\n  _loop while( iSample < MAX_KERNEL_SIZE) {\n#endif\n    // calc surrounding texture coords\n    vTexCoordsRL += vSampleStepRL;\n    // clamp those coordinates\n    float4 vSampleCoordRL = clamp( vTexCoordsRL, c_vSampleRect.xyxy, c_vSampleRect.zwzw);\n    vSampleCoordRL = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoordRL);\n\n    // sample surrounding pixels\n  #ifndef DOF_EARLY_OUT\n    float4 vSampleL = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordRL.xy);\n    float4 vSampleR = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordRL.zw);\n  #else\n    float4 vSampleL = texLod2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordRL.xy, 0.0f);\n    float4 vSampleR = texLod2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordRL.zw, 0.0f);\n  #endif\n\n    // unpack CoCs from samples' alpha channels\n    vCocRs.xy = float2( vSampleL.a, vSampleR.a);\n    vCocRs.xy = (vCocRs.xy *2.0f -1.0f) *MAX_DEVIATION;\n    // use minimum distance between center and side pixel gives the proper effect\n    // that the farther objects never blur over nearer objects\n    vCocRs.xy = min( vCocRs.xy, vCocRs.zz);\n    // (clamp absolute of CoCs to avoid division by zero)\n    vCocRs.xy = max( abs( vCocRs.xy), _tcast(float2,0.001f));\n    // calculate blur weights based on stored circle-of-confusions\n    float2 vWeights2 = NormalizedGaussianFactor2( float(iSample), vCocRs.xy);\n\n    // accumulate weighted colors \n    vTotalColor.rgb += vSampleL.rgb*vWeights2.xxx + vSampleR.rgb*vWeights2.yyy;\n    // and weights themselves\n    float fWeights = vWeights2.x + vWeights2.y;\n    fTotalWeight += fWeights;\n\n  #ifdef DOF_EARLY_OUT\n\n    // if this weight is too low, signal loop exit\n    iSample += (fWeights>=0.0001f) ? 1 : MAX_KERNEL_SIZE;\n  #endif\n  }\n  // average by weight\n  vTotalColor.rgb /= fTotalWeight;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vTotalColor);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vTotalColor);\n}\n\n#endif // run_DepthBlurPS\n\n\n// --- LIGHT STREAKS (a.k.a. God Rays)\n\n\n#ifdef run_LightStreaksPS\n\n\n// light streaks constants\nstatic float3 c_vLightPos = c_vSampleStep.xyz;\nstatic float2 c_vRaysDith = c_vBlurFactors.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vDepthMap = c_vBlurFactors.zw;\nstatic float  c_fRaysLen  = c_vcolModulate.w;\n\n#ifndef NUM_RAY_SAMPLES\n  #define NUM_RAY_SAMPLES 35\n#endif\n#define RAY_DECAY 0.95f\n\n\n/// Applies god rays over the source.\nPS_ENTRY( LightStreaksPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // calculate vector from pixel to light source on the screen\n  float4 vSampleCoord, vDeltaCoord;  // (.xy=color, .zw=depth)\n  vSampleCoord.xy = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy);\n  vDeltaCoord.xy  = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) - c_vLightPos.xy;\n  // divide by number of samples and scale by control factor\n  vDeltaCoord.xy *= 1.0f / float(NUM_RAY_SAMPLES) *c_fRaysLen;\n  vDeltaCoord.xy *= Randomizer( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)) *c_vRaysDith.x +c_vRaysDith.y;\n  // readjust coords for depth sampling\n  vSampleCoord.zw = vSampleCoord.xy *c_vDepthMap;\n  vDeltaCoord.zw  = vDeltaCoord.xy  *c_vDepthMap;\n\n  // initial illumination decay and accumulated color\n  float  fSampleDepth, fIllumDecay=1.0f;\n  float4 vTotalColor = _tcast( float4, 0);\n  float3 vSampleColor;\n\n  // loop thru samples and accumulate\n  _unroll for( int i=0; i<NUM_RAY_SAMPLES; i++) {\n\n    // next coord and sample\n    vSampleCoord -= vDeltaCoord;\n    float4 vSampleCoordMV = MultiviewUV2( vSampleCoord);\n    vSampleColor = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vSampleCoordMV.xy).rgb;\n    fSampleDepth = texLod2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vSampleCoordMV.zw, 2.0f).r;\n    fSampleDepth = abs( fSampleDepth);\n\n    // mask out pixel that are nearer than light source\n    vSampleColor.rgb *= step( c_vLightPos.z, fSampleDepth);\n    // attenuate\n    vSampleColor.rgb *= fIllumDecay;\n    // accumulate\n    vTotalColor.rgb += vSampleColor.rgb;\n    // update decay\n    fIllumDecay *= RAY_DECAY;\n  }\n  // and finally, do exposure correction\n  vTotalColor.rgb *= c_vcolModulate.rgb;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vTotalColor);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vTotalColor);\n}\n\n#endif // run_LightStreaksPS\n\n\n// --- COMBINE FRAMES FOR MOTION BLUR\n\n#ifdef run_MotionBlurBlendPS\n\n// output input texture's color channel and constant in alpha\nPS_ENTRY( MotionBlurBlendPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  float4 vRes;\n  float4 vInTexCoords = MultiviewUV2( PS_IN( vTexCoords)); \n  vRes.rgb = texSample2D( t_sOriginal, s_tOriginal, vInTexCoords.xy).rgb;\n  // (constant comes from vertex shader to avoid constant register uploading in pixel shader)\n  vRes.a = vInTexCoords.z; \n  PS_OUT( vRes);\n}\n\n#endif // run_AddTexturesPSPS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PPDownsampleShaders.psh\n\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0);  // (copy of the back buffer)\n#ifdef DEPTHSIGN_TO_ALPHA\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDistance, s_tDistance, 1);  // (distance buffer)\n#endif\n\n// lower-right edge of downsampling rectangle\n_CregF( float2, c_vSampleEdgeDS, 0);\n\n#if _HLSL\n\n  // sampling pixel offsets\n  const uniform float2 c_avSampleOffsetsDS[ FILTER_SAMPLES] : register(c1);\n  // and theirs fetching function\n  static inline float2 _getSampleOffset( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avSampleOffsetsDS[ iIndex];\n  }\n#elif _GLSL\n\n  // sampling pixel offset fetching function\n  static inline float2 _getSampleOffset( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avUniformsF[ iIndex+1].xy;\n  }\n#endif // API\n\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy), depth/bloom (.zw)\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n#ifdef run_DownsamplePS\n\n\n/// Pixel program that downsamples the input texture to one four times smaller.\nPS_ENTRY( DownsamplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample the area around the given pixel\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( 0,0,0, 0); // (result)\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<FILTER_SAMPLES; iSample++) {\n\n    // (sample by sample)\n    float2 vUV = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + _getSampleOffset( iSample);\n    vUV = min( vUV, c_vSampleEdgeDS);\n    // accumulating result\n    vOutCol += texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vUV));\n  }\n  // calc average of accumulated samples\n  vOutCol /= float(FILTER_SAMPLES);\n\n#ifdef DEPTHSIGN_TO_ALPHA\n\n  // flag alpha for negative depth value\n  float fDepth = texSample2D( t_sDistance, s_tDistance, MultiviewUV(PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw))).r;\n  vOutCol.a = (fDepth>=0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f;\n\n#endif\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // return average luminance of all samples\n  vOutCol = min( vOutCol, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_DownsamplePS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PPFinalPassShaders.psh\n\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0); // (copy of the back buffer)\n#ifndef run_SimplePostprocessPS\n  _Sreg2D( t_sLuminance, s_tLuminance, 1); // (currently calculated luminance)\n  #ifdef BLOOM\n    _Sreg2D( t_sBloom, s_tBloom, 2); // (bloom texture)\n  #endif\n  #ifdef COLOR_RAMP\n    _Sreg2D( t_sColorRamp, s_tColorRamp, 3); // (for color remapping)\n  #endif\n  #ifdef LENS_DIRT\n    _Sreg2D( t_sLensDirt, s_tLensDirt, 4); // (lens dirt texture)\n    _Sreg2D( t_sLumaDS,   s_tLumaDS,   5); // (downsampled luminosity texture)\n    #define LUMA_DS_DIM 64.0f // (LumaDS is 64x64 texture)\n  #endif\n#endif\n\n// constant registers\n\n// bloom effect\n_CregF( float4, c_vBloomLum, 0);\nstatic float  c_fFixedExposure   = c_vBloomLum.x;  // (HDR output denormalization value inside!)\nstatic float  c_fBloomMultiplier = c_vBloomLum.y;\nstatic float2 c_vBloomTexSize    = c_vBloomLum.zw;\n// gamma, brightness and constrast\n_CregF( float4, c_vGammaRamp, 1);\nstatic float c_fInvGamma    = c_vGammaRamp.x;\nstatic float c_fSaturation  = c_vGammaRamp.y;\nstatic float c_fLightness   = c_vGammaRamp.z;\nstatic float c_fLightTarget = c_vGammaRamp.w;\n// lens dirt params\n_CregF( float3, c_vLensDirt, 2);\nstatic float c_fLensDirtStrength = c_vLensDirt.x;\nstatic float c_fLensDirtTreshold = c_vLensDirt.y;\nstatic float c_f1oLensDirtRange  = c_vLensDirt.z;\n// screen pixel size and levels\n_CregF( float4, c_vScrSizeLvl, 3);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScrSize = c_vScrSizeLvl.xy;\nstatic float  c_fLevels    = c_vScrSizeLvl.z;\nstatic float  c_f1oLevels  = c_vScrSizeLvl.w;\n// global gamma, brighntess, contrast, saturation\n_CregF( float4, c_vGlobalRamp, 4);\nstatic float c_fGlGamma     = c_vGlobalRamp.x;\nstatic float c_fGlBrighness = c_vGlobalRamp.y;\nstatic float c_fGlContrast  = c_vGlobalRamp.z;\nstatic float c_fGlSaturation= c_vGlobalRamp.w;\n// global color channels bias\n_CregF( float3, c_vChannelBias, 5);\n\n                                               \n// color component weights be used for luminance calculations (in RGB order)\nstatic const float3 LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS = float3( 0.2125f, 0.7154f, 0.0721f);\n\n// max value for HDR output\n#define MAX_HDR_OUTPUT 256.0f\n\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy), depth/bloom (.zw)\n#ifdef LENS_DIRT\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos); // for lens-dirt texture\n#endif\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n/// Apply the gamma ramp to the output color.\ninline float3 GammaRamp( in float3 vColor)\n{\n#ifdef REAL_SRGB\n\n  float3 vColorLo = vColor * 12.92f;\n#if _HLSL\n  float3 vColorHi = pow( vColor, 1.0f/2.4f) *1.055f -0.055f;\n  vColor = (vColor<0.0031308f) ? vColorLo : vColorHi;\n#elif _GLSL\n  const float f1oG = 1.0f / 2.4f;\n  float3 vColorHi = pow( vColor, _tcast(float3,f1oG)) *1.055f -0.055f;\n  vColor.r = (vColor.r<0.0031308f) ? vColorLo.r : vColorHi.r;\n  vColor.g = (vColor.g<0.0031308f) ? vColorLo.g : vColorHi.g;\n  vColor.b = (vColor.b<0.0031308f) ? vColorLo.b : vColorHi.b;\n#endif // API\n#endif // REAL_SRGB\n\n#ifndef NO_GAMMA_CORRECTION\n  // apply additional correction set by the postproceffect\n  vColor = pow( vColor, _tcast(float3,c_fInvGamma));\n#endif\n  // return gamma-ed color\n  return vColor;\n}\n\n\n#ifdef run_FinalPassPS\n\n#ifdef BLOOM\n\n/// Perform manual bilinear filter on the bloom texture to avoid pixelization.\ninline float3 SampleBloom( const float2 vTexCoords)\n{\n  // if texture unit supports bilinear filtering for bloom texture format\n#ifdef BLOOM_HW_BILINEAR\n\n  // just sample the texture\n  return texSample2D( t_sBloom, s_tBloom, MultiviewUV(vTexCoords)).rgb;\n\n  // if texture unit doesn't support bilinear filtering\n#else\n\n  // do it manually\n  float2 vBloomPixSize = 0.499f / c_vBloomTexSize;\n\n  // calc coord and fraction\n  float4 vOffsetCoord = vTexCoords.xyxy + float4( -vBloomPixSize, vBloomPixSize);\n  float2 vLerpFactor  = frac( vOffsetCoord.xy *c_vBloomTexSize);\n  // 4 samples\n  vOffsetCoord = MultiviewUV2( vOffsetCoord);\n  float3 vBloomCol00 = texSample2D( t_sBloom, s_tBloom, vOffsetCoord.xy).rgb;\n  float3 vBloomCol10 = texSample2D( t_sBloom, s_tBloom, vOffsetCoord.zy).rgb;\n  float3 vBloomCol01 = texSample2D( t_sBloom, s_tBloom, vOffsetCoord.xw).rgb;\n  float3 vBloomCol11 = texSample2D( t_sBloom, s_tBloom, vOffsetCoord.zw).rgb;\n  // interpolate\n  return lerp(\n    lerp( vBloomCol00, vBloomCol10, vLerpFactor.x),\n    lerp( vBloomCol01, vBloomCol11, vLerpFactor.x), vLerpFactor.y);   \n\n#endif // BLOOM_HW_BILINEAR\n}\n\n#endif // BLOOM\n#ifdef LENS_DIRT\n\n\n/// Apply lens dirt effect.\ninline void ApplyLensDirt( inout float3 vFinalColor, const float2 vTexCoord)\n{\n  // sample lens dirt texture\n  float4 vcolLensDirt = texSample2D( t_sLensDirt, s_tLensDirt, vTexCoord);\n  float fLogLum;\n\n  // if texture unit supports bilinear filtering for luminance texture format\n#ifdef LUM_HW_BILINEAR\n\n  // just sample downsampled luminance texture\n  fLogLum = texSample2D( t_sLumaDS, s_tLumaDS, MultiviewUV(vTexCoord)).r;\n\n  // if texture unit doesn't support bilinear filtering\n#else\n\n  // do it manually\n  const float2 vLumPixSize = float2(-0.499f,0.499f) / LUMA_DS_DIM;\n\n  // calc coord and fraction\n  float4 vOffsetCoord = vTexCoord.xyxy + vLumPixSize.xxyy;\n  float2 vLerpFactor  = frac( vOffsetCoord.xy *LUMA_DS_DIM);\n  // 4 samples\n  float4 vLum;\n  vOffsetCoord = MultiviewUV2( vOffsetCoord);\n  vLum.x = texSample2D( t_sLumaDS, s_tLumaDS, vOffsetCoord.xy).r;  // 00\n  vLum.y = texSample2D( t_sLumaDS, s_tLumaDS, vOffsetCoord.zy).r;  // 10\n  vLum.z = texSample2D( t_sLumaDS, s_tLumaDS, vOffsetCoord.xw).r;  // 01\n  vLum.w = texSample2D( t_sLumaDS, s_tLumaDS, vOffsetCoord.zw).r;  // 11\n  // interpolate\n  vLum.xy = lerp( vLum.xz, vLum.yw, vLerpFactor.x);\n  fLogLum = lerp( vLum.x,  vLum.y,  vLerpFactor.y);   \n\n#endif // LUM_HW_BILINEAR\n\n  // calculate luminosity\n  float fLumaDS = exp2( fLogLum);\n\n  // apply treshold and range\n  fLumaDS-= c_fLensDirtTreshold;\n  fLumaDS*= c_f1oLensDirtRange;\n  fLumaDS = saturate( fLumaDS);\n  fLumaDS*= vcolLensDirt.a;\n  fLumaDS*= c_fLensDirtStrength;\n\n  // lerp between lens-dirt and final scene color\n  vFinalColor = lerp( vFinalColor, vcolLensDirt.rgb, fLumaDS);\n}\n\n\n#endif // LENS_DIRT\n\n\n/// Compress the dynamic range of the image to 0-1.0 range.\ninline float3 ToneMap( float3 vColor) \n{\n#ifdef TONE_MAPPING\n  // tonemapping is just a plain ramp for now\n  return saturate( vColor);\n#else\n  // perform range compression\n  return vColor / (1.0f+vColor);\n#endif\n}\n\n\n\n/// Final pass pixel program - applies luminance adjustment and blooming and renders to screen.\nPS_ENTRY( FinalPassPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  \n  // sample HDR render target\n  float2 vInTexCoords = MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy));\n  float4 vOutCol = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTexCoords);\n  vOutCol.rgb = clamp( vOutCol.rgb, 0.0f, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n  // adjust pixel luminance with constant factors and adapted one (if any)\n  float fExp = texSample2D( t_sLuminance, s_tLuminance, MultiviewUV(float2(0.5f,0.5f))).r;\n  fExp *= c_fFixedExposure;\n\n  // if blooming\n#ifdef BLOOM\n\n  // apply bloom to the pixel, with given alpha\n  float3 vBloomCol = SampleBloom( PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw));\n  vBloomCol *= c_fBloomMultiplier;\n//vBloomCol *= saturate( vBloomCol-vOutCol.rgb);\n  vOutCol.rgb += vBloomCol;\n\n#endif\n\t\t\n  // adjust exposure\n  vOutCol.rgb *= fExp;  \n\n// if no HDR output\n#ifndef HDR_OUTPUT\n\n  // apply gamma ramping and tone mapping\n  vOutCol.rgb = GammaRamp( vOutCol.rgb);\n  vOutCol.rgb = ToneMap( vOutCol.rgb);\n#endif\n#ifdef LENS_DIRT\n\n  // convert texture coords from screen to UV space\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), c_v1oScrSize);\n  float2 vTexCoord = GetRasterClipPos();\n  // apply lens dirt effect\n  ApplyLensDirt( vOutCol.rgb, vTexCoord);\n#endif\n  \n  // saturation (lerp towards or away from middle gray)\n  float fDesatTarget = dot( vOutCol.rgb, LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n  vOutCol.rgb = lerp( _tcast(float3,fDesatTarget), vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,c_fSaturation));\n  // lightness (lerp towards black or white)\n  vOutCol.rgb = lerp( vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,c_fLightTarget), _tcast(float3,c_fLightness));\n\n// if not using HDR output\n#ifndef HDR_OUTPUT\n\n  // do final output clamp\n  vOutCol.rgb = saturate( vOutCol.rgb);\n\n// if HDR output with debugging\n#elif defined(HDR_DEBUGGING)\n\n  // generate 10 bands across the screen with \"LDR clamp\" in every odd one\n  if( frac( vInTexCoords.x*5.0f) > 0.5f) {\n    vOutCol.rgb = saturate( vOutCol.rgb);\n  }\n#endif\n#ifdef COLOR_RAMP\n\n  // remap the color using the color ramp texture (channel by channel)\n  vOutCol.r = texSample2D( t_sColorRamp, s_tColorRamp, float2( vOutCol.r, 0.5f)).r;\n  vOutCol.g = texSample2D( t_sColorRamp, s_tColorRamp, float2( vOutCol.g, 0.5f)).g;\n  vOutCol.b = texSample2D( t_sColorRamp, s_tColorRamp, float2( vOutCol.b, 0.5f)).b;\n\n#endif\n\n  // global saturation\n  fDesatTarget = dot( vOutCol.rgb, LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n  vOutCol.rgb = lerp( _tcast(float3,fDesatTarget), vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,c_fGlSaturation));\n  #ifdef HDR_OUTPUT\n    vOutCol.rgb = max( vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,0));\n  #else\n    vOutCol.rgb = saturate( vOutCol.rgb);\n  #endif\n\n#ifdef GLOBAL_GAMMA\n  // global gamma correction\n  vOutCol.rgb = pow( vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,c_fGlGamma));\n#endif\n\n  // global brightness\n  vOutCol.rgb += c_fGlBrighness;\n  #ifdef HDR_OUTPUT\n    vOutCol.rgb = max( vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,0));\n  #else\n    vOutCol.rgb = saturate( vOutCol.rgb);\n  #endif\n\n#ifdef GLOBAL_CONTRAST\n  // global contrast\n  vOutCol.rgb = (vOutCol.rgb-0.5f) *c_fGlContrast +0.5f;\n  #ifdef HDR_OUTPUT\n    vOutCol.rgb = max( vOutCol.rgb, _tcast(float3,0));\n  #else\n    vOutCol.rgb = saturate( vOutCol.rgb);\n  #endif\n#endif\n\n  // channels' bias\n  vOutCol.rgb *= c_vChannelBias;\n\n#ifdef OUTPUT_LEVELS\n  // and output levels \n  vOutCol.rgb = floor( vOutCol.rgb *c_fLevels) *c_f1oLevels;\n#endif\n\n  // safe clamp for \n#ifdef HDR_OUTPUT\n  // final HDR\n  vOutCol.rgb = clamp( vOutCol.rgb, 0.0f, MAX_HDR_OUTPUT);\n#else\n  // or LDR output\n  vOutCol.rgb = saturate( vOutCol.rgb);\n#endif\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // all done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_FinalPassPS\n#ifdef run_SimplePostprocessPS\n\n\n/// Simple postprocessing pixel program - applies fixed exposure, range compression and gamma ramp.\nPS_ENTRY( SimplePostprocessPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // sample HDR render target\n  float4 vOutCol = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)));\n  vOutCol.rgb = clamp( vOutCol.rgb, 0.0f, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  \n  // adjust pixel luminance with constant factors\n  vOutCol.rgb *= c_fFixedExposure;\n\n  // perform range compression\n  vOutCol.rgb = vOutCol.rgb / (1.0f+vOutCol.rgb);\n\n  // and gamma ramping\n  vOutCol.rgb = GammaRamp( vOutCol.rgb);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_SimplePostprocessPS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PPLuminanceShaders.psh\n\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n#ifndef run_LuminanceAdaptationPS\n  _Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0); // (copy of the back buffer)\n  #ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n    _Sreg2D( t_sDistance, s_tDistance, 1);  // (distance buffer)\n  #endif\n#else\n  _Sreg2D( t_sLuminance,  s_tLuminance,  1); // (currently calculated luminance)\n  _Sreg2D( t_sAdaptedLum, s_tAdaptedLum, 2); // (adaptation luminance)\n#endif\n\n// constant register containing luminance params\n_CregF( float3, c_vLuminance, 0);\nstatic float c_fDesiredLumLog2    = c_vLuminance.x;\nstatic float c_fFixedExposure     = c_vLuminance.y;  // (HDR output denormalization value inside!)\nstatic float c_fAntiClipThreshold = c_vLuminance.z;  // how many stops above average is considered clipping\n\n_CregF( float4, c_vAdaptExpEdge, 1);\nstatic float  c_fAdaptationRatio = c_vAdaptExpEdge.x;\nstatic float  c_fExpCompensation = c_vAdaptExpEdge.y;\nstatic float2 c_vSampleEdgeLum   = c_vAdaptExpEdge.zw;\n\n_CregF( float4, c_vEVs, 2);\nstatic float c_fMinEV  = c_vEVs.x;\nstatic float c_fMaxEV  = c_vEVs.y;\nstatic float c_fMidEV  = c_vEVs.z;\nstatic float c_fEVStep = c_vEVs.w;\n\n#ifndef FILTER_SAMPLES\n  #define FILTER_SAMPLES 1\n#endif\n\n\n// color component weights be used for luminance calculations (in RGB order)\nstatic const float3 LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS = float3( 0.2125f, 0.7154f, 0.0721f);\n\n#if _HLSL\n  // sampling pixel offsets\n  const uniform float2 c_avSampleOffsetsLum[ FILTER_SAMPLES] : register(c3);\n  // and theirs fetching function\n  static inline float2 _getSampleOffset( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avSampleOffsetsLum[ iIndex];\n  }\n#elif _GLSL\n\n  // sampling pixel offset fetching function\n  static inline float2 _getSampleOffset( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avUniformsF[ iIndex+3].xy;\n  }\n#endif // API\n\n\n#if _PSSL\n  // (let this pixel shaders know that underlying render-target is in R32F format)\n  #pragma PSSL_target_output_format(default FMT_32_R)\n#endif\n\n\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy), depth/bloom (.zw)\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n#ifdef run_LumDownsampleIniPS\n\n\n/// Pixel program that downsamples the back buffer and calculates luminance.\nPS_ENTRY( LumDownsampleIniPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n#ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n\n  // sample distance (depth) \n  float fDepth = texSample2D( t_sDistance, s_tDistance, MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw))).r;\n\n#endif\n\n  // sample the 4x4 area around the given pixel\n  float2 vLogLumSum = float2( 0.0f, 0.0001f);\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<FILTER_SAMPLES; iSample++) {\n\n    // get sample offset\n    // (assuming that source buffer and depth buffer are of the same canvas size!)\n    float2 vUV = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) + _getSampleOffset( iSample);\n    vUV = min( vUV, c_vSampleEdgeLum);\n\n    // sample source color texture\n    float4 vSample = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vUV));\n    vSample.rgb = clamp( vSample.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n    float fLum = dot( vSample.rgb, LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n\n    // (with HDR output denormalization)\n    fLum *= c_fFixedExposure;\n\n    // do log2 of luminance\n    float fLogLum = log2( fLum);\n  #ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n    // (excluding weapon)\n    _flatten if( fDepth >= 0.0f) {\n      vLogLumSum.x += fLogLum;\n      vLogLumSum.y += 1.0f;\n    }\n  #else\n    // (including weapon)\n    vLogLumSum.x += fLogLum;\n  #endif\n  }\n  // calculate the average luminance of all samples\n#ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n  // (excluding weapon)\n  vLogLumSum.x /= vLogLumSum.y;\n  vLogLumSum.x = (vLogLumSum.y<1.0f) ? 10000.0f : vLogLumSum.x;\n#else\n  // (including weapon)\n  vLogLumSum.x /= float(FILTER_SAMPLES);\n#endif\n  // and prepare output\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( vLogLumSum.x,0,0, 1);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // send out average luma\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // main_LumDownsampleIniPS\n#ifdef run_LumDownsample4x4PS\n\n\n/// Pixel program that downsamples the input (log!) luminance texture with 4x4 sampling.\nPS_ENTRY( LumDownsample4x4PS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // result (sum,count)\n  float2 vLogLumSum = float2( 0.0f, 0.0001f);\n\n  // sample the 4x4 area around the given pixel\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<FILTER_SAMPLES; iSample++) {\n\n    // compute the sum of luminances throughout the sample points\n    float2 vUV = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)+ _getSampleOffset( iSample);\n  //vUV = min( vUV, c_vSampleEdgeLum);\n    float fLogLum = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vUV)).r;\n\n  #ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n    // (excluding weapon)\n    _flatten if( fLogLum < 16.0f) {\n      vLogLumSum.x += fLogLum;\n      vLogLumSum.y += 1.0f;\n    }\n  #else\n    // (including weapon)\n    vLogLumSum.x += fLogLum;\n  #endif\n  }\n\n  // calculate the average luminance of all samples\n#ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n  // (excluding weapon)\n  vLogLumSum.x /= vLogLumSum.y;\n  vLogLumSum.x = (vLogLumSum.y<1.0f) ? 10000.0f : vLogLumSum.x;\n#else\n  // (including weapon)\n  vLogLumSum.x /= float(FILTER_SAMPLES);\n#endif\n  // and prepare output\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( vLogLumSum.x,0,0, 1);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // send out average luma\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_LumDownsample4x4PS\n#ifdef run_LumDownsampleFinPS\n\n\n/// Pixel program that downsamples the log luminance texture to 1x1 and calculates the real average luminance.\nPS_ENTRY( LumDownsampleFinPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // temps and result\n  float2 vUV, vLogLumSum;\n  vLogLumSum = float2( 0.0f, 0.0001f);\n\n  // sample the 4x4 area around the given pixel\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<FILTER_SAMPLES; iSample++) {\n\n    // compute the sum of luminances \n    vUV = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)+ _getSampleOffset( iSample);\n  //vUV = min( vUV, c_vSampleEdgeLum);\n    float fLogLum = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vUV)).r;\n\n    // but only in the middle area (2x2)\n    if( vUV.x<0.8f && vUV.x>0.2f && vUV.y<0.8f && vUV.y>0.2f) {\n\n    #ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n      // (excluding weapon)\n      _flatten if( fLogLum < 16.0f) {\n        vLogLumSum.x += fLogLum;\n        vLogLumSum.y += 1.0f;\n      }\n    #else\n      // (including weapon)\n      vLogLumSum.x += fLogLum;\n    #endif\n    }\n  }\n  // average this sum\n#ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n  // (excluding weapon)\n  vLogLumSum.x /= vLogLumSum.y;\n  vLogLumSum.x = (vLogLumSum.y<1.0f) ? 10000.0f : vLogLumSum.x;\n#else\n  // (including weapon)\n  vLogLumSum.x /= float(FILTER_SAMPLES)*0.25f;\n#endif\n  // scale the average so that the average scene in the end has desired luminance\n  vLogLumSum.x -= c_fDesiredLumLog2;\n  \n  // do several iterations to reduce luminance clipping\n  _unroll for( int iIteration=0; iIteration<3; iIteration++) {\n\n    // for each area on the screen\n    float fMaxError = 0.0f;  // (keep maximum error here)\n    _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<FILTER_SAMPLES; iSample++) {\n\n      // sample\n      vUV = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)+ _getSampleOffset( iSample);\n      float fLogLum = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vUV)).r;\n\n    #ifdef EXCLUDE_FPW\n      // if excluding weapon but these weren't weapons' pixels\n      if( fLogLum < 16.0f)\n    #endif\n      { // determine how much it goes in clip\n        float fError = max( fLogLum-vLogLumSum.x+c_fAntiClipThreshold, 0.0f);\n        // and keep the error maximum\n        fMaxError = max( fError*vUV.y, fMaxError); \n      }\n    }\n    // move the average so that this area is not clipped\n    vLogLumSum.x += fMaxError;\n  }\n  // convert the result back to linear from log space\n  float fLuminance = 1.0f / exp2( vLogLumSum.x);\n  // and prepare output\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( fLuminance,0,0, 1);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // send out average luma\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_LumDownsampleFinPS\n#ifdef run_LuminanceAdaptationPS\n\n\n/// Pixel program that simulates latency in adapting to changed scene luminance.\nPS_ENTRY( LuminanceAdaptationPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // sample current and last luminance\n  float2 vCenterCoord  = MultiviewUV( float2( 0.5f,0.5f));\n  float fCurrentLum    = texSample2D( t_sLuminance,  s_tLuminance,  vCenterCoord.xy).r;\n  float fLastAdaptedLum= texSample2D( t_sAdaptedLum, s_tAdaptedLum, vCenterCoord.xy).r;\n  // (safe) inverse are used in further calculations\n  fCurrentLum     = 1.0f / max( fCurrentLum,     SMALL_HDR_FLOAT);\n  fLastAdaptedLum = 1.0f / max( fLastAdaptedLum, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n  // to logarithmic space\n  float fCurrentLumLog = log2( fCurrentLum);\n  // incorporate exposure compensation\n  fCurrentLumLog = lerp( c_fMidEV, fCurrentLumLog, c_fExpCompensation);\n  // round it to nearest appropriate f-stop step\n  fCurrentLumLog = floor( fCurrentLumLog/c_fEVStep +0.5f) *c_fEVStep;\n  // clamp it to the allowed limits\n  fCurrentLumLog = clamp( fCurrentLumLog, c_fMinEV, c_fMaxEV);\n  // back to linear space\n  fCurrentLum = exp2( fCurrentLumLog);\n\n  // adapt the luminance by lerping it into the measured luminance,\n  // using a time-dependent factor to assure same result on different framerates\n  float fNewLum = 1.0f / lerp( fCurrentLum, fLastAdaptedLum, c_fAdaptationRatio);\n  // and prepare output\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( fNewLum,0,0, 1);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n#if _GLSL_METAL\n  // hack for the black screen issue on A7 iOS devices\n  if (fNewLum >= -1e6f && fNewLum <= 1e6f) {\n    vOutCol = float4( fNewLum,0,0, 1);\n  } else {\n    vOutCol = float4( 1,0,0, 1);\n  }\n#endif\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_LuminanceAdaptationPS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PPOffsetRGB.psh\n\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource,     s_tSource,     0); // (copy of the back buffer)\n_Sreg2D( t_sOffsetMask, s_tOffsetMask, 1); // (currently calculated luminance)\n\n// constant registers\n_CregF( float3, c_vOffsetR, 0);\n_CregF( float3, c_vOffsetG, 1);\n_CregF( float3, c_vOffsetB, 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vCoordsAdj, 3);\n_CregF( float4, c_vClampRect, 4);\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy), mask (.zw)\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n#ifdef run_RGBOffsetPS\n\n\n/// Pixel program that downsamples the input texture to one four times smaller.\nPS_ENTRY( RGBOffsetPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare\n  float4 vOutCol;\n  vOutCol.a = 1.0f;\n  float2 vTexCoord = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy);\n  float2 vSampleCoord;\n\n  // sample offset mask texture\n  float3 vOffsetMask = texSample2D( t_sOffsetMask, s_tOffsetMask, MultiviewUV(PS_IN( vTexCoords.zw))).rgb;\n  float3 vChannelOffset;\n\n  // apply mask to R channel offset\n  vChannelOffset.xy = c_vOffsetR.xy * vOffsetMask.rr;\n  vChannelOffset.z = lerp( 1.0f, c_vOffsetR.z, vOffsetMask.r);\n\n  // calculate Z offset for R\n  vSampleCoord = vTexCoord *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vSampleCoord *= vChannelOffset.z;\n  vSampleCoord = vSampleCoord *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // calculate X and Y offsets for R\n  vSampleCoord = saturate( vSampleCoord+ vChannelOffset.xy);\n  vSampleCoord = vSampleCoord *c_vCoordsAdj.xy + c_vCoordsAdj.zw;\n  vSampleCoord = clamp( vSampleCoord, c_vClampRect.xy, c_vClampRect.zw);\n  // sample R channel\n  vOutCol.r = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vSampleCoord)).r;\n\n  // apply mask to G channel offset\n  vChannelOffset.xy = c_vOffsetG.xy * vOffsetMask.gg;\n  vChannelOffset.z = lerp( 1.0f, c_vOffsetG.z, vOffsetMask.g);\n\n  // calculate Z offset for G\n  vSampleCoord = vTexCoord *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vSampleCoord *= vChannelOffset.z;\n  vSampleCoord = vSampleCoord *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // calculate G offset\n  vSampleCoord = saturate( vSampleCoord+ vChannelOffset.xy);\n  vSampleCoord = vSampleCoord *c_vCoordsAdj.xy + c_vCoordsAdj.zw;\n  vSampleCoord = clamp( vSampleCoord, c_vClampRect.xy, c_vClampRect.zw);\n  // sample G channel\n  vOutCol.g = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vSampleCoord)).g;\n\n  // apply mask to B channel offset\n  vChannelOffset.xy = c_vOffsetB.xy * vOffsetMask.bb;\n  vChannelOffset.z = lerp( 1.0f, c_vOffsetB.z, vOffsetMask.b);\n\n  // calculate Z offset for R\n  vSampleCoord = vTexCoord *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vSampleCoord *= vChannelOffset.z;\n  vSampleCoord = vSampleCoord *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // calculate B offset\n  vSampleCoord = saturate( vSampleCoord+ vChannelOffset.xy);\n  vSampleCoord = vSampleCoord *c_vCoordsAdj.xy + c_vCoordsAdj.zw;\n  vSampleCoord = clamp( vSampleCoord, c_vClampRect.xy, c_vClampRect.zw);\n  // sample B channel\n  vOutCol.b = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, MultiviewUV(vSampleCoord)).b;\n\n  // clamp range (for 64-bit HDR)\n  vOutCol.rgb = clamp( vOutCol.rgb, 0.0f, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_RGBOffsetPS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ProbeShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClip, 0);\n// object (model) to world matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);    \n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float3, vVexPosAbs, 0);\n  _outReg( float3, vNormalAbs, 1);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\nVS_ENTRY( ProbeVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mObjToClip);\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = mulM43F( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mObjToAbs);\n  VS_OUT( vNormalAbs) = mul( VS_IN( vInPos.xyz), _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs));\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// probe cube-map\n_SregCUBE( t_sSphereReflectMap, s_tSphereReflectMap, 0);\n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float3, c_vEyePosAbs, 0);\n\n#if _HLSL\n  // spherical harmonics coefficients \n  const uniform float3 c_avSHCs[9] : register(c1);\n  // and theirs fetching function\n  static inline float3 _getSHC( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avSHCs[ iIndex];\n  }\n#elif _GLSL\n  // spherical harmonics coefficients fetching function\n  static inline float3 _getSHC( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avUniformsF[ iIndex+1].xyz;\n  }\n#endif // API\n\n\n// pixel input(s)\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float3, vVexPosAbs, 0);\n  _inReg( float3, vNormalAbs, 1);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( ProbePS)\n{\n  // take normal (no roataion->already in absolute space)\n  float3 vNormalAbs = normalize( PS_IN( vNormalAbs));\n  float3 vViewDistAbs = c_vEyePosAbs - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs);\n\n  // calc normal factors\n  float3 vNorSqr = vNormalAbs.xyz * vNormalAbs.xyz;\n  float3 vNorMix = vNormalAbs.xzy * vNormalAbs.zyx;\n\n  // and apply spherical harmonics lighting\n  float3 vSH = _getSHC(0);  \n  vSH += _getSHC(1) * vNormalAbs.x;\n  vSH += _getSHC(2) * vNormalAbs.y;\n  vSH += _getSHC(3) * vNormalAbs.z;\n  vSH += _getSHC(4) * vNorMix.x;\n  vSH += _getSHC(5) * vNorMix.y;\n  vSH += _getSHC(6) * vNorMix.z;\n  vSH += _getSHC(7) *(vNorSqr.z *3.0f -1.0f);\n  vSH += _getSHC(8) *(vNorSqr.x - vNorSqr.y);\n  // (SH can end up negative, so clamping is needed)\n  vSH = max( vSH, _tcast(float3,0));\n  \n  // reflect eye vector around normal; 2N(N.E) - E(N.N) \n  float3 vReflect = reflect( vViewDistAbs, vNormalAbs);\n  vReflect.xy = -vReflect.xy;\n\n  // apply reflection color and convert to linear space\n  float4 vSphere = texSampleCube( t_sSphereReflectMap, s_tSphereReflectMap, vReflect);\n\n  // multiply with evaluated spherical harmonics\n  vSphere.rgb *= exp2( vSphere.a *32.0f -16.0f); // (RGBE format, 5-bit signed exponent) \n  vSphere.rgb *= vSH.rgb;\n  PS_OUT( float4( vSphere.rgb, 1));\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// RefractionShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sRefr,  s_tRefr,  0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sBumps, s_tBumps, 1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sMask,  s_tMask,  2);\n// depth texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 3);\n\n// distorsion and bump strength\n_CregF( float4, c_vBumpsRatio, 0);\nstatic float  c_fDistorsion  = c_vBumpsRatio.x;\nstatic float  c_fBumpPower   = c_vBumpsRatio.y;\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize= c_vBumpsRatio.zw;\n// grabbed rectangle edges (.xy=min, .zw=max)\n_CregF( float4, c_vRectEdges, 1);\n// \"fresnel\" edge attenuation (scale and bias)\n_CregF( float4, c_vEdgeDepthSoftness, 2);\nstatic float c_fEdgeExp   = c_vEdgeDepthSoftness.x;\nstatic float c_fEdgeBias  = c_vEdgeDepthSoftness.y;\nstatic float c_fEdgeScale = c_vEdgeDepthSoftness.z;\nstatic float c_fSoftDepth = c_vEdgeDepthSoftness.w;\n// reciprocal of depth texture dimensions\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepthSize, 3);\nstatic float2 c_v1oDepthSize  = c_vDepthSize.xy;\nstatic float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepthSize.z;\nstatic float  c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepthSize.w;\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\n// output to PS\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpMaskUV,  0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNorViewDepth,1);  // (normal in view-space, depth in .w)\n  _inReg( float4, vVexColor,    2);  // (alpha attenuates bumps!)\n  _inReg( float3, vVexPosViewLeft,  3);\n  _inReg( float3, vVexPosViewRight,  4);\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// begin one light pass\nPS_ENTRY( RefractionPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // modulate mask texture with vertex color\n  float fTexMask = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, PS_IN( vBumpMaskUV.zw)).a;\n  fTexMask *= PS_IN( vVexColor.a);\n  // attenuate distorsion and bumps with it\n  float fDistorsion = c_fDistorsion *fTexMask;\n  float fBumpPower  = c_fBumpPower  *fTexMask;\n\n  // calculate normal Z coord in view space\n  float3 vNorView = normalize( PS_IN( vNorViewDepth.xyz));\n  float3 vPosView = normalize( VRSelect(PS_IN(vVexPosViewLeft), PS_IN(vVexPosViewRight)));\n  vNorView.z = dot( vNorView, vPosView);\n\n  // attenuate bumps at edges\n  float fSoftEdge = abs( vNorView.z);\n  fSoftEdge = saturate( fSoftEdge -c_fEdgeScale) *c_fEdgeBias +0.00001f;\n  fSoftEdge = pow( fSoftEdge, c_fEdgeExp);\n  fBumpPower  *= fSoftEdge;\n  fDistorsion *= fSoftEdge;\n\n  // sample and \"unpack\" bumps\n  float4 vTexBump = texSample2D( t_sBumps, s_tBumps, PS_IN( vBumpMaskUV.xy));\n  vTexBump.xy = nor2D( vTexBump);\n\n  // get attenuated distorsion and bumps\n  float2 vOffset = fDistorsion* vNorView.xy;\n  vOffset += fBumpPower * vTexBump.xy;\n\n  // get coorinate for depth (distance) buffer texture and current pixel depth value\n  float2 vDepthCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oDepthSize));\n  float fPixDepth = PS_IN( vNorViewDepth.w);\n  float fTexDepth, fDepthDiff;\n\n  // if using depth softness\n#ifdef DEPTH_FADE\n\n  // sample original pixel depth\n  fTexDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoord).r;\n  fTexDepth = fTexDepth *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // calcuate depth (distance) difference\n  fDepthDiff = fTexDepth - fPixDepth;\n  // attenuate it by viewing angle (so that it looks fine in the distance)\n  // (but add a little bias for extreme case like grazing angles; big_depth_difference * angle_0 = wrong_result!)\n  fDepthDiff *= saturate( abs( vNorView.z) +0.001f);\n  // attenuate offset by that softness\n  // (this one is for sampling the pixel to be offseted)\n  vOffset *= saturate( fDepthDiff *c_fSoftDepth);\n\n#endif\n\n  // sample offseted depth\n  vDepthCoord = saturate( vDepthCoord+ vOffset);\n  fTexDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoord).r;\n  fTexDepth = fTexDepth *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // forbid offseting if offseted depth value is nearer than rendered pixel\n  vOffset = (fTexDepth<fPixDepth) ? _tcast(float2,0) : vOffset;\n\n  // sample refraction coords from screen space\n  float2 vRefrCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n  // and apply (attenuated) offset\n  vRefrCoord += vOffset;\n\n  // but don't go outside rendered part of refraction texture\n  float4 vRectEdgesMV = MultiviewUV2( c_vRectEdges);\n  vRefrCoord = clamp( vRefrCoord, vRectEdgesMV.xy, vRectEdgesMV.zw);\n\n  // finally, sample and modulate refraction texture\n  float4 vcolRefr = texSample2D( t_sRefr, s_tRefr, vRefrCoord);\n  vcolRefr.rgb *= PS_IN( vVexColor.rgb);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vcolRefr);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vcolRefr);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// RefractionShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// transformation to clip, absolute or view space\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n// fog and haze calculation\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n// object to world (absolute) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToViewLeft, 5);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToViewRightX, 8);\n\n// 3rd row (Z) of model-view matrix\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewDist, 9);\n// (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n// masking out of input normals (if there aren't any)\n_CregF( float4, c_vColorNorMask, 14);\nstatic float2 c_vColorMapMask = c_vColorNorMask.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vNormalMask   = c_vColorNorMask.zw;\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskMapping, 15);\n// model-view matrix for normal\n_CregM33F( c_mObjToViewRot, 16);\n// mapping constants\n_CregM42F( c_mBumpMapping, 19);\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV,   2);\n  _inReg( float2, vMaskUV,   3);\n  _inReg( float4, vColorMap, 4);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices,  5); // (matrix indices)\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,  6); // (blend weights)\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vBumpMaskUV,  0);\n  _outReg( float4, vNorViewDepth,1);
