// (normal in view-space, depth in .w)\n  _outReg( float4, vVexColor,    2); // (alpha attenuates bumps!)\n  _outReg( float3, vVexPosViewLeft,  3);\n  _outReg( float3, vVexPosViewRight,  4);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( RefractionVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // skin position, normal and tangent\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNormalMask.yyyx);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  // (if needed)\n  vPos.xyz = SkinVertexNor( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor);\n#endif\n\n  // clip-space pixel positions\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // transform normal into view-space\n  // (accounted for non-uniform stretching)\n  float4 vOutNorViewDepth;  // (do in here)\n  vOutNorViewDepth.xyz = mul( vNor, c_mObjToViewRot);\n  vOutNorViewDepth.xyz = normalize( vOutNorViewDepth.xyz);\n\n  // transform position to view space\n  float3 vOutPosViewLeft = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToViewLeft);\n  float3 vOutPosViewRight = mulM43F( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToViewLeft, c_vObjToViewRightX));\n  // and output it to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosViewLeft) = vOutPosViewLeft;\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosViewRight) = vOutPosViewRight;\n\n  // output depth value from Z for depth comparison (in meters) and\n  // apply ~10cm offset in order to successfully apply refraction as an overlay for a different shader on the same surface\n  // (we cannot output W here, because of ortho projection used by distant light which has W=1)\n  vOutNorViewDepth.w = dot( vPos, c_vViewDist) -0.1f;\n  VS_OUT( vNorViewDepth) = vOutNorViewDepth;\n\n  // mapping coordinates\n  // (4-component dot product: Z is 0, W is offset; cannot use Z for offset\n  //  since 2D vectors will be expanded to X,Y,0,1, and we need 1 for dot product)\n  VS_OUT( vBumpMaskUV.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vBumpUV), c_mBumpMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vBumpMaskUV.zw) = VS_IN( vMaskUV) *c_vMaskMapping.xy +c_vMaskMapping.zw;\n\n  // color map array (maybe masked out)\n  float4 vOutVexColor = VS_IN( vColorMap);\n  vOutVexColor = vOutVexColor *c_vColorMapMask.xxxx +c_vColorMapMask.yyyy;\n  // (needs to be gamma corrected for HDR)\n  vOutVexColor.rgb *= vOutVexColor.rgb; \n  // attenuate vertex color by its alpha channel\n  vOutVexColor.rgb = lerp( _tcast(float3,1), vOutVexColor.rgb, vOutVexColor.a);\n  VS_OUT( vVexColor) = vOutVexColor;\n\n  // ? attenuate distorsion by Z clip coord\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// RescaleShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// sampling pixel distance, fall-off and darkness\n_CregF( float4, c_vSizes, 0); \nstatic float2 c_vTexSize = c_vSizes.xy;   // texture resolution\nstatic float2 c_vPixSize = c_vSizes.zw;   // 1 / tex-size\n_CregF( float4, c_vCubicRatios32, 1);     // for f^3 (.xy) and f^2 (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vCubicRatios10, 2);     // for f^1 (.xy) and f^0 (.zw)\nstatic float4 c_vRenSize= c_vCubicRatios32; \nstatic float2 c_vKernel = c_vCubicRatios32.xy; \n_CregF( float4, c_vDrawPortEdges, 3);     // .xy=min, .zw=max\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vTex0, 0);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex1, 1);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex2, 2);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex3, 3);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex4, 4);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex5, 5);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex6, 6);\n  _outReg( float4, vTex7, 7);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n/// rescale w/ filtering\nVS_ENTRY( RescaleVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( VS_IN( vInPos.xy), 0,1); \n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n\n  float2 vTexUL;\n  vTexUL = VS_IN( vInPos.zw) *c_vRenSize.xy +c_vRenSize.zw;\n  vTexUL-= c_vPixSize *1.5f;\n\n  VS_OUT( vTex0) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(0,0,1,0);\n  VS_OUT( vTex1) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(2,0,3,0);\n  VS_OUT( vTex2) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(0,1,1,1);\n  VS_OUT( vTex3) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(2,1,3,1);\n  VS_OUT( vTex4) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(0,2,1,2);\n  VS_OUT( vTex5) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(2,2,3,2);\n  VS_OUT( vTex6) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(0,3,1,3);\n  VS_OUT( vTex7) = vTexUL.xyxy+ c_vPixSize.xyxy *float4(2,3,3,3);\n\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// use lookup textures or math\n#define USE_LOOKUP_TEX_BICUBIC 0\n#define USE_LOOKUP_TEX_LANCZOS 1\n\n#ifndef FILTER\n  // (just to keep ATI's GLSL compiler happy)\n  #define FILTER 0\n#endif\n\n// source for rescaling\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0);\n// lookup textures for rescaling ratios\n_Sreg2D( t_sLookup, s_tLookup, 1);\n\n// PI constants\nstatic const float4 _c_vPIs = float4( PI, 0, -PI, -2.0f*PI);\n\n// rectantle PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTex0, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex1, 1);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex2, 2);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex3, 3);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex4, 4);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex5, 5);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex6, 6);\n  _inReg( float4, vTex7, 7);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// interpolate 4 values with ratios (axis filtering)\ninline float4 Interpolate4( const float4 vWeights,\n                            const float4 vSampleOL, const float4 vSampleIL,  // outer, inner left\n                            const float4 vSampleIR, const float4 vSampleOR)  // inner, outer right\n{\n  return\n    vSampleOL * vWeights.x + vSampleIL * vWeights.y +\n    vSampleIR * vWeights.z + vSampleOR * vWeights.w;\n}\n\n\n// for bicubic interpolation\ninline float4 CalcBicubicWeights( const float fFrac)\n{\n  // vectorize!\n  float4 vFrac  = abs( fFrac+ float4( 1,0,-1,-2));\n  float4 vFrac2 = vFrac * vFrac;\n  float4 vFrac3 = vFrac * vFrac2;\n  float4 vRes = c_vCubicRatios10.wzzw +\n    c_vCubicRatios32.yxxy * vFrac3 +\n    c_vCubicRatios32.wzzw * vFrac2;\n  vRes.xw += c_vCubicRatios10.y * vFrac.xw; // (.x ratio==0)\n  return vRes;\n}\n\n\n// for Lanczos interpolation\ninline float4 CalcLanczosWeights( const float fFrac)\n{\n  // vectorize!\n  float4 vFracPI = (fFrac*PI) +_c_vPIs;\n  float4 vRes = 2.0f* sin(vFracPI) * sin(vFracPI*0.5f) / (vFracPI * vFracPI); // ... / (PI^2 * f^2)\n#if _HLSL\n  return (abs(vFracPI)>=0.001f) ? vRes : 1.0f;\n#elif _GLSL\n  vFracPI= abs( vFracPI);\n  vRes.x = (vFracPI.x>=0.001f) ? vRes.x : 1.0f;\n  vRes.y = (vFracPI.y>=0.001f) ? vRes.y : 1.0f;\n  vRes.z = (vFracPI.z>=0.001f) ? vRes.z : 1.0f;\n  vRes.w = (vFracPI.w>=0.001f) ? vRes.w : 1.0f;\n  return vRes;\n#endif // API\n}\n\n\n#ifdef run_RescalePS\n\n\n/// rescale w/ filtering\nPS_ENTRY( RescalePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // calc tex coords of upper left texel and fraction\n  float2 vFracCoord = frac( PS_IN( vTex0.xy) * c_vTexSize);\n  float4 vcolTex[7];\n\n  // clamp coords inside drawport\n  float4 vInTex0 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex0), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex1 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex1), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex2 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex2), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex3 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex3), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex4 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex4), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex5 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex5), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex6 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex6), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n  float4 vInTex7 = clamp( PS_IN( vTex7), c_vDrawPortEdges.xyxy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zwzw);\n\n  // make coordinates multi-view friendly\n  vInTex0 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex0);\n  vInTex1 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex1);\n  vInTex2 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex2);\n  vInTex3 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex3);\n  vInTex4 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex4);\n  vInTex5 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex5);\n  vInTex6 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex6);\n  vInTex7 = MultiviewUV2( vInTex7);\n\n  // sample top 4 texels\n  vcolTex[0] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex0.xy); // -1,-1 \n  vcolTex[1] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex0.zw); //  0,-1\n  vcolTex[2] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex1.xy); //  1,-1\n  vcolTex[3] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex1.zw); //  2,-1\n\n  // make 4 weights factor for X axis...\n  float4 vWeights;\n\n  // if bicubic\n#if FILTER == 1\n\n  #if USE_LOOKUP_TEX_BICUBIC\n    // from texture\n    vWeights = texSample2D( t_sLookup, s_tLookup, vFracCoord.xy) *2.0f -1.0f;\n    vWeights/= dot( vWeights, _tcast(float4,1));  // (renormalize)\n  #else\n    // or just calculate them\n    vWeights = CalcBicubicWeights( vFracCoord.x);\n  #endif\n\n  // if Lanczos\n#elif FILTER == 2\n\n  #if USE_LOOKUP_TEX_LANCZOS\n    // from texture\n    vWeights = texSample2D( t_sLookup, s_tLookup, vFracCoord.xy) *2.0f -1.0f;\n  #else\n    // or just calculate them\n    vWeights = CalcLanczosWeights( vFracCoord.x);\n  #endif\n  // and normalize\n  vWeights /= dot( vWeights, _tcast(float4,1));  \n\n  // if average\n#else \n\n  // weights are evenly distributed\n  vWeights = _tcast( float4, 0.25f);\n\n#endif // FILTER\n\n  // apply horizontal bicubic\n  vcolTex[0] = Interpolate4( vWeights, vcolTex[0], vcolTex[1], vcolTex[2], vcolTex[3]);\n\n  // sample upper 4 texels\n  vcolTex[1] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex2.xy); //  2, 0\n  vcolTex[2] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex2.zw); //  1, 0\n  vcolTex[3] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex3.xy); //  0, 0\n  vcolTex[4] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex3.zw); // -1, 0\n\n  // apply horizontal bicubic\n  vcolTex[1] = Interpolate4( vWeights, vcolTex[1], vcolTex[2], vcolTex[3], vcolTex[4]);\n\n  // sample lower 4 texels\n  vcolTex[2] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex4.xy); // -1, 1\n  vcolTex[3] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex4.zw); //  0, 1 \n  vcolTex[4] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex5.xy); //  1, 1 \n  vcolTex[5] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex5.zw); //  2, 1 \n\n  // apply horizontal bicubic\n  vcolTex[2] = Interpolate4( vWeights, vcolTex[2], vcolTex[3], vcolTex[4], vcolTex[5]);\n\n  // sample bottom 4 texels\n  vcolTex[3] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex6.xy); //  2, 2\n  vcolTex[4] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex6.zw); //  1, 2\n  vcolTex[5] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex7.xy); //  0, 2\n  vcolTex[6] = texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vInTex7.zw); // -1, 2\n\n  // apply horizontal bicubic\n  vcolTex[3] = Interpolate4( vWeights, vcolTex[3], vcolTex[4], vcolTex[5], vcolTex[6]);\n\n  // make 4 weights factor for Y axis...\n\n  // if bicubic\n#if FILTER == 1\n\n  #if USE_LOOKUP_TEX_BICUBIC\n    // from texture\n    vWeights = texSample2D( t_sLookup, s_tLookup, vFracCoord.yx) *2.0f -1.0f;\n    vWeights/= dot( vWeights, _tcast(float4,1));  // (renormalize)\n  #else\n    // or just calculate them\n    vWeights = CalcBicubicWeights( vFracCoord.y);\n  #endif\n\n  // if Lanczos\n#elif FILTER == 2\n\n    // make 4 weights factor for X axis\n  #if USE_LOOKUP_TEX_LANCZOS\n    // from texture\n    vWeights = texSample2D( t_sLookup, s_tLookup, vFracCoord.yx) *2.0f -1.0f;\n  #else\n    // or just calculate them\n    vWeights = CalcLanczosWeights( vFracCoord.y);\n  #endif\n  // and normalize\n  vWeights /= dot( vWeights, _tcast(float4,1));  \n\n  // (for average we already have weights form X-axis - they're the same)\n#endif // FILTER\n\n  // and finally, apply vertical bicubic\n  vcolTex[0] = Interpolate4( vWeights, vcolTex[0], vcolTex[1], vcolTex[2], vcolTex[3]);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vcolTex[0]);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vcolTex[0]);\n}\n\n\n#endif\n#ifdef run_BigRescalePS\n\n\n/// rescale w/ filtering\nPS_ENTRY( BigRescalePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // eliminate coord adjustment from vertex shader\n  float2 vInTex = PS_IN( vTex0).xy;\n  vInTex += c_vPixSize*1.5f;\n  // calculate upper-left pixel coord \n  vInTex -= (c_vKernel-1.0f)*0.5f *c_vPixSize;\n\n  // prepare\n  float4 vColRes = _tcast(float4,0);\n  float2 vStep;\n\n  // for each row in kernel\n  for( vStep.y=0; vStep.y<c_vKernel.y; vStep.y+=1.0f) {\n\n    // for each column in kernel\n    for( vStep.x=0; vStep.x<c_vKernel.x; vStep.x+=1.0f) {\n\n      // calculate and clamp sampling coordinate\n      float2 vTexCoords = vInTex+ vStep *c_vPixSize;\n      vTexCoords = clamp( vTexCoords, c_vDrawPortEdges.xy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zw);\n      // sample source there and accumulate\n      vColRes += texSample2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vTexCoords);\n    }\n  }\n  // calc accumulated average\n  vColRes /= (c_vKernel.x*c_vKernel.y);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vColRes);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vColRes);\n}\n\n#endif\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// RippleShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeBlend.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// refraction texture\n#ifndef NO_REFRACTION\n  _Sreg2D( t_sRefraction, s_tRefraction, 0);\n#endif\n// reflection texture\n#ifdef CUBE_REFLECTION\n  _SregCUBE( t_sReflection, s_tReflection, 1);\n#else // projective\n  _Sreg2D( t_sReflection, s_tReflection, 1);\n#endif\n// mask texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, 6);\n// bump textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sBumpMap,  s_tBumpMap,  2);\n_Sreg2D( t_sBumpMap2, s_tBumpMap2, 3);\n_Sreg2D( t_sBumpMap3, s_tBumpMap3, 4);\n_Sreg2D( t_sBumpMap4, s_tBumpMap4, 5);\n#ifdef DEPTH_FADE\n  // depth texture\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 7);\n#endif\n\n// reflection and refraction colors\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolRefl, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolRefr, 1);\n\n// bumps and fresnel exponent\n_CregF( float4, c_vBumpsBias, 2);\n_CregF( float3, c_fFresBlurs, 3);\nstatic float c_fFresnelPower= c_fFresBlurs.x;\nstatic float c_fRefractBlur = c_fFresBlurs.y;\nstatic float c_fReflectBlur = c_fFresBlurs.z;\n// lerp destination and mask colors dependant on the blend type\n_CregF( float4, c_vLerpDestMask, 4);\nstatic float4 c_vLerpDest = c_vLerpDestMask.xxxy;\nstatic float4 c_vLerpMask = c_vLerpDestMask.zzzw;\n  // (fog/haze use const reg c5-c7!)\n// views\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, 8);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight, 9);\nstatic float4 g_vViewPosAbsPix;\n// soft depth for shore and refraction color (.x=shore, .y=depth)\n// and alpha range adjustment (for transparency AA, if any)\n_CregF( float4, c_vAlphaSoftDepth, 10);\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange= c_vAlphaSoftDepth.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vSoftDepth = c_vAlphaSoftDepth.zw;\n\n#ifdef DEPTH_FADE\n  // depth range and rcp of tex dim \n  _CregF( float4, c_vDepthSize, 11);\n  static float2 c_v1oDepthSize  = c_vDepthSize.xy;\n  static float  c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepthSize.z;\n  static float  c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepthSize.w;\n#endif\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vProjUVLeftRight, 0);    // projection UV, .xy=left eye, .zw=right eye\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosProjZ,1);    // vertex position in world space (.xyz), .w=projection Z\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV12,   2);    // .xy=bump1 UV; .zw=bump2 UV\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV34,   3);    // .xy=bump3 UV; .zw=bump4 UV\n  _inReg( float4, vWeightsUV,  4);    // .xy=maskUV, .z=bumps, .w=reflection, \n  _inReg( float3,  vVexDepthFoze,   5); // .x=depth, .y=fog, .z=haze amount    \n  _inReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 6);\n#ifdef DEPTH_FADE\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n#endif\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n\n// main function\nPS_ENTRY( RipplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vViewPosAbsPix = VRSelect(c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight);\n\n  // (final output)\n  float4 vOutColor;\n\n  // calculate view distance and direction (in absolute space)\n  float3 vViewDistAbs = g_vViewPosAbsPix.xyz - PS_IN( vVexPosProjZ.xyz);\n  float3 vViewDirAbs  = normalize( vViewDistAbs); \n  float3 vMask;\n  vMask.z = 1.0f;\n\n  // compute viewing angle\n  float fViewNorAngle = dot( PS_IN( mTanToAbs[2]), vViewDirAbs);\n  fViewNorAngle = abs( fViewNorAngle);\n\n  // sample mask texture\n  vMask.xy = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, PS_IN( vWeightsUV.xy)).ar;\n  // mix with pixel (vertex weights)\n  vMask.xy *= PS_IN( vWeightsUV.zw);\n\n  // if using depth softness\n#ifdef DEPTH_FADE\n\n  // sample depth\n  float2 vDepthCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oDepthSize));\n  float fTexDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoord).r;\n  fTexDepth = saturate( fTexDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // calculate depth difference\n  float fDepthDiff = fTexDepth - PS_IN( vVexDepthFoze.x);\n  // attenuate it by viewing angle (so that it looks fine in the distance)\n  // and add a little bias for extreme case like grazing angles\n  // (big_depth_difference * angle_0 = wrong_result!)\n  fDepthDiff *= saturate( abs( fViewNorAngle) +0.001f);\n\n  // calculate attenuation factor for that\n  float2 vAttenuation = saturate( fDepthDiff *c_vSoftDepth);\n  // better gradients are with squared attenuation\n  // (but only for shore, not depth color!)\n  vAttenuation.x *= vAttenuation.x;\n\n  // attenuate weights by it\n  vMask *= vAttenuation.xxy;\n  // apply shore softness to depth (refraction color) softness\n  vMask.z *= vMask.y;\n\n#endif\n\n  // projection mapping\n  float2 vProjUV = VRSelect(PS_IN( vProjUVLeftRight.xy), PS_IN(vProjUVLeftRight.zw));\n  float2 vcrdProj = vProjUV / PS_IN( vVexPosProjZ.ww);\n\n  // water bumps\n  float4 vNormals[2];\n  float4 vNor;\n  vNor = texSample2D( t_sBumpMap,  s_tBumpMap,  PS_IN( vBumpUV12.xy));\n  vNormals[0].xy = nor2Du( vNor);\n  vNor = texSample2D( t_sBumpMap2, s_tBumpMap2, PS_IN( vBumpUV12.zw));\n  vNormals[0].zw = nor2Du( vNor);\n  vNor = texSample2D( t_sBumpMap3, s_tBumpMap3, PS_IN( vBumpUV34.xy));\n  vNormals[1].xy = nor2Du( vNor);\n  vNor = texSample2D( t_sBumpMap4, s_tBumpMap4, PS_IN( vBumpUV34.zw));\n  vNormals[1].zw = nor2Du( vNor);\n  // (signed and flipped!)\n  vNormals[0] = vNormals[0] *(-2.0f) +1.0f;\n  vNormals[1] = vNormals[1] *(-2.0f) +1.0f;\n\n  // calculate UV adjustment numbers\n  // (attenuated by bump biases)\n  vNormals[0] *= c_vBumpsBias.xxyy;\n  vNormals[1] *= c_vBumpsBias.zzww;\n  vNormals[0] += vNormals[1];\n  float2 vcrdAdj = vNormals[0].xy + vNormals[0].zw;\n  // attenuate by weights also\n  vcrdAdj *= vMask.x;\n\n  // calculate average normal (in tangent space)\n  float3 vNormalTan;\n  vNormalTan.xy = vcrdAdj;\n  vNormalTan.z  = CalcNormalZ( vNormalTan.xy);\n  // and (re)normalize it\n  vNormalTan = normalize( vNormalTan);\n\n#ifndef NO_REFRACTION\n\n  // sample refraction\n  float4 vtexRefr = texLod2D( t_sRefraction, s_tRefraction, MultiviewUV(vcrdProj+vcrdAdj.yx), c_fRefractBlur*vMask.x);\n  vtexRefr.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vtexRefr); // (RGBE HDR)\n\n#endif // !NO_REFRACTION\n\n  // transform normal to absolute space \n  float3 vNormalAbs = _mulT( vNormalTan, PS_IN( mTanToAbs)); \n  // and renormalize\n  vNormalAbs = normalize( vNormalAbs); \n\n  // calc distance from viewer\n  float fDist = length( vViewDistAbs);\n\n  // sample reflection\n#ifdef CUBE_REFLECTION\n\n  // cube...\n  // reflect eye vector around normal; 2N(N.E) - E(N.N) \n  float3 vReflectDir = reflect( vViewDistAbs, vNormalAbs);\n  // switch north-south faces because of left-hand orientation\n  vReflectDir.xy = -vReflectDir.xy;\n\n  // sample cube reflection map (RGBE format, 5-bit signed exponent)  \n  float4 vtexRefl = texLodCube( t_sReflection, s_tReflection, vReflectDir, c_fReflectBlur);\n  vtexRefl.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vtexRefl);\n\n  // attenuate by viewer's distance (up to 1 meter)\n  vMask.yz *= saturate( fDist);\n\n#else // !CUBE_REFLECTION\n\n  // attenuate by viewer distance and angle towards surface\n  fViewNorAngle = pow( fViewNorAngle, 0.666f);\n  vMask.yz *= saturate( fDist* fViewNorAngle);\n\n  // projective\n  float4 vtexRefl = texLod2D( t_sReflection, s_tReflection, MultiviewUV(vcrdProj+vcrdAdj.xy), c_fReflectBlur);\n  vtexRefl.rgb = UnpackRGBE( vtexRefl);\n\n#endif // CUBE_REFLECTION\n\n  // modulate texture by constant color\n  vOutColor.rgb = c_vcolRefl.rgb * vtexRefl.rgb;\n  // and force opaque alpha\n  vOutColor.a = 1.0f;\n\n  // calc refraction translucency \n  float fRefrFactor = c_vcolRefl.a;\n  // attenuate refraction by fresnel term\n  float fNdotV = saturate( dot( vViewDirAbs, vNormalAbs));\n  fRefrFactor *= pow( 1.0f-fNdotV, c_fFresnelPower);\n\n  // if has refraction texture\n#ifndef NO_REFRACTION\n\n  // lerp refraction to constant color\n  vtexRefr.rgb = lerp( vtexRefr.rgb, c_vcolRefr.rgb, vMask.z*c_vcolRefr.a);\n  // lerp between reflection and refraction\n  vOutColor.rgb = lerp( vtexRefr.rgb, vOutColor.rgb, fRefrFactor*vMask.y);\n  \n  // if no refraction\n#else\n\n  // apply depth fade to translucency\n  float4 vcolRefr = c_vcolRefr * vMask.z;\n  // lerp between reflection fully translucent\n  vOutColor = lerp( vcolRefr, vOutColor, fRefrFactor*vMask.y);\n\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  float2 vFozeStrength = PS_IN( vVexDepthFoze.yz);\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, vFozeStrength);\n\n  // lerp color and/or alpha for output (depends on mask)\n  vOutColor = lerp( vOutColor, c_vLerpDest, c_vLerpMask*(1.0f-vOutColor.a));\n\n#endif\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// RippleShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0); \n_CregF( float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n// object (model) to world matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 5); \n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, 8);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight, 9);\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n\n// mappings for bumps\n// (these needs to be sqeuential!)\n_CregM42F( c_mBumpMapping,  14);\n_CregM42F( c_mBumpMapping2, 16);\n_CregM42F( c_mBumpMapping3, 18);\n_CregM42F( c_mBumpMapping4, 20);\n_CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping,  22);\n\n// normal and tangent signed/unsigned masks\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorTanMask, 24);\n// 3rd row (Z) of model-view matrix\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewDist, 25);\n// weights mask (.x=mul, .y=add)\n_CregF( float2, c_vWeightsMask, 26);\n\n\n// vertex shader input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vTangent,  2);\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,  3); // bumps, reflection\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV1,  4);\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV2,  5);\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV3,  6);\n  _inReg( float4, vBumpUV4,  7);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,   8);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// vertex shader output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vProjUVLeftRight, 0);   // projection UV, .xy=left eye, .zw=right eye\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosProjZ,1);   // vertex position in world space (.xyz), .w=projection Z\n  _outReg( float4, vBumpUV12,   2);   // .xy=bump1 UV; .zw=bump2 UV\n  _outReg( float4, vBumpUV34,   3);   // .xy=bump3 UV; .zw=bump4 UV\n  _outReg( float4, vWeightsUV,  4);   // .xy=maskUV, .z=bumps, .w=reflection, \n  _outReg( float3,  vVexDepthFoze,   5); // .x=depth, .y=fog, .z=haze amount\n  _outReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 6);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( RippleVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // project point\n  float4 vInPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  float4 vClipPosLeft = mul( vInPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  float4 vClipPosRight = mul( vInPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n  VS_OUT_POS = vClipPosLeft;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = vClipPosRight;\n\n  // calculate projection coords\n  // (adjusted by perspective divisor)\n#if _HLSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  // (need to flip coord because of flipped texture RT)\n  VS_OUT( vProjUVLeftRight.xy) = vClipPosLeft.xy *float2( 0.5f,-0.5f) +vClipPosLeft.w*0.5f;\n  VS_OUT( vProjUVLeftRight.zw) = vClipPosRight.xy *float2( 0.5f,-0.5f) +vClipPosRight.w*0.5f;\n#else\n  // (already flipped under GLSL or CG!)\n  VS_OUT( vProjUVLeftRight.xy) = vClipPosLeft.xy *float2( 0.5f, 0.5f) +vClipPosLeft.w*0.5f;\n  VS_OUT( vProjUVLeftRight.zw) = vClipPosRight.xy *float2( 0.5f, 0.5f) +vClipPosRight.w*0.5f;\n#endif\n\n  // transform vertex position to absolute space\n  float4 vOutTexPosProjZ;\n  vOutTexPosProjZ.xyz = mulM43F( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToAbs);\n  // and store perspective divider\n  vOutTexPosProjZ.w = vClipPosLeft.w;\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosProjZ) = vOutTexPosProjZ;\n\n  // bumps' UV-mappings\n  VS_OUT( vBumpUV12.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vBumpUV1), c_mBumpMapping);\n  VS_OUT( vBumpUV12.zw) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vBumpUV2), c_mBumpMapping2);\n  VS_OUT( vBumpUV34.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vBumpUV3), c_mBumpMapping3);\n  VS_OUT( vBumpUV34.zw) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vBumpUV4), c_mBumpMapping4);\n  // mask's UV-mapping\n  VS_OUT( vWeightsUV.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vMaskUV), c_mMaskMapping);\n\n  // and (possibly masked out) weights\n  float2 vInWeights = VS_IN( vWeights).xy;\n  VS_OUT( vWeightsUV.zw) = vInWeights *c_vWeightsMask.x +c_vWeightsMask.y; \n\n  // expand normal and tangent (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal(  VS_IN( vNormal),  c_vNorTanMask.yyyx);\n  float4 vTan = ExpandTangent( VS_IN( vTangent), c_vNorTanMask.wwwz);\n\n  // tangent-space transformation matrix\n  float3 vBinormal = cross( vNor*vTan.w, vTan.xyz);\n  float3x3 mOutTanToAbs = float3x3( vTan.xyz, vBinormal, vNor);\n  // goes to absolute space\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n#if _GLSL\n  mObjToAbsRot = transpose( mObjToAbsRot);\n#endif\n  // with fixed stretching and (re)normalizing\n  FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n  mOutTanToAbs = _mulT( mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRot);\n  VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = NormalizeRotation( mOutTanToAbs);\n\n  // output depth value from Z for depth comparison (in meters) and\n  VS_OUT( vVexDepthFoze.x) = dot( vInPos, c_vViewDist);\n\n  // calculate fog and haze amount\n  float4 vViewPosAbsVex = VRMiddle(c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight);\n  float3 vVexDist = vOutTexPosProjZ.xyz - vViewPosAbsVex.xyz;\n  float  fVexDist = length( vVexDist); // (via precached vertex-viewer distance)\n  VS_OUT( vVexDepthFoze.y) = CalcFogAmount( float4( vOutTexPosProjZ.xyz,1), vViewPosAbsVex, fVexDist);\n  VS_OUT( vVexDepthFoze.z) = CalcHazeAmount( vOutTexPosProjZ.y, fVexDist);\n\n  // go with that to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SimpleShaders.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProjLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vModelViewProjRightX, 4);\n\n#ifdef run_SimpleVS\n\n// gamma and exposure (with HDR normalization!) correction\n_CregF( float3, c_vVexMisc, 5);\nstatic float c_fGamma    = c_vVexMisc.x;\nstatic float c_fExposure = c_vVexMisc.y;\n// virtual depth (for stereoscopic 3D)\nstatic float c_fVirtualDepth = c_vVexMisc.z;\n\n// constant color\n_CregF( float4, c_vConstColor, 6);\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos,   0);\n#ifdef USE_TEX\n  _inReg( float3, vInTexUV, 1);\n#endif\n#ifdef COLOR_ARRAY\n  _inReg( float4, vColorMap,2);\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vVexCol,0);\n#ifdef USE_TEX\n  _outReg( float3, vTexUV, 1);\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( SimpleVS)\n{\n  // output\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProjLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), VRRightMatrix(c_mModelViewProjLeft, c_vModelViewProjRightX));\n#ifdef USE_TEX\n  VS_OUT( vTexUV) = VS_IN( vInTexUV);\n#endif\n\n#ifdef COLOR_ARRAY\n  // use color array  (depends on mask)\n  float4 vOutColor = VS_IN( vColorMap);\n#else\n  // or constant color\n  float4 vOutColor = c_vConstColor;\n#endif\n\n  // apply gamma correction on color (if any)\n  vOutColor.rgb = pow( vOutColor.rgb, _tcast( float3,c_fGamma));\n  // apply exposure correction (if any)\n  vOutColor.rgb *= c_fExposure;\n\n  // and virtual depth\n  VS_OUT_POS *= c_fVirtualDepth;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT *= c_fVirtualDepth;\n  VS_OUT( vVexCol) = vOutColor;\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_SimpleVS\n#ifdef run_NakedVS\n\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// very simple vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( NakedVS)\n{\n  // object to clip space\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProjLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), VRRightMatrix(c_mModelViewProjLeft, c_vModelViewProjRightX));\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_NakedVS\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n#ifdef USE_TEX\n  #if defined(ARRAY_TEX)\n    _SregAry2D( t_sTexAry2D, s_tTexAry2D, 0);\n  #elif defined(CUBE_TEX)\n    // cube texture\n    _SregCUBE( t_sTexCube, s_tTexCube, 0);\n  #else\n    // 2D texture\n    _Sreg2D( t_sTex2D, s_tTex2D, 0);\n  #endif\n#endif\n_CregF( float4, c_vPixMisc1, 0); // .x=RGBE texture, .y=multi-view (2D!) texture\nstatic float  c_fTexRGBE = c_vPixMisc1.x;\nstatic float  c_fMultiView = c_vPixMisc1.y;\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange = c_vPixMisc1.zw;\n#if defined(ARRAY_TEX)\n  _CregF( float4, c_vPixMisc2, 1); // .x=array slice\n  static float c_fArraySliceAdd = c_vPixMisc2.x;\n#endif\n\n// PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vVexCol,0);\n#ifdef USE_TEX\n  _inReg( float3, vTexUV, 1);\n#endif\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( SimplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // get vertex color\n  float4 vOutColor = PS_IN( vVexCol);\n\n#ifdef USE_TEX\n\n  #if defined(ARRAY_TEX)\n    // sample array texture\n    float3 vInTex = PS_IN( vTexUV);\n    vInTex.z += c_fArraySliceAdd;\n    float4 vTexture = texSample2D( t_sTexAry2D, s_tTexAry2D, vInTex);\n  #elif defined(CUBE_TEX)  \n    // sample cube texture\n    float4 vTexture = texSampleCube( t_sTexCube, s_tTexCube, PS_IN( vTexUV));  \n  #else\n    // sample 2D texture\n    float2 vTexMV = MultiviewUVConditional( PS_IN( vTexUV.xy), c_fMultiView);\n    float4 vTexture = texSample2D( t_sTex2D, s_tTex2D, vTexMV);\n  #endif\n  // if texture is in RGBE format\n  float4 vUnpacked;\n  vUnpacked.rgb = vTexture.rgb * exp2( vTexture.a *32.0f -16.0f);\n  vUnpacked.a = 1.0f;\n\n  // based on texture state choose whether unpacked on normal texture color is used\n  float4 vTexColor = (c_fTexRGBE>=0.0f) ? vUnpacked : vTexture;\n  // and modulate final color with texture\n  vOutColor *= vTexColor; \n\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n\n#endif // USE_TEX\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SlopeShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProj, 0); \n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\n  _inReg( float3, vInNor, 1);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float3, vNormal, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( SlopeVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // output all\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vInPos), c_mModelViewProj);\n  VS_OUT( vNormal) = VS_IN( vInNor);\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// pixel input(s)\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float3, vNormal, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( SlopePS)\n{\n  // final output\n  float fSlope = PS_IN( vNormal.y);\n  PS_OUT( float4( fSlope, fSlope, fSlope, 1));\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SmartBlurShader.psh\n\n\n// handy macros\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// scene depth and SSAO textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sBufDist, s_tBufDist, 0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sBufSSAO, s_tBufSSAO, 1);\n\n// sampling pixel distance\n_CregF( float3, c_vDistMiscMod, 0);\nstatic float c_fDistance        = c_vDistMiscMod.x;\nstatic float c_fWeaponRadiusMul = c_vDistMiscMod.y;\nstatic float c_fFOVAdjust       = c_vDistMiscMod.z;\n\n// Z-buffer scale and offset\n_CregF( float2, c_vDepthScaler, 1);\nstatic float c_fDepthNear    = c_vDepthScaler.x;\nstatic float c_f1oDepthRange = c_vDepthScaler.y;\n\n// tex coords stepping for screen and depth buffers\n_CregF( float4, c_vScrDepthSteps, 2);\nstatic float2 c_vScreenStep = c_vScrDepthSteps.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vDepthStep  = c_vScrDepthSteps.zw;\n\n// SSAO radius modulation data\n_CregF( float4, c_vFocusStretch, 3);\nstatic float c_fFocusDistance   = c_vFocusStretch.x;\nstatic float c_f1oFocusDistance = c_vFocusStretch.y;\nstatic float c_fMaxStretch      = c_vFocusStretch.z;\nstatic float c_f1oStretchRange  = c_vFocusStretch.w;\n\n#if BLUR_SAMPLES == 5\n\n  // blur pivot weight\n  static const float c_fPivotWeight = 0.295513f;\n  // blur sample weights (inner, outer)\n  static const float2 c_avBlurSampleWeights[1] = {\n    float2( 0.22461f, 0.0986244f),\n  };\n\n#elif BLUR_SAMPLES == 9\n\n  // blur pivot weight\n  static const float c_fPivotWeight = 0.221635f;\n  // blur sample weights\n  static const float2 c_avBlurSampleWeights[2] = {\n    float2( 0.18994f,   0.119551f),\n    float2( 0.0552651f, 0.0187631f)\n  };\n\n#elif BLUR_SAMPLES == 13\n\n  // blur pivot weight\n  static const float c_fPivotWeight = 0.160218f;\n  // blur sample weights\n  static const float2 c_avBlurSampleWeights[3] = {\n    float2( 0.147804f,  0.116043f),\n    float2( 0.0775358f, 0.04409f),\n    float2( 0.0213369f, 0.00878772f)\n  };\n\n#endif // BLUR_SAMPLES\n\n\n// loop iteration steps\n#define BLUR_STEPS ((BLUR_SAMPLES-1)/4)\n\n\n// rectangle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n/// Ambient occlusion blur\nPS_ENTRY( SmartBlurPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // get input tex coords\n  float4 vInTexCoords = PS_IN( vTexCoords);\n  float4 vTexCoordsMV = MultiviewUV2( vInTexCoords);\n\n  // get pivot AO value\n  float4 vResult;\n  vResult.rgb = _tcast( float3, 0);\n  vResult.a = texSample2D( t_sBufSSAO, s_tBufSSAO, vTexCoordsMV.xy).a;\n  // get pivot's raw depth\n  float fRawPivotDepth = texSample2D( t_sBufDist, s_tBufDist, vTexCoordsMV.zw).r;\n\n  // (ignore background pixels)\n  if( fRawPivotDepth > 0.95f) {\n    PS_OUT( vResult);\n  }\n\n  // linearize pivot's depth\n  float fPivotDepth = DECODE_DEPTH(fRawPivotDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n\n  // Compute SSAO radius multiplier. We want:\n  // - smaller radius for close-ups (to prevent a huge performance drop, due to sampling a very large area of screen; bonus: capture small surface details)\n  // - larger radius for distant objects (practicaly free, due to still small screen-space sampling area; more noticable and visually pleasing AO shadows for distant occluders)\n          \n  // for pixels futher away than focus distance, lerp the multiplier between 1.0f and max stretch factor, based on pixel depth\n  float fSceneRadiusMul = c_fMaxStretch* saturate( (-fPivotDepth-c_fFocusDistance) *c_f1oStretchRange) +1.0f;\n  // for pixels closer than focus distance, lerp the multiplier between 0.0f and 1.0f, based on pixel depth\n  fSceneRadiusMul *= saturate( -fPivotDepth * c_f1oFocusDistance); \n\n  // select proper multiplier for scene / first person weapon rendering\n  float fRadiusMultiplier = fRawPivotDepth<0.0f ? c_fWeaponRadiusMul : fSceneRadiusMul;\n  // Scale AO radius by FOV adjustment factor (wide FOV allows for a wide radius, narrow FOV requires a narrow radius).\n  // Note: weapon radius is adjusted by scene FOV factor. This produces errors because weapon renders in its own FOV. \n  // The correct solution would be to use different projection matrices for reconstructing samples' view space positions, \n  // depending on whether sampled depth is negative (weapon) or positive (scene). However, this would add complexity and \n  // was deemed unnecessary.\n  fRadiusMultiplier *= c_fFOVAdjust;\n\n  // determine average AO radius for current pivot\n  float fAvgAoRadius = c_fDistance * fRadiusMultiplier;\n  // determine which samples need to be discarded (by setting their weight to zero)\n  float4 vWeightSum = float4( c_fPivotWeight, 0,0,0);\n  vResult.a *= c_fPivotWeight;\n\n  // calculate initial sample coordinates for screen and depth (inner and outer)\n  float4 vScreenCoords = vInTexCoords.xyxy+ c_vScreenStep.xyxy*float4(-1.5f,-1.5f, 1.5f,1.5f);\n  float4 vDepthCoordsI = vInTexCoords.zwzw+ c_vDepthStep.xyxy *float4(-1,-1, 1,1); // (inner)\n  float4 vDepthCoordsO = vInTexCoords.zwzw+ c_vDepthStep.xyxy *float4(-2,-2, 2,2); // (outer)\n  float4 vRawSampleDepths, vSampleDepths, vDepthDeltas, vWeights;\n  float4 vScreenCoordsMV, vDepthCoordsIMV, vDepthCoordsOMV;\n  float2 vAOSamples;\n\n  // loop thru neighbour samples (processing 4 at once)\n  _unroll for( int iPass=0; iPass<BLUR_STEPS; iPass++) {\n\n    // sample raw depths\n    vDepthCoordsIMV = MultiviewUV2( vDepthCoordsI);\n    vDepthCoordsOMV = MultiviewUV2( vDepthCoordsO);\n    vRawSampleDepths.x = texSample2D( t_sBufDist, s_tBufDist, vDepthCoordsIMV.xy).r;\n    vRawSampleDepths.y = texSample2D( t_sBufDist, s_tBufDist, vDepthCoordsIMV.zw).r;\n    vRawSampleDepths.z = texSample2D( t_sBufDist, s_tBufDist, vDepthCoordsOMV.xy).r;\n    vRawSampleDepths.w = texSample2D( t_sBufDist, s_tBufDist, vDepthCoordsOMV.zw).r;\n    // sample AO buffer\n    vScreenCoordsMV = MultiviewUV2( vScreenCoords);\n    vAOSamples.x = texSample2D( t_sBufSSAO, s_tBufSSAO, vScreenCoordsMV.xy).a;\n    vAOSamples.y = texSample2D( t_sBufSSAO, s_tBufSSAO, vScreenCoordsMV.zw).a;\n\n    // linearize depths and calculate depth difference between samples and pivot\n    vSampleDepths = DECODE_DEPTH( vRawSampleDepths) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthNear;\n    vDepthDeltas  = abs( vSampleDepths - fPivotDepth);\n\n    // determine if samples need to be discarded, and if so, set their weight to zero\n  #if _HLSL\n    vWeights = (vDepthDeltas>=fAvgAoRadius) ? 0.0f : c_avBlurSampleWeights[iPass].xxyy;\n  #elif _GLSL\n    float2 vBlurSampleWeights = c_avBlurSampleWeights[ iPass];\n    vWeights.x = (vDepthDeltas.x>=fAvgAoRadius) ? 0.0f : vBlurSampleWeights.x;\n    vWeights.y = (vDepthDeltas.y>=fAvgAoRadius) ? 0.0f : vBlurSampleWeights.x;\n    vWeights.z = (vDepthDeltas.z>=fAvgAoRadius) ? 0.0f : vBlurSampleWeights.y;\n    vWeights.w = (vDepthDeltas.w>=fAvgAoRadius) ? 0.0f : vBlurSampleWeights.y;\n  #endif\n\n    // accumulate all samples and total weight\n    vResult.a += dot( vAOSamples.xyxy, vWeights);\n    vWeightSum += vWeights;\n\n  #if BLUR_STEPS > 1\n\n    // move to next tex coords for screen and depth\n    vScreenCoords += c_vScreenStep.xyxy *float4(-2,-2, 2,2);\n    vDepthCoordsI += c_vDepthStep.xyxy  *float4(-2,-2, 2,2);\n    vDepthCoordsO += c_vDepthStep.xyxy  *float4(-2,-2, 2,2);\n  #endif\n  }\n\n  // normalize result\n  float fWeights = dot( vWeightSum, _tcast(float4,1));\n  vResult.a /= fWeights;\n\n  // return result\n  PS_OUT( vResult);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// StainShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sBlendMask, s_tBlendMask, 0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sStains,    s_tStains,    1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sDetailMap, s_tDetailMap, 2);\n\n// constant colors\n_CregF( float3, c_vColStains,  0);\n_CregF( float3, c_vColBacklit, 1);\n// mixed params\n_CregF( float3, c_vDetFadeAng, 2);\nstatic float c_fDetailBias   = c_vDetFadeAng.x;\nstatic float c_fDistanceFade = c_vDetFadeAng.y;\nstatic float c_fBacklitAngle = c_vDetFadeAng.z; // (cosine!)\n// viewer position (in world space)\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, 3);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight,4);\nstatic float4 g_vViewPosAbsPix;\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // position and normal\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 0);\n  _inReg( float3, vVexNorAbs, 1);\n  // mappings\n  _inReg( float4, vStnDetUV,  2);\n  _inReg( float3, vMaskUVFoze,3);  // .z = fog/haze amount\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n\n// begin one light pass\nPS_ENTRY( StainPS)\n{\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vViewPosAbsPix = VRSelect( c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight);\n\n  // sample textures\n  float4 vMask   = texSample2D( t_sBlendMask, s_tBlendMask, PS_IN( vMaskUVFoze.xy));\n  float3 vStains = texSample2D( t_sStains,    s_tStains,    PS_IN( vStnDetUV.xy)).rgb;\n  float3 vDetails= texSample2D( t_sDetailMap, s_tDetailMap, PS_IN( vStnDetUV.zw)).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( vStains);\n  LinearSpace( vDetails);\n\n  // apply color and bias\n  vStains *= c_vColStains; \n  vStains  = lerp( _tcast(float3,1), vStains,  vMask.a);\n  vDetails = lerp( _tcast(float3,1), vDetails, vMask.b *c_fDetailBias);\n\n  // blend stains and details\n  vStains *= vDetails;\n\n  // calc distance from viewer\n  float3 vDistance = g_vViewPosAbsPix.xyz - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  float fViewDistance = length( vDistance);\n\n  // apply backlighting\n  float fNorView = dot( normalize( PS_IN( vVexNorAbs)), normalize( vDistance));\n  fNorView = 1.0f- saturate( fNorView);\n  float fFader = 1.0f- saturate( fViewDistance *0.01f);\n  fNorView = smoothstep( c_fBacklitAngle*fFader, 1.0f, fNorView); \n  vStains += c_vColBacklit;// *fNorView;\n\n  // apply (lerp to gray) distance fading and fog/haze\n  vStains = lerp( _tcast(float3,0.5f), vStains, c_fDistanceFade);\n  vStains = lerp( vStains, _tcast(float3,0.5f), PS_IN( vMaskUVFoze.z));\n  // (with alpha of 0.5, depth in alpha channel won't be affected because of SHADE blend mode)\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( vStains, 0.5f);\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// StainShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// transformation to clip, absolute or view space\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n// fog and haze calculation\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 22);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n\n// mapping constants\n_CregM42F( c_mMaskMapping, 7);\n_CregF( float4, c_vDetailMapping, 9);\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n_CregM42F( c_mStainsMapping, 14);\n\n// mapping masks for UV coords (select UV-map or XY, YZ or XY plane)\n_CregF( float3, c_vBlendMappingMask, 16);\n_CregF( float3, c_vStainMappingMask, 17);\n_CregF( float3, c_vDetMappingMask,   18);\n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, 19);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight,20);\n\n// normal and tangent signed/unsigned masks\n_CregF( float2, c_vNorMask, 21);\n\n// (c_vObjToClipRightX uses const reg c22!)\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,   2);\n  _inReg( float4, vStainsUV, 3);\n  _inReg( float2, vDetailUV, 4);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices,  5); // (matrix indices)\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,  6); // (blend weights)\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // position and normal\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 0);\n  _outReg( float3, vVexNorAbs, 1);\n  // mappings\n  _outReg( float4, vStnDetUV,  2);\n  _outReg( float3, vMaskUVFoze,3);  // .z = fog/haze amount\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( StainVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // skin position and normal\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorMask.yyyx);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  // (if needed)\n  vPos.xyz = SkinVertexNor( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor);\n#endif\n\n  // calc clip-space vertex positions\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix( c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // and world-space also\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n  vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToAbs);\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n  // and vertex normal\n  VS_OUT( vVexNorAbs) = mul( vNor, _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs));\n\n  // mapping masks\n  float4 vInMaskUV   = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vMaskUV.xy),   vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vBlendMappingMask); \n  float4 vInStainsUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vStainsUV.xy), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vStainMappingMask); \n  float2 vInDetailUV = SelectUV(  VS_IN( vDetailUV),    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vDetMappingMask); \n\n  // mapping coordinates\n  // (4-component dot product: Z is 0, W is offset; cannot use Z for offset\n  //  since 2D vectors will be expanded to X,Y,0,1, and we need 1 for dot product)\n  VS_OUT( vMaskUVFoze.xy) = mulM42F( vInMaskUV, c_mMaskMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vStnDetUV.xy) = mulM42F( vInStainsUV, c_mStainsMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vStnDetUV.zw) = vInDetailUV *c_vDetailMapping.xy +c_vDetailMapping.zw;\n\n  // calculate fog and haze amount (via precached vertex-viewer distance)\n  float4 vViewPosAbsVex = VRMiddle(c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight);\n  float fVexDist = length( vViewPosAbsVex.xyz - vOutVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  VS_OUT( vMaskUVFoze.z) = CalcFozeAmount( vOutVexPosAbs, vViewPosAbsVex, fVexDist);\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// StandardShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/RGBEConversion.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpMapping.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ParallaxMapping.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeBlend.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sBase, s_tBase, 0);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  _Sreg2D( t_sNormalMap, s_tNormalMap, 1);\n  _Sreg2D( t_sDetailMap, s_tDetailMap, 6);\n#endif\n_SregCUBE(t_sEnvMap,    s_tEnvMap,    2);\n_Sreg2D(  t_sLightMap,  s_tLightMap,  3);\n_Sreg2D(  t_sGlossMask, s_tGlossMask, 4);\n_Sreg2D(  t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, 5);\n_Sreg2D(  t_sBlendMask, s_tBlendMask, 7);\n// fast-lights & ambient-occlusuon texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, 8);\n\n// base and coating colors\n_CregF( float4, c_vColBase, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vColCoatingShade, 1);\nstatic float3 c_vColCoating    = c_vColCoatingShade.rgb;\nstatic float  c_fShadeStrength = c_vColCoatingShade.a;\n// reflection color\n_CregF( float4, c_vColReflBump, 2);\nstatic float3 c_vColRefl  = c_vColReflBump.rgb;\nstatic float  c_fReflBump = c_vColReflBump.a;\n// illumination color\n_CregF( float4, c_vColIllumFres, 3);\nstatic float3 c_vColIllum = c_vColIllumFres.rgb;\nstatic float  c_fFresnel  = c_vColIllumFres.a;\n\n// lerp destination and mask colors dependant on the blend type\n_CregF( float4, c_vLerpDestMask, 4);\nstatic float4 c_vLerpDest = c_vLerpDestMask.xxxy;\nstatic float4 c_vLerpMask = c_vLerpDestMask.zzzw;\n  // (fog/haze use const reg c5-c7!)\n  // (bump mapping uses const reg c8!)\n  // (parallax mapping uses const reg c9!)\n\n// mask for usage of FLAO texture values\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskFLAO, 10);\n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, 11);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight, 12);\nstatic float4 g_vViewPosAbsPix;\n\n// edge smoothing bias (.x) and mask (.y)\n_CregF( float4, c_vEdgeAlpha, 13);\nstatic float2 c_vEdgeSmoothing = c_vEdgeAlpha.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange    = c_vEdgeAlpha.zw;\n\n// base layer specularity\n_CregF( float4, c_vSpecMipFace, 14);\nstatic float  c_fBaseSpec = c_vSpecMipFace.x;\nstatic float  c_fCoatSpec = c_vSpecMipFace.y;\nstatic float2 c_vBaseCoatSpec = c_vSpecMipFace.xy; // (combined)\n// number of mipmaps of the reflection map        \nstatic float c_fReflMips = c_vSpecMipFace.z; \n// clockwiseness (rendering direction)\nstatic float c_fFacingness = c_vSpecMipFace.w;\n\n// offset mapping UV-map ratios\n_CregF( float4, c_vDetailOffsetRatio, 15);  // detail X (.xy), Y (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vBaseGlossOfsRatioX,16);  // base X (.xy), gloss X (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vBaseGlossOfsRatioY,17);  // base Y (.xy), gloss Y (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskOffsetRatio,   18);  // blend-mask X (.xy), Y (.zw)\n_CregF( float4, c_vNormUnstretchFade, 19);  // normal-map offset unstretched\nstatic float2 c_vNormMapUnstretch = c_vNormUnstretchFade.xy;\nstatic float  c_f1oNormalMaxDist2 = c_vNormUnstretchFade.z;\nstatic float  c_f1oHeightMaxDist2 = c_vNormUnstretchFade.w;\n\n// fake light usage mask and attenuation\n_CregF( float4, c_vFakeLightBools, 20);\nstatic float c_fFakeLightAtt  = c_vFakeLightBools.x;\nstatic float c_fFakeLightMask = c_vFakeLightBools.y;\n// baking? \n#ifdef BAKING\n  // in RGBE or LDR?                                            \n  static float c_fBakeRGBE  = c_vFakeLightBools.z;\n  static float c_fBakeGamma = c_vFakeLightBools.w;\n#endif\n\n// for screen coords sampling and colorization mask strength\n_CregF( float3, c_vScrSizeColMask, 21);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize= c_vScrSizeColMask.xy;\nstatic float  c_fColorizer   = c_vScrSizeColMask.z;\n\n\n// global vars\nstatic float4 g_vBaseColor;\nstatic float3 g_vPixNormalTan;\nstatic float4 g_vRawNorDet;\nstatic float3 g_vPixNormalAbs;\nstatic float3 g_vViewDirAbs;\nstatic float4 g_vIllumAmbOccSample = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n\n// if using ambient specularity\n#if defined(HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT) && defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && (defined(HAS_SPECULARITY) || defined(HAS_COATING))\n\n  // need vertex normal for bump attenuation\n  static float3 g_vVexNormalAbs;\n#endif\n\nstatic float4 g_vGlossTex;\n#define g_fCoatSpec g_vGlossTex.r\n#define g_fCoatMask g_vGlossTex.g\n#define g_fDetAtt   g_vGlossTex.b\n#define g_fBaseSpec g_vGlossTex.a\n#define g_vBaseCoatSpec g_vGlossTex.ar\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 0);\n  // mappings\n  _inReg( float4, vBasGlosUV, 1);\n  _inReg( float4, vLitMaskUV, 2);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormDetUV, 3);\n#ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n  // .x=fog, .y=haze amount\n  _inReg( float2, vFozeAmount, 4); \n#endif\n  _inReg( float4, vVexColor,   5);\n  _inReg( float3, vDiffuseLit, 6);\n#if defined(HAS_PARALLAX) || (defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT))\n  // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n  _inReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 7);\n#else\n  // or just vertex normal\n  _inReg( float3, vNormalAbs,  7);\n#endif\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\n  _inFacReg;\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n\n// can sample reflection map only if has specularity\n#if (defined(HAS_SPECULARITY) || defined(HAS_COATING)) && defined(HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT)\n\n\n// apply cube reflection map\ninline float3 GetReflectionMap( float4 vReflect, const float3 vReflMask)\n{\n  // choose cube LOD\n  vReflect.xyz -= vReflect.xyz * vReflMask / exp2( c_fReflMips-floor(vReflect.w));\n  // == vReflect.xyz *= lerp( 1, 1- 1/exp2(c_fReflMips-floor(vReflect.w)), vReflMask);\n  // lookup the reflection texture\n  vReflect.rgba = texLodCube( t_sEnvMap, s_tEnvMap, vReflect.xyz, vReflect.w);\n  vReflect.rgb  = UnpackRGBE( vReflect);\n  // modulate by constant reflection color\n  return vReflect.rgb * c_vColRefl;\n}\n\n\n// Evaluate Schlick BRDF function for ambient light.\ninline float3 CalcAmbientReflection(void)\n{\n  // (common vars for base and coating layer)\n  float3 vReflectCol, vNorAbs;\n  float4 vReflectDir;\n\n  // get normal\n#ifndef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  // from vertex\n  vNorAbs = g_vPixNormalAbs;\n#elif defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT)\n  // attenuated from pixel\n  vNorAbs = lerp( g_vVexNormalAbs, g_vPixNormalAbs, _tcast(float3,c_fReflBump));\n#else\n  // faked from pixel\n  vNorAbs = g_vVexNormalAbs;\n  vNorAbs.xy -= g_vPixNormalTan.xy *c_fReflBump;\n#endif\n  // calculate reflection fresnel factor\n  float fNV = saturate( dot( vNorAbs, g_vViewDirAbs));\n  float fF = pow( 1.0f-fNV, 4.0f) * c_fFresnel;\n\n  // and get specularity of the base (.x) and coating (.y) layers\n  float2 vR = g_vBaseCoatSpec- g_vBaseCoatSpec*fF; // lerp( vR, 0, fF);\n\n  // reflect eye vector around normal; 2N(N.E) - E(N.N)\n  vReflectDir.xyz = reflect( g_vViewDirAbs, vNorAbs);\n\n  // if no coating layer\n  #ifndef HAS_COATING\n    // use base layer reflection factor\n    float fSA = vR.x;\n  // if no base layer\n  #elif !defined(HAS_SPECULARITY)\n    // use coating layer reflection factor\n    float fSA = vR.y;\n  // if has both layers\n  #else\n    // use average\n    float fSA = (vR.x+vR.y) *0.5f;\n  #endif\n  // attenuate reflection vector by specularity factor\n  vReflectDir.xyz = lerp( vReflectDir.xyz, -vNorAbs, _tcast(float3,fSA));\n  // (no need for renormalization, since this vector will be used for sampling cubemap)\n//vReflectDir.xyz = normalize( vReflectDir.xyz);  \n  // (\"reflect()\" function returns negative vector, so we need to switch .xy, instead of .z,\n  //  but it'll be done a bit later...)\n//vReflectDir.xy = -vReflectDir.xy; \n\n  // add sharpening bias because of the specifically convoluted mipmaps\n  float3 vReflAbs = abs( vReflectDir.xyz);\n  float fMax = max( vReflAbs.x, max( vReflAbs.y, vReflAbs.z));\n  float fMaxTolerance = fMax -0.001f;\n  float3 vReflMask = step( vReflAbs, _tcast( float3,fMaxTolerance));  // 1 where max, 0 where UV\n  vReflectDir.xyz *= float3(-1,-1,1) / fMax;  // (includes \"vReflectDir.xy = -vReflectDir.xy\")\n\n  // for a start, base color is just diffuse\n  float3 vBase = g_vBaseColor.rgb; \n\n  // if base layer has specularity\n#ifdef HAS_SPECULARITY\n\n  // get reflection map using base specularity as a blur factor\n  vReflectDir.w = vR.x * (c_fReflMips-1.0f);\n  vReflectCol = GetReflectionMap( vReflectDir, vReflMask);\n  \n  // calculate final color by lerping between white (diffuse) and specular (reflection) values\n  // (it has to be multiplied by diffuse because the reflection map is divided by the spherical harmonics)\n  vR.x = saturate( vR.x *2.0f -1.0f); // (lean towards reflectivity a bit)\n  vBase *= lerp( vReflectCol, _tcast(float3,1), vR.xxx);\n\n#endif // HAS_SPECULARITY\n\n  // if there is a coating layer\n#ifdef HAS_COATING\n\n  // get reflection map using coating specularity as a blur factor\n  vReflectDir.w = vR.y * (c_fReflMips-1.0f);\n  vReflectCol = GetReflectionMap( vReflectDir, vReflMask);\n\n  // calculate final color by lerping between diffuse and specular (reflection) values\n  float3 vC  = c_vColCoating * g_fCoatMask * g_fCoatMask;\n  float3 vCF = lerp( vC, _tcast(float3,1), _tcast(float3,fF));\n  vR.y = saturate( vR.y *2.0f -1.0f);\n  float3 vCoat = lerp( vC*vReflectCol, vC, vR.yyy);\n  \n  // blend the layers by fresnel\n  vBase = lerp( vBase, vCoat, vCF);\n\n#endif // HAS_COATING\n\n  // done\n  return vBase;\n}\n\n#endif // (HAS_SPECULARITY || HAS_COATING) && HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n\n#ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n\n// Evaluate Schlick BRDF function for given incoming light.\n/*\n  Division by PI was removed because lights are pre-divided by PI. Extra division \n  by 4 in the original formula seems to be an error. (It yields 1/4 of expected\n  result for perfectly diffuse reflector.) So it was removed as well.\n  V and L were removed from denominator of D and from nominators of GV and GL.\n*/\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  // lambert diffuse light component\n  float  fL = saturate( dot( g_vPixNormalAbs, vLightDirAbs));\n  float3 vB = g_vBaseColor.rgb;\n\n  // if needs specular component\n#if defined(HAS_SPECULARITY) || defined(HAS_COATING)\n\n  // calculate half vector and light fresnel\n  float3 vH = normalize( g_vViewDirAbs + vLightDirAbs);\n  float fHV = saturate( dot( vH, g_vViewDirAbs));\n  float  fF = pow( 1.0f-fHV, 4.0f) * c_fFresnel;\n\n  // get specularity for the base (.x) and coating (.y) layers\n  float2 vR = g_vBaseCoatSpec- g_vBaseCoatSpec*fF; // lerp( vR, 0, fF);\n  vR = saturate( pow( vR, _tcast(float2,4)) +0.0000001f);\n\n  // calculate dot products, view-normal and half vector\n  float fNV = saturate( dot( g_vPixNormalAbs, g_vViewDirAbs));\n  float fVL = sqrt( max( fNV*fL, 0.01f));\n  float fHN = dot( vH, g_vPixNormalAbs);\n\n  // spread specularity\n  float fDT = 0.00001f;\n  fDT += fwidth( fHN) *0.5f;\n  float2 vT2 = saturate( fHN+ fDT*float2(-1,1));\n  fDT = vT2.y-vT2.x +0.000001f;\n\n  // evaluate the base (.x) and coating layer (.y) diffuse factors\n  float4 vI2 = (vT2.xyxy*vR.xxyy) / (vT2.xyxy*(vR.xxyy-1.0f)+1.0f);\n  vI2 = saturate( vI2);\n  float2 vD = (vI2.yw-vI2.xz) / (fDT * lerp( _tcast(float2,fVL), _tcast(float2,1), vR.xy));\n\n  // if base layer has specularity\n  #ifdef HAS_SPECULARITY\n    // apply it now\n    vB *= vD.x;\n  #endif\n\n  // if there is a coating layer (specularity assumed)\n  #ifdef HAS_COATING\n    // return blended result between the layers\n    float3 vC = c_vColCoating * g_fCoatMask * g_fCoatMask;\n    vB = lerp( vB, vD.yyy, vC);\n  #endif\n\n#endif // (HAS_SPECULARITY || HAS_COATING)\n\n  // mix eventual specular with diffuse\n  return vB *fL;\n}\n\n\n#endif // HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n\n// calculate ambient light intensity\ninline float3 AmbientLight( const float2 vLMapUV, const float3 vDiffuseLight, const float fFakeMask)\n{\n  // light color is self-illumination \n  float3 vLightColor = c_vColIllum;\n  // modulated by HDR lightmap\n  vLightColor *= SampleRGBE( t_sLightMap, s_tLightMap, vLMapUV);\n  // and overlayed by diffuse light\n  vLightColor += vDiffuseLight;\n\n  // modulate by ambient occlusion\n  vLightColor *= g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  // and modulate illumination (fast-)light influence by it\n  g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a = g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  float3 vIllumLight = g_vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // if has ambient specular component\n#if defined(HAS_SPECULARITY) || defined(HAS_COATING)\n\n  // calculate \"specularity\" from reflection map\n  vLightColor *= CalcAmbientReflection();\n  // and add illumination (fast-)light modulated by diffuse texture\n  vLightColor += vIllumLight * g_vBaseColor.rgb;\n\n  // if no specularity\n#else\n\n  // add illumination (fast-)light\n  vLightColor += vIllumLight;\n  // and modulate by diffuse (texture) color\n  vLightColor *= g_vBaseColor.rgb;\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n  // need some fake bumps on diffuse lightmapped surfaces no matter the actual lighting\n  float fFakeAtt = saturate( fFakeMask+c_fFakeLightMask) *c_fFakeLightAtt;\n  float2 vRawNorTan = g_vRawNorDet.xy *fFakeAtt +g_vRawNorDet.zw;\n  float fFakeLightMul = vRawNorTan.x - vRawNorTan.y;\n  // apply fake bumps (if any)\n  vLightColor += vLightColor*fFakeLightMul;\n\n#endif\n\n  // final color\n  return vLightColor;\n}\n\n#endif // HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n\n\n// MAIN RENDERING PASS\n\nPS_ENTRY( StandardPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vViewPosAbsPix = VRSelect(c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight);\n\n  // calculate pixel-view distance(^2!) and direction\n\n  g_vViewDirAbs = g_vViewPosAbsPix.xyz - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  float fPixDist2 = dot( g_vViewDirAbs, g_vViewDirAbs);\n  g_vViewDirAbs *= rsqrt( fPixDist2); // ==normalize\n\n  // cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n\n  // prepare textures' coordinates\n  float2 vMaskUV = PS_IN( vLitMaskUV.zw);\n  float4 vNormDetOfsUV = PS_IN( vNormDetUV);\n  float4 vBasGlosOfsUV = PS_IN( vBasGlosUV);\n  float4 vOffsetAmbDepthMask;\n\n  // and if rendering with parallax mapping\n  #if !defined(BAKING) && defined(HAS_PARALLAX)\n\n    // calc attenuation by distance for height\n    float fHeightAtt = 1.0f- saturate( fPixDist2*c_f1oHeightMaxDist2); \n\n    // transform view direction to tangent space\n    float3 vViewDirTan = _mulT( PS_IN( mTanToAbs), g_vViewDirAbs);  // (already normalized!)\n    // calculate parallaxing offset\n    vOffsetAmbDepthMask = GetMappingOffset( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, vNormDetOfsUV.xy, fHeightAtt, vViewDirTan, fPixDist2);\n\n    // apply that offset to texture coords\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    // for normal-map\n    vNormDetOfsUV.xy += vOffsetAmbDepthMask.xy;\n  #endif\n    // (unstretch offset)\n    vOffsetAmbDepthMask.xy *= c_vNormMapUnstretch;\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    // for detail-map\n    vNormDetOfsUV.zw += vOffsetAmbDepthMask.xx*c_vDetailOffsetRatio.xy + vOffsetAmbDepthMask.yy*c_vDetailOffsetRatio.zw;\n  #endif\n    // and blend-mask ratio\n    vMaskUV += vOffsetAmbDepthMask.xx*c_vMaskOffsetRatio.xy + vOffsetAmbDepthMask.yy*c_vMaskOffsetRatio.zw;\n    // and/or base (diffuse) texture and gloss mask\n    vBasGlosOfsUV += vOffsetAmbDepthMask.xxxx*c_vBaseGlossOfsRatioX + vOffsetAmbDepthMask.yyyy*c_vBaseGlossOfsRatioY;\n\n  // if no parallaxing\n  #else\n\n    // just sample ambient depth texture\n    vOffsetAmbDepthMask.zw = texSample2D( t_sHeightMap, s_tHeightMap, vNormDetOfsUV.xy).gb;\n\n  #endif\n\n  // sample mask alpha usage for blending and shading\n  float4 vBlendMaskTex = texSample2D( t_sBlendMask, s_tBlendMask, vMaskUV);\n  LinearSpace( vBlendMaskTex.rgb);\n  // \"shade\" (multiply 2x) mode in linear space\n  vBlendMaskTex.rgb *= LINEAR_2; \n  // (attenuated)\n  vBlendMaskTex.rgb = lerp( _tcast(float3,1), vBlendMaskTex.rgb, _tcast(float3,c_fShadeStrength));  \n\n  // sample diffuse texture\n  float4 vBaseTex = texSample2D( t_sBase, s_tBase, vBasGlosOfsUV.xy);\n  LinearSpace( vBaseTex.rgb);\n  // modulate diffuse color by texture and vertex colors\n  g_vBaseColor = vBaseTex * c_vColBase * PS_IN( vVexColor);\n\n  // attenuate colorizer by some (any?) amount via alpha value\n  float fColorize = (1.0f-vBaseTex.a) * c_fColorizer;\n  g_vBaseColor.rgb = lerp( g_vBaseColor.rgb, vBaseTex.rgb, _tcast( float3,fColorize));\n\n  // also sample gloss mask (will be used later, channel by channel)\n  g_vGlossTex = texSample2D( t_sGlossMask, s_tGlossMask, vBasGlosOfsUV.zw);\n\n  // if has specularity or coating layer,\n  #if defined(HAS_SPECULARITY) || defined(HAS_COATING)\n\n    // combine their constant specular factors with gloss mask\n    g_vBaseCoatSpec = 1.0f- c_vBaseCoatSpec *g_vBaseCoatSpec;\n  #endif\n\n  // shade base color by blend mask texel\n  g_vBaseColor *= vBlendMaskTex;\n\n  // if has normal map\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n    // calc attenuation by distance for bumps\n    float fBumpAtt = 1.0f- saturate( fPixDist2*c_f1oNormalMaxDist2); \n    // (.x=all bumps attenuation, .y=only detail bump attenuation)\n    float2 vNorDetAtt = float2( fBumpAtt, g_fDetAtt); \n\n    // sample normal (and detail) maps' normal value\n    g_vPixNormalTan = GetBumpedNormal( t_sNormalMap, s_tNormalMap, t_sDetailMap, s_tDetailMap, vNormDetOfsUV, vNorDetAtt, g_vRawNorDet);\n\n    #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n      // and transform it to absolute space\n      g_vPixNormalAbs = _mulT( g_vPixNormalTan, PS_IN( mTanToAbs));\n    #else\n      // or just use tangent space\n      g_vPixNormalAbs = g_vPixNormalTan;\n    #endif\n\n  // if doesn't have normal map\n  #else\n\n    // normal is from vertex then\n    g_vPixNormalTan = float3(0,0,1);\n    #if defined(HAS_PARALLAX)\n      g_vPixNormalAbs = PS_IN( mTanToAbs[2]);\n    #else\n      g_vPixNormalAbs = PS_IN( vNormalAbs);\n    #endif\n  #endif // HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n  #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n    // renormalize pixel normal\n    g_vPixNormalAbs = normalize( g_vPixNormalAbs);\n  #endif\n\n  // adjust facing sign\n  float fInPolyFace = PS_FACE * c_fFacingness;\n  #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n    // and possibly flip normal (for 2-sided lighting)\n    g_vPixNormalAbs = FlipNormal( g_vPixNormalAbs, fInPolyFace);\n  #endif\n\n  // final output gets accumulated here\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, g_vBaseColor.a);\n\n  // if not baking\n#ifndef BAKING\n\n  // sample fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n  g_vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos());\n  g_vIllumAmbOccSample = g_vIllumAmbOccSample *c_vMaskFLAO.xxxz +c_vMaskFLAO.yyyw;\n\n#endif // FLAO\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // if has pixel normal and uses specularity of some sort\n  #if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && (defined(HAS_SPECULARITY) || defined(HAS_COATING))\n\n    // get vertex normal also (for attenuation)\n    #if defined(HAS_PARALLAX) || defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT)\n      // (from tangent matrix)\n      g_vVexNormalAbs = PS_IN( mTanToAbs[2]);\n    #else\n      // (or from vertex shader)\n      g_vVexNormalAbs = PS_IN( vNormalAbs);\n    #endif\n    // renormalize it\n    g_vVexNormalAbs = normalize( g_vVexNormalAbs);\n    // and eventually flip (for 2-sided lighting)\n    g_vVexNormalAbs = FlipNormal( g_vVexNormalAbs, fInPolyFace);\n\n  #endif\n\n  // apply ambient light\n  vOutColor.rgb += AmbientLight( PS_IN( vLitMaskUV.xy), PS_IN( vDiffuseLit), vOffsetAmbDepthMask.w);\n\n#else // HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a = g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // apply (shadowed) distant light\n  float3 vDistColor = DistantLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs));\n  // add to final color (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vDistColor *g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // spot (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += SpotLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // omni (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += OmniLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *g_vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#endif  // LIGHTS\n\n  // apply depth and ambient occlusion from 'height' map\n  vOffsetAmbDepthMask.z = lerp( 1.0f, vOffsetAmbDepthMask.z, vBlendMaskTex.a);\n  vOutColor.rgb *= GetDepthOcclusion( vOffsetAmbDepthMask.z);\n\n  // calculate translucency fresnel for edge smooting\n  // (but with a bit less influence; ^2 instead of ^5!)\n  float fNV = abs( dot( g_vPixNormalAbs, g_vViewDirAbs));\n  float fF  = 1.0f- saturate( fNV*fNV *c_vEdgeSmoothing.x +c_vEdgeSmoothing.y);\n  // and apply it to final color\n  vOutColor = lerp( vOutColor, c_vLerpDest, c_vLerpMask*fF);\n\n  // if baking\n#ifdef BAKING\n\n  // in LDR\n  if( c_fBakeGamma != 0.0f) {\n\n    // apply gamma\n    vOutColor.rgb = pow( vOutColor.rgb, _tcast(float3,0.4545f));\n  }\n  // in RGBE\n  if( c_fBakeRGBE != 0.0f) {\n\n    // convert output\n    vOutColor.rgba = PackRGBE( vOutColor.rgb);\n  }\n\n  // if not baking and has fog and/or haze\n#elif defined(APPLY_FOZE)\n\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, PS_IN( vFozeAmount));\n\n#endif // BAKING\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n  // == vOutColor.a = saturate( (vOutColor.a-(c_vAlphaRange.x-0.001625f)) / ((c_vAlphaRange.x+0.001625f)-(c_vAlphaRange.x-0.001625f)) );\n  // == sat( a-min/delta) == sat( a/delta - min/delta)\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// StandardShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// misc helper functions\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n// transformation to clip, absolute or view space\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n// spherial harmonics calculation\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/SphericalHarmonics.hs>\n// fog and haze calculation\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 40);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n\n// mapping constants\n_CregM42F( c_mBaseMapping, 7);\n_CregF( float4, c_vDetailMapping, 9);\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n  // (SPH calc uses const regs c14-c22!)\n_CregM42F( c_mNormalMapping, 23);\n_CregM42F( c_mGlossMapping,  25);\n_CregM42F( c_mBlendMapping,  27);\n_CregF( float4, c_vLightMapping, 29);\n\n// color map array mask (can be 0,1 or 1,0)\n_CregF( float3, c_vMapMasks, 30);\nstatic float2 c_vColorMapMask = c_vMapMasks.xy;\nstatic float  c_fAmbiMapMask  = c_vMapMasks.z;\n\n// mapping masks for UV coords (select UV-map or XY, YZ or XY plane)\n_CregF( float3, c_vBlendMappingMask, 31);\n_CregF( float3, c_vBaseMappingMask,  32);\n_CregF( float3, c_vGlossMappingMask, 33);\n_CregF( float3, c_vNorMappingMask,   34);\n_CregF( float3, c_vDetMappingMask,   35);\n\n// mask for normal and tangents\n// (up/right constant vector, signed or unsigned inputs)\n_CregF( float3, c_vNorMask, 36);\n_CregF( float3, c_vTanMask, 37);\n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, 38);\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight, 39);\n\n// (c_vObjToClipRightX uses const reg c40!)\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vBaseUV,   2);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  _inReg( float4, vNormalUV, 3);\n#endif\n  _inReg( float2, vLightUV,  4);\n  _inReg( float4, vMaskUV,   5);\n  _inReg( float4, vGlossUV,  6);\n  _inReg( float4, vColorMap, 7);\n  _inReg( float4, vAmbiMap,  8);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  #ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n    _inReg( float4, vTangent, 9);\n  #endif\n  _inReg( float2, vDetailUV, 10);\n#endif\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  _inReg( float4x3, mInstObjToAbs, 11);\n  _inReg( float4, vLightMapping, 14);\n#elif defined(HAS_BONES)\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices, 11); // (matrix indices)\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights, 12); // (blend weights)\n#endif\n#ifdef BAKING\n  _inReg( float4, vBakePos, 13);\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 0);\n  // mappings\n  _outReg( float4, vBasGlosUV, 1);\n  _outReg( float4, vLitMaskUV, 2);\n  _outReg( float4, vNormDetUV, 3);\n#ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n  // .x=fog, .y=haze amount\n  _outReg( float2, vFozeAmount, 4); \n#endif\n  _outReg( float4, vVexColor,   5);\n  _outReg( float3, vDiffuseLit, 6);\n#if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS)\n  // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n  _outReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 7);\n#else\n  // or just vertex normal\n  _outReg( float3, vNormalAbs,  7);\n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( StandardVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // skin position, normal and tangent\n#ifdef BAKING\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vBakePos);\n#else\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n#endif\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorMask.xyxz);    // (up vector)\n#if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS)\n  float4 vTan = ExpandTangent( VS_IN( vTangent), c_vTanMask.xyxz);  // (right vector)\n#endif\n#if !defined(INSTANCING) && defined(HAS_BONES)\n  #if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS)\n    vPos.xyz = SkinVertexTan( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor, vTan.xyz);\n  #else\n    vPos.xyz = SkinVertexNor( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor);\n  #endif\n#endif\n\n  // calc world and clip-space pixel positions\n#ifdef BAKING\n\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n#else // BAKING\n\n  #ifdef INSTANCING\n\n    // fetch object-to-absolute matrix\n    // (straight from instanced vertex inputs)\n    #define i_mInstObjToAbs VS_IN( mInstObjToAbs)\n\n    // combine model and view-proj matrices first (obj-to-clip here is infact abs-to-clip matrix!)\n    float4x4 mObjToAbs4 = \n    #if _GLSL \n      float4x4( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n    #elif _HLSL\n    { float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[0], 0),\n      float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[1], 0),\n      float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[2], 0),\n      float4( i_mInstObjToAbs[3], 1) };\n    #endif\n    float4x4 mMVPLeft = mul( mObjToAbs4, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n    float4x4 mMVPRight = mul( mObjToAbs4, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n    // to project to clip space\n    VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, mMVPLeft);\n    VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, mMVPRight);\n    // obj to abs matrix is provided through instance stream\n    vPos.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, i_mInstObjToAbs);\n\n  #else // !INSTANCING\n\n    // w/o instancing, project directly from object to clip space\n    VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n    VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( vPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  #endif // INSTANCING\n\n#endif // BAKING\n\n  // out with position in absolute space\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n  #ifdef INSTANCING\n    vOutVexPosAbs = vPos;\n  #else\n    vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToAbs);\n    vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n  #endif\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n  \n  // get rotation matrix\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot;\n  #ifdef INSTANCING\n    // (use instanced location matrix)\n    mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( i_mInstObjToAbs);\n  #else\n    // (use fixed location matrix)\n    mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n  #endif\n  // fix stretching\n  FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n\n  // transform normal from object to absolute space\n  float3 vNorAbs = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRot);\n  // and (re)normalize it\n  vNorAbs = normalize( vNorAbs);\n\n  // if has normal-map(s) and needs to export tangents\n  #if defined(HAS_NORMAL_MAP) && defined(NEEDS_TANGENTS)\n\n    // if using planar mapping\n    float3x3 mOutTanToAbs;\n    if( c_vNorMappingMask.z > 0.0f) {\n\n      // construct tangent to object space plane matrix\n      mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToAbsPlaneMatrix( vNorAbs, c_vNorMappingMask.x);\n      // and apply normal-map's rotation and/or stretching\n      mOutTanToAbs = StretchTanToObjMatrix( mOutTanToAbs, c_mNormalMapping);\n\n    // if using UV-mapping\n    } else {\n\n      // construct tangent to object space transformation matrix\n      mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToObjMatrix( vNor, vTan);\n      // apply normal-map's rotation and/or stretching\n      mOutTanToAbs = StretchTanToObjMatrix( mOutTanToAbs, c_mNormalMapping);\n    #if _GLSL\n      mObjToAbsRot = transpose( mObjToAbsRot);\n    #endif\n      // and move tangents from object to absolute space\n      mOutTanToAbs = _mulT( mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRot);\n    }\n    // (re)normalize rotation matrix\n    VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = NormalizeRotation( mOutTanToAbs);\n\n  // if no normal-map(s)\n  #else \n\n    // just use vertex normal\n    // (in absolute space!)\n    VS_OUT( vNormalAbs) = vNorAbs;\n\n  #endif\n\n  // if has spherical harmonics\n  #ifdef HAS_SPHARMONICS\n\n    // calculate diffuse light component from them\n    VS_OUT( vDiffuseLit) = CalcSHLight( vNorAbs);\n\n  // if doesn't have spherical harmonics\n  #else\n\n    // unpack light color and pass it to the pixel program\n    float4 vVexLightColor = VS_IN( vAmbiMap);\n    VS_OUT( vDiffuseLit) = UnpackRGBE( vVexLightColor) *c_fAmbiMapMask;\n  #endif\n\n  // apply mapping masks\n  float4 vInMaskUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vMaskUV.xy),  vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vBlendMappingMask); \n  float4 vInBaseUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vBaseUV.xy),  vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vBaseMappingMask); \n  float4 vInGlosUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vGlossUV.xy), vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vGlossMappingMask); \n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  float4 vInNormUV = SelectUV4( VS_IN( vNormalUV.xy),vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vNorMappingMask); \n  float2 vInDetailUV = SelectUV(VS_IN( vDetailUV),   vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, c_vDetMappingMask); \n#endif\n\n  // mapping adjustments\n  #ifdef INSTANCING\n    VS_OUT( vLitMaskUV.xy) = VS_IN( vLightUV) *VS_IN( vLightMapping.xy) +VS_IN( vLightMapping.zw);\n  #else\n    VS_OUT( vLitMaskUV.xy) = VS_IN( vLightUV) *c_vLightMapping.xy +c_vLightMapping.zw;\n  #endif\n  // (4-component dot product: Z is 0, W is offset; cannot use Z for offset\n  //  since 2D vectors will be expanded to X,Y,0,1, and we need 1 for dot product)\n  VS_OUT( vLitMaskUV.zw) = mulM42F( vInMaskUV, c_mBlendMapping);\n  VS_OUT( vBasGlosUV.xy) = mulM42F( vInBaseUV, c_mBaseMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vBasGlosUV.zw) = mulM42F( vInGlosUV, c_mGlossMapping);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  VS_OUT( vNormDetUV.xy) = mulM42F( vInNormUV, c_mNormalMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vNormDetUV.zw) = vInDetailUV *c_vDetailMapping.xy +c_vDetailMapping.zw;\n#else\n  VS_OUT( vNormDetUV) = _tcast(float4,0);\n#endif\n\n  // color map array\n  float4 vOutVexColor = VS_IN( vColorMap);\n  // apply overbrighting (\"shade\" mode)\n  vOutVexColor.rgb *= 2.0f;\n  // (needs to be gamma corrected for HDR, fast!)\n  vOutVexColor.rgb *= vOutVexColor.rgb; \n  // (maybe masked out)\n  VS_OUT( vVexColor) = vOutVexColor *c_vColorMapMask.x +c_vColorMapMask.y; \n\n#ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n\n  #ifdef BAKING\n    // no fog when baking\n    VS_OUT( vFozeAmount) = _tcast(float2,0);\n  #else\n    // calculate fog and haze amount\n    float4 vViewPosAbsVex = VRMiddle(c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight);\n    float3 vVexDist = vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - vViewPosAbsVex.xyz;\n    float  fVexDist = length( vVexDist); // (via precached vertex-viewer distance)\n    VS_OUT( vFozeAmount.x) = CalcFogAmount( vOutVexPosAbs, vViewPosAbsVex, fVexDist);\n    VS_OUT( vFozeAmount.y) = CalcHazeAmount( vOutVexPosAbs.y, fVexDist);\n  #endif\n#endif  //
