APPLY_FOZE\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SubSurfaceShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpMapping.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/SphericalHarmonics.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeBlend.hs>\n\n\n// this shader counts on both normal and detail maps\n#define HAS_NORMAL_MAP 1\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sBaseMap,     s_tBaseMap,    0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sHemoMap,     s_tHemoMap,    1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sNormalMap,   s_tNormalMap,  2);\n_Sreg2D( t_sDetailMap,   s_tDetailMap,  3);\n_Sreg2D( t_sGlossMap,    s_tGlossMap,   4);\n_Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc,5);\n\n// base colors\n_CregF( float4, c_vColBase, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vColSpec, 1);\n_CregF( float4, c_vColRefl, 2);\n// and hemo color\n_CregF( float4, c_vColHemoFace, 3);\nstatic float3 c_vColHemo = c_vColHemoFace.rgb;\n// clockwiseness (rendering direction)\nstatic float c_fFacingness = c_vColHemoFace.w;\n\n// viewer position (in world space)\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsPix, 4);\n  // (fog/haze use const reg c5-c7!)\n  // (bump mapping uses const reg c8!)\n\n// mask for usage of FLAO texture values\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskFLAO, 9);\n\n// reflection factors\n_CregF( float3, c_vReflFactors, 10);\nstatic float c_fScattering = c_vReflFactors.x;\nstatic float c_fReflBump   = c_vReflFactors.y;\nstatic float c_fRoughness  = c_vReflFactors.z;\n          \n// for screen coords sampling\n_CregF( float4, c_vAlphaScreenSize, 11);\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange   = c_vAlphaScreenSize.xy;\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_vAlphaScreenSize.zw;\n\n\n// global vars\nstatic float  g_fNdotV;\nstatic float3 g_vNormalAbs;\nstatic float3 g_vViewDirAbs;\n// colors\nstatic float4 g_vBlurColor;  // (base blurred)\nstatic float4 g_vBaseColor;\nstatic float3 g_vHemoColor;\n// gloss map\nstatic float4 g_vGlossTex;\n#define g_fHemoMask g_vGlossTex.r\n#define g_fDetAtt   g_vGlossTex.b\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs,  0); // (for pixel shader)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexGlosUV,  1); // mappings\n  _inReg( float4, vNormDetUV,  2);\n  _inReg( float2, vFozeAmount, 3);\n  // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n  _inReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 4);\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  _inFacReg;\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// modulate diffuse color by diffuse texture\ninline void ModulateSkinColors( const float2 vTexUV)\n{\n  // sample and modulate\n  g_vBlurColor = texBias2D( t_sBaseMap, s_tBaseMap, vTexUV,2.0f);\n  g_vBaseColor = texSample2D( t_sBaseMap, s_tBaseMap, vTexUV);\n  g_vHemoColor = texSample2D( t_sHemoMap, s_tHemoMap, vTexUV).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( g_vBlurColor.rgb); \n  LinearSpace( g_vBaseColor.rgb);\n  LinearSpace( g_vHemoColor);\n  g_vBlurColor *= c_vColBase;\n  g_vBaseColor *= c_vColBase;\n  g_vHemoColor *= c_vColHemo;\n}\n\n\n// calculate lighting\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  // N.L (N.V is already calculated)\n  float fNdotL = dot( g_vNormalAbs, vLightDirAbs);\n\n  float3 vH = normalize( g_vViewDirAbs + vLightDirAbs);\n  float  fT = dot( vH, g_vNormalAbs);\n  float  fU = saturate( dot( vH, g_vViewDirAbs));\n  float  fV = saturate( fNdotL);\n  float fVP = saturate( g_fNdotV);\n\n  float fR1  = c_fRoughness;\n  float fGV  = 1 / (fR1-fR1*fV +fV);\n  float fGVP = 1 / (fR1-fR1*fVP+fVP);\n  float fZ = (1 + fR1*fT*fT - fT*fT);\n        fZ = fR1 / (fZ*fZ);\n\n  float fFres = pow( 1.0f-fU, 5.0f);\n  float3 vS1 = lerp( c_vColSpec.rgb, _tcast(float3,1), fFres) *g_fHemoMask;\n\n  float fD1 = fZ * fGV * fGVP;   // should be *0.25 ?!\n  float3 vScatter = smoothstep( -c_fScattering, 1.0f, fNdotL) * (1.0f-g_vBlurColor.rgb)*g_vBlurColor.a;\n\t\n  // final blend\n  vScatter = g_vHemoColor*vScatter + g_vBaseColor.rgb*fV;\n  return lerp( vScatter, _tcast(float3,fD1*fV), vS1);\n}\n\n\n\n// MAIN RENDERING PASS\nPS_ENTRY( SubSurfacePS)\n{\n  // calculate view direction\n  g_vViewDirAbs = normalize( c_vViewPosAbsPix.xyz - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz));\n  // and cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), c_v1oScreenSize);\n\n  // sample gloss mask\n  // (will be used later by detail-map and/or specularity)\n  g_vGlossTex = texSample2D( t_sGlossMap, s_tGlossMap, PS_IN( vTexGlosUV.zw));\n  float4 vRawNorDet;\n\n  // attenuate details, sample normal (and detail) maps' normal value\n  float2 vNorDetAtt = float2( 1.0f, g_fDetAtt);\n  float3 vNormalTan = GetBumpedNormal( t_sNormalMap, s_tNormalMap,\n    t_sDetailMap, s_tDetailMap, PS_IN( vNormDetUV), vNorDetAtt, vRawNorDet);\n  // and transform it to absolute space\n  g_vNormalAbs = normalize( mul( vNormalTan, PS_IN( mTanToAbs)));\n  g_vNormalAbs = FlipNormal( g_vNormalAbs, PS_FACE *c_fFacingness);\n\n  // modulate skin colors by skin textures\n  ModulateSkinColors( PS_IN( vTexGlosUV.xy));\n\n  // calc view-normal angle once (for fresnel, later on)\n  g_fNdotV = saturate( dot( g_vNormalAbs, g_vViewDirAbs));\n\n\n  // final result\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, g_vBaseColor.a);\n\n  // sample fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos());\n  vIllumAmbOccSample = vIllumAmbOccSample *c_vMaskFLAO.xxxz +c_vMaskFLAO.yyyw;\n\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // spherical harmonics lighting\n  float3 vSHLight = CalcSHLight( g_vNormalAbs);\n\n  // we need some bumps on diffuse lightmapped surfaces\n  // no matter the actual lighting (for in-shadow pixels)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vSHLight * CalcLight( float3( 0,0,g_vNormalAbs.z));\n\n  // modulate by ambient occlusion\n  vOutColor.rgb *= vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // and add illumination (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#else // HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n#endif\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // distant light\n  float3 vDistColor = DistantLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs));\n  // added to final color (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vDistColor *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // spot (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += SpotLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // omni (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += OmniLight( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs)) *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n#endif\n\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, PS_IN( vFozeAmount));\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SubSurfaceShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// transformation to clip, absolute or view space\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n// matrix pallete skinning (bones transformations)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Skinning.hs>\n// fog and haze calculation\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClip, 0);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n// mapping constants\n_CregM42F( c_mBaseMapping, 7);\n_CregF( float4, c_vDetailMapping, 9);\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n_CregM42F( c_mNormalMapping, 14);\n_CregM42F( c_mGlossMapping,  16);\n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVex, 18);\n\n// normal and tangent signed/unsigned masks\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorTanMask, 19);\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,   1);\n  _inReg( float4, vTangent,  2);\n  _inReg( float4, vBaseUV,   3);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormalUV, 4);\n  _inReg( float4, vGlossUV,  5);\n  _inReg( float2, vDetailUV, 6);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  _inReg( float4, vIndices,  7); // (matrix indices)\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,  8); // (blend weights)\n#endif\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs,  0); // (for pixel shader)\n  _outReg( float4, vTexGlosUV,  1); // mappings\n  _outReg( float4, vNormDetUV,  2);\n  _outReg( float2, vFozeAmount, 3);\n  // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n  _outReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 4);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( SubSurfaceVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // skin position, normal and tangent\n  float4 vPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal(  VS_IN( vNormal),  c_vNorTanMask.yyyx);\n  float4 vTan = ExpandTangent( VS_IN( vTangent), c_vNorTanMask.wwwz);\n#ifdef HAS_BONES\n  // (if needed)\n  vPos.xyz = SkinVertexTan( VS_IN( vIndices), VS_IN( vWeights), vPos, vNor, vTan.xyz);\n#endif\n\n  // calc world and clip-space pixel positions\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vPos, c_mObjToClip);\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n  vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vPos, c_mObjToAbs);\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n\n  // construct tangent to object space transformation matrix\n  float3x3 mOutTanToAbs;\n  mOutTanToAbs = MakeTanToObjMatrix( vNor, vTan);\n  // apply normal-map's rotation and/or stretching\n  mOutTanToAbs = StretchTanToObjMatrix( mOutTanToAbs, c_mNormalMapping);\n\n  // and move tangents from object to tangent space\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( c_mObjToAbs);\n#if _GLSL\n  mObjToAbsRot = transpose( mObjToAbsRot);\n#endif\n  // with fixed stretching\n  FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRot);\n  mOutTanToAbs = _mulT( mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRot);\n  // and (re)normalized\n  VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = NormalizeRotation( mOutTanToAbs);\n\n  // mapping coordinates\n  // (4-component dot product: Z is 0, W is offset; cannot use Z for offset\n  //  since 2D vectors will be expanded to X,Y,0,1, and we need 1 for dot product)\n  VS_OUT( vTexGlosUV.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vBaseUV),   c_mBaseMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vTexGlosUV.zw) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vGlossUV),  c_mGlossMapping);\n  VS_OUT( vNormDetUV.xy) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vNormalUV), c_mNormalMapping); \n  VS_OUT( vNormDetUV.zw) = VS_IN( vDetailUV.xy) *c_vDetailMapping.xy +c_vDetailMapping.zw;\n\n  // calculate fog and haze amount \n  float3 vVexDist = vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - c_vViewPosAbsVex.xyz;\n  float  fVexDist = length( vVexDist); // (via precached vertex-viewer distance)\n  VS_OUT( vFozeAmount.x) = CalcFogAmount( vOutVexPosAbs, c_vViewPosAbsVex, fVexDist);\n  VS_OUT( vFozeAmount.y) = CalcHazeAmount( vOutVexPosAbs.y, fVexDist);\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// TerrainCrumbsCachingShaders.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Terrain/Shaders/TerrainMaterialMapCommon.hs>\n#include <Engine/Terrain/Shaders/TerrainHelpers.hs>\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vElevationUVmad, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vHorizontalDisplacementUVmad, 1);\n_CregF(float4, c_vHeightUVMad, 2);\n_CregF(float4, c_vCrumbsDensityUVmad, 3);\n\n_CregF(float4, c_vNoiseCoordsBase, 4);\n_CregF(float4, c_vGridDimAndAncestorSlice, 5);\nstatic float c_f1oTileSize = c_vGridDimAndAncestorSlice.x;\nstatic float c_fGridStretch = c_vGridDimAndAncestorSlice.y;\nstatic float2 c_vPivotOffset = c_vGridDimAndAncestorSlice.zw;\n_CregF(float4, c_vMiscConsts, 6);\nstatic float c_f1oMaterialCount = c_vMiscConsts.x;\nstatic int c_iArraySlice = int(c_vMiscConsts.y);\nstatic float c_fDensityLevel = c_vMiscConsts.z;\nstatic float c_fCrumbTypes = c_vMiscConsts.w;\n// random noise consts\n_CregF(float4, c_vNoiseConsts, 7);\nstatic float c_f1oRandomDim = c_vNoiseConsts.x;\nstatic float c_fStretchFrequency = c_vNoiseConsts.y;\nstatic float c_fNoisePositionStrength = c_vNoiseConsts.z;\nstatic float c_fHighFreqNoiseFreq = c_vNoiseConsts.w;\n_CregF(float4, c_vElevConsts, 8);\nstatic float c_fBaseElevation = c_vElevConsts.x;\nstatic float c_f1oElevRange = c_vElevConsts.y;\nstatic float c_f1oMaxScale = c_vElevConsts.z;\nstatic int c_iDensitySlice = int(c_vElevConsts.w);\n_CregF(float4, c_vCrumbsDensitySizeConsts, 9);\n_CregF(float4, c_vGrassAOConsts, 10);\nstatic float c_fGrassAOStrength = c_vGrassAOConsts.x;\n_CregF(float4, c_vDrawportUVmad, 11);\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n_Sreg2D(t_sElevation, s_tElevation, 1);\n_Sreg2D(t_sHorizontalDisplacement, s_tHorizontalDisplacement, 2);\n_SregAry2D(t_sHeight, s_tHeight, 3);\n_SregAry2D(t_sCrumbsDensity, s_tCrumbsDensity, 4);\n_Sreg2D(t_sPivotPosition, s_PivotPosition, 5);\n_Sreg2D(t_sMaterialMapping, s_tMaterialMapping, 6);\n_Sreg2D(t_sMaterialMappingGrass, s_tMaterialMappingGrass, 7);\n_Sreg2D(t_sCrumbsParams, s_tCrumbsParams, 8);\n_Sreg2D(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, 9);\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float2, vPivotData, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg(float4, vCrumbsData, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n/* Crumbs params texture sampling */\n// For parameter packing details see CTerrainGeography::InitializeCrumbConfigs().\nstatic const float c_fCrumbsParamsTextureWidth = 2.0f;\nstatic const float c_fCrumbsParamsSampling1 = (0 + 0.5f) / c_fCrumbsParamsTextureWidth;\nstatic const float c_fCrumbsParamsSampling2 = (1 + 0.5f) / c_fCrumbsParamsTextureWidth;\n// Returns the requested parameters for the provided crumb type.\n// Expects the provided type to be in [0 / c_fCrumbTypes, (c_fCrumbTypes - 1) / c_fCrumbTypes] + 0.5f / c_fCrumbTypes.\nfloat4 GetCrumbTypeParameters(float fCrumbType, float fParameterSamplingColumn)\n{\n  return texLod2D(t_sCrumbsParams, s_tCrumbsParams, float2(fParameterSamplingColumn, fCrumbType), 0.0f);\n}\n\nstatic float4 g_vCrumbTypeParams1;\nstatic float4 g_vCrumbTypeParams2;\n// Chooses one of the available crumb types from the provided range [offset, offset + count>\n// and initializes g_vCrumbTypeParams1 and g_vCrumbTypeParams2 with the chosen type's parameters.\nfloat SelectCrumbType(float fNoise, float fTypeOffset, float fTypeCount)\n{\n\n#if !DBG_DISABLE_NOISE\n  for (int iCrumb = 0; iCrumb < fTypeCount - 1; ++iCrumb) {\n    float fCrumbType = (fTypeOffset + iCrumb + 0.5f) / c_fCrumbTypes;\n    g_vCrumbTypeParams1 = GetCrumbTypeParameters(fCrumbType, c_fCrumbsParamsSampling1);\n    if (fNoise <= g_vCrumbTypeParams1.y /*tcc_fWeightThreshold*/) {\n      g_vCrumbTypeParams2 = GetCrumbTypeParameters(fCrumbType, c_fCrumbsParamsSampling2);\n      return fTypeOffset + iCrumb;\n    }\n  }\n#endif\n\n  float fDefault = (fTypeOffset + fTypeCount - 0.5f) / c_fCrumbTypes;\n  g_vCrumbTypeParams1 = GetCrumbTypeParameters(fDefault, c_fCrumbsParamsSampling1);\n  g_vCrumbTypeParams2 = GetCrumbTypeParameters(fDefault, c_fCrumbsParamsSampling2);\n  return fTypeOffset + fTypeCount - 1.0f;\n}\n\nfloat SampleElevationWithHeight(float2 vInGridPos)\n{\n  float2 vElevationUV = c_vElevationUVmad.xy*vInGridPos + c_vElevationUVmad.zw;\n  float2 vHeightUV = c_vHeightUVMad.xy * vInGridPos + c_vHeightUVMad.zw;\n\n  float fElevation = texLod2D(t_sElevation, s_tElevation, vElevationUV, 0.0f).r;\n  float fHeight = texLod2D(t_sHeight, s_tHeight, float3(vHeightUV, c_iArraySlice), 0.0f).r;\n\n  return fElevation + fHeight;\n}\n\nfloat2 GetHorizontalDisplacement(float2 vInGridPos)\n{\n  float2 vHorizontalDisplacementUV = c_vHorizontalDisplacementUVmad.xy*vInGridPos + c_vHorizontalDisplacementUVmad.zw;\n  return texLod2D(t_sHorizontalDisplacement, s_tHorizontalDisplacement, vHorizontalDisplacementUV, 0.0f).rg;\n}\n\n#if _HLSL\n  float PackFloat(float fHigh, float fLow)\n  {\n    const float fHighBits = 16;\n    const float fLowBits = 8;\n    float fExp;\n    // adding a small eps here to cover the case where fHigh is 0, which would\n    // cause the final packed float to not have the exponent we expect AND\n    // cause sign() to return 0\n    float fAdjustedHigh = fHigh + (fHigh == 0 ? 0.00001f : 0);\n    float fMant = frexp(abs(fAdjustedHigh), fExp);\n    float fMant2 = (ldexp(floor(ldexp(fMant, fHighBits)), fLowBits) + floor(fLow));\n    return sign(fAdjustedHigh) * ldexp(fMant2, fExp - (fLowBits + fHighBits));\n  }\n#elif _GLSL\n  float PackFloat(float fHigh, float fLow)\n  {\n    const int iHighBits = 16;\n    const int iLowBits = 8;\n    int iExp;\n    // adding a small eps here to cover the case where fHigh is 0, which would\n    // cause the final packed float to not have the exponent we expect AND\n    // cause sign() to return 0\n    float fAdjustedHigh = fHigh + (fHigh == 0 ? 0.00001f : 0);\n    float fMant = frexp(abs(fAdjustedHigh), iExp);\n    float fMant2 = (ldexp(floor(ldexp(fMant, iHighBits)), iLowBits) + floor(fLow));\n    return sign(fAdjustedHigh) * ldexp(fMant2, iExp - (iLowBits + iHighBits));\n  }\n#endif // API\n\nVS_ENTRY(TerrainCrumbsCachingVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  float2 vInputPivot = VS_IN(vPivotData).xy;\n\n  // determine pivot position in grid (in meters)\n  float2 vPivotGridMeters = (vInputPivot + c_vPivotOffset) * c_fGridStretch;\n \n  // sample the random noise texture, used for stretch, rotation, position\n  const int ctDensityLevels = 1 + _tcast(int,c_fDensityLevel);\n  float2 vNoiseCoords = c_vNoiseCoordsBase.xy + vPivotGridMeters;\n  float2 vWhiteNoisePos = floor((float2(\n    SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, vNoiseCoords * 99989 * ctDensityLevels),\n    SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, (vNoiseCoords + float2(13, 17) * c_fGridStretch) * 99989 * ctDensityLevels)\n  ) * 0.5f + 0.5f) * 255.0f);\n  float2 vWhiteNoisePosNorm = vWhiteNoisePos / 256.0f;\n\n  // determine offsetted pivot position in normalized grid space [0, 1]\n  float2 vPivot = (vPivotGridMeters + (2.0f * vWhiteNoisePosNorm - float2(1.0f, 1.0f)) * c_fNoisePositionStrength) * c_f1oTileSize;\n\n  float2 vMatAndProbUV = vPivot * c_vCrumbsDensityUVmad.xy + c_vCrumbsDensityUVmad.zw;\n  float fMaterialAndCrumbsProb = texLod2D(t_sCrumbsDensity, s_tCrumbsDensity, float3(vMatAndProbUV, c_iDensitySlice), 0.0f).r;\n  float fCrumbsProbability = frac(fMaterialAndCrumbsProb) * 2.0f; // encoded like this during material mixing\n  float fMaterial = floor(fMaterialAndCrumbsProb);\n  \n  float fMaterialCrumbCount = GetMaterialCrumbTypeCount(fMaterial, c_f1oMaterialCount, t_sMaterialMapping, s_tMaterialMapping);\n  float fMaterialCrumbOffset = texLod2D(t_sMaterialMapping, s_tMaterialMapping, float2(0.75f, (fMaterial + 0.5f) * c_f1oMaterialCount), 0.0f).a * 255;\n  float fCrumbType = SelectCrumbType(vWhiteNoisePosNorm.x, fMaterialCrumbOffset, fMaterialCrumbCount);\n\n  // crumb should be rendered only if the probability for this pixel is high enough\n#if GRASS_CRUMBS\n  float fCrumbsProbabilityNoise = SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, vNoiseCoords * 5.0f) * 0.5f + 0.5f;\n  fCrumbType = fCrumbsProbability > fCrumbsProbabilityNoise ? fCrumbType : c_fCrumbTypes;\n#else\n  float fLowFreqNoise = SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, vNoiseCoords) * 0.5f + 0.5f;\n  float fHighFreqNoise = SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, vNoiseCoords * c_fHighFreqNoiseFreq) * 0.5f + 0.5f;\n  fCrumbType =\n    fHighFreqNoise > g_vCrumbTypeParams1.w /*tcc_fHighFreqStrength*/ || fLowFreqNoise > g_vCrumbTypeParams1.z /*tcc_fLowFreqStrength*/ ?\n    fCrumbType : c_fCrumbTypes;\n#endif\n  fCrumbType = fMaterialCrumbCount > 0.5 ? fCrumbType : c_fCrumbTypes;\n\n  float2 vHorDisOffset = GetHorizontalDisplacement(vPivot);\n  VS_OUT(vCrumbsData.x) = PackFloat(vHorDisOffset.x, vWhiteNoisePos.x);\n  VS_OUT(vCrumbsData.y) = PackFloat(vHorDisOffset.y, vWhiteNoisePos.y);\n\n  float fElevation = (SampleElevationWithHeight(vPivot) - c_fBaseElevation) * c_f1oElevRange;\n  VS_OUT(vCrumbsData.z) = PackFloat(fElevation, fCrumbType);\n\n  float fSampledDensity = SampleGrassCrumbsProbability(vMatAndProbUV, c_vCrumbsDensitySizeConsts, t_sCrumbsDensity, s_tCrumbsDensity,\n    c_f1oMaterialCount, t_sMaterialMappingGrass, s_tMaterialMappingGrass, c_iDensitySlice);\n  float fGrassAOBase = saturate(1.0f - c_fGrassAOStrength * fSampledDensity);\n\n  float3 vWhiteNoiseRot = float3(\n    SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, (vNoiseCoords + float2(31, 73) * c_fGridStretch) * 43 * ctDensityLevels),\n    SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, (vNoiseCoords + float2(113, 197) * c_fGridStretch) * 43 * ctDensityLevels),\n    SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, (vNoiseCoords + float2(239, 317) * c_fGridStretch) * 43 * ctDensityLevels)\n  );\n  float3 vNoiseRotationStrength = float3(1.0f, g_vCrumbTypeParams2.x /*tcc_fPitchOffsetStrength*/, g_vCrumbTypeParams2.y /*tcc_fBankingOffsetStrength*/);\n  float3 vRotations = vNoiseRotationStrength * vWhiteNoiseRot;\n  float fStretchNoise = SampleBilinear(t_sRandom, s_tRandom, c_f1oRandomDim, vNoiseCoords * c_fStretchFrequency);\n  float fStretch = lerp(1.0f, (fStretchNoise < 0.0f ? g_vCrumbTypeParams2.z /*tcc_fMinRndScale*/ : g_vCrumbTypeParams2.w /*tcc_fMaxRndScale*/), abs(fStretchNoise));\n  fStretch *= c_f1oMaxScale; // normalize using the maximum scale over all types so we don't have to sample type-specific parameters in render time\n  VS_OUT(vCrumbsData.w) = ldexp(\n    (floor((fStretch * 0.5f + 0.5f) /*keeping the mantissa >=0.5 so the exponent is 0*/ * 64) * 64 * 8 * 8 * 64  +\n    floor((vRotations.x * 0.5f + 0.5f) * 64) * 8 * 8 * 64 +\n    floor((vRotations.y * 0.5f + 0.5f) * 8) * 8 * 64 +\n    floor((vRotations.z * 0.5f + 0.5f) * 8) * 64 +\n    floor(fGrassAOBase * 63)) / (64 * 64 * 8 * 8 * 64),\n#if _HLSL\n    g_vCrumbTypeParams1.x);\n#elif _GLSL\n    int(g_vCrumbTypeParams1.x));\n#endif // API\n\n  float2 vOutputPos = vInputPivot * c_fGridStretch * c_f1oTileSize;\n  VS_OUT_POS = float4(vOutputPos * c_vDrawportUVmad.xy + c_vDrawportUVmad.zw, 0, 1);\n\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n// PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg(float4, vCrumbsData, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY(TerrainCrumbsCachingPS)\n{\n  float4 vOutput = PS_IN(vCrumbsData);\n  PS_OUT(vOutput);\n}\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// TextureMetricsShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER  // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProj, 0);\n_CregM43F( c_mModelToAbs, 4);\n_CregF( float2, c_vTextureStretch, 7);\n\n// vs in\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition,  0);  // (dst drawport coords)\n  _inReg( float2, vTextureUV, 1);  // sampled texture\nVS_IN_END\n\n// vs out\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float2, vTexCoords, 0);  // texture UV coordinates\n  _outReg( float3, vAbsCoords, 1);  // meters\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n// texture metrix vertex program\nVS_ENTRY( texmetVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n  // model->absolute->view->clip space transformation\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mModelViewProj);\n  // texture \n  VS_OUT( vTexCoords) = VS_IN( vTextureUV) *c_vTextureStretch;\n  // meters\n  VS_OUT( vAbsCoords) = mulM43F( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mModelToAbs);\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER  // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// targeted texels per meters\n_CregF( float2, c_vNominalMexelsExp, 0);\nstatic float c_fNominalMexels = c_vNominalMexelsExp.x;\nstatic float c_fFixedExposure = c_vNominalMexelsExp.y;\n\n// ps in\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float2, vTexCoords, 0);  // texture UV coordinates\n  _inReg( float3, vAbsCoords, 1);  // meters\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// texture metrix pixel program\nPS_ENTRY( texmetPS)\n{\n  // calc per pixel deltas for UV and XYZ\n  float2 vUVoI  = ddx( PS_IN( vTexCoords));\n  float2 vUVoJ  = ddy( PS_IN( vTexCoords));\n  float3 vXYZoI = ddx( PS_IN( vAbsCoords));\n  float3 vXYZoJ = ddy( PS_IN( vAbsCoords));\n\n  // make XYZ/IJ matrix\n  float3x3 mXYZoIJ = float3x3( \n    vXYZoI.x, vXYZoJ.x, 0,\n    vXYZoI.y, vXYZoJ.y, 0, \n    vXYZoI.z, vXYZoJ.z, 0);\n\n  // make inverse of UV/IJ matrix\n  float fInvDet = 1.0f / (vUVoI.x*vUVoJ.y - vUVoJ.x*vUVoI.y);  // determinant\n  float3x3 mInvUVoIJ = float3x3(\n     vUVoJ.y, -vUVoJ.x, 0, \n    -vUVoI.y,  vUVoI.x, 0, \n           0,        0, 0); \n  mInvUVoIJ *= fInvDet;\n\n#if _GLSL\n  // (transpose matrices under GLSL)\n  mXYZoIJ   = transpose( mXYZoIJ);\n  mInvUVoIJ = transpose( mInvUVoIJ);\n#endif\n  // multiply with XYZ\n  float3x3 mXYZoUV = mul( mXYZoIJ, mInvUVoIJ);\n\n  // calc meters/UV\n  float2 vMoUV, vMexels;\n#if _GLSL\n  vMoUV.x = length( mXYZoUV[0]);\n  vMoUV.y = length( mXYZoUV[1]);\n#elif _HLSL\n  vMoUV.x = length( mXYZoUV._m00_m10_m20);  // U\n  vMoUV.y = length( mXYZoUV._m01_m11_m21);  // V\n#endif\n\n  // normalized (0.5=red, 1.0=green, 2.0=blue)\n  vMexels = vMoUV * c_fNominalMexels;\n  vMexels = clamp( vMexels, 0.5f, 2.0f);\n  float3 vOutCol = float3( 0,1,0);\n  float3 vOutColU, vOutColV;\n  \n  // mapping ratio U\n  if( vMexels.x < 1.0f) {\n    // under-sampling U\n    vMexels.x = vMexels.x *2.0f -1.0f;\n    vOutColU  = float3( 1,0,0);\n  } else {\n    // over-sampling U\n    vMexels.x = 2.0f- vMexels.x;\n    vOutColU  = float3( 0,0,1);\n  }\n  // mapping ratio V\n  if( vMexels.y < 1.0f) {\n    // under-sampling V\n    vMexels.y = vMexels.y *2.0f -1.0f;\n    vOutColV  = float3( 1,0,0);\n  } else {\n    // over-sampling V\n    vMexels.y = 2.0f- vMexels.y;\n    vOutColV  = float3( 0,0,1);\n  }\n  // colorize U & V\n  vMexels  = 1.0f- vMexels;\n  vMexels *= vMexels; // (slower toward extreme)\n  vOutColU = lerp( vOutCol, vOutColU, vMexels.x);\n  vOutColV = lerp( vOutCol, vOutColV, vMexels.y);\n  \n  // mix those two (leaning towards extremes!)\n  vOutCol.rb = max( vOutColU.rb, vOutColV.rb);\n  vOutCol.g  = min( vOutColU.g,  vOutColV.g);\n  vOutCol   *= c_fFixedExposure;   // adjust exposure (also normalizes HDR output value!)\n  PS_OUT( float4( vOutCol, 0.5f)); // (50% translucent when needed)\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// VegetationShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/ShadowBuffer.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Lighting.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeBlend.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDiffuse,     s_tDiffuse,     0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sTransMap,    s_tTransMap,    1);   // translucency map\n_Sreg2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, 2);\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  _Sreg2D( t_sNormalMap, s_tNormalMap,   3);\n#endif\n#ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n  _Sreg2D( t_sShade, s_tShade, 4);\n#endif\n\n// translucency\n_CregF( float4, c_vTranslucencyBiasFace, 0);\nstatic float3 c_vTranslucencyBias = c_vTranslucencyBiasFace.rgb;\nstatic float  c_fFacingness = c_vTranslucencyBiasFace.w;\n\n// specularity\n_CregF( float4, c_vSpecularity, 1);\nstatic float3 c_vSpecColor = c_vSpecularity.rgb;\nstatic float  c_fSpecPower = c_vSpecularity.w;\n// normal map strength and 1/max_distance^2\n_CregF( float2, c_vNormalMapStrengthMaxDist, 2);\nstatic float c_fNormalMapStrength = c_vNormalMapStrengthMaxDist.x;\nstatic float c_f1oNormalMaxDist2  = c_vNormalMapStrengthMaxDist.y;\n// viewer position \n_CregF( float3, c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, 3);\n_CregF( float3, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight, 12);\nstatic float3 g_vViewPosAbsPix;\n// alpha range adjustment (for transparency AA, if any)\n_CregF( float4, c_vAlphaRangeShade, 4);\nstatic float2 c_vAlphaRange = c_vAlphaRangeShade.xy;\nstatic float2 c_vShadePower = c_vAlphaRangeShade.zw; // (.z=shade_power, .w= -shade_power*0.5-0.5)\n\n  // (fog/haze use const reg c5-c7!)\n  // (bump mapping uses const reg c8!)\n  // (parallax mapping uses const reg c9!)\n// mask for usage of FLAO texture values\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskFLAO, 10);\n// screen coords sampling and HDR output normalization value\n_CregF( float3, c_vScreenSizeSmooth, 11);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize  = c_vScreenSizeSmooth.xy;\nstatic float  c_fSmoothShading = c_vScreenSizeSmooth.z;\n// (c_vViewPosAbsPixRight uses const reg c12!)\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (name of 1st two members must match names of depth/shadow pass vertex shaders!)\n  _inReg( float4, vUV_Z_AMul, 0);        // tex coordinates, z value and alpha-channel multiplier\n  _inReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);        // (.w is used for light occlusion!)\n  _inReg( float4, vFrontAmbientHaze, 2); // haze amount (.w)  \n  _inReg( float4, vBackAmbientFog,   3); // fog amount (.w)\n  _inReg( float4, vColDiffMod, 4);       // shade color modulator for diffuse\n  _inReg( float3, vVexTintColor, 5);        // tint color\n#ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n  // shade (detail) texture coodinates\n  _inReg( float2, vDetShadeUV, 6);\n#endif\n#if defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT) || defined(RSM_NORMALMAP)\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n    _inReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 7);\n  #else\n    // or just vertex normal\n    _inReg( float3, vNormalAbs, 7);\n  #endif\n#endif // HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\n  _inFacReg;\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// static variables used\nstatic float3 g_vNormalAbs;\nstatic float3 g_vViewDirAbs;\nstatic float4 g_vDiffuse;\nstatic float4 g_vTranslucencyMap;\nstatic float3 g_vBackFaceLit;\n\n\n// apply shading\ninline float3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs)\n{\n  // diffuse lit\n  float2 vNdotL;\n  vNdotL.x = dot( g_vNormalAbs, vLightDirAbs);\n  vNdotL.y = dot( g_vNormalAbs,-vLightDirAbs);\n  float2 vSmooth = vNdotL *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // lerp between smooth and normal diffuse lighting\n  vNdotL = lerp( saturate( vNdotL), vSmooth, _tcast(float2,c_fSmoothShading));\n\n  // add front specularity\n  float fSpecularityFactor = PhongSpecularity( g_vNormalAbs, g_vViewDirAbs, vLightDirAbs, c_fSpecPower);\n  float3 vShading = g_vDiffuse.rgb + c_vSpecColor *fSpecularityFactor *g_vTranslucencyMap.a;\n  // and apply front diffuse\n  vShading *= vNdotL.x;\n\n  // calculate back face diffuse lighting\n  g_vBackFaceLit = c_sli_vColor *vNdotL.y;\n  g_vBackFaceLit*= GetLightFactor();\n\n  // but return front-face lighting here\n  return vShading;\n}\n\n#ifdef run_VegetationPS\n\n// Screen rendering shader.\nPS_ENTRY( VegetationPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vViewPosAbsPix = VRSelect(c_vViewPosAbsPixLeft, c_vViewPosAbsPixRight);\n\n  // cache screen raster coordinates\n  SetRasterPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_v1oScreenSize));\n\n  // adjust facing sign\n  float fInPolyFace = PS_FACE * c_fFacingness;\n\n  // fetch pixel from diffuse texture\n  g_vDiffuse = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy));\n  LinearSpace( g_vDiffuse.rgb);\n\n  // modulate by constant color, combined with shade of color map (if any)\n  g_vDiffuse *= PS_IN( vColDiffMod);\n\n#ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n\n  // sample (detail) shade texture (in gamma space!)\n  float3 vShadeTex = texSample2D( t_sShade, s_tShade, PS_IN( vDetShadeUV)).rgb;\n  \n#if 1\n  // (optimized)\n  vShadeTex = saturate( vShadeTex *c_vShadePower.x +c_vShadePower.y);\n#else\n  // (original)\n  vShadeTex = vShadeTex *2.0f -1.0f;\n  vShadeTex*= c_vShadePower.x;\n  vShadeTex = vShadeTex *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // don't go negative\n  vShadeTex = saturate( vShadeTex);\n#endif\n  // to shade mode\n  vShadeTex *= 2.0f;\n  // into linear space fast (instead of ^2.2)\n  vShadeTex *= vShadeTex;\n  // and modulate diffuse with it\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb *= vShadeTex;\n\n#endif // SHADE_DETAIL\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n  // calculate pixel-view distance(^2!) and direction\n  g_vViewDirAbs = g_vViewPosAbsPix - PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  float fPixDist2 = dot( g_vViewDirAbs, g_vViewDirAbs);\n  // and attenuate bumps (normal-map) by that\n  float fBumpAtt = 1.0f- saturate( fPixDist2*c_f1oNormalMaxDist2); \n  fBumpAtt *= c_fNormalMapStrength;\n\n  // fetch normal in tangent space\n  float4 vNormalTan = texSample2D( t_sNormalMap, s_tNormalMap, PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy));\n  vNormalTan.xyz = nor3D(vNormalTan);  \n  vNormalTan.xyz = norAttenuate(vNormalTan.xyz, fBumpAtt);\n  vNormalTan.w = 0.0f;\n\n#endif // HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n#if defined(HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT) || defined(RSM_NORMALMAP)\n\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    // and transform it to absolute space\n    g_vNormalAbs = _mulT( vNormalTan.xyz, PS_IN( mTanToAbs));\n  #else \n    // fetch normal in absolute space\n    g_vNormalAbs = PS_IN( vNormalAbs);\n  #endif\n  // (re)normalize it\n  g_vNormalAbs = normalize( g_vNormalAbs);\n  // and eventually flip (for 2-sided lighting)\n  g_vNormalAbs = FlipNormal( g_vNormalAbs, fInPolyFace);\n\n#endif // HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT || RSM_NORMALMAP\n\n  // final output gets accumulated here\n  float4 vOutColor = float4( 0,0,0, g_vDiffuse.a);\n\n  // fetch pixel from translucency texture\n  g_vTranslucencyMap = texSample2D( t_sTransMap, s_tTransMap, PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy));\n  // calculate sub-surface light passing factor\n  float3 vSSSFactor = g_vTranslucencyMap.rgb * c_vTranslucencyBias;\n\n  // modulate by tint color adjusted by SSS factor\n  g_vDiffuse.rgb *= lerp(\n    PS_IN(vVexTintColor.rgb),\n    float3(1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f), \n    step(vSSSFactor, float3(0.1f, 0.1f, 0.1f))\n  );\n\n  // sample fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n  float4 vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos());\n  vIllumAmbOccSample = vIllumAmbOccSample *c_vMaskFLAO.xxxz +c_vMaskFLAO.yyyw;\n\n#ifdef HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT\n\n  // get front and back ambient, depending on polygon orientation\n  float3 vFrontAmbient= (fInPolyFace>0.0f) ? PS_IN( vBackAmbientFog.rgb)   : PS_IN( vFrontAmbientHaze.rgb);  \n  float3 vBackAmbient = (fInPolyFace>0.0f) ? PS_IN( vFrontAmbientHaze.rgb) : PS_IN( vBackAmbientFog.rgb);  \n\n  // note that vertex shading vales also contain static light influence, so they represent full solution\n  // result = (front shading + back shading*embraced front light*biases) * texture\n  vOutColor.rgb = vFrontAmbient+ vBackAmbient *(1.0f-g_vDiffuse.rgb) *vSSSFactor;\n  // modulate by ambient occlusion \n  vOutColor.rgb *= vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n  // and add illumination (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vOutColor.rgb += vIllumAmbOccSample.rgb *vIllumAmbOccSample.a;\n\n  // modulate all that by diffuse component\n  vOutColor.rgb *= g_vDiffuse.rgb;\n\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    // fake light direction for ambient normal-map\n    vOutColor.rgb *= CalcFakeLightModulator( vNormalTan.xyz);\n  #endif\n\n#else // !HAS_AMBIENT_LIGHT \n\n  // attenuate ambient occlusion by 50% for direct lights\n  vIllumAmbOccSample.a = vIllumAmbOccSample.a *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n#endif\n\n  // if has dynamic light\n#ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n\n  // calculate view direction vector\n  float4 vInVexPosAbs = float4( PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.xyz), 1.0f);\n  #ifndef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    g_vViewDirAbs = normalize( g_vViewPosAbsPix - vInVexPosAbs.xyz);\n  #else\n    g_vViewDirAbs *= rsqrt( fPixDist2);\n  #endif\n  #ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n    // apply distant (directional) light\n    float3 vDynamicLight = DistantLight( vInVexPosAbs);\n\n  #elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n    // apply spot (reflector) light\n    float3 vDynamicLight = SpotLight( vInVexPosAbs);\n\n  #elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n    // apply omni (point) light\n    float3 vDynamicLight = OmniLight( vInVexPosAbs);\n\n  #endif\n\n  // modulate dynamic light by ambient and light occlusion\n  vDynamicLight *= vIllumAmbOccSample.a * PS_IN( vVexPosAbs.w);\n\n  // dynamic light = (front shading dynamic (CalcLight()) + sss of back dynamic light) * diffuse\n  float3 vBackEmbracedDyn = (1.0f-g_vDiffuse.rgb) * g_vBackFaceLit;\n  // sss of back dynamic light = back embraced dynamic light * not in shadow factor * light passing factor\n  float3 vDynamicSSS = vBackEmbracedDyn * vSSSFactor;\n  vDynamicSSS *= GetShadowFactor(); // ? *0.75f +0.25f\n  // back embraced dynamic light = (1-diffuse) * vertex back dynamic light\n  vOutColor.rgb += vDynamicLight + (vDynamicSSS * g_vDiffuse.rgb);\n\n#endif // HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n\n  // if has fog and/or haze\n#ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  float2 vFozeAmount = float2( PS_IN( vBackAmbientFog.w), PS_IN( vFrontAmbientHaze.w));\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, vFozeAmount);\n#endif\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n  // apply alpha fading\n  vOutColor.a *= PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.a);\n\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a *c_vAlphaRange.x +c_vAlphaRange.y);\n\n#if RSM_NORMALMAP\n  vOutColor.rgb = g_vNormalAbs.xyz * 0.5f + 0.5f;\n#endif\n\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n}\n\n#endif // run_VegetationPS\n#ifdef run_BakeVegetationPS\n\n// Baking shader.\nPS_ENTRY( BakeVegetationPS)\n{\n  // fetch pixel from diffuse texture\n  float4 vDiffuse = texSample2D( t_sDiffuse, s_tDiffuse, PS_IN( vUV_Z_AMul.xy));\n  PS_OUT( vDiffuse);\n}\n\n#endif // run_BakeVegetationPS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// VegetationShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BasicTransformations.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/SphericalHarmonics.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Shockwave.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/FozeCalc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n#ifdef run_VegetationVS\n\n// view-proj matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mViewProjLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vViewProjRightX, 31);\n// object to absolute (world) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToAbs, 4);\n// 3rd row (Z) of model-view matrix, for shadow casting\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewZ, 7);\n\n// time, ambient occlusion factor and number of shockwaves\n_CregF( float4, c_fTimeShockAMulAO, 8);\nstatic float c_fCurrentTime = c_fTimeShockAMulAO.x;\nstatic float c_fAOInfluence = c_fTimeShockAMulAO.y;\nstatic float c_fShockwavesCt= c_fTimeShockAMulAO.z;\nstatic float c_fAlphaMul    = c_fTimeShockAMulAO.w;\n\n// tree sway strengths\n_CregF( float4, c_vTreeSwayStrengthsLitOcc, 9);\nstatic float3 c_vTreeSwayStrengths = c_vTreeSwayStrengthsLitOcc.xyz;\nstatic float  c_fLightOcclusionInfluence = c_vTreeSwayStrengthsLitOcc.w;\n  // (fog/haze use const regs c10-c13!)\n  // (SPH calc uses const regs c14-c22!)\n// branch sway Strengths\n_CregF( float4, c_vBranchSwayAmbient, 23);\nstatic float c_fBranchSwayStrength= c_vBranchSwayAmbient.x;\nstatic float c_fEdgeSwayStrength  = c_vBranchSwayAmbient.y;\nstatic float c_fBranchSwaySpeed   = c_vBranchSwayAmbient.z;\nstatic float c_fAmbientModulator  = c_vBranchSwayAmbient.w;\n\n// viewer position in absolute space\n_CregF( float4, c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft, 24);\n_CregF( float3, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight,25);\n// using separate channel for back facing ambient occlusion? (-1=no, 1=yes)\nstatic float c_fBackFaceAO = c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft.w;\n\n// mask for color map\n_CregF( float4, c_vInputColorMasksShockElast, 26);\nstatic float2 c_vInputColorMapMask = c_vInputColorMasksShockElast.xy;\nstatic float  c_fShockwaveStrength = c_vInputColorMasksShockElast.z;\nstatic float  c_fElasticityFactor  = c_vInputColorMasksShockElast.w;\n\n// constant diffuse color\n_CregF( float4, c_vDiffuseColor, 27);\n\n// mapping adjustment for detail shade texture\n_CregM42F( c_mShadeMapping, 28);\n\n// normal and tangent signed/unsigned masks\n_CregF( float4, c_vNorTanMask, 30);\n\n// (c_vViewProjRightX uses reg c31!)\n// \n_CregM44F( c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft, 32);\n\n\n#elif run_BakeVegetationVS\n\n// model view-proj matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mModelViewProj, 0);\n\n#endif\n\n\n// object to absolute space transformation matrix\nstatic float4x3 g_mObjToAbs;\nstatic float3 g_vTreeSwayStrengths;\nstatic float4 g_vDiffuseColor;\nstatic float3 g_vTintColor;\nstatic float  g_fAlphaMul;\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition,  0);\n  _inReg( float2, vDiffuseUV, 1);\n  _inReg( float4, vWeights,   2);\n  _inReg( float4, vNormal,    3);\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n  _inReg( float4, vColorShade,4); // shade color modulation for diffuse texture\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    _inReg( float4, vTangent, 5);\n  #endif\n  #ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n    _inReg( float4, vShadeUV, 6);\n  #endif\n#endif \n#ifdef INSTANCING\n  _inReg( float4x3, mInstObjToAbs, 7);\n  _inReg( float4, vTreeSwaysAMul, 10);\n  _inReg( float4, vDiffuseCol, 11);\n  _inReg( float3, vTintColor, 12);\n#endif \nVS_IN_END\n\n// weight map values\nstatic float4 i_vWeights;\n// (r=sway pitch, g=sway phase, b=edges strength, a=ambient occlusion)\n#define i_fWeightBranchSwayStrength i_vWeights.r\n#define i_fWeightBranchSwayPhase    i_vWeights.g\n#define i_fWeightEdgeSwayStrength   i_vWeights.b\n#define i_fWeightAmbientOcclusion   i_vWeights.a\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  // (name of 1st two members must match names of depth/shadow pass pixel shaders!)\n  _outReg( float4, vUV_Z_AMul, 0);  // tex coordinates, z value and alpha keying multiplier\n#ifdef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n  #ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n    _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);  // (.w is used for light occlusion!)\n  #endif\n  #ifdef GENERATE_MVECS\n    _outReg( float4, vClipSpacePos, 3);\n    _outReg( float4, vPreviousClipSpacePos, 4);\n  #endif\n  #if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n    _outReg( float4, vModelSpacePos, 5);\n  #endif\n#else\n  _outReg( float4, vVexPosAbs, 1);  // (.w is used for light occlusion!)\n  _outReg( float4, vFrontAmbientHaze, 2);  // haze amount (.w)  \n  _outReg( float4, vBackAmbientFog,   3);  // fog amount (.w)\n  _outReg( float4, vColDiffMod, 4);        // shade color modulator for diffuse\n  _outReg( float3, vVexTintColor, 5);         // tint color\n  #ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n    // shade (detail) texture coodinates\n    _outReg( float2, vDetShadeUV, 6);      \n  #endif\n  #ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n    #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n      // transformation matrix from tangent to absolute space\n      _outReg( float3x3, mTanToAbs, 7);        \n    #else\n      // or just vertex normal\n      _outReg( float3, vNormalAbs, 7);\n    #endif\n  #endif // NEEDS_TANGENTS\n#endif // DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n#ifdef run_VegetationVS\n\n\ninline float4 SmoothCurve( float4 fx)\n{\n  return fx*fx * (3.0f-2.0f*fx);\n}\n\ninline float4 TriangleWave( float4 fx)\n{\n  return abs( frac( fx+0.5f) *2.0f -1.0f);\n}\n\ninline float4 SmoothTriangleWave( float4 fx)\n{\n  return SmoothCurve( TriangleWave(fx));\n}\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( VegetationVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n#ifdef INSTANCING\n\n  g_mObjToAbs = VS_IN( mInstObjToAbs);\n  g_vTreeSwayStrengths = VS_IN( vTreeSwaysAMul.xyz);\n  g_vDiffuseColor = VS_IN( vDiffuseCol);\n  g_vTintColor = VS_IN( vTintColor);\n  g_fAlphaMul = VS_IN( vTreeSwaysAMul.w);\n\n#else\n\n  g_mObjToAbs = c_mObjToAbs;\n  g_vTreeSwayStrengths = c_vTreeSwayStrengths;\n  g_vDiffuseColor = c_vDiffuseColor;\n  g_vTintColor = float3(1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f);\n  g_fAlphaMul = c_fAlphaMul;\n\n#endif\n\n  // extract object-to-absolute space rotation matrix\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRot = _tcastM33F( g_mObjToAbs);\n\n  // expand normal (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n  float3 vNor = ExpandNormal( VS_IN( vNormal), c_vNorTanMask.yyyx);\n\n  // prepare weight factors\n  i_vWeights = VS_IN( vWeights);\n\n  // (vertex position in absolute space)\n  float4 vOutVexPosAbs;\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = 1.0f;\n\n#if GENERATE_MVECS==1\n  float4 vOutPosPreviousClipLeft = float4( 0,0,0,0 );\n  float4 vOutPosPreviousClipRight = float4( 0,0,0,0 );\n#endif\n\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    // expand tangent (from unsigned to signed, if needed)\n    float4 vTan = ExpandTangent( VS_IN( vTangent), c_vNorTanMask.wwwz);\n  #endif\n\n  // fix stretching on it\n  float3x3 mObjToAbsRotFix = mObjToAbsRot;\n  FixRotationStretch( mObjToAbsRotFix);\n  // transform normal from object to absolute space\n  float3 vNorAbs = mul( vNor, mObjToAbsRotFix);\n\n  // calculate SH lighting for front and back lighting\n  float2 vFrontBackAO = float2( i_fWeightAmbientOcclusion, VS_IN( vColorShade).a);\n  vFrontBackAO = lerp( _tcast(float2,c_fAmbientModulator), vFrontBackAO, _tcast(float2,c_fAOInfluence));\n  vFrontBackAO.y = (c_fBackFaceAO>=0) ? vFrontBackAO.y : vFrontBackAO.x;\n  // and apply ambient occlusion to it (separated or same for back-faces)\n  VS_OUT( vFrontAmbientHaze.rgb)= CalcSHLight( vNorAbs) *vFrontBackAO.x;\n  VS_OUT( vBackAmbientFog.rgb)  = CalcSHLight(-vNorAbs) *vFrontBackAO.y;\n\n  #ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n\n    // if has normal-map\n    #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n      // construct tangent to object space transformation matrix\n      float3 vBiN = cross( vNor*vTan.w, vTan.xyz);\n      float3x3 mOutTanToAbs = float3x3( vTan.xyz, vBiN, vNor);\n\n      // combine that with absolute space matrix\n      #if _GLSL\n        mObjToAbsRotFix = transpose( mObjToAbsRotFix);\n      #endif\n      // to get tangent to absolute transformation\n      mOutTanToAbs = _mulT( mOutTanToAbs, mObjToAbsRotFix);\n      // (re)normalized\n      VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = NormalizeRotation( mOutTanToAbs);\n\n    // if no normal-map\n    #else\n\n      // just use vertex normal\n      // (in absolute space!)\n      VS_OUT( vNormalAbs) = vNorAbs;\n\n    #endif \n  #endif // NEEDS_TANGENTS\n\n  // get diffuse color shade-modulation (if any)\n  float3 vVexDiffuseColor = VS_IN( vColorShade).rgb;\n  vVexDiffuseColor = vVexDiffuseColor *c_vInputColorMapMask.xxx +c_vInputColorMapMask.yyy;\n  vVexDiffuseColor = pow( vVexDiffuseColor, _tcast(float3,2.2f));\n  g_vDiffuseColor.rgb *= vVexDiffuseColor;\n  VS_OUT( vColDiffMod) = g_vDiffuseColor;\n\n  // get tint color\n  VS_OUT(vVexTintColor) = g_vTintColor;\n\n  // pass light occlusion influence to pixel shader (via vertex position in absolute space's W coord)\n  vOutVexPosAbs.w = lerp( 1.0f, i_fWeightAmbientOcclusion, c_fLightOcclusionInfluence);\n\n  #ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n    // detail shade texture coords\n    VS_OUT( vDetShadeUV) = mulM42F( VS_IN( vShadeUV), c_mShadeMapping); \n  #endif\n\n#endif // !DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n\n  // copy diffuse mapping coordinates\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.xy) = VS_IN( vDiffuseUV);\n\n  // fetch object space position\n  float4 vObjVtxPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  // and distance from origin\n  float fOriginDistOrg = length( vObjVtxPos.xyz);\n\n  // apply tree bending (stronger with height)\n  float fTreeBend = vObjVtxPos.y *g_vTreeSwayStrengths.x +1.0f;\n  // bending curve is not linear\n  fTreeBend*= fTreeBend;\n  fTreeBend = fTreeBend*fTreeBend - fTreeBend;\n  vObjVtxPos.xz += g_vTreeSwayStrengths.yz * fTreeBend;\n\n  // keep vertex to origin distance (rotate around origin)\n  float fOriginDistBend = max( length( vObjVtxPos.xyz), 0.00001f);\n  float3 vVtxObjNor = vObjVtxPos.xyz / fOriginDistBend;\n  vObjVtxPos.xyz = vVtxObjNor * fOriginDistOrg;\n\n  // phase randoms are generated from model abs position (tree), from user map (branch) and from vertex position (edge)\n#if _GLSL\n  float fTreeSwayPhase = g_mObjToAbs[0].w + g_mObjToAbs[1].w + g_mObjToAbs[2].w;\n#elif _HLSL\n  float fTreeSwayPhase = dot( g_mObjToAbs._m30_m31_m32, 1.0f);\n#endif\n  float fBranchSwayPhase = fTreeSwayPhase + i_fWeightBranchSwayPhase*8.0f;\n  float fEdgeSwayPhase   = fBranchSwayPhase + dot( vObjVtxPos.xyz, _tcast(float3,1));\n\n  // calculate wave function arguments (x=edge, y=branch)\n  float2 vPhases = float2( fEdgeSwayPhase, fBranchSwayPhase) +c_fCurrentTime;\n  float4 vFrequencyMultipliers = float4( 1.856f, 0.756f, 0.345f, 0.185f);\n  // calculate, renormalize (-1..1) and bias wave function arguments\n  float4 vWaveArg = (vPhases.xxyy*vFrequencyMultipliers *2.0f -1.0f) *c_fBranchSwaySpeed;\n  float4 vSway = SmoothTriangleWave( vWaveArg);\n  // vertex sway is sum of branch and edge movement\n  float2 vVtxSway = vSway.xz + vSway.yw;\n  float fEdgeSwayStrength   = i_fWeightEdgeSwayStrength   *c_fEdgeSwayStrength;\n  float fBranchSwayStrength = i_fWeightBranchSwayStrength *c_fBranchSwayStrength;\n  float2 vNormalSway = vNor.xz *fEdgeSwayStrength;\n\n  // apply branch displace to y, x displace along normal's xz direction\n  // (needed to [isolate] this one to avoid z-fighting between depth prepass and render pass!)\n  vObjVtxPos.xyz += vVtxSway.xyx * float3( vNormalSway.x, fBranchSwayStrength, vNormalSway.y);\n\n  // transform vertex position to absolute space\n  vOutVexPosAbs.xyz = mulM43F( vObjVtxPos, g_mObjToAbs);\n  #if !defined(DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS) || defined(APPLY_FOZE)\n    VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = vOutVexPosAbs;\n  #endif\n  // and give its Z for depth prepass\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.z) = dot( vOutVexPosAbs, c_vViewZ);\n  // along with alpha-channel multiplier\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.w) = g_fAlphaMul;\n  \n#if _GLSL\n  // get pivot position in to absolute space\n  float3 vAbsPivotPos = float3( g_mObjToAbs[0].w, g_mObjToAbs[1].w, g_mObjToAbs[2].w);\n#else\n  // (it's just an offset of world-space matrix)\n  float3 vAbsPivotPos = g_mObjToAbs[3];\n#endif\n\n  // and there are some shockwaves\n  if( c_fShockwavesCt > 0.0f) {\n\n    // apply shockwave effects (if any)\n    ApplyShockwavesAbs( c_fShockwavesCt, vOutVexPosAbs.xyz, vAbsPivotPos,\n      c_fElasticityFactor, 1.5f*fBranchSwayStrength, c_fShockwaveStrength);\n    \n    // extract scaling part of obj-to-abs transformation matrix\n    float3 v1oScale;\n    v1oScale.x = length( mObjToAbsRot[0]);\n    v1oScale.y = length( mObjToAbsRot[1]);\n    v1oScale.z = length( mObjToAbsRot[2]);\n    v1oScale = 1.0f / v1oScale;\n    // normalize rotation matrix\n    float3x3 mScaledRot;\n    mScaledRot[0] = mObjToAbsRot[0] *v1oScale.x;\n    mScaledRot[1] = mObjToAbsRot[1] *v1oScale.y;\n    mScaledRot[2] = mObjToAbsRot[2] *v1oScale.z;\n    // (translation part is pivot position!)\n    \n    // untranslate, unrotate and unscale absolute space vertex to get object space vertex\n    vObjVtxPos.xyz = vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - vAbsPivotPos;\n    vObjVtxPos.xyz = mul( mScaledRot, vObjVtxPos.xyz);  // (transposed multiply)\n    vObjVtxPos.xyz*= v1oScale;\n  }\n  \n  // and then to clip-space\n  float4x4 mObjToAbs4 =\n  #if _GLSL\n    float4x4( g_mObjToAbs);\n  #elif _HLSL\n  { float4( g_mObjToAbs[0], 0),\n    float4( g_mObjToAbs[1], 0),\n    float4( g_mObjToAbs[2], 0),\n    float4( g_mObjToAbs[3], 1) };\n  #endif\n  // (but don't use abs coordinate, as it may lack precision;\n  //  needs to project from object-space, DIRECTLY to clip-space!)\n  float4x4 mMVPLeft = mul( mObjToAbs4, c_mViewProjLeft);\n  float4x4 mMVPRight = mul( mObjToAbs4, VRRightMatrix(c_mViewProjLeft, c_vViewProjRightX));\n  float4 vOutPosClipLeft = mul( vObjVtxPos, mMVPLeft);\n  float4 vOutPosClipRight = mul( vObjVtxPos, mMVPRight);\n\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n  \n  #ifdef APPLY_FOZE\n    // calculate fog and haze amount\n    float4 vViewPosAbsVex;\n    vViewPosAbsVex.w = 1.0f;\n    vViewPosAbsVex.xyz = VRMiddle( c_vViewPosAbsVexLeft.xyz, c_vViewPosAbsVexRight);\n    float fVexDist = length( vOutVexPosAbs.xyz - vViewPosAbsVex.xyz);\n    VS_OUT( vBackAmbientFog.w)  = CalcFogAmount( vOutVexPosAbs, vViewPosAbsVex, fVexDist);\n    VS_OUT( vFrontAmbientHaze.w)= CalcHazeAmount( vOutVexPosAbs.y, fVexDist);\n  #else\n    // no fog nor haze\n    VS_OUT( vBackAmbientFog.w)  = 0.0f;\n    VS_OUT( vFrontAmbientHaze.w)= 0.0f;\n  #endif\n\n#else\n  #ifdef GENERATE_MVECS\n    VS_OUT( vClipSpacePos) = vOutPosClipLeft;\n    // for this shader 'c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft' is actually just View*Proj\n    float4x4 mMVPPrevLeft = mul( mObjToAbs4, c_mPreviousModelToClipLeft);\n    VS_OUT( vPreviousClipSpacePos) = mul( vObjVtxPos, mMVPPrevLeft );\n  #endif\n  #if USE_HASH_ALPHA\n    VS_OUT( vModelSpacePos ) = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  #endif\n#endif\n\n  // output clip-space position\n  VS_OUT_POS = vOutPosClipLeft;\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = vOutPosClipRight;\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_VegetationVS\n#ifdef run_BakeVegetationVS\n\n\n// main for baking\nVS_ENTRY( BakeVegetationVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // apply projection\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mModelViewProj);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = VS_OUT_POS;\n  // copy diffuse mapping coordinates\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.xy) = VS_IN( vDiffuseUV);\n  VS_OUT( vUV_Z_AMul.zw) = float2(0,1);\n  // and set various dummies\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosAbs) = _tcast(float4,0);\n#ifndef DEPTH_SHADOW_PASS\n  VS_OUT( vColDiffMod) = _tcast(float4,1);\n  VS_OUT( vFrontAmbientHaze) = _tcast(float4,0);\n  VS_OUT( vBackAmbientFog) = _tcast(float4,0);\n  VS_OUT( vVexTintColor) = _tcast(float3,0);\n  #ifdef SHADE_DETAIL\n    VS_OUT( vDetShadeUV) = _tcast(float2,0);\n  #endif\n  #ifdef NEEDS_TANGENTS\n    #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n      VS_OUT( mTanToAbs) = _tcast(float3x3,0);\n    #else\n      VS_OUT( vNormalAbs) = _tcast(float3,0);\n    #endif\n  #endif\n#endif\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n#endif // run_BakeVegetationVS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// VolumetricShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// depth range \n_CregF( float3, c_vDepthRange, 0);\nstatic float c_fDepthStart  = c_vDepthRange.x;\nstatic float c_f1oDepthRange= c_vDepthRange.y;\nstatic float c_fFaceStart   = c_vDepthRange.z;\n\n\n#ifdef run_DistancePS\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float, fVexDistView, 0);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// begin distance value\nPS_ENTRY( DistancePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // (output)\n\n  // adjust depth range (so we can flatten everything out of this range;\n  float fDistance = PS_IN( fVexDistView) *c_f1oDepthRange +c_fDepthStart;\n  // clamp depth to 0 to 1 range\n  fDistance = saturate( fDistance);\n\n  // encode depth from one 32bit float into 4 RGBA 8-bit integer components\n  float4 vEncodedDist;\n  vEncodedDist.r = fDistance;\n  vEncodedDist.g = frac( fDistance*255.0f);\n  vEncodedDist.r-= vEncodedDist.g /255.0f;\n  vEncodedDist.b = frac( vEncodedDist.g *255.0f);\n  vEncodedDist.g-= vEncodedDist.b /255.0f;\n  vEncodedDist.a = frac( vEncodedDist.b *255.0f);\n  vEncodedDist.b-= vEncodedDist.a /255.0f;\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vEncodedDist);\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(run_VolumetricPS)\n\n\n// distance buffer\n_Sreg2D( t_sDistance, s_tDistance, 0);\n// depth buffer\n_Sreg2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, 1);\n\n\n// diffuse color\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolDiffuse, 1);\n// pixel size of distance texture\n_CregF( float4, c_vPixSizeDensitySmooth, 2);\nstatic float2 c_vPixSize = c_vPixSizeDensitySmooth.xy;\n// (along with density and smoothing)\nstatic float  c_fDensity = c_vPixSizeDensitySmooth.z;\nstatic float  c_fSmooth  = c_vPixSizeDensitySmooth.w;\n// pixel size of depth texture\n_CregF( float3, c_vDepthPixSizeFace, 3);\nstatic float2 c_vDepthPixSize = c_vDepthPixSizeFace.xy;\nstatic float  c_fViewerFacing = c_vDepthPixSizeFace.z;\n// coord clamp edges (.xy=min, .zw=max)\n_CregF( float4, c_vEdges, 4);\n// lerp destination color dependant on the blend type\n_CregF( float4, c_vLerpDestMask, 5);\nstatic float4 c_vLerpDest = c_vLerpDestMask.xxxy;\nstatic float4 c_vLerpMask = c_vLerpDestMask.zzzw;\n// rotation model-view matrix (for normal)\n_CregM33F( c_mObjToViewRotPix, 6);\n\n\n// decoding depth factors\nstatic const float4 _c_vDecodeDistance = float4( 1.0f, 1.0f/255.0f, 1.0f/65025.0f, 1.0f/16581375.0f);\n\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n#ifdef FAST_VER\n  // .x=distance, .y=normal dot position\n  _inReg( float2, vDistNorPos, 0);  \n#else\n  _inReg( float3, vVexPosView, 0);  \n  _inReg( float3, vVexNorObj,  1);  \n#endif\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// begin volumetric\nPS_ENTRY( VolumetricPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // four depth distances (pixel, other-face, scene, front-back diff)\n  float4 vDistances;\n  #define fPixelDepth vDistances.x \n  #define fOtherFaceDepth vDistances.y \n  #define fSceneDepth vDistances.z \n  #define fDepthDiff vDistances.w \n\n  // adjust depth range (so we can flatten everything out of this range;\n#ifdef FAST_VER\n  fPixelDepth = PS_IN( vDistNorPos.x);\n#else\n  // transform position to view space\n  float3 vPosView = PS_IN( vVexPosView);\n  fPixelDepth = vPosView.z;\n#endif\n  fPixelDepth = abs( fPixelDepth);\n\n  // calc depth sampling texture coordinates\n  float2 vDistCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_vPixSize));\n\n  // sample and decode distance buffer\n  float4 vTexDistance = texSample2D( t_sDistance, s_tDistance, vDistCoord);\n  fOtherFaceDepth = dot( vTexDistance, _c_vDecodeDistance);\n  // restore depth range\n  fOtherFaceDepth = abs( fOtherFaceDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fFaceStart;\n\n  // sample depth texture\n  float2 vDepthCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize(c_vDepthPixSize));\n  fSceneDepth = texSample2D( t_sDepth, s_tDepth, vDepthCoord).r;\n  fSceneDepth = abs( fSceneDepth) *c_f1oDepthRange -c_fDepthStart;\n\n  // calculate depth difference\n#if 0\n  // SLOW\n  if( c_fViewerFacing >= 0.0f) {\n    fOtherFaceDepth = min( fOtherFaceDepth, fSceneDepth);\n    fDepthDiff = fOtherFaceDepth - fPixelDepth;\n  } else {\n    fPixelDepth = min( fPixelDepth, fSceneDepth);\n    fDepthDiff = fPixelDepth - fOtherFaceDepth;\n  }\n#else\n  // FAST\n  float2 vMinDiff = min( vDistances.yx, vDistances.zz) -vDistances.xy;\n  fDepthDiff = (c_fViewerFacing>=0.0f) ? vMinDiff.x : vMinDiff.y;\n#endif\n\n// (fast but edges visible with high smoothing)\n#ifdef FAST_VER\n\n\n  // get normal Z in view space\n  float fNorViewZ = PS_IN( vDistNorPos.y);\n\n// (slow but no edges)\n#else\n\n  // normalize position to get direction\n  vPosView = normalize( vPosView);\n\n  // transform normal to view space \n  // (accounted for non-uniform stretching)\n  float3 vInNor = PS_IN( vVexNorObj);\n  float3 vNorView = mul( vInNor, c_mObjToViewRotPix);\n  vNorView = normalize( vNorView);\n\n  // calculate dot product between view direction and normal\n  float fNorViewZ = dot( vNorView, vPosView);\n\n#endif\n\n  // calcuate thickness accounting for normal\n  fNorViewZ = abs( fNorViewZ); // (absolute normal)\n  float fDensityNor = c_fDensity *pow( fNorViewZ, c_fSmooth);\n  float fThickness = saturate( exp(-fDepthDiff *fDensityNor));\n\n  // apply thickness to color\n  float4 vOutColor = lerp( c_vcolDiffuse, c_vLerpDest, c_vLerpMask*fThickness);\n  //vOutColor = float4( fOtherFaceDepth, fNorViewZ, fPixelDepth, 1.0f);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutColor);\n\n  // undefine some\n  #undef fPixelDepth\n  #undef fOtherFaceDepth\n  #undef fSceneDepth\n  #undef fDepthDiff\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// VolumetricShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n\n// object (model) to clip space transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n\n\n#ifdef run_DistanceVS\n\n// 3rd row (Z) of model-view matrix\n_CregF( float4, c_vModelViewZ, 5);  \n\n// input to VS\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float, fVexDistView, 0);\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( DistanceVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // transform position to clip-space\n  float4 vInPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vInPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul(vInPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // output depth value from Z (in meters, will be normalized later)\n  // (we cannot output W here, because of ortho projection has W==1)\n  VS_OUT( fVexDistView) = dot( vInPos, c_vModelViewZ);\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(run_VolumetricVS)\n\n\n// model-view matrix for position\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToViewPos, 6);\n// model-view matrix for normal\n_CregM33F( c_mObjToViewRotVex, 9);\n// multiply-add for normal (either 2,-1 or 1,0)\n_CregF( float2, c_vNorSign, 12);  \n\n\n// input to VS\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float3, vNormal, 1);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n#ifdef FAST_VER\n  // .x=distance, .y=normal dot position\n  _outReg( float2, vDistNorPos, 0);  \n#else\n  _outReg( float3, vVexPosView, 0);  \n  _outReg( float3, vVexNorObj,  1);  \n#endif\nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( VolumetricVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // transform position to clip-space\n  float4 vInPos = VS_IN( vPosition);\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( vInPos, c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul(vInPos, VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // transform position to view space\n  float3 vPosView = mulM43F( vInPos, c_mObjToViewPos);\n  \n  // get (and expand) normal from input\n  float3 vInNor = VS_IN( vNormal) *c_vNorSign.xxx +c_vNorSign.yyy;\n\n#ifdef FAST_VER\n\n  // output view-space vertex positon Z coord to pixel shader\n  VS_OUT( vDistNorPos.x) = vPosView.z;\n\n  // normalize position to get direction\n  vPosView = normalize( vPosView);\n\n  // transform normal to view space \n  // (accounted for non-uniform stretching)\n  float3 vNorView = mul( vInNor, c_mObjToViewRotVex);\n  vNorView = normalize( vNorView);\n\n  // output dot product between position and normal\n  VS_OUT( vDistNorPos.y) = dot( vNorView, vPosView);\n\n#else\n\n  // output position in view space\n  VS_OUT( vVexPosView) = vPosView;\n  // and normal in object space\n  VS_OUT( vVexNorObj) = vInNor;\n\n#endif\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n\n\n#endif // run_\n\n\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// WaterMapAnimatorShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sHeightTexM1, s_tHeightTexM1, 0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sHeightTexM2, s_tHeightTexM2, 1);\n_Sreg2D( t_sShoreMapTex, s_tShoreMapTex, 2);\n\n// constants\n_CregF( float2, c_v1oHeightM1Size, 0);  ///< 1.0 / size of M1 frame texture (in pixels)\n_CregF( float4, c_vConstants,      1);  ///< x:damping; y:wavespeed; z:2-4*wavespeed\n\n// input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( mainPS)\n{\n  float2 vInTexCoord = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy);\n  float fXPosOfs = (vInTexCoord.x > (1.0f-c_v1oHeightM1Size.x)) ? -1.0f :  1.0f;  \n  float fXNegOfs = (vInTexCoord.x <       c_v1oHeightM1Size.x)  ?  1.0f : -1.0f;  \n  float fYPosOfs = (vInTexCoord.y > (1.0f-c_v1oHeightM1Size.y)) ? -1.0f :  1.0f;  \n  float fYNegOfs = (vInTexCoord.y <       c_v1oHeightM1Size.y)  ?  1.0f : -1.0f;  \n\n  // sample height (from m1 and m2 frames)\n  float fHeightM1C = texSample2D( t_sHeightTexM1, s_tHeightTexM1, vInTexCoord).r;\n  float fHeightM1E = texSample2D( t_sHeightTexM1, s_tHeightTexM1, vInTexCoord+ c_v1oHeightM1Size*float2(fXPosOfs, 0)).r;\n  float fHeightM1W = texSample2D( t_sHeightTexM1, s_tHeightTexM1, vInTexCoord+ c_v1oHeightM1Size*float2(fXNegOfs, 0)).r;\n  float fHeightM1N = texSample2D( t_sHeightTexM1, s_tHeightTexM1, vInTexCoord+ c_v1oHeightM1Size*float2( 0,fYNegOfs)).r;\n  float fHeightM1S = texSample2D( t_sHeightTexM1, s_tHeightTexM1, vInTexCoord+ c_v1oHeightM1Size*float2( 0,fYPosOfs)).r;\n  float fHeightM2C = texSample2D( t_sHeightTexM2, s_tHeightTexM2, vInTexCoord).r;\n  \n  /** formula:\n  p1 - result (height in this frame)\n  m1 - height in last frame\n  m2 - height in frame before last\n  t  - time delta (from last to this frame)\n  K  - damping constant\n  c  - wave speed\n  p1[i,j] = m1[i,j] + (1-K*t)*(m1[i,j]-m2[i,j]) +\n    ((t*t*c*c)/(x*x))*(4*m1[i,j] - m1[i+1,j] - m1[i-1,j] - m1[i,j+1] - m1[i,-j])\n  */\n  // simulate wave\n  float fHeight = c_vConstants.y* (fHeightM1E+fHeightM1W+fHeightM1N+fHeightM1S) +c_vConstants.z *fHeightM1C -fHeightM2C;\n  // damping\n  fHeight *= c_vConstants.x;\n  // apply fixed points\n  fHeight *= texSample2D( t_sShoreMapTex, s_tShoreMapTex, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy)).r;\n\n  // clamp height to valid range\n  fHeight = clamp( fHeight, -1.0f, 1.0f);\n\n  // output\n  PS_OUT( _tcast( float4, fHeight));\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// WaterMapDisruptorShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if VS_VER // - - - - - - VERTEX SHADER\n\n\n// constants\n_CregF( float4, c_vPosCoordsAdj, 0); // adjustment for position coordinates\n\n// VS input\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vInPos, 0);\nVS_IN_END\n\n// VS output\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float2, vDisSrcUVs, 0);\nVS_OUT_END\n\n\n// vertex shader\nVS_ENTRY( WaterDisruptVS)\n{\n  // output\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  // adjust position by \"sub-rectangle\"\n  float2 vPosAdj = VS_IN( vInPos.xy) *c_vPosCoordsAdj.xy +c_vPosCoordsAdj.zw; \n  VS_OUT_POS = float4( vPosAdj, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n  // and output full texture mapping coords\n  VS_OUT( vDisSrcUVs) = VS_IN( vInPos.zw);\n\n  // done\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT;\n}\n\n\n#elif PS_VER // - - - - - - PIXEL SHADER\n\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sDisrupt, s_tDisrupt, 0);\n\n// constants\n_CregF( float, c_fDisruptStrength, 0);\n\n// input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float2, vDisSrcUVs, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( WaterDisruptPS)\n{\n  // sample disruption texture\n  float fDisrupt = texSample2D( t_sDisrupt, s_tDisrupt, PS_IN( vDisSrcUVs.xy)).r;\n  // calculate new pixel depth modulator\n  float fNewDepth = fDisrupt * c_fDisruptStrength;\n  // clamp depth to valid range\n  fNewDepth = saturate( fNewDepth);\n  // output\n  PS_OUT( _tcast( float4, fNewDepth));\n}\n\n\n#endif // VS_VER/PS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// WaterMapToBumpMapShader.sh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n\n// NORMAL MAP CALC OUT OF RGB OR GRAY TEXTURE\n\n// The Sobel filter extracts the first order derivates of the image,\n// that is, the slope. The slope in X and Y directon allows us to\n// given a heightmap evaluate the normal for each pixel. This is\n// the same this as ATI's NormalMapGenerator application does,\n// except this is in hardware.\n//\n// These are the filter kernels:\n//\n//  SobelX       SobelY\n//  1  0 -1      1  2  1\n//  2  0 -2      0  0  0\n//  1  0 -1     -1 -2 -1\n\n// bump texture\n_Sreg2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, 0);\n\n// size of displacement texture (in pixels)\n_CregF( float3, c_vSizeBumpDamp, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oDispSize  = c_vSizeBumpDamp.xy;\nstatic float  c_fBumpDamping = c_vSizeBumpDamp.z;\n\n// input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// pixel shader\nPS_ENTRY( mainPS)\n{\n  // take all neighbor samples\n  // (top row)\n  float s00 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2(-c_v1oDispSize.x,-c_v1oDispSize.y)).r;\n  float s01 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2(               0,-c_v1oDispSize.y)).r;\n  float s02 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2( c_v1oDispSize.x,-c_v1oDispSize.y)).r;\n  // (middle row)                              \n  float s10 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2(-c_v1oDispSize.x, 0)).r;\n  float s12 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2( c_v1oDispSize.x, 0)).r;\n  // (bottom row)                              \n  float s20 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2(-c_v1oDispSize.x, c_v1oDispSize.y)).r;\n  float s21 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2(               0, c_v1oDispSize.y)).r;\n  float s22 = texSample2D( t_sBump, s_tBump, PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy) +float2( c_v1oDispSize.x, c_v1oDispSize.y)).r;\n\n  // slope in X and Y directions\n  float3 vNormal; // (via Sobel filter)\n  vNormal.x = s00 + 2.0f*s10 + s20 - s02 - 2.0f*s12 - s22;\n  vNormal.y = s00 + 2.0f*s01 + s02 - s20 - 2.0f*s21 - s22;\n  // apply damping (attenuate)\n  vNormal.xy *= c_fBumpDamping;\n\n  // calc normal's Z component from X and Y\n  vNormal.z = CalcNormalZ(vNormal.xy);\n  // renormalize (just in case)\n  vNormal = normalize( vNormal);\n  // and pack [-1,1] into [0,1]\n  vNormal = vNormal *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // have to return only X and Y components with 0 in Z, \n  // because of normal-maps' \"packed\" format\n  PS_OUT( float4( vNormal.xy, 0,1));\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ZoomShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sZoomee, s_tZoomee, 0);\n_Sreg2D( t_sMask,   s_tMask,   1);\n\n// center texture coordinate\n_CregF( float4, c_vCenterTexLR, 0);\nstatic float2 g_vCenterTex;\n// screen size and mip scaling\n_CregF( float4, c_v1oScreenMip, 1);\nstatic float2 c_v1oScreenSize = c_v1oScreenMip.xy;\nstatic float  c_fMipRatio = c_v1oScreenMip.z;\nstatic float  c_fMipOffset= c_v1oScreenMip.w;\n\n// grabbed rectangle edges (.xy=min, .zw=max)\n_CregF( float4, c_vRectEdgesLeft, 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vRectEdgesRight, 3);\nstatic float4 g_vRectEdges;\n\n// center in eye (view) and texture space\n_CregF( float4, c_vCenterEyeLenLeft, 4);\n_CregF( float4, c_vCenterEyeLenRight, 5);\nstatic float4 g_vCenterEyeLen;\n#define g_fRaysLen g_vCenterEyeLen.w\n\n// rays' color and alpha (power)\n_CregF( float4, c_vColRays, 6);\n\n\n// if zoom samples were not specified\n#ifndef ZOOM_SAMPLES\n  // use less than min as a warning\n  #define ZOOM_SAMPLES 4\n#endif\n\n// vertex shader output = pixel shader input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPixPosEyeLeftMaskU, 0);  // (in view, eye space)\n  _inReg( float4, vPixPosEyeRightMaskV,1);\n  _inScrReg( vScreenPos);\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n// begin one light pass\nPS_ENTRY( ZoomPS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // prepare vars for VR\n  g_vCenterTex = VRSelect(c_vCenterTexLR.xy, c_vCenterTexLR.zw);\n  g_vRectEdges = VRSelect(c_vRectEdgesLeft, c_vRectEdgesRight);\n  g_vCenterEyeLen = VRSelect(c_vCenterEyeLenLeft, c_vCenterEyeLenRight);\n\n  // blend by distance from center\n  float4 vPixZoom; // (result)\n  float4 vPixPosEyeLMaskU = PS_IN( vPixPosEyeLeftMaskU);\n  float4 vPixPosEyeRMaskV = PS_IN( vPixPosEyeRightMaskV);\n  float3 vPixPosEye = VRSelect( vPixPosEyeLMaskU.xyz, vPixPosEyeRMaskV.xyz);\n  float fDepthRatio = g_vCenterEyeLen.z / vPixPosEye.z;  // (\"distance\" from plane of center)\n  float fEyeDistance = length( vPixPosEye - g_vCenterEyeLen.xyz);\n  float fScrDistance = length( vPixPosEye * fDepthRatio -g_vCenterEyeLen.xyz);\n  vPixZoom.a = saturate( fScrDistance / fEyeDistance);\n\n  // sample mask texture\n  float2 vMaskUV = float2( vPixPosEyeLMaskU.w, vPixPosEyeRMaskV.w);\n  float fMask = texSample2D( t_sMask, s_tMask, vMaskUV).r;\n\n  // calc zoom texture mapping (\"projective\" from screen coords)\n  float2 vZoomCoord = RasterToClipPos( PS_IN( vScreenPos.xy), Multiview1oScreenSize( c_v1oScreenSize));\n  float fZoomOffset = (vZoomCoord.x>=0.5f) ? c_fMipOffset : 0.0f;\n  vZoomCoord = vZoomCoord *c_fMipRatio +float2(fZoomOffset,0);\n\n  // don't go over rendered part of refraction texture\n  float4 vRectEdgesMV = MultiviewUV2( g_vRectEdges);\n  vZoomCoord = clamp( vZoomCoord, vRectEdgesMV.xy, vRectEdgesMV.zw);\n\n  // calculate texture coordinates steps\n  float2 vDeltaCoord = MultiviewUV(g_vCenterTex) -vZoomCoord;  \n  vDeltaCoord /= float(ZOOM_SAMPLES);\n  // attenuate by distance from center and ray length\n  vDeltaCoord *= vPixZoom.a *g_fRaysLen *fMask;\n\n  // loop thru samples\n  vPixZoom.rgb = float3(0,0,0);\n  for( int i=0; i<ZOOM_SAMPLES; i++) {\n\n    // sample and move to next coord\n    vPixZoom.rgb += texSample2D( t_sZoomee, s_tZoomee, vZoomCoord).rgb;\n    vZoomCoord += vDeltaCoord;\n  }\n  // average\n  vPixZoom.rgb /= float(ZOOM_SAMPLES);\n\n  // attenuate translucency\n  vPixZoom.a*= vPixZoom.a;\n  vPixZoom.a = 1.0f- vPixZoom.a*vPixZoom.a;\n  // and modulate zoomer\n  vPixZoom *= c_vColRays;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vPixZoom);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vPixZoom);\n}\n\n\n/*\nFOR JITTERING:\nfloat2 vZoomCoordJittered = vZoomCoord+ frac( vPixZoom.xy)*0.01f;// or *10 *c_vScreenMapping.xy;\n*/\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2014 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ZoomShader.vsh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// model-view-projection transformation matrix\n_CregM44F( c_mObjToClipLeft, 0); \n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToClipRightX, 4);\n// object to view (eye) matrix\n_CregM43F( c_mObjToViewLeft, 5);\n_CregF(float4, c_vObjToViewRightX, 8);\n_CregF( float4, c_vMaskMapping, 9);\n\n\n// input to VS for rendering\nVS_IN_BEGIN\n  _inReg( float4, vPosition, 0);\n  _inReg( float2, vInMaskUV, 1); // (matrix indices)\nVS_IN_END\n\n// output to PS\nVS_OUT_BEGIN\n  _outReg( float4, vPixPosEyeLeftMaskU, 0);  // (in view, eye space)\n  _outReg( float4, vPixPosEyeRightMaskV,1); \nVS_OUT_END_VR\n\n\n// main for rendering\nVS_ENTRY( ZoomVS)\n{\n  VS_OUT_DECLARE;\n\n  VS_OUT_POS = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToClipLeft);\n  VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT = mul( VS_IN( vPosition), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToClipLeft, c_vObjToClipRightX));\n\n  // clip and eye-space pixel positions\n  float4 vOutPixPosEyeLMaskU, vOutPixPosEyeRMaskV; \n  vOutPixPosEyeLMaskU.xyz = mulM43F( VS_IN( vPosition), c_mObjToViewLeft);\n  vOutPixPosEyeRMaskV.xyz = mulM43F( VS_IN( vPosition), VRRightMatrix(c_mObjToViewLeft, c_vObjToViewRightX));\n\n  float2 vOutMaskUV = VS_IN( vInMaskUV) *c_vMaskMapping.xy +c_vMaskMapping.zw;\n  vOutPixPosEyeLMaskU.w = vOutMaskUV.x;\n  vOutPixPosEyeRMaskV.w = vOutMaskUV.y;\n  VS_OUT( vPixPosEyeLeftMaskU)  = vOutPixPosEyeRMaskV;\n  VS_OUT( vPixPosEyeRightMaskV) = vOutPixPosEyeRMaskV;\n\n  // go to pixel shader now\n  VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR;\n}\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n#ifndef COMMONNODESHADERFUNCTIONS_HS\n#define COMMONNODESHADERFUNCTIONS_HS 1\n\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/BumpNormal.hs>\n\n// forward declarations\nfloat3 GetBumpedNormalNode( const float4 vInNormal, const float4 vInDetail,\n  const float2 vNorDetBias, out float4 vRawNorDet );\n\n#ifdef RENDER_TYPE_COLOR\n  float GetDepthOcclusion( in float fDepth);\n#endif\n\n// macro that samples fast-lights and ambient-occlusion texture\n//===============================================================================\n#define MacroCalculateFastLightsAndAmbientOcclusion( __vIllumAmbOccSample ) \\\n  __vIllumAmbOccSample = texSample2D( t_sIllumAmbOcc, s_tIllumAmbOcc, GetRasterClipPos() ) * c_vMaskFLAO.xxxz + c_vMaskFLAO.yyyw;\n\n// calculates normals\n//===============================================================================\nvoid CalculateNormals( inout float3 vPixNormalTan, inout float3 vPixNormalAbs,\n  in float fPixDist2, in float4 vNormal, in float4 vDetail, in float bfFace,\n  inout float fFacingness, out float fInPolyFace\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n    #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n      , in float3x3 mTanToAbs\n    #endif\n  #else\n    // #if defined(HAS_PARALLAX)\n      , in float3 mTanToAbs\n    // #else\n    //   , in float3 vNormalAbs\n    // #endif\n  #endif\n  )\n{\n  // if has normal map\n  #ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n    // calc attenuation by distance for bumps\n    float fBumpAtt = 1.0f- saturate( fPixDist2*c_f1oNormalMaxDist2);\n    // (.x=all bumps attenuation, .y=only detail bump attenuation)\n    float2 vNorDetAtt = float2( fBumpAtt, g_fDetAtt );\n\n  // ==============================================================================================\n  // This entire block is removed and node-ified. Input pin 'in_vNormal' now represents sampled normal\n  // map color. Also 'in_vDetail' represents sampled detail map. These two are just used here and\n  // sampled elsewhere.\n  // ==============================================================================================\n    // sample normal (and detail) maps' normal value\n    // vPixNormalTan = GetBumpedNormal( t_sNormalMap, s_tNormalMap, t_sDetailMap, s_tDetailMap, vNormDetOfsUV, vNorDetAtt, g_vRawNorDet);\n    vPixNormalTan = GetBumpedNormalNode( vNormal, vDetail, vNorDetAtt, g_vRawNorDet );\n  // ==============================================================================================\n\n    #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n      // and transform it to absolute space\n      vPixNormalAbs = _mulT( vPixNormalTan, mTanToAbs );\n    #else\n      // or just use tangent space\n      vPixNormalAbs = vPixNormalTan;\n    #endif\n\n  // if doesn't have normal map\n  #else\n\n    // normal is from vertex then\n    vPixNormalTan = float3(0,0,1);\n    // #if defined(HAS_PARALLAX)\n      vPixNormalAbs = mTanToAbs;\n    // #else\n    //   vPixNormalAbs = vNormalAbs;\n    // #endif\n  #endif // HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n  #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n    // renormalize pixel normal\n    vPixNormalAbs = normalize( vPixNormalAbs );\n  #endif\n\n  // adjust facing sign\n  fInPolyFace = bfFace * fFacingness;\n  #ifdef HAS_DYNAMIC_LIGHT\n    // and possibly flip normal (for 2-sided lighting)\n    vPixNormalAbs = FlipNormal( vPixNormalAbs, fInPolyFace );\n  #endif\n}\n\n// apply depth and ambient occlusion from 'height' map\n//===============================================================================\nfloat ApplyDepthOcclusion( in float fOutParallaxOcclusion, in float vBlendMaskTexAlpha )\n{\n#ifdef RENDER_TYPE_COLOR\n  float fOcc = lerp( 1.0f, fOutParallaxOcclusion, vBlendMaskTexAlpha );\n  return GetDepthOcclusion( fOcc );\n#else\n  return 1.0f;\n#endif\n}\n\n// get surface normal (in tangent space!) from normal and detail-map\n// (vNorDetBias.x=all bumps attenuation, .y=only detail bump attenuation)\ninline float3 GetBumpedNormalNode( const float4 vInNormal, const float4 vInDetail,\n  const float2 vNorDetBias, out float4 vRawNorDet )\n{\n  // if using bump mapping\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n\n  // sample normal
