and invert V (Y) coord\n  // because normalmap is in left coord system (V goes down)\n  // (choose format between .rg or .ra based on 'signal' from B channel)\n  vRawNorDet.xy = nor2Du(vInNormal);\n\n  // also sample detail map (into that normal-map)\n  // while converting everything to -1 - +1 range  \n  vRawNorDet.zw = nor2Du(vInDetail);\n  vRawNorDet = vRawNorDet *(-2.0f) +1.0f;\n  // attenuate normal and detail\n  vRawNorDet *= c_vBumpStrengths.xxyy * vNorDetBias.xxxx;\n\n  // combine normal and detail\n  float3 vOutNor; // (in here)\n  vOutNor.xy = vRawNorDet.xy+ vRawNorDet.zw *vNorDetBias.yy;\n\n  // derive normal Z coord\n  vOutNor.z = CalcNormalZ(vOutNor.xy);  \n\n  // need to renormalize the result because of added detail map\n  // (X and/or Y can end up being >=1, so there...)\n  // HOWEVER, we won't do that here afterall, since usual next step would be\n  // to transform this tangent-space normal to absolute-space, and then\n  // renormalize - so there's no point to renormalize it here. Still,\n  // renormalization might need to be applied in cases when working in tangent-space!\n//vNormal.xyz = normalize( vNormal.xyz);\n\n  // and that's it\n  return vOutNor.xyz;\n\n  // if not using bump mapping\n#else \n\n  // just return up-vector Z-normal\n  return float3( 0,0,1);\n\n#endif // HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n}\n\n\n// This function applies lighting to current pixel.\n//===============================================================================\nfloat3 ApplyLights( in float4 vVexPosAbs, in float fvIllumAmbOccSampleAlpha )\n{\n  float3 vColor = float3( 0,0,0 );\n\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // apply (shadowed) distant light\n  float3 vDistColor = DistantLight( vVexPosAbs);\n  // add to final color (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vColor = vDistColor *fvIllumAmbOccSampleAlpha;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // spot (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vColor += SpotLight( vVexPosAbs) *fvIllumAmbOccSampleAlpha;\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // omni (modulated by ambient occlusion)\n  vColor += OmniLight( vVexPosAbs) *fvIllumAmbOccSampleAlpha;\n#endif  // LIGHTS\n\n  return vColor;\n}\n\n\n// Called just before color is output from pixel shader, this function colorizes\n// invalid pixels and applies alpha range, basically everything that goes at the\n// very end of standard pixel shader\n//===============================================================================\nvoid PostColorize( inout float4 vOutColor, in float2 vAlphaRange, in float3 vPixNormalAbs, in float3 vViewDirAbs, in float2 vEdgeSmoothing, in float4 vLerpDest, in float4 vLerpMask\n#ifdef BAKING\n#elif defined(APPLY_FOZE)\n  , in float2 vFozeAmount\n#endif\n )\n{\n  // calculate translucency fresnel for edge smooting\n  // (but with a bit less influence; ^2 instead of ^5!)\n  float fNV = abs( dot( vPixNormalAbs, vViewDirAbs ) );\n  float fF  = 1.0f - saturate( fNV * fNV * vEdgeSmoothing.x + vEdgeSmoothing.y);\n\n  // ==============================================================================================\n  // For some reason 'c_vLerpMask' is always zero/black. This has been temporarily changed just\n  // so we can see normal map influence. This should be reverted back as soon as 'c_vLerpMask' is\n  // reactivated.\n  // ==============================================================================================\n  // and apply it to final color\n  vOutColor = lerp( vOutColor, vLerpDest, vLerpMask * fF );\n  // ==============================================================================================\n\n  // if baking\n#ifdef BAKING\n\n  // in LDR\n  if( c_fBakeGamma != 0.0f) {\n\n    // apply gamma\n    vOutColor.rgb = pow( vOutColor.rgb, _tcast(float3,0.4545f));\n  }\n  // in RGBE\n  if( c_fBakeRGBE != 0.0f) {\n\n    // convert output\n    vOutColor.rgba = PackRGBE( vOutColor.rgb);\n  }\n\n  // if not baking and has fog and/or haze\n#elif defined(APPLY_FOZE)\n\n  // apply (lerp) fog and haze with color and/or alpha\n  vOutColor = ApplyFoze( vOutColor, vFozeAmount);\n\n#endif // BAKING\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutColor);\n\n  // clamp to useable range \n  // (some HW has problems with denormals in the frame buffer, so we clamp on the bottom side as well)\n  vOutColor.rgb = clamp( vOutColor.rgb, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n  // compress alpha range\n  // (for purpose of transparency anti-aliasing with proper alpha-tresholding)\n  vOutColor.a = saturate( vOutColor.a * vAlphaRange.x + vAlphaRange.y );\n  // == vOutColor.a = saturate( (vOutColor.a-(vAlphaRange.x-0.001625f)) / ((vAlphaRange.x+0.001625f)-(vAlphaRange.x-0.001625f)) );\n  // == sat( a-min/delta) == sat( a/delta - min/delta)\n}\n\n#ifdef RENDER_TYPE_DEPTHSHADOW\n\nvoid CalculateDiffusion( inout float2 vClipTreshold, in float2 vScreenPos )\n{\n#if DIFFUSION != 0\n\n  // get screen raster coordinates\n  float2 vRasterPos = vScreenPos.xy;\n  // adjust by object position\n  vRasterPos -= c_vDissolveMap.zw;\n\n  // do dithering with it\n  #if DIFFUSION == 1\n    // (via noise texture)\n    vRasterPos *= c_vDissolveMap.xy;\n    vClipTreshold.x = texSample2D( t_sDiffusion, s_tDiffusion, vRasterPos).r;\n  #else\n    // (or directly from screen position)\n    vClipTreshold.x = dot( vRasterPos, float2( 12.9898f,78.233f));\n    vClipTreshold.x = sin( vClipTreshold.x *0.001f);\n    vClipTreshold.x = frac(vClipTreshold.x *43758.5453f);\n  #endif\n\n  // convert diffusion (noise) to signed values\n  vClipTreshold.y = vClipTreshold.x *2.0f -1.0f;\n\n  // apply fading to diffusion\n  vClipTreshold.xy += _tcast(float2,c_fFadeFactor);\n\n#endif // DIFFUSION\n}\n\n#endif // RENDER_TYPE_DEPTHSHADOW\n\n#endif //COMMONNODESHADERFUNCTIONS_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n#ifndef MACROS_HS\n#define MACROS_HS 1\n\n// some constants...\n\n#define HALF_PI 1.570795f\n#define PI 3.14159f\n\n// 2.0 and 0.5 in linear space\n// (mostly used as multiplier for shade textures)\n#define LINEAR_2  4.61312223f // = 2^2.205743518781 ! (4.5947934f = 2^2.2)\n#define LINEAR_05 0.21763764f // = 0.5^2.2\n\n// clamping values for\n#ifdef HDR_128BIT\n  // 128-bit HDR render target\n  #define MAX_HDR_FLOAT   3.40282e+38f\n  #define SMALL_HDR_FLOAT 1.17549e-38f  // (minimum normalized!)\n// or\n#else\n  // 64-bit HDR render target\n  #define MAX_HDR_FLOAT   65504.0f\n  #define SMALL_HDR_FLOAT 5.96046e-8f  // (use 6.10352e-5f for minimum normalized!)\n#endif\n\n// depth normalization value\n#define DEPTH16_NORM 32752.0f\n\n// encode/decode depth (distance) value\n#define ENCODE_DEPTH(d) d // sqrt(d)\n#define DECODE_DEPTH(d) abs(d) // d*d\n\n\n// LANGUAGE MACROS\n\n\n// for high-level shader language\n#if _HLSL\n\n  #if !_PSSL\n\n    // disable annoyances\n    #pragma warning(disable:3571)  // abs() for pow() required\n    #pragma warning(disable:3556)  // integer divides/modulus may be much slower, try using uints if possible.\n    #pragma warning(disable:3557)  // loop unrolling report\n    #pragma warning(disable:3577)  // allow isnan() and isinf()\n\n  #else\n    \n    // (too dangerous to ignore this one!)\n  //#pragma warning(disable:3203)  // implicitly converted right hand side of operator from -1 to 4294967295 (even for #defines?!)\n\n  #endif\n\n  // type casting\n  #define _tcast( typ,nam) (typ)nam\n  // matrix casting\n  #define _tcastM33F( nam) (float3x3)nam\n\n  // not-a-number value detection\n  #define _isNaN isnan\n  // infinite value detection\n  #define _isInf isinf\n\n  // non-square matrix multiply\n  #define mulM43F mul\n  #define mulM42F mul\n\n  // compiler hints\n  #define _branch [branch]\n  #define _flatten [flatten]\n  #define _unroll [unroll]\n  #define _loop   [loop]\n  // non-transposed 2x2, 3x3 or 4x4 matrix multiply\n  #define _mulT mul\n\n  // any()/all() functions\n  #define _any4(c) any(c)\n  #define _any3(c) any(c)\n  #define _any2(c) any(c)\n  #define _all4(c) all(c)\n  #define _all3(c) all(c)\n  #define _all2(c) all(c)\n\n  // shader input registers\n  #define _inReg( typ,nam,idx) typ nam :TEXCOORD##idx\n\n  #if VS_VER\n\n    // declare input to vertex shader\n    #define VS_IN_BEGIN struct VS_INPUT {\n    #define VS_IN_END };\n    #define VS_ENTRY( func) VS_OUTPUT func( VS_INPUT Vin)\n    // specify vertex input\n    #define VS_IN(nam) Vin.nam\n    // declare output from vertex shader\n    #define VS_OUT_BEGIN struct VS_OUTPUT {\n    #define VS_OUT_END float4 vOutPosition : SV_Position; };\n    // define output from vertex shader\n    #define VS_OUT_DECLARE VS_OUTPUT Vout\n    // use output from vertex shader\n    #define VS_OUT_EXPORT return Vout\n    // specify vertex output\n    #define VS_OUT(nam) Vout.nam\n    // specify vertex position output\n    #define VS_OUT_POS Vout.vOutPosition\n    // specify right eye vertex position output\n    #define VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT Vout.vXRight\n\n    // vertex shader output registers\n    #define _outReg( typ,nam,idx) typ nam :TEXCOORD##idx\n    #if _HLSL > 1\n      #define VS_OUT_END_VR float4 vOutPosition : SV_Position; float4 vXRight : NV_X_RIGHT; };\n    #else\n      #define VS_OUT_END_VR float4 vOutPosition : SV_Position; float4 vXRight : NV_X_RIGHT; uint4 vViewportMask : NV_VIEWPORT_MASK; };\n    #endif\n\n  #elif PS_VER\n\n    // declare input to pixel shader\n    #define PS_IN_BEGIN struct PS_INPUT {\n    #define PS_IN_END };\n    // specify pixel input\n    #define PS_IN( nam) Pin.nam\n\n    // declare one output from pixel shader\n    #define PS_ENTRY( func) float4 func( PS_INPUT Pin) :SV_Target\n    // declare no output from pixel shader\n    #define PS_ENTRY_NOOUT( func) void func( PS_INPUT Pin)\n\n    // declare two outputs from pixel shader\n    #define PS_ENTRY_2OUTS( func) \\\n      struct PS_OUTPUT { \\\n        float4 vOut0: SV_Target0; \\\n        float4 vOut1: SV_Target1; \\\n      }; \\\n      PS_OUTPUT func( PS_INPUT Pin)\n\n    // specify pixel output\n    #define PS_OUT(nam) return nam\n    // specify 2 pixel outputs\n    #define PS_2OUTS(out0,out1) PS_OUTPUT Pout; Pout.vOut0=out0; Pout.vOut1=out1; return Pout\n\n    // pixel shader input registers\n    #define _inScrReg( nam) float4 nam :SV_Position\n    #define _inFacReg bool bInFace :SV_IsFrontFace \n    #if _HLSL==1 && !_PSSL\n      #define PS_IN_VR_REGS uint iViewport : SV_ViewportArrayIndex;\n    #else\n      #define PS_IN_VR_REGS\n    #endif\n    #define PS_FACE (Pin.bInFace ? -1.0f : 1.0f)\n\n  #endif // VS/PS\n\n  // constant registers\n  #define _CregF( typ,nam,idx) const uniform typ nam :register(c##idx)\n  // matrix constants (4 rows, 3 and 2)\n  #define _CregM44F( nam,idx) const uniform float4x4 nam :register(c##idx)\n  #define _CregM43F( nam,idx) const uniform float4x3 nam :register(c##idx)\n  #define _CregM33F( nam,idx) const uniform float3x3 nam :register(c##idx)\n  #define _CregM42F( nam,idx) const uniform float4x2 nam :register(c##idx)\n\n  // texture and sampler\n  #define _Sreg2D( tex,sam,idx) Texture2D tex :register(t##idx); SamplerState sam :register(s##idx)\n  #define _SregCUBE( tex,sam,idx) TextureCube tex :register(t##idx); SamplerState sam :register(s##idx)\n  #define _SregAry2D( tex,sam,idx) Texture2DArray tex :register(t##idx); SamplerState sam :register(s##idx)\n  #define _SregShd2D( tex,sam,idx) Texture2D tex :register(t##idx); SamplerComparisonState sam :register(s##idx)\n  #define _SregShdCUBE( tex,sam,idx) TextureCube tex :register(t##idx); SamplerComparisonState sam :register(s##idx)\n  #define _SregShdAry2D( tex,sam,idx) Texture2DArray tex :register(t##idx); SamplerComparisonState sam :register(s##idx)\n\n  // (PSSL texture sampling is defined in internal header file)\n  #if !_PSSL\n\n    // texture and sampler\n    #define texSample2D( tex,sam,crd) tex.Sample( sam, crd)\n    #define texSampleCube( tex,sam,crd) tex.Sample( sam, crd)\n    #define texShadow2D( tex,sam,crd,cmp) tex.SampleCmpLevelZero( sam, crd, cmp)\n    #define texShadowAry( tex,sam,crd,cmp) tex.SampleCmpLevelZero( sam, crd, cmp)\n    #define texShadowCube( tex,sam,crd,cmp) tex.SampleCmpLevelZero( sam, crd, cmp)\n    #define texLod2D( tex,sam,crd,mip) tex.SampleLevel( sam, crd, mip)\n    #define texLodCube( tex,sam,crd,mip) tex.SampleLevel( sam, crd, mip)\n    #define texGrad2D( tex,sam,crd,x,y) tex.SampleGrad( sam, crd, x,y)\n    #define texGradCube( tex,sam,crd,x,y) tex.SampleGrad( sam, crd, x,y)\n    #define texBias2D( tex,sam,crd,bias) tex.SampleBias( sam, crd, bias)\n    #define texBiasCube( tex,sam,crd,bias) tex.SampleBias( sam, crd, bias)\n\n  #endif \n\n// for graphic library shader language\n#elif _GLSL\n\n\n  // type casting\n  #define _tcast( typ,nam) typ(nam)\n\n  // not-a-number value detection\n  #define _isNaN( val) (val!=val)\n  // infinite value detection\n  #define _isInf( val) (abs(val)>1000000000.0f)\n  // compiler hints\n  #define _flatten\n  #define _branch\n  #define _unroll\n  #define _loop\n\n  // transposed 2x2, 3x3 or 4x4 matrix multiply\n  // (used when matrices have been passed via input/output and not constant registers;\n  //  in that case, for GLSL matrix ends up being transposed, so this \"fix\" the issue)\n  #define _mulT(x,y) (y)*(x)\n\n  // parallel calculation of sine & cosine of an angle\n  #define sincos(x,s,c) s=sin(x); c=cos(x)\n\n  // any()/all() functions\n  #define _any4( val4) any( notEqual( val4, _tcast(float4,0)))\n  #define _any3( val3) any( notEqual( val3, _tcast(float3,0)))\n  #define _any2( val2) any( notEqual( val2, _tcast(float2,0)))\n  #define _all4( val4) all( notEqual( val4, _tcast(float4,0)))\n  #define _all3( val3) all( notEqual( val3, _tcast(float3,0)))\n  #define _all2( val2) all( notEqual( val2, _tcast(float2,0)))\n\n  // shader input registers\n  #define _inReg( typ,nam,idx) layout (location=idx) in typ in_##nam\n\n  #if VS_VER\n\n    // declare input to vertex shader\n    #define VS_IN_BEGIN\n    #define VS_IN_END\n    // use input to vertex shader\n    #if _GLSL_METAL\n      #define VS_ENTRY( func) void main(void)\n    #else\n      #define VS_ENTRY( func) void func(void)\n    #endif\n    // specify vertex input\n    #define VS_IN(nam) in_##nam\n    // declare output from vertex shader\n    #define VS_OUT_BEGIN\n    #define VS_OUT_END\n    // define output from vertex shader\n    #define VS_OUT_DECLARE\n    // use output from vertex shader\n    #define VS_OUT_EXPORT\n    // specify vertex output\n    #define VS_OUT(nam) out_##nam\n\n    // vertex position output\n    #define VS_OUT_POS gl_Position\n    // specify right eye vertex position output\n    #define VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT vXRight\n    #define VS_OUT_END_VR vec4 vXRight;\n\n    // vertex shader output register\n    #define _outReg( typ,nam,idx) layout (location=idx) out typ out_##nam\n\n  #elif PS_VER\n\n    // declare input to pixel shader\n    #define PS_IN_BEGIN\n    #define PS_IN_END\n\n    // declare (no) output from pixel shader\n    #if _GLSL_METAL\n      #define PS_ENTRY_NOOUT( func) void main(void)\n      #define PS_ENTRY( func) \\\n        out vec4 _glPixOut; \\\n        void main(void)\n    #else\n      #define PS_ENTRY_NOOUT( func) void func(void)\n      #define PS_ENTRY( func) \\\n        layout (location=0) out vec4 _glPixOut; \\\n        void func(void)\n    #endif\n\n    // declare two outputs from pixel shader\n    #define PS_ENTRY_2OUTS \\\n      layout (location=1) out vec4 _glPixOut1; \\\n      PS_ENTRY\n\n    // specify pixel input\n    #define PS_IN(nam) in_##nam\n    // specify pixel output\n    #define PS_OUT(nam) _glPixOut = nam; return\n    // specify 2 pixel outputs\n    #define PS_2OUTS(out0,out1) _glPixOut=out0; _glPixOut1=out1; return\n    // specify face register\n    #define PS_FACE in_fInFace\n\n    // pixel shader input/output registers\n    #define _inScrReg( nam) vec2 in_##nam = gl_FragCoord.xy\n    #define _inFacReg float in_fInFace = gl_FrontFacing ? -1.0f : 1.0f\n    #define PS_IN_VR_REGS float fDummy;\n\n  #endif // VS/PS\n\n  // texture and sampler\n  #if _GLSL_METAL\n    #define _Sreg2D(   tex,sam,idx) layout (binding=idx) uniform sampler2D   tex; float sam\n    #define _SregCUBE( tex,sam,idx) layout (binding=idx) uniform samplerCube tex; float sam\n    #define _SregAry2D(tex,sam,idx) layout (binding=idx) uniform sampler2DArray tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShd2D(   tex,sam,idx) layout (binding=idx) uniform sampler2DShadow   tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShdCUBE( tex,sam,idx) layout (binding=idx) uniform samplerCubeShadow tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShdAry2D(tex,sam,idx) layout (binding=idx) uniform sampler2DShadowArray tex; float sam\n  #elif VS_VER\n    #define _Sreg2D(   tex,sam,idx) layout (set=2, binding=idx) uniform sampler2D   tex; float sam\n    #define _SregCUBE( tex,sam,idx) layout (set=2, binding=idx) uniform samplerCube tex; float sam\n    #define _SregAry2D(tex,sam,idx) layout (set=2, binding=idx) uniform sampler2DArray tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShd2D(   tex,sam,idx) layout (set=2, binding=idx) uniform sampler2DShadow   tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShdCUBE( tex,sam,idx) layout (set=2, binding=idx) uniform samplerCubeShadow tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShdAry2D(tex,sam,idx) layout (set=2, binding=idx) uniform sampler2DShadowArray tex; float sam\n  #elif PS_VER\n    #define _Sreg2D(   tex,sam,idx) layout (set=1, binding=idx) uniform sampler2D   tex; float sam\n    #define _SregCUBE( tex,sam,idx) layout (set=1, binding=idx) uniform samplerCube tex; float sam\n    #define _SregAry2D(tex,sam,idx) layout (set=1, binding=idx) uniform sampler2DArray tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShd2D(   tex,sam,idx) layout (set=1, binding=idx) uniform sampler2DShadow   tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShdCUBE( tex,sam,idx) layout (set=1, binding=idx) uniform samplerCubeShadow tex; float sam\n    #define _SregShdAry2D(tex,sam,idx) layout (set=1, binding=idx) uniform sampler2DShadowArray tex; float sam\n  #endif\n\n  // (texture sampling is defined in internal header file!)\n\n  // constant registers\n  #define _CregF( typ,nam,idx) typ nam = typ( c_avUniformsF[idx])\n  // matrix constants\n  #define _CregM44F( nam,idx) mat4 nam = mat4( c_avUniformsF[idx], c_avUniformsF[idx+1], c_avUniformsF[idx+2], c_avUniformsF[idx+3])\n  #define _CregM33F( nam,idx) mat3 nam = mat3( c_avUniformsF[idx].xyz, c_avUniformsF[idx+1].xyz, c_avUniformsF[idx+2].xyz)\n  #define _CregM43F( nam,idx) mat3x4 nam = mat3x4( c_avUniformsF[idx], c_avUniformsF[idx+1], c_avUniformsF[idx+2])\n  #define _CregM42F( nam,idx) mat2x4 nam = mat2x4( c_avUniformsF[idx], c_avUniformsF[idx+1])\n\n  // matrix casting\n  #define _tcastM33F( nam) mat3(nam)\n\n  // non-square matrix multiply\n  #define mulM43F( vtx,mtx) (vtx)*(mtx)\n  #define mulM42F( vtx,mtx) (vtx)*(mtx)\n\n#endif // API\n\n\n// APIs' DIFFERENCES FUNCTIONS\n\n\n// screen raster position (cached); .xy=screen pos, .zw=clip pos (0-1)\nstatic float4 g_vScreenClipPos;\n\n// remap raster position from screen to clip space\ninline float2 RasterToClipPos( const float2 vRasterPos, const float2 vPixelScaling)\n{\n  return vRasterPos*vPixelScaling;\n}\n\n// cache screen raster position\ninline void SetRasterPos( const float2 vRasterPos, const float2 vPixelScaling)\n{\n#if _HLSL\n  g_vScreenClipPos.xy = vRasterPos -0.5f;\n#else\n  g_vScreenClipPos.xy = floor( vRasterPos);\n#endif\n  g_vScreenClipPos.zw = RasterToClipPos( vRasterPos, vPixelScaling);\n}\n\n// get cached screen raster position\ninline float2 GetRasterPos(void)\n{\n  return g_vScreenClipPos.xy;\n}\n\n// get cached clip position\ninline float2 GetRasterClipPos(void)\n{\n  return g_vScreenClipPos.zw;\n}\n\n\n#if PS_VER\n\n// flip normal based on sign\ninline float3 FlipNormal( const float3 vNormalAbs, const float fPolyFace)\n{\n#ifndef BAKING\n\n  // flip normal if backfacing\n  return (fPolyFace>0.0f) ? -vNormalAbs : vNormalAbs;\n\n#else // BAKING\n\n  // (cannot flip normals when baking, because destination is not position in world space,\n  //  but UV-map in texture space, and polygons there can be flipped for mapping purposes)\n  return vNormalAbs;\n\n#endif \n}\n\n\n// if colorizing wrong output values\n#ifdef COLORIZE_WRONG_OUTPUTS\n\n  // define function for colorizing NaNs and Infs in pixel shader outputs\n  inline void ColorizeWrongOutput( inout float4 vRes4)\n  {\n    // (have a warning color)\n    const float3 vMagenta = float3( 30.0f, 0.0f, 30.0f);\n    // add all components together\n    float fAll = dot( vRes4, _tcast(float4,1));\n    // check for not-a-number\n    vRes4.rgb = _isNaN( fAll) ? vMagenta : vRes4.rgb;\n    // check for +/-infinite\n    vRes4.rgb = _isInf( fAll) ? vMagenta : vRes4.rgb;\n  }\n\n// otherwise\n#else\n\n  // don't do a squat\n  #define ColorizeWrongOutput( res4)\n\n#endif\n\n\n#elif VS_VER\n\n\n// \"unpack\" signed vertex input for normal (vAddMul.xyz=add, .w=mul)\ninline float3 ExpandNormal( in float4 vNormal, const float4 vAddMul)\n{\n  // return signed normal\n  vNormal.xyz = vNormal.xyz *vAddMul.www +vAddMul.xyz;\n  vNormal.y += 0.001f; // (add a little bias towards up to avoid zero vector)\n  return vNormal.xyz; \n}\n\n// \"unpack\" signed vertex input for tangent (vAddMul.xyz=add, .w=mul)\ninline float4 ExpandTangent( in float4 vTangent, const float4 vAddMul)\n{\n  // return signed tangent\n  vTangent = vTangent *vAddMul.wwww +vAddMul.xyyz; \n  vTangent.x += 0.001f; // (add a little bias towards right to avoid zero vector)\n  return vTangent;\n}\n\n#endif // PS/VS\n\n\n#endif // (include-once check)\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n#ifndef RGBECONVERSION_HS\n#define RGBECONVERSION_HS 1\n\n// convert RGB HDR color to RGBE\ninline float4 PackRGBE( float3 vColor)\n{\n  // output\n  float4 vOutColor;\n  // find the maximum channel\n  float fMaxCh = max( max( vColor.r, vColor.g), vColor.b);\n  // add a bias to prevent division by zero and bring denormalized numbers into proper range\n  fMaxCh += 1.0f / 131072.0f; // (1<<17)\n\n  // determine the exponent\n  float fLog2 = log2( fMaxCh);\n  float fExp = ceil( fLog2*8.0f *255.0f /256.0f +128.0f);\n  fExp = max( fExp, 0.0f);\n  float fScale = 1.0f / pow( 2.0f, fExp /255.0f *32.0f -16.0f);\n  // pack it all into the resulting color\n  vOutColor.rgb = vColor * fScale;\n  vOutColor.a   = fExp / 255.0f;\n\n  // done\n  return vOutColor;\n}\n\n#endif // RGBECONVERSION_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n#ifndef TERRAINELEVATIONSAMPLINGCOMMON_HS\n#define TERRAINELEVATIONSAMPLINGCOMMON_HS 1\n\nfloat GetSimpleElevationSample(sampler2D tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize, float2 vElevationmapPix)\n{\n  return texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, vElevationmapPix * c_v1oElevationMapSize).r;\n}\n\n#define USE_HW_BILINEAR 0\n\nfloat GetElevationmapSample(sampler2D tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize, float2 vElevationmapPix, float2 vFrac)\n{\n#if !USE_HW_BILINEAR\n  float fSample00 = GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(0, 0));\n  float fSample10 = GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(1, 0));\n  float fSample01 = GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(0, 1));\n  float fSample11 = GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(1, 1));\n  return lerp(lerp(fSample00, fSample10, vFrac.x), lerp(fSample01, fSample11, vFrac.x), vFrac.y);\n#else\n  return GetSimpleElevationSample(vElevationmapPix);\n#endif\n}\n\nfloat4 EncodeElevationmapSample(float fElevation, float fAlpha)\n{\n  return float4(fElevation, 0.f, 0.f, fAlpha);\n}\n\n#define APPROX_BICUBIC 1\n\n#if !APPROX_BICUBIC\nstatic const float4x4 mCubic = float4x4(\n  0, -1, 2, -1,\n  2, 0, -5, 3,\n  0, 1, 4, -3,\n  0, 0, -1, 1) / 2.f;\n#else\nstatic const float4x4 mCubic = float4x4(\n  363, -1051, 1008, -320,\n  1331, 40, -1968, 960,\n  363, 1016, 912, -960,\n  0, -5, 48, 320) / 2057.f;\n#endif\n\nfloat4 CubicFilterWeights(float fFrac)\n{\n  float fFrac2 = fFrac * fFrac;\n  float fFrac3 = fFrac2 * fFrac;\n  return _mulT(mCubic, float4(1, fFrac, fFrac2, fFrac3));\n}\n\nfloat4 CubicFilterDerivativeWeights(float fFrac)\n{\n  return _mulT(mCubic, float4(0, 1, 2 * fFrac, 3 * fFrac * fFrac));\n}\n\nfloat3 GetSimpleElevationLine(sampler2D tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize, float2 vCenter)\n{\n  return float3(\n    GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vCenter + float2(-1, 0)),\n    GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vCenter + float2( 0, 0)),\n    GetSimpleElevationSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vCenter + float2( 1, 0)));\n}\n\nstatic const float3 c_vWeightsInt = float3(3, 16, 3) / 22;\nstatic const float3 c_vWeightsMid = float3(0, 1, 1) / 2;\nstatic const float3 c_vWeightsGradInt = float3(-1, 0, 1) / 2;\n//static const float4 c_vWeightsGradMid = float4(-283, -1028, 1028, 283) / 2057;\nstatic const float3 c_vWeightsGradMid = float3(0, -1, 1) / 2;\n\n// Returns interpolated elevation sample and gradient for provided elevationmap Pix coordinates.\nfloat3 GetInterpolatedElevation(sampler2D tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize, float2 vElevationmapPix, float2 vFrac)\n{\n#if 1 // bicubic\n#if !APPROX_BICUBIC\n\n  float4 vWeightsX = CubicFilterWeights(vFrac.x);\n  float4 vWeightsY = CubicFilterWeights(vFrac.y);\n  float4 vWeightsDX = CubicFilterDerivativeWeights(vFrac.x);\n  float4 vWeightsDY = CubicFilterDerivativeWeights(vFrac.y);\n\n#else\n\n  // Frac should always hit either the borders or the center of the pixel, therefore this eps is just a hacky way to hide problems with precision.\n  // Imprecision problems manifested when applying patch elevation (the noise-negating version) to 256x256 upsampled elevation (caused incorrect normals)\n  // and even without upsampling elevation if the patch center triangles were too long (caused terrain ravines). Patch triangulation was modified a bit\n  // so these problems shouldn't be so easy to reproduce anymore, but the eps will remain, at least for now.\n  const float fFracEps = 0.1f;\n  if (abs(vFrac.x - 1.0f) < fFracEps) {\n    vFrac.x = 0;\n    vElevationmapPix.x += 1;\n  }\n  if (abs(vFrac.y - 1.0f) < fFracEps) {\n    vFrac.y = 0;\n    vElevationmapPix.y += 1;\n  }\n\n  float3 vWeightsX = float3(0, 0, 0);\n  float3 vWeightsDX = float3(0, 0, 0);\n  if (abs(vFrac.x) < fFracEps) {\n    vWeightsX = c_vWeightsInt;\n    vWeightsDX = c_vWeightsGradInt;\n  } else if (abs(vFrac.x - 0.5f) < fFracEps) {\n    vWeightsX = c_vWeightsMid;\n    vWeightsDX = c_vWeightsGradMid;\n  }\n  float3 vWeightsY = float3(0, 0, 0);\n  float3 vWeightsDY = float3(0, 0, 0);\n  if (abs(vFrac.y) < fFracEps) {\n    vWeightsY = c_vWeightsInt;\n    vWeightsDY = c_vWeightsGradInt;\n  } else if (abs(vFrac.y - 0.5f) < fFracEps) {\n    vWeightsY = c_vWeightsMid;\n    vWeightsDY = c_vWeightsGradMid;\n  }\n#endif\n\n  float3x3 mSamples = float3x3(\n    GetSimpleElevationLine(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(0, -1)),\n    GetSimpleElevationLine(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(0,  0)),\n    GetSimpleElevationLine(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix + float2(0,  1)));\n\n  float fV  = dot(vWeightsY,  _mulT(mSamples, vWeightsX));\n  float fGx = dot(vWeightsY,  _mulT(mSamples, vWeightsDX));\n  float fGy = dot(vWeightsDY, _mulT(mSamples, vWeightsX));\n\n#else // bilinear\n\n  float fV = GetElevationmapSample(tTex2D, sTex2D, c_v1oElevationMapSize, vElevationmapPix, vFrac);\n  float fGx = 0;\n  float fGy = 0;\n\n#endif\n\n  return float3(fV, fGx, fGy);\n}\n\n\n//float3 LinearFromCubic(float fFrac)\n//{\n//  // TODO: try out lookup texture for these computations\n//  float4 vW = CubicFilterWeights(fFrac);\n//  float fG0 = vW.x + vW.y;\n//  float fG1 = vW.z + vW.w;\n//  float fH0 = 1 - vW.y / fG0 + fFrac;\n//  float fH1 = 1 + vW.w / fG1 - fFrac;\n//\n//  return float3(fH0, fH1, fG1);\n//}\n\nfloat SampleElevBilinear(sampler2D tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize, float2 vElevPix, float2 vFrac)\n{\n#if 1\n  float fSample00 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, (vElevPix + float2(0, 0)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize ).r;\n  float fSample10 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, (vElevPix + float2(1, 0)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize ).r;\n  float fSample01 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, (vElevPix + float2(0, 1)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize ).r;\n  float fSample11 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, (vElevPix + float2(1, 1)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize).r;\n  return lerp(lerp(fSample00, fSample10, vFrac.x), lerp(fSample01, fSample11, vFrac.x), vFrac.y);\n#else\n  return texSample2D(tElev2D, sElev2D, float3(vElevPix * c_v1oElevationMapSize.xy, fSlice)).r;\n#endif\n}\n\nfloat SampleElevBilinearArray(sampler2DArray tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 c_v1oElevationMapSize, float2 vElevPix, float2 vFrac, float fSlice)\n{\n#if 1\n  float fSample00 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, float3((vElevPix + float2(0, 0)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize, fSlice)).r;\n  float fSample10 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, float3((vElevPix + float2(1, 0)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize, fSlice)).r;\n  float fSample01 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, float3((vElevPix + float2(0, 1)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize, fSlice)).r;\n  float fSample11 = texSample2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, float3((vElevPix + float2(1, 1)) * c_v1oElevationMapSize, fSlice)).r;\n  return lerp(lerp(fSample00, fSample10, vFrac.x), lerp(fSample01, fSample11, vFrac.x), vFrac.y);\n#else\n  return texSample2D(tElev2D, sElev2D, float3(vElevPix * c_v1oElevationMapSize.xy, fSlice)).r;\n#endif\n}\n\nfloat CalcConvexity(float2 vElevUV, float2 vFrac, float4 vElevMapSizeConsts, sampler2D tElev2D, SamplerState sElev2D) {\n\n  float fHx0 = SampleElevBilinear(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV - float2(1, 0), vFrac);\n  float fHx1 = SampleElevBilinear(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV + float2(1, 0), vFrac);\n  float fHy0 = SampleElevBilinear(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV - float2(0, 1), vFrac);\n  float fHy1 = SampleElevBilinear(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV + float2(0, 1), vFrac);\n\n  float fH = SampleElevBilinear(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV, vFrac);\n\n  float fElevPixelWorldSize = vElevMapSizeConsts.z;\n\n  float fConvexity = (4 * fH - fHx0 - fHx1 - fHy0 - fHy1) / fElevPixelWorldSize;\n\n  return fConvexity;\n}\n\nfloat CalcConvexityArray(float2 vElevUV, float2 vFrac, float fSlice, float4 vElevMapSizeConsts, sampler2DArray tElev2D, SamplerState sElev2D) {\n\n  float fHx0 = SampleElevBilinearArray(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV - float2(1, 0), vFrac, fSlice);\n  float fHx1 = SampleElevBilinearArray(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV + float2(1, 0), vFrac, fSlice);\n  float fHy0 = SampleElevBilinearArray(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV - float2(0, 1), vFrac, fSlice);\n  float fHy1 = SampleElevBilinearArray(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV + float2(0, 1), vFrac, fSlice);\n\n  float fH = SampleElevBilinearArray(tElev2D, sElev2D, vElevMapSizeConsts.xy, vElevUV, vFrac, fSlice);\n\n  float fElevPixelWorldSize = vElevMapSizeConsts.z;\n\n  float fConvexity = (4 * fH - fHx0 - fHx1 - fHy0 - fHy1) / fElevPixelWorldSize;\n\n  return fConvexity;\n}\n\n#endif // TERRAINELEVATIONSAMPLINGCOMMON_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n#ifndef VREYE_HS\n#define VREYE_HS 1\n\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/AmdShaderIntrinsics.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// viewport is used as the current eye in multiview rendering\nstatic float g_fVRViewport = 0.0f;\n\n#if _HLSL && !_PSSL // (HLSL 5)\n  cbuffer CBVREye :register(b1) { float2 sc_vVREyeMV :packoffset(c0); }\n  #define sc_fVREye sc_vVREyeMV.x\n  #define sc_fMultiview sc_vVREyeMV.y\n#elif _GLSL && !_GLSL_METAL\n  layout(push_constant) uniform pushBlock { float2 sc_vVREyeMV; } CBVREye;\n  #define sc_fVREye CBVREye.sc_vVREyeMV.x\n  #define sc_fMultiview CBVREye.sc_vVREyeMV.y\n#else\n  #define sc_fVREye 0.0f\n  #define sc_fMultiview 0.0f\n#endif // API\n\n#define USING_AMD_MULTIVIEW (sc_fMultiview < 1.01f)\n\n// this needs to be used instead of VS_OUT_EXPORT in all shaders that use multiview rendering\n#if _GLSL\n  #define VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR gl_Position.x = lerp( gl_Position.x, vXRight.x, sc_fVREye); VS_OUT_EXPORT\n#elif _HLSL > 1\n  #define VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR VS_OUT_POS.x = VRSelectPosX_VS( VS_OUT_POS.x, VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT.x); VS_OUT_EXPORT\n#else\n  #define VS_OUT_EXPORT_VR VS_OUT(vViewportMask) = 0x00020001; VS_OUT_POS.x = VRSelectPosX_VS(VS_OUT_POS.x, VS_OUT_POS_X_RIGHT.x); VS_OUT_EXPORT\n#endif\n\n// this should the only eye dependent part of the vertex shader\ninline float VRSelectPosX_VS(float fLeftX, float fRightX)\n{\n#if _HLSL==1 && !_PSSL\n  // return right eye coordinate if rendering the right eye view on AMD\n  if (sc_fMultiview > 0.0f) {\n    return (USING_AMD_MULTIVIEW && AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_GetViewportIndex() == 1) ? fRightX : fLeftX;\n  } else {\n    return lerp( fLeftX, fRightX, sc_fVREye);\n  }\n#else\n  return lerp( fLeftX, fRightX, sc_fVREye);\n#endif\n}\n\n// Returns the right eye transform matrix\ninline float4x4 VRRightMatrix(float4x4 mMatrix, float4 vRightX)\n{\n  #if _GLSL\n    mMatrix[0] = vRightX;\n  #elif _HLSL\n    mMatrix._m00_m10_m20_m30 = vRightX;\n  #endif\n  return mMatrix;\n}\n\n// Returns the right eye transform matrix\ninline float4x3 VRRightMatrix(float4x3 mMatrix, float4 vRightX)\n{\n  #if _GLSL\n    mMatrix[0] = vRightX;\n  #elif _HLSL\n    mMatrix._m00_m10_m20_m30 = vRightX;\n  #endif\n  return mMatrix;\n}\n\n/// Returns the point halfway between the given two vectors\ninline float3 VRMiddle(float3 vLeft, float3 vRight)\n{\n  return lerp(vLeft, vRight, 0.5f);\n}\n\n/// Returns the point halfway between the given two vectors\ninline float4 VRMiddle(float4 vLeft, float4 vRight)\n{\n  return lerp(vLeft, vRight, 0.5f);\n}\n\n// The following functions are only usable in the pixel shader - vertex shaders shouldn't be eye dependent\n#if PS_VER\n\n#if _HLSL==1 && !_PSSL\n\n  // sets either the AMD's or nvidia's viewport index\n  inline void SetVRViewport( int iViewportIndex)\n  {\n    g_fVRViewport = (sc_fMultiview>0.0f && USING_AMD_MULTIVIEW) ? AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_GetViewportIndex() : iViewportIndex;\n  }\n\n  // sets the viewport for the pixel shader, needed for multiview rendering\n  #define PS_VR_INIT SetVRViewport(Pin.iViewport)\n\n#else\n\n  #define SetVRViewport(vp)\n  #define PS_VR_INIT\n\n#endif\n\n\ninline float GetVREye()\n{\n  return (sc_fMultiview>0.0f) ? g_fVRViewport : sc_fVREye;\n}\n\n// Selects either the left eye or the right eye variable\ninline float2 VRSelect(float2 vLeft, float2 vRight)\n{\n  return lerp(vLeft, vRight, GetVREye());\n}\n\n// Selects either the left eye or the right eye variable\ninline float3 VRSelect(float3 vLeft, float3 vRight)\n{\n  return lerp(vLeft, vRight, GetVREye());\n}\n\n// Selects either the left eye or the right eye variable\ninline float4 VRSelect(float4 vLeft, float4 vRight)\n{\n  return lerp(vLeft, vRight, GetVREye());\n}\n\n// Selects either the left eye or the right eye variable\ninline float4x3 VRSelect(float4x3 mLeft, float4x3 mRight)\n{\n  #if _GLSL\n    // mix doesn't work directly for matrices - so we do it manually\n    float fVREye = GetVREye();\n    return mLeft- fVREye* (mLeft+mRight);\n  #else\n    return lerp( mLeft, mRight, GetVREye());\n  #endif\n}\n\n// Returns MAD for multiview UV coordinates\ninline float4 MultiviewMAD( float fMultiviewTexture)\n{\n#if _PSSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  return float4( 1.0f,1.0f, 0.0f,0.0f);\n#else\n  fMultiviewTexture *= sc_fMultiview;\n  float2 vOutX = (fMultiviewTexture>0.0f) ? float2(0.5f,0.5f*GetVREye()) : float2(1.0f,0.0f);\n  return float4( vOutX.x, 1.0f, vOutX.y, 0.0f);\n#endif\n}\n\n// Returns MAD for multiview UV coordinates\ninline float4 MultiviewMAD(void)\n{\n  return MultiviewMAD( 1.0f);\n}\n\n// Returns multiview adjusted UV coordinates if texture is marked as multiview and multiview is enabled\ninline float2 MultiviewUVConditional( float2 vUV, float fMultiviewTexture)\n{\n#if _PSSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  return vUV;\n#else\n  fMultiviewTexture *= sc_fMultiview;\n  float2 vMadX = (fMultiviewTexture>0.0f) ? float2(0.5f,0.5f*GetVREye()) : float2(1.0f,0.0f);\n  vUV.x = vUV.x *vMadX.x +vMadX.y;\n  return vUV;\n#endif\n}\n\n// Returns multiview adjusted UV coordinates if multiview is enabled (texture is assumed to be multiview)\ninline float2 MultiviewUV( float2 vUV)\n{\n#if _PSSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  return vUV;\n#else\n  float2 vMadX = (sc_fMultiview>0.0f) ? float2(0.5f,0.5f*GetVREye()) : float2(1.0f,0.0f);\n  vUV.x = vUV.x *vMadX.x +vMadX.y;\n  return vUV;\n#endif\n}\n\n// Returns multiview adjusted for two set of UV coordinates if multiview is enabled (texture is assumed to be multiview)\ninline float4 MultiviewUV2( float4 vUV2)\n{\n#if _PSSL || _GLSL_METAL\n  return vUV2;\n#else\n  float2 vMadX = (sc_fMultiview>0.0f) ? float2(0.5f,0.5f*GetVREye()) : float2(1.0f,0.0f);\n  vUV2.xz = vUV2.xz *vMadX.xx +vMadX.yy;\n  return vUV2;\n#endif\n}\n\n// Adjusts screen size for multiview textures if multiview is enabled\ninline float2 Multiview1oScreenSize( float2 v1oScreenSize)\n{\n  v1oScreenSize.x *= (sc_fMultiview>0.0f) ? 0.5f : 1.0f;\n  return v1oScreenSize;\n}\n\n#endif // PS_VER\n\n#endif // (include-once check)\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// FOG & HAZE blending\n\n// used constant registers: c5-c7\n\n#ifndef FOZEBLEND_HS\n#define FOZEBLEND_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// blending for fog and haze\n_CregF( float4, c_vFozeBlend, 5);   // (.xy=fog, .zw=haze, .xz=color, .yw=alpha)\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolFogDst, 6);   // fog destination color and alpha\n_CregF( float4, c_vcolHazDst, 7);   // haze destination color and alpha\n\n\n// attenuate color by fog (.x) and haze (.y) amount\ninline float4 ApplyFoze( in float4 vColor, in float2 vFozeAmount)\n{\n  // calculate blend amount for color and alpha\n  float4 vBlend = vFozeAmount.xxyy;\n\n  // adjust attenuation\n  float4 vAttenuation;\n  vAttenuation.xy = vBlend.yw * vBlend.yw;\n  vAttenuation.zw = 2.0f*vBlend.yw -vAttenuation.xy;  // == 1- (1-vBlend.yw)*(1-vBlend.yw) - better than sqrt()\n  // (when lerping alpha channel to 0, do faster atenuation, when lerping to 1, do slower)\n  vBlend.yw = (c_vcolHazDst.a>0.5f) ? vAttenuation.xy : vAttenuation.zw;\n  vBlend *= c_vFozeBlend;\n\n  // lerp color and/or alpha to destination value, first for haze \n  vColor = lerp( vColor, c_vcolHazDst, vBlend.zzzw);\n  // and then for fog\n  return lerp( vColor, c_vcolFogDst, vBlend.xxxy);\n}\n\n\n#endif // FOZEBLEND_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// FOG & HAZE calculation\n\n// used constant registers: c10-c13\n\n#ifndef FOZECALC_HS\n#define FOZECALC_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// fog params\n_CregF( float4, c_vFozeCalc, 10);\nstatic float c_fFogDensity  = c_vFozeCalc.x;\nstatic float c_f1oFogHeight = c_vFozeCalc.y;\nstatic float c_fHazeDensity = c_vFozeCalc.z;   // H = exp(-k*x)\nstatic float c_f1oHazeHeight= c_vFozeCalc.w;   // 1 / maximum height of haze\n_CregF( float4, c_vFogParams, 11);\nstatic float  c_fFogCenterY = c_vFogParams.x;\nstatic float  c_fInvFogGrad = c_vFogParams.y;   // 0.5f / fog_gradient\nstatic float  c_fFogAbove   = c_vFogParams.z;   // = fog_height\nstatic float  c_fFogBelow   = c_vFogParams.w;   // = 0\nstatic float2 c_vFogRange   = c_vFogParams.zw;\n_CregF( float4, c_vFogPosY,  12); // 2nd row of fog placement matrix\n_CregF( float4, c_vHazeParams, 13);\nstatic float  c_fHazeStartZ  = c_vHazeParams.x;   // starting distance\nstatic float  c_fHazeStartY  = c_vHazeParams.y;   // starting height\nstatic float2 c_vBackFactors = c_vHazeParams.zw;  // background strength and height factors\n\n\n// (to avoid division by zero and stuff)\nstatic const float _c_fEpsilon = 0.001f;\n\n// (for testing only!)\n#define _FOG_VER 2\n#define _NO_HAZE 0\n\n\n// calc fog strength (0=not fogged, 1=fully fogged)\ninline float CalcFogAmount( const float4 vVexPosAbs, const float4 vEyePosAbs, const float fDistance)\n{ \n#if _FOG_VER == 2 // optimized code 2\n\n  // if used\n  float fFogAmount;\n#ifndef NO_FOG_CHECK\n  fFogAmount = 0.0f;\n  if( c_fFogDensity > 0.0f) \n#endif\n  {\n    // calc pixel and viewer height in fog space\n    float2 vFogLimits; // (.x=pix, .y=eye)\n    vFogLimits.x = dot( vVexPosAbs, c_vFogPosY);\n    vFogLimits.y = dot( vEyePosAbs, c_vFogPosY);\n\n    // find minimum (.x) and maximum (.y)\n    float fEyePixDelta = vFogLimits.x - vFogLimits.y;\n    vFogLimits  = (fEyePixDelta>=0.0f) ? vFogLimits.yx : vFogLimits.xy;\n    vFogLimits -= c_fFogCenterY;\n    /* WAS:\n    vFogLimits.x = min( fPixFogY, fEyeFogY);\n    vFogLimits.y = max( fPixFogY, fEyeFogY);\n    vFogLimits  += float2( -_c_fEpsilon,_c_fEpsilon);\n    vFogLimits  -= c_fFogCenterY; // ==0 in fog space\n    */\n    // and difference between rendered pixel and viewer height\n    fEyePixDelta = abs( fEyePixDelta) +_c_fEpsilon;\n\n    // calc fog vertical gradient (.x=above, .y=below)\n    float2 vFogHeights = saturate( (c_vFogRange - vFogLimits.xx) /fEyePixDelta);\n    // mix above and below gradients\n    float fFogGradient = saturate( vFogHeights.x - vFogHeights.y);\n\n    // calculate fog height for two points, limited to be inside fog\n    vFogHeights = saturate( 1.0f- vFogLimits * c_f1oFogHeight);\n    // apply linear graduation\n    fFogGradient *= saturate( (vFogHeights.x+vFogHeights.y) *c_fInvFogGrad);\n\n    // apply distance fading\n  #if 0 // LINEAR\n    fFogAmount = saturate( fDistance *c_fFogDensity *fFogGradient);\n  #else // EXP\n    fFogAmount = 1.0f- saturate( exp(-fDistance *c_fFogDensity *fFogGradient));\n  #endif\n\n  }\n  // return fog attenuation value\n  return fFogAmount;\n\n#elif _FOG_VER == 1 // \"make-it-work\"(tm) code\n\n  // if used\n  float fFogAmount;\n#ifndef NO_FOG_CHECK\n  fFogAmount = 0.0f;\n  if( c_fFogDensity > 0.0f) \n#endif\n  { \n    // calc pixel and viewer height in fog space\n    float fPixFogY = dot( vVexPosAbs, c_vFogPosY);\n    float fEyeFogY = dot( vEyePosAbs, c_vFogPosY);\n\n    // calc min, max and delta between rendered pixel and viewer height\n    float fPixHeight = fPixFogY;\n    float fEyeHeight = fEyeFogY;\n    float fHA, fHB;\n    if( fPixHeight < fEyeHeight-_c_fEpsilon) {\n      fHA = fPixHeight;\n      fHB = fEyeHeight;\n    } else if( fPixHeight > fEyeHeight+_c_fEpsilon) {\n      fHA = fEyeHeight;\n      fHB = fPixHeight;\n    } else {\n      fHA = fEyeHeight -_c_fEpsilon;\n      fHB = fPixHeight +_c_fEpsilon;\n    }\n    fHA -= c_fFogCenterY;\n    fHB -= c_fFogCenterY;\n\n    float fDH = fHB - fHA;\n    float f1oDH = 1.0f / fDH;\n    // calculate relative part of height that goes through the fog\n    float fA2 = saturate( (c_fFogAbove -fHA) *f1oDH);\n    float fA1 = saturate( (c_fFogBelow -fHA) *f1oDH);\n    float fA  = saturate( fA2 - fA1);\n\n    // calculate fog height for two points, limited to be inside fog\n    float fFH0 = (c_fFogAbove- clamp( fHA, 0.0f, c_fFogAbove));\n    float fFH1 = (c_fFogAbove- clamp( fHB, 0.0f, c_fFogAbove));\n    float fFogGraduation = 0.5f/c_fInvFogGrad *c_fFogAbove; \n    fFH0 /= fFogGraduation;\n    fFH1 /= fFogGraduation;\n    // apply linear graduation\n    fA *= saturate( (fFH0 + fFH1) / 2.0f);\n\n    // apply distance fading\n  #if 0 // LINEAR\n    fFogAmount = saturate( fDistance *c_fFogDensity *fA);\n  #else // EXP\n    fFogAmount = 1.0f- saturate( exp(-fDistance *c_fFogDensity *fA));\n  #endif\n  }\n  // return fog attenuation value\n  return fFogAmount;\n\n#elif _FOG_VER == 9\n\n  // full fog\n  return 1.0f;\n\n#else // no ver\n\n  // = no fog\n  return 0.0f;\n\n#endif\n}\n\n\n// calc haze strength (0=not hazed, 1=fully hazed)\ninline float CalcHazeAmount( const float fHeight, in float fDistance)\n{\n  // if haze is disabled\n#if _NO_HAZE \n  // no hazing\n  return 0.0f;\n#else\n\n  // if has some haze\n  float2 vHazeAmountHeight;\n#ifndef NO_HAZE_CHECK\n  vHazeAmountHeight.x = 0.0f;\n  if( c_fHazeDensity > 0.0f)\n#endif\n  {\n    // since background is far away, calc special factors for it\n    // (to better match haze of foreground objects)\n    float2 vBackFactors; \n    vBackFactors.x = saturate( fDistance/8900.0f);\n    vBackFactors = _tcast(float2,1.0f)- c_vBackFactors.xy *vBackFactors.xx;\n\n    // apply exponential distance attenuation\n    fDistance -= c_fHazeStartZ; // (from haze starting point)\n    vHazeAmountHeight.x = saturate( 1.0f- exp( -c_fHazeDensity*fDistance)); \n    // and get default height (in absolute space)\n    vHazeAmountHeight.y = fHeight - c_fHazeStartY;\n\n    // bow attenuate by background strength and height factors\n    vHazeAmountHeight *= vBackFactors; // == lerp( vStrengthHeight, vStrengthHeight*0.02f, saturate( fDistance*0.0001f));\n\n    // attenuate by (background attenuated) height\n    vHazeAmountHeight.y = saturate( 1.0f- vHazeAmountHeight.y *c_f1oHazeHeight);\n    // (quadratic height attenuation looks much better)\n    vHazeAmountHeight.y *= vHazeAmountHeight.y; \n    // finally, combine attenuations\n    vHazeAmountHeight.x *= vHazeAmountHeight.y;\n  }\n  // return haze attenuation value\n  return vHazeAmountHeight.x;\n\n#endif // _NO_HAZE\n}\n\n\n// calc fog and haze strengths combined\ninline float CalcFozeAmount( const float4 vVexPosAbs, const float4 vEyePosAbs, const float fDistance)\n{\n  // calculate fog and haze amounts\n  float2 vFozeAmount; // (right in here)\n  vFozeAmount.x = CalcFogAmount( vVexPosAbs, vEyePosAbs, fDistance);\n  vFozeAmount.y = CalcHazeAmount( vVexPosAbs.y, fDistance);\n  vFozeAmount = _tcast(float2,1) - vFozeAmount;\n  // combine their influences together\n  vFozeAmount.x *= vFozeAmount.y;\n  // (exponential attenuation looks better?)\n//vFozeAmount.x *= vFozeAmount.x;\n  return 1.0f-vFozeAmount.x;\n}\n\n\n#endif // FOZECALC_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// LIGHT CALCULATION WRAPPER\n\n// used constant registers: c29-c31\n\n#ifndef LIGHTING_HS\n#define LIGHTING_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n/*\n// light's data\nstruct ShaderLightInfo {\n  // light \n  float4 sli_vColCones; // color and 1/cones\n  float4 sli_vPosOuter; // position and outer cone  \n  float4 sli_vDirRange; // direction and range (falloff)\n}; //*/\n// light's data\n// (these has to match the structure!)\n_CregF( float4, c_sli, 29);\nstatic float3 c_sli_vColor = c_sli.rgb;\nstatic float  c_sli_f1oConeRange = c_sli.w;\n_CregF( float4, c_sli_vPosOuter, 30);\nstatic float3 c_sli_vPosition = c_sli_vPosOuter.xyz;\nstatic float  c_sli_fOuterCone = c_sli_vPosOuter.w;\n_CregF( float4, c_sli_vDirRange, 31);\nstatic float3 c_sli_vDirection = c_sli_vDirRange.xyz;\nstatic float  c_sli_f1oFalloff = c_sli_vDirRange.w;\n\n\n// calculate fake light modulator from normal (in tangent space!)\nfloat CalcFakeLightModulator( const float3 vNormalTan)\n{\n  // fake light direction (don't let it go to full black!)\n  // NOTE: with fake light .z being 0.8, it'll have no influence when\n  // normal-map is missing (normal in tangent space is up vector; 0,0,1)\n  float3 vFakeLightDirTan = float3( 0.424264f, -0.424264f, 0.8f);\n  float fFakeNdotL;\n#if 0\n  // original approach\n  fFakeNdotL = dot( vNormalTan, vFakeLightDirTan) *0.5f +0.6f;\n#else\n  // ~2x more contrast\n  fFakeNdotL = dot( vNormalTan, vFakeLightDirTan) *1.25f;\n#endif\n  // square for (even) more contast and to get rid of negative values\n  return fFakeNdotL*fFakeNdotL;\n}\n\n\n// (this is the lighting calculation function and\n//  needs to be implemented inside caller file!)\nfloat3 CalcLight( const float3 vLightDirAbs);\n\n\n// how much of original light is casting on vertex or pixel (0=none, 1=full)\n// (used by spot and omni lights; distant is always 1.0, as it doesn't have attenuation)\nstatic float g_fLightFactor = 1.0f;\n\n// gets power of the light\ninline float GetLightFactor(void)\n{\n  // (1=none, 0=full)\n  return g_fLightFactor;\n}\n\n// shadowing term, calculated BEFORE the CalcLight() callback is called, in 0-1 range\nstatic float3 g_vShadowingFactor = float3( 1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f );\n\n// gets cached shadowing factor\ninline float3 GetShadowingFactor(void)\n{\n  return g_vShadowingFactor;\n}\n\n// original lit color before shadowing is applied\nstatic float3 g_cColorAndAttenuated = float3( 0, 0, 0 );\n\n// gets color of the pixel after lighting is applied\ninline float3 GetColorAndAttenuated(void)\n{\n  return g_cColorAndAttenuated;\n}\n\n// sets max SSS transmission depth\nstatic float g_fMaxSSSTransmissionDepth = 0.1f;\n\n// sets max transmission depth\ninline void SetMaxSSSTransmissionDepth( float f )\n{\n  g_fMaxSSSTransmissionDepth = f;\n}\n\n\n// calculate phong specular component\ninline float PhongSpecularity( const float3 vNormal, const float3 vViewDir,\n                               const float3 vLightDir, const float fSpecPower)\n{\n  // reflect view direction around normal\n  float3 vReflect = reflect( vViewDir, vNormal);\n  // dot reflected normal with light direction\n  float fNdotR = saturate( dot( -vReflect, vLightDir));\n  // (we need to small constant to avoid pow(0,0) since\n  //  the GPU will puke NaN as a result in that case)\n  fNdotR = max( abs( fNdotR), 0.0001f);\n  return pow( fNdotR, fSpecPower);\n}\n\n\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n\n// calculate distant-light intensity\ninline float3 DistantLight( const float4 vPixPosAbs)\n{\n  // (NOTE: Cannot use dynamic branching here, because there are lotta\n  //  gradient usage and sampling inside the branch. HLSL compiler will\n  //  not optimize this code, but instead just use \"flatten\" method\n  //  (execute both branches and choose result - SLOW!)\n\n  // if has shadow\n#ifdef HAS_SHADOW\n  float fCasterReceiverDistance = 0;\n  g_vShadowingFactor = CascadedPlanarShadow( vPixPosAbs, fCasterReceiverDistance);\n\n  // Note: for materials with generic subsurface scattering, use this to generate\n  // transmission color bleeding falloff... this define will be generated in PBR node shader,\n  // ONLY if Generic SSS is chosen.\n#if defined(DEF_SSSTYPE_GENERIC) || defined(DEF_SSSTYPE_IMPOSTER_CRUMB)\n  float fDistanceToPixel = dot( vPixPosAbs.xyz - c_sli_vPosition, c_sli_vDirection );\n  fCasterReceiverDistance = fDistanceToPixel - ( 1-DECODE_DEPTH(fCasterReceiverDistance) ) / c_sli_f1oFalloff;\n  g_vShadowingFactor = saturate( g_vShadowingFactor + saturate( 1-fCasterReceiverDistance / g_fMaxSSSTransmissionDepth ) );\n#endif\n\n#endif\n\n  // apply lighting (calculations are in tangent space)\n  g_cColorAndAttenuated = c_sli_vColor; // must be before CalcLight() call!\n  float3 vDistantLight = CalcLight( -c_sli_vDirection) * c_sli_vColor;\n  g_fLightFactor = 1.0f;\n\n  // if has shadow\n#ifdef HAS_SHADOW\n  // but colorizing cascades\n  #ifdef COLORIZE_CASCADED_SHADOWS\n    // set shadow to distant light\n    vDistantLight = g_vShadowingFactor;\n  // if not colorizing cascades\n  #else\n    // attenuate by shadow amount\n    vDistantLight *= g_vShadowingFactor;\n  #endif\n#endif\n\n  // done\n  return vDistantLight;\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n\n// calculate spot-light intensity\ninline float3 SpotLight( const float4 vPixPosAbs)\n{\n  // distance attenuation\n  float3 vDist = vPixPosAbs.xyz - c_sli_vPosition;\n  float fDist = length( vDist);\n  float f1oDist = 1.0f / fDist;\n  // apply linear fall-off attenuation\n  g_fLightFactor = 1.0f- saturate( fDist * c_sli_f1oFalloff);\n  // and linear distance attenuation\n  g_fLightFactor *= f1oDist;\n            \n  // (branching?)\n\n  // cone attenuation       \n  float3 vLightDir = vDist * -f1oDist; // =normalize()\n  float fAngleCos  = dot( vLightDir, -c_sli_vDirection);\n  g_fLightFactor *= saturate( c_sli_fOuterCone- fAngleCos*c_sli_f1oConeRange);\n\n  // if has shadow (or projector, implied!)\n#ifdef HAS_SHADOW\n  g_vShadowingFactor = PlanarShadow( vPixPosAbs);\n#endif\n\n  // (branching?)\n\n  // apply lighting\n  g_cColorAndAttenuated = c_sli_vColor * g_fLightFactor; // must be before CalcLight() call!\n  float3 vSpotLight = CalcLight( vLightDir);\n  // attenuate by distance and cone\n  vSpotLight *= g_cColorAndAttenuated;\n\n  // if has shadow (or projector, implied!)\n#ifdef HAS_SHADOW\n  // adjust by shadow and/or projector\n  vSpotLight *= g_vShadowingFactor;\n#endif\n\n  // done\n  return vSpotLight;\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n\n// calculate omni-light intensity\ninline float3 OmniLight( const float4 vPixPosAbs)\n{\n  // distance attenuation\n  float3 vDist = vPixPosAbs.xyz - c_sli_vPosition;\n  float fDist2 = dot( vDist, vDist);\n  float fDist = sqrt( fDist2);\n  // apply linear fall-off attenuation\n  g_fLightFactor = 1.0f- saturate( fDist * c_sli_f1oFalloff);\n  // and quadratic distance attenuation\n  g_fLightFactor /= fDist2;\n\n  // if has shadow (or projector, implied!)\n#ifdef HAS_SHADOW\n  g_vShadowingFactor = CubeShadow( vDist);\n#endif\n\n  // (branching?)\n\n  // apply lighting\n  float3 vLightDir  = vDist / -fDist; // (normalize)\n  g_cColorAndAttenuated = c_sli_vColor * g_fLightFactor; // must be before CalcLight() call!\n  float3 vOmniLight = CalcLight( vLightDir);\n  // attenuate by distance\n  vOmniLight *= g_cColorAndAttenuated;\n\n  // if has shadow (or projector, implied!)\n#ifdef HAS_SHADOW\n  // adjust by shadow and/or projector\n  vOmniLight *= g_vShadowingFactor;\n#endif\n\n  // done\n  return vOmniLight;\n}\n\n#endif // LIGHT_TYPE\n\n#endif // LIGHTING_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// MATRIX PALETTE SKINNING (bones transformation)\n\n// used constant registers: c41-c238\n\n// (works only for vertex shader and gotta have bones!)\n#if VS_VER && defined(HAS_BONES)\n\n#ifndef SKINNING_HS\n#define SKINNING_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n#if _HLSL\n\n  // bones transformation matrices\n  // (NOTE: This register is loaded from the Engine code, and it must be at the position specified by the Engine constant SHA_CREG_BONES!)\n  const uniform float4x3 c_amMatrices[66] : register(c41);\n\n  // get one matrix for skinning\n  #define _getSkinMatrix( idx) c_amMatrices[idx]\n\n#elif _GLSL\n\n  // get one matrix for skinning\n  #define _getSkinMatrix( idx) float4x3( c_avVexUniformsF[ 41+idx*3], c_avVexUniformsF[ 42+idx*3], c_avVexUniformsF[ 43+idx*3])\n\n#endif // API\n\n\n\n// HELPER: make skinning matrix\nstatic inline float4x3 _makeSkinMatrix( in float4 vIndices, in float4 vWeights)\n{\n  // calculate last weight\n  int4 vIdx = int4( vIndices *255.01f);\n  vWeights.w = 1.0f- dot( vWeights.xyz, _tcast(float3,1));\n\n  // return matrix\n  return _getSkinMatrix( vIdx.x) *vWeights.x +\n         _getSkinMatrix( vIdx.y) *vWeights.y +\n         _getSkinMatrix( vIdx.z) *vWeights.z +\n         _getSkinMatrix( vIdx.w) *vWeights.w;\n}\n\n\n// transform position, normal and tangent by bones\nfloat3 SkinVertexTan( const float4 vIndices, in float4 vWeights,\n                      const float4 vPos, inout float3 vNor, inout float3 vTan) \n{\n  // do bones transformation\n  // (matrix-palette skinning)\n  float4x3 mBlendPos = _makeSkinMatrix( vIndices, vWeights);\n  // for position, normal and tangent\n  vNor.xyz = mul( vNor, _tcastM33F(mBlendPos));\n  vTan.xyz = mul( vTan, _tcastM33F(mBlendPos));\n  return mulM43F( vPos, mBlendPos);  \n}\n\n\n// transform position and normal by bones\nfloat3 SkinVertexNor( const float4 vIndices, in float4 vWeights,          \n                      const float4 vPos, inout float3 vNor)\n{\n  // do bones transformation\n  // (matrix-palette skinning)\n  float4x3 mBlendPos = _makeSkinMatrix( vIndices, vWeights);\n  // for position and normal\n  vNor.xyz = mul( vNor, _tcastM33F(mBlendPos));\n  return mulM43F( vPos, mBlendPos);\n}\n\n\n// transform position by bones\nfloat3 SkinVertexPos( const float4 vIndices, in float4 vWeights,\n                      const float4 vPos) \n{\n  // do bones transformation\n  // (matrix-palette skinning)\n  float4x3 mBlend = _makeSkinMatrix( vIndices, vWeights);\n  // for position only\n  return mulM43F( vPos, mBlend);\n}\n\n#endif // SKINNING_HS\n\n#endif // VS_VER && HAS_BONES\n\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// MISCELLANEOUS FUNCTIONS\n\n// used constant registers: -\n\n#ifndef MISC_HS\n#define MISC_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n/*\n// calculate fresnel value from fresnel term\ninline float CalcFresnel( const float fFresnelTerm, const float fNdotV)\n{\n  float fFresPow = pow( 1.0f-saturate(fNdotV), 5.0f);\n  return (1.0f-fFresnelTerm)+ fFresnelTerm *fFresPow;\n}\n//*/\n\n// RGBE textures sampling and unpacking\n\n\n// unpack RGBE color\ninline float3 UnpackRGBE( const float4 vcol)\n{\n  // (looks like it's better to use 'exp2' than 'ldexp',\n  //  because of some rounding precision issues)\n  return vcol.rgb * exp2( vcol.a *32.0f -16.0f);\n}\n\n// TerrainCrumbsShaders.sh needs this in vertex shader, hence this check was removed\n//#if PS_VER\n\n\n// sample and unpack 2D RGBE texture\ninline float3 SampleRGBE( sampler2D tTex, SamplerState sSam, const float2 vUV)\n{\n  float4 vcol = texSample2D( tTex, sSam, vUV);\n  return UnpackRGBE( vcol);\n}\n\n\n// if doing sRGB conversion\n#ifdef DO_SRGB\n\n  // this \"function\" converts to linear space\n  #if DO_SRGB < 2\n    // fast but less accurate\n    #define LinearSpace( colRGB) colRGB *= colRGB\n  #else\n    // or slow but (almost) accurate\n    #define LinearSpace( colRGB) colRGB = pow( colRGB, _tcast(float3,2.2f))\n  #endif\n\n// if not\n#else \n\n  // this \"function\" does nothing\n  #define LinearSpace( colRGB) \n\n#endif\n\n\n#endif // MISC_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PARALLAX MAPPING\n\n// used constant registers: c9\n\n#ifndef PARALLAXMAPPING_HS\n#define PARALLAXMAPPING_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// use gradient texture sampling instead LOD 0?\n#define USE_GRADIENTS 2\n\n\n// if parallax sub-steps are not defined\n#ifndef PARALLAX_STEPS\n  // assume only one\n  #define PARALLAX_STEPS 1\n#endif\n#ifndef PARALLAX_METHOD\n  // (just to keep ATI's GLSL compiler happy)\n  #define PARALLAX_METHOD 0\n#endif\n\n// depth occlusion mask and height bias\n_CregF( float4, c_vDepthOccHeightSize, 9);\nstatic float  c_fDepthOccl  = c_vDepthOccHeightSize.x;\nstatic float  c_fHeightBias = c_vDepthOccHeightSize.y;\nstatic float2 c_vHeightSize = c_vDepthOccHeightSize.zw;\n\n// float of parallax steps\nstatic const float sc_fParallaxSteps = float(PARALLAX_STEPS);\n\n\n#ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n\n// get mapping offset from two height maps (.xy), sampled depth texture (.z) and ambient roughness mask (.w)\ninline float4 GetMappingOffset2( sampler2D tHeightMap, SamplerState sHeightMap, sampler2D tHeightMap2, SamplerState sHeightMap2,\n                                 const float2 vHeightUVMap, const float2 vHeightUVMap2, const float fHeightBlendRatio,\n                                 const float fHeightRatio, in float3 vViewDirTan, const float fViewDist2)\n#else \n\n// get mapping offset from one height map (.xy), sampled depth texture (.z) and ambient roughness mask (.w)\ninline float4 GetMappingOffset( sampler2D tHeightMap, SamplerState sHeightMap, const float2 vHeightUVMap,\n                                const float fHeightRatio, in float3 vViewDirTan, const float fViewDist2)\n\n#endif\n{\n  // if no parallaxing\n#if PARALLAX_METHOD<1 || PARALLAX_METHOD>3\n\n  // no offseting\n  return float4( 0,0,1,1);\n\n  // if has one of parallaxing methods\n#else\n\n  // go with one of parallaxing method...\n  float2 vSampledTex;\n\n  // make sure view Z is between 0 and 1\n  // (it is near-normalized, but it might go over 1 in case of some weird non-uniform stretching)\n  vViewDirTan.z = saturate( vViewDirTan.z *0.8f +0.2f);\n  vViewDirTan.z += 0.0001f;\n\n  // set initial texture coordinates\n  float4 vOffset; // (final result!)\n  vOffset.xy = vHeightUVMap;\n  // attenute initial sampling height by view distance\n  // (this way linear loop will exit much faster!)\n  vOffset.z = 1.0f- saturate( fViewDist2 / (float(PARALLAX_STEPS*PARALLAX_STEPS)*25.0f*25.0f));\n  vOffset.w = 0.0f;\n\n  // bias view vector by height factor (with a bit of view-angle attenuation)\n  // (cannot use power of 0.25 here because AMD driver will wrongly optimize generated SPIR-V code!)\n  vViewDirTan.xy *= c_fHeightBias * pow( vViewDirTan.z, 0.256f);\n\n  // if only one height map\n  #ifndef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n    // attenuate depth biasing by height ratio\n    vViewDirTan.xy *= fHeightRatio;\n  // if two of them\n  #else\n    // set initial 2nd texture coordinates\n    float4 vOffset2 = float4( vHeightUVMap2, 1,0);\n    float fHeight2;\n  #endif\n\n  // if using parallax or relief methods\n#if PARALLAX_METHOD == 2  // PARALLAX OCCLUSION MAPPING\n\n#if USE_GRADIENTS == 1\n\n  // calculate gradients for sampling height-map texture\n  float4 vGradUV1;\n  vGradUV1.xy = ddx( vHeightUVMap);\n  vGradUV1.zw = ddy( vHeightUVMap);\n  #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n    // (and also for 2nd height-map)\n    float4 vGradUV2;\n    vGradUV2.xy = ddx( vHeightUVMap2);\n    vGradUV2.zw = ddy( vHeightUVMap2);\n  #endif\n\n#elif USE_GRADIENTS > 1\n\n  // calculate gradients for sampling height-map texture\n  float4 vGradUV;\n  vGradUV.xy = ddx( vHeightUVMap);\n  vGradUV.zw = ddy( vHeightUVMap);\n  vGradUV.x  = dot( vGradUV, vGradUV);\n  vGradUV.xy = vGradUV.xx * c_vHeightSize.xy;\n  vOffset.w  = log2( vGradUV.x) *0.5f;\n  #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n    // (and also apply to 2nd height-map)\n    vOffset2.w = log2( vGradUV.y) *0.5f;\n  #endif\n#endif // USE_GRADIENTS\n\n  // determine number of ray-trace linear search steps\n  // (Z coord view direction in tangents space CAN GO under 0, so compensate for this, otherwise div-by-zero is imminent!)\n  float fSteps = sc_fParallaxSteps*12.0f *fHeightRatio *(1.0f-vViewDirTan.z) +4.0f;\n  vViewDirTan /= -fSteps * vViewDirTan.zzz;\n\n  // ray-trace the height-map to find the intersection with the view vector\n  int iMaxSteps = PARALLAX_STEPS * 25;\n  float fDifPrev, fDifThis=1.0f;\n  do {\n\n    // step along the view direction\n  #if USE_GRADIENTS == 1\n    vSampledTex = texGrad2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy, vGradUV1.xy, vGradUV1.zw).gb;\n  #else\n    vSampledTex = texLod2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy, vOffset.w).gb;\n  #endif\n    #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n    #if USE_GRADIENTS == 1\n      fHeight2 = texGrad2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy, vGradUV2.xy, vGradUV2.zw).g;\n    #else\n      fHeight2 = texLod2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy, vOffset2.w).g;\n    #endif\n      vSampledTex.x = lerp( vSampledTex.x, fHeight2, fHeightBlendRatio);\n      vOffset2.xyz += vViewDirTan;\n    #endif\n\n    // until we find a point below the height-map\n    vOffset.xyz += vViewDirTan;\n    fDifPrev = fDifThis;\n    fDifThis = vOffset.z - vSampledTex.x;\n    iMaxSteps--;\n  \n  // until inside height is found\n  } while( iMaxSteps>0 && fDifThis>0.0f);\n\n  // refine coordinate by intersecting the view direction with the surface\n  // (assume the surface is linear between the last two height-map samples)\n  vOffset.xyz += (fDifThis / (fDifPrev-fDifThis) -1.0f) *vViewDirTan.xyz;\n\n#elif PARALLAX_METHOD == 3  // RELIEF MAPPING\n\n#if USE_GRADIENTS == 1\n\n  // calculate gradients for sampling height-map texture\n  float4 vGradUV1;\n  vGradUV1.xy = ddx( vHeightUVMap);\n  vGradUV1.zw = ddy( vHeightUVMap);\n  #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n    // (and also for 2nd height-map)\n    float4 vGradUV2;\n    vGradUV2.xy = ddx( vHeightUVMap2);\n    vGradUV2.zw = ddy( vHeightUVMap2);\n  #endif\n\n#elif USE_GRADIENTS > 1\n\n  // calculate gradients for sampling height-map texture\n  float4 vGradUV;\n  vGradUV.xy = ddx( vHeightUVMap);\n  vGradUV.zw = ddy( vHeightUVMap);\n  vGradUV.x  = dot( vGradUV, vGradUV);\n  vGradUV.xy = vGradUV.xx * c_vHeightSize.xy;\n  vOffset.w  = log2( vGradUV.x) *0.5f;\n  #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n    // (and also apply to 2nd height-map)\n    vOffset2.w = log2( vGradUV.y) *0.5f;\n  #endif\n\n#endif // USE_GRADIENTS\n\n  // determine number of ray-trace linear search steps\n  float fSteps = sc_fParallaxSteps*8.0f *fHeightRatio *(1.0f-vViewDirTan.z) +4.0f;\n  vViewDirTan /= -fSteps * vViewDirTan.z;\n  int iMaxSteps = PARALLAX_STEPS * 25;\n  do {\n\n    // linear search thru height-map\n    vOffset.xyz += vViewDirTan;\n  #if USE_GRADIENTS == 1\n    vSampledTex = texGrad2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy, vGradUV1.xy, vGradUV1.zw).gb;\n  #else\n    vSampledTex = texLod2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy, vOffset.w).gb;\n  #endif\n    #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n      vOffset2.xyz += vViewDirTan;\n    #if USE_GRADIENTS == 1\n      fHeight2 = texGrad2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy, vGradUV2.xy, vGradUV2.zw).g;\n    #else\n      fHeight2 = texLod2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy, vOffset2.w).g;\n    #endif\n      vSampledTex.x = lerp( vSampledTex.x, fHeight2, fHeightBlendRatio);\n    #endif\n    iMaxSteps--;\n\n  // until inside height is found\n  } while( iMaxSteps>0 && vSampledTex.x<vOffset.z);\n\n  // binary search thru height-map\n  for( int ib=0; ib<(PARALLAX_STEPS+4); ib++) {\n\n    // sample height-map\n    vSampledTex = texSample2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy).gb;\n    #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n      fHeight2 = texSample2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy).g;\n      vSampledTex.x = lerp( vSampledTex.x, fHeight2, fHeightBlendRatio);\n    #endif\n    // (next advancing is 2 times shorter than the last one)\n    vViewDirTan *= 0.5f;\n\n    // if mapping height is higher than sampled height go forward, otherwise backpedal\n    float fSign = (vOffset.z >= vSampledTex.x) ? +1.0f : -1.0f;\n    vOffset.xyz += vViewDirTan *fSign;\n    #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n      vOffset2.xyz += vViewDirTan *fSign;\n    #endif\n  }\n\n#else // PARALLAX_METHOD == 1  // OFFSET (REFIREMENT) w/ LIMITING\n\n  // depth needs to be attenuated a bit\n  vViewDirTan.xy /= sc_fParallaxSteps;\n\n  // initial sampling of height map\n  vSampledTex = texSample2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy).gb;\n#ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n  fHeight2 = texSample2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy).g;\n  vSampledTex.x = lerp( vSampledTex.x, fHeight2, fHeightBlendRatio);\n#endif\n  vOffset.xy += vViewDirTan.xy* (vSampledTex.x-1.0f);\n\n  // if quality is not low(est)\n  _unroll for( int i=1; i<PARALLAX_STEPS; i++) {\n\n    // do offset refinement via extra sampling\n    vSampledTex = texSample2D( tHeightMap, sHeightMap, vOffset.xy).gb;\n    #ifdef DOUBLE_PARALLAX\n      fHeight2 = texSample2D( tHeightMap2, sHeightMap2, vOffset2.xy).g;\n      vSampledTex.x = lerp( vSampledTex.x, fHeight2, fHeightBlendRatio);\n      vOffset2.xy += vViewDirTan.xy * (vSampledTex.x-1.0f);\n    #endif\n    vOffset.xy += vViewDirTan.xy * (vSampledTex.x-1.0f);\n  }\n\n#endif  // PARALLAX_METHOD\n\n  // and da offset is...\n  return float4( vOffset.xy-vHeightUVMap, vSampledTex);\n\n#endif  // PS_VER\n}\n\n\n// get depth occlusion from height map\ninline float GetDepthOcclusion( in float fDepth)\n{\n  // apply depth attenuation and modulate it by ambient occlusion\n  return lerp( 1.0f, fDepth, c_fDepthOccl);\n}\n\n#undef USE_GRADIENTS\n\n#endif // PARALLAXMAPPING_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// PPBloomShaders.psh\n\n// Thanx to Jorge Jimenez\n// (\"Next Generation Post Processing in Call of Duty Advanced Warfare\")\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// textures\n_Sreg2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, 0);\n\n// constant registers\n_CregF( float3, c_vBloomPixSize, 0);\nstatic float2 c_v1oPixSize= c_vBloomPixSize.xy;\nstatic float  c_fTreshold = c_vBloomPixSize.z;\n_CregF( float4, c_vDrawPortEdges, 1); // .xy=min, .zw=max\n\n\n// color component weights be used for luminance calculations (in RGB order)\nstatic const float3 LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS = float3( 0.2125f, 0.7154f, 0.0721f);\n\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy), depth/bloom (.zw)\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n#if defined(run_BloomIniDownsamplePS) || defined(run_BloomMipDownsamplePS)\n\n// offsets and weights for downsampling\n#define DOWN_SAMPLES 13\nstatic const float4 c_vDownsamples[ DOWN_SAMPLES] =\n{\n  float4( 1.0f,-1.0f, 0.5f, 0.125f),\n  float4(-1.0f, 1.0f, 0.5f, 0.125f),\n  float4( 1.0f, 1.0f, 0.5f, 0.125f),\n  float4( 1.0f,-1.0f, 0.5f, 0.125f),\n\n  float4(-2.0f,-2.0f, 0.125f, 0.03125f),\n  float4(-2.0f, 0.0f, 0.25f,  0.0625f),\n  float4(-2.0f, 2.0f, 0.125f, 0.03125f),\n\n  float4( 0.0f,-2.0f, 0.25f, 0.0625f),\n  float4( 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.5f,  0.125f),\n  float4( 0.0f, 2.0f, 0.25f, 0.0625f),\n\n  float4( 2.0f,-2.0f, 0.125f, 0.03125f),\n  float4( 2.0f, 0.0f, 0.25f,  0.0625f),\n  float4( 2.0f, 2.0f, 0.125f, 0.03125f)\n};\n#endif // def(run_BloomIniDownsamplePS) || def(BloomMipDownsamplePS)\n#ifdef run_BloomIniDownsamplePS\n\nPS_ENTRY( BloomIniDownsamplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // get initial texture coordinates and prepare for accumulation\n  float2 vTexCoord = MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy));\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n  float fLum, fTotalWeight=0;\n\n  // for each sample position\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<DOWN_SAMPLES; iSample++)\t{\n\n    // calculate and clamp coordinates to drawport edges\n    float2 vSampleCoord = vTexCoord+ c_vDownsamples[ iSample].xy *c_v1oPixSize; \n    vSampleCoord = clamp( vSampleCoord, c_vDrawPortEdges.xy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zw);\n    // and sample texture there\n    float3 vSample = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vSampleCoord, 0).rgb;\n    // (needs to clamp in case some negative or too big values ended up in HDR RT somehow)\n    vSample = clamp( vSample, SMALL_HDR_FLOAT, MAX_HDR_FLOAT);\n\n    // calculate luma\n    fLum = dot( vSample, LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS);\n\n    // apply cutoff\n    /*\n    // (can produce banding!)\n    vSample = (fLum<c_fTreshold) ? _tcast(float3,0) : vSample;\n    /*/\n    // (better looking in most cases)\n    vSample -= c_fTreshold / (1.0f+fLum);\n    vSample = max( vSample, _tcast(float3,0.0f));\n    //*/\n    // get sample weight\n    float fWeight = c_vDownsamples[ iSample].z;\n  #if LUM_AVG\n    // scale it by inverse luma\n    // (to minimize shimmering effect)\n  //fLum = pow( fLum, 0.125f);\n    fWeight *= 1.0f / (1.0f+fLum);\n  #endif\n    // accumulate color and weight\n    vOutCol.rgb += vSample * fWeight;\n    fTotalWeight+= fWeight;\n  }\n  // average color by (luma) weight\n  vOutCol.rgb /= fTotalWeight;\n\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_BloomIniDownsamplePS\n\n\n#ifdef run_BloomMipDownsamplePS\n\n\nPS_ENTRY( BloomMipDownsamplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // get initial texture coordinates and prepare for accumulation\n  float2 vTexCoord = MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy));\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n  float fTotalWeight = 0;\n\n  // for each sample position\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<DOWN_SAMPLES; iSample++)\t{\n\n    // calculate and clamp coordinates to drawport edges\n    float2 vSampleCoord = vTexCoord+ c_vDownsamples[ iSample].xy *c_v1oPixSize; \n    vSampleCoord = clamp( vSampleCoord, c_vDrawPortEdges.xy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zw);\n    float3 vSample = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vSampleCoord, 0).rgb;\n    // sample texture there and accumulate weightened color\n    vOutCol.rgb += vSample.rgb * c_vDownsamples[ iSample].w;\n  }\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_BloomMipDownsamplePS\n\n\n#ifdef run_BloomFinalUpsamplePS\n\n\n// offsets and weights for upsampling\n#define UP_SAMPLES 9\nstatic const float3 c_vUpsamples[ UP_SAMPLES] =\n{\n  float3(-1.0f,-1.0f, 0.0625f),\n  float3( 0.0f,-1.0f, 0.125f),\n  float3( 1.0f,-1.0f, 0.0625f),\n\n  float3(-1.0f, 0.0f, 0.125f),\n  float3( 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.25f),\n  float3( 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.125f),\n\n  float3(-1.0f, 1.0f, 0.0625f),\n  float3( 0.0f, 1.0f, 0.125f),\n  float3( 1.0f, 1.0f, 0.0625f)\n};\n\n\nPS_ENTRY( BloomFinalUpsamplePS)\n{\n  PS_VR_INIT;\n\n  // get initial texture coordinates and prepare for accumulation\n  float2 vTexCoord = MultiviewUV( PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy));\n  float4 vOutCol = float4( 0,0,0, 1);\n\n  // for each sample position\n  _unroll for( int iSample=0; iSample<UP_SAMPLES; iSample++)\t{\n\n    // calculate and clamp coordinates to drawport edges\n    float2 vSampleCoord = vTexCoord+ c_vUpsamples[ iSample].xy *c_v1oPixSize; \n    vSampleCoord = clamp( vSampleCoord, c_vDrawPortEdges.xy, c_vDrawPortEdges.zw);\n    // sample texture there and accumulate weightened color\n    float3 vSample = texLod2D( t_sSource, s_tSource, vSampleCoord, 0).rgb;\n    vOutCol.rgb += vSample * c_vUpsamples[ iSample].z;\n  }\n  // output magenta for NaN or Inf values\n  ColorizeWrongOutput( vOutCol);\n\n  // done\n  PS_OUT( vOutCol);\n}\n\n#endif // run_BloomFinalUpsamplePS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// REFLECTIONS\n\n// used constant registers: -\n\n#ifndef REFLECTION_HS\n#define REFLECTION_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// calculate reflection vector for cube-map\ninline float3 CalcCubeReflectionVector( const float3 vNormalAbs, const float3 vViewDistAbs)\n{\n  // reflect eye vector around normal; 2N(N.E) - E(N.N) \n  float3 vReflect = reflect( vViewDistAbs, vNormalAbs);\n  // switch north-south faces because of left-hand orientation\n  vReflect.xy = -vReflect.xy;\n  return vReflect;\n}\n                                        \n\n// calculate reflection vector for sphere-map\ninline float2 CalcSphereReflectionVector( const float3 vNormalAbs, const float3 vViewDistAbs)\n{\n  // reflect eye vector around normal; 2N(N.E) - E(N.N) \n  float3 vReflect = -reflect( vViewDistAbs, vNormalAbs);\n  // normalize and move \"inflection\" point from +z to -y\n  // (+ to - because of left-hand orientation)\n  vReflect = normalize( vReflect.xzy);\n  // and convert to spherical coords\n  vReflect.z += 1;\n  float f1oSphereMap = 0.5f * rsqrt( dot(vReflect,vReflect));  // =1.0f / (2* sqrt(...));\n  vReflect.xy = vReflect.xy * f1oSphereMap +0.5f;\n  return vReflect.xy;\n}\n\n\n// sample reflection cube-map (HDR)\ninline float3 SampleCubeMap( samplerCUBE tCubeMap, SamplerState sCubeMap, const float3 vReflect, const float fReflBlur)\n{\n  // sample cube reflection map\n  float4 vReflColor = texBiasCube( tCubeMap, sCubeMap, vReflect, fReflBlur);\n  // (RGBE format, 5-bit signed exponent)  \n  return vReflColor.rgb * exp2( vReflColor.a *32.0f -16.0f);\n}\n\n\n// sample reflection sphere-map (HDR)\ninline float3 SampleSphereMap( sampler2D tSphereMap, SamplerState sSphereMap, const float2 vReflect, const float fReflBlur)\n{\n  // sample cube reflection map\n  float4 vReflColor = texBias2D( tSphereMap, sSphereMap, vReflect, fReflBlur);\n  // (RGBE format, 5-bit signed exponent)  \n  return vReflColor.rgb * exp2( vReflColor.a *32.0f -16.0f);\n}\n\n\n\n// get cube reflection map\nfloat3 GetCubeReflection( samplerCUBE tCubeMap, SamplerState sCubeMap, in float3 vNormal, const float fReflBlur,\n                          const float fReflMask, const float3 vViewDistAbs, const float3x3 mTanToAbs)\n{\n  // transform attenuated normal to absolute space\n  vNormal = mul( vNormal, mTanToAbs);\n  // calculate cube mapping coords\n  float3 vCubeCoords = CalcCubeReflectionVector( vNormal, vViewDistAbs);\n  // sample sphere map right there\n  float3 vReflect = SampleCubeMap( tCubeMap, sCubeMap, vCubeCoords, fReflBlur);\n  // and apply reflection mask\n  return vReflect * fReflMask;\n}\n\n\n// get spherical (2D) reflection map\nfloat3 GetSphericalReflection( sampler2D tSphereMap, SamplerState sSphereMap, in float3 vNormal, const float fReflBlur,\n                               const float fReflMask, const float3 vViewDistAbs, const float3x3 mTanToAbs)\n{\n  // transform attenuated normal to absolute space\n  vNormal = mul( vNormal, mTanToAbs);\n  // calculate spherical mapping coords\n  float2 vSphereCoords = CalcSphereReflectionVector( vNormal, vViewDistAbs);\n  // sample sphere map right there\n  float3 vReflect = SampleSphereMap( tSphereMap, sSphereMap, vSphereCoords, fReflBlur);\n  // and apply reflection mask\n  return vReflect * fReflMask;\n}\n\n#endif // REFLECTION_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// ShadowBuffer.hs\n\n// used constant registers: c32-c46\n// used texture units: s14, s15\n\n#ifndef SHADOWBUFFER_HS\n#define SHADOWBUFFER_HS 1\n\n// TerrainCrumbsShaders.sh calculates shadow in vertex shader, hence this check was removed\n//#if PS_VER\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// for pixel shader, we use regular texture sampling, which uses gradients to do mipmapping\n// in vertex shader, gradients are not available, so we manually sample first mipmap\n// (terrain crumbs apply shadow in vertex shader, hence we wrap this call to reuse the same code)\n#if PS_VER\n  #define shbTexSample2D texSample2D\n  #define shbTexSampleCube texSampleCube\n#else  \n  inline float4 shbTexSample2D(sampler2D tTex2D, SamplerState sTex2D, float2 uv)\n  {\n    return texLod2D(tTex2D, sTex2D, uv, 0.0f);\n  }\n  inline float4 shbTexSampleCube(samplerCUBE tTexCUBE, SamplerState sTexCUBE, float3 uv)\n  {\n    return texLodCube(tTexCUBE, sTexCUBE, uv, 0.0f);\n  }  \n#endif\n\n// (just to keep ATI's GLSL compiler happy)\n#ifndef SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING\n  #define SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING 0\n#endif\n\n// used in pixel program, so declare shadow depth buffer and projector textures\n#ifdef HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n\n  // for distant light\n  _SregShdAry2D( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, 14); \n  _Sreg2D( t_sCascadeProj, s_tCascadeProj, 15); \n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n  // for spot light\n  _SregShd2D( t_sPlanarShd, s_tPlanarShd, 14); \n  _Sreg2D( t_sPlanarProj, s_tPlanarProj, 15); \n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n  // or for omni-directional light\n  _SregShdCUBE( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, 14);\n  _SregCUBE( t_sCubeProj, s_tCubeProj, 15);\n\n#endif\n\n// shadow's data for distant, spot and omni light\n// (these has to match the structure!)\n// various shadow factors\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi, 32);\n  static float c_ssi_fDitherRadius  = c_ssi.x;\n  static float c_ssi_fDarkShadow    = c_ssi.y;\n  static float c_ssi_fTrilinearSpan = c_ssi.z;\n  static float c_ssi_f1oTrilinSpan  = c_ssi.w;\n// shadow buffer texture sizes (x=pixEdge, y=1/pixEdge) \n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_vShadowSizeRange, 33);\nstatic float c_ssi_vCascadeStep5    = c_ssi_vShadowSizeRange.x;\nstatic float c_ssi_f1oShadowMapSize = c_ssi_vShadowSizeRange.y;\nstatic float c_ssi_f1oSharpRange    = c_ssi_vShadowSizeRange.z; // 1 / (1-2*sha_fShadowSmoothness)\nstatic float c_ssi_fSharpStart      = c_ssi_vShadowSizeRange.w; // ssi_fSharpShadow / (1-2*sha_fShadowSmoothness)\n// projector mapping stretch (.xy) and offset (.zw)\n_CregF( float4,
