c_ssi_vProjectorMapping, 34);\nstatic float2 c_ssi_vProjectorStretch = c_ssi_vProjectorMapping.xy;\nstatic float2 c_ssi_vProjectorOffset  = c_ssi_vProjectorMapping.zw;\n// cascades for distant light\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_vCascadeSteps, 35);\n\n#ifdef HAS_SPOT_LIGHT\n  // light's perspective projection matrix\n  _CregM44F( c_ssi_mLightViewProj, 36);\n#elif defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n  // light's parallel projection matrix\n  _CregM43F( c_ssi_mLightViewOrtho, 36);\n  // shadow viewer position (in absolute space)\n  _CregF( float4, c_ssi_vShadowViewerPosProjDist, 39);\n  static float3 c_ssi_vShadowViewerPos = c_ssi_vShadowViewerPosProjDist.xyz;\n  // and reciprocal of squared maximum projector distance\n  static float  c_ssi_f1oProjectorMaxDist2 = c_ssi_vShadowViewerPosProjDist.w;\n#elif defined( HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n  // light's view matrix\n  _CregM33F( c_ssi_mLightView, 36);\n  // normalized depth distance\n  _CregF( float2, c_ssi_fOmniDistFactors, 39);  // .x=(fFar+fNear)/(fFar-fNear)*0.5+0.5, .y=(2*fFar*fNear)/(fFar-fNear)*0.5f\n#endif\n// cascaded buffer's scale and offsets for X and Y\n// (relative to main cascade bounding box, from farthest to nearest)\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias0, 40); // (far cascade)\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias1, 41);\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias2, 42);\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias3, 43);\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias4, 44);\n_CregF( float4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias5, 45);  \n_CregF( float2, c_ssi_vMAddZ, 46); \n\n\n// how much light is seen thru shadow (0-1)\nstatic float3 g_vShadowFactor = _tcast(float3,1);\n\n\n// gets power of the shadow \ninline float3 GetShadowFactor(void)\n{\n  // (1=none, 0=full)\n  return g_vShadowFactor;\n}\n                  \n#if defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT) || defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n\n/*\n// Apply biasing for provided depth at given position.\ninline void ApplyDepthBiasing( inout float3 vPixPosLit)\n{\n  // packing derivatives of u,v, and distance to light source w.r.t. screen space x, and y\n  float3 duvdist_dx = ddx(vPixPosLit);\n  float3 duvdist_dy = ddy(vPixPosLit);\n  // invert texture Jacobian and use chain rule to compute ddist/du and ddist/dv\n  //  |ddist/du| = |du/dx du/dy|-T  * |ddist/dx|\n  //  |ddist/dv|   |dv/dx dv/dy|      |ddist/dy|\n  // multiply ddist/dx and ddist/dy by inverse transpose of Jacobian\n  float invDet = 1.0f / ((duvdist_dx.x * duvdist_dy.y) - (duvdist_dx.y * duvdist_dy.x));\n  // top row of 2x2\n  float2 ddist_duv;\n  ddist_duv.x = duvdist_dy.y * duvdist_dx.z; // invJtrans[0][0] * ddist_dx\n  ddist_duv.x -= duvdist_dx.y * duvdist_dy.z; // invJtrans[0][1] * ddist_dy\n  // bottom row of 2x2\n  ddist_duv.y = duvdist_dx.x * duvdist_dy.z;   // invJtrans[1][1] * ddist_dy\n  ddist_duv.y -= duvdist_dy.x * duvdist_dx.z;  // invJtrans[1][0] * ddist_dx\n  ddist_duv *= invDet;\n  // set biased depth\n  vPixPosLit.z += (100.0f / 65536.0f) * dot(vPixPosLit.xy, ddist_duv) + (1.0f / 65536.0f);\n}\n*/\n\n\n// sample from planar shadow buffer (vPixPosLit: .xy=coord, .z=compare)\ninline float SamplePlanarShadow( sampler2DShadow tShadowBuffer, SamplerComparisonState sShadowBuffer, in float3 vPixPosLit)\n{\n  float fShadow;\n\n#if !SOFT_SHADOWS\n\n  fShadow = texShadow2D( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vPixPosLit.xy, vPixPosLit.z);\n\n#else\n\n  // sample shadow map in a regular 2x2 grid\n  // pivot pixel is located on texel borders, so use symmetric texel offsets for samples\n  float fOffset = c_ssi_f1oShadowMapSize *0.5f;\n  float2 vTexCoords;\n  float4 vCompares;\n  \n  // compare depth samples from shadow map to pivot depth\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xy +float2(-fOffset,-fOffset);\n  vCompares.x= texShadow2D( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords, vPixPosLit.z);\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xy +float2(-fOffset, fOffset);\n  vCompares.y= texShadow2D( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords, vPixPosLit.z);\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xy +float2( fOffset, fOffset);\n  vCompares.z= texShadow2D( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords, vPixPosLit.z);\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xy +float2( fOffset,-fOffset);\n  vCompares.w= texShadow2D( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords, vPixPosLit.z);\n  fShadow = dot( vCompares, _tcast(float4,0.25f));\n\n#endif\n\n  // apply darkening and sharpening\n  fShadow = 1.0f- saturate( (1.0f-fShadow) *c_ssi_fDarkShadow);\n  fShadow = saturate( fShadow *c_ssi_f1oSharpRange +c_ssi_fSharpStart);\n  return fShadow;\n}\n\n\n// sample from planar cascaded shadow buffer (vPixPosLit: .xy=coord, .z=slice, .w=compare)\ninline float SampleCascadeShadow( sampler2DShadowArray tShadowBuffer, SamplerComparisonState sShadowBuffer, in float4 vPixPosLit\n#if defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n  , out float fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance\n#endif\n  )\n{\n  float fShadow;\n\n#if !SOFT_SHADOWS\n\n  fShadow = texShadowAry( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vPixPosLit.xyz, vPixPosLit.w);\n\n#else\n\n  // sample shadow map in a regular 2x2 grid\n  // pivot pixel is located on texel borders, so use symmetric texel offsets for samples\n  float fOffset = c_ssi_f1oShadowMapSize *0.5f;\n  float3 vTexCoords;\n  float4 vCompares;\n  \n  // compare depth samples from shadow map to pivot depth\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xyz +float3(-fOffset,-fOffset, 0);\n  vCompares.x= texShadowAry( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords.xyz, vPixPosLit.w);\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xyz +float3(-fOffset, fOffset, 0);\n  vCompares.y= texShadowAry( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords.xyz, vPixPosLit.w);\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xyz +float3( fOffset, fOffset, 0);\n  vCompares.z= texShadowAry( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords.xyz, vPixPosLit.w);\n  vTexCoords = vPixPosLit.xyz +float3( fOffset,-fOffset, 0);\n  vCompares.w= texShadowAry( tShadowBuffer, sShadowBuffer, vTexCoords.xyz, vPixPosLit.w);\n  fShadow = dot( vCompares, _tcast(float4,0.25f));\n\n#endif\n\n#if defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n#if defined(DEF_SSSTYPE_GENERIC) || defined(DEF_SSSTYPE_IMPOSTER_CRUMB)\n  float3 vTexCoordsDet = vPixPosLit.xyz;\n  fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance = 1.0f; // texSample2D( tShadowBuffer, s_tCascadeProj, vTexCoordsDet.xyz ).r;\n#else\n  fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance = 1.0f;\n#endif\n#endif\n\n  // apply darkening and sharpening\n  fShadow = 1.0f- saturate( (1.0f-fShadow) *c_ssi_fDarkShadow);\n  fShadow = saturate( fShadow *c_ssi_f1oSharpRange +c_ssi_fSharpStart);\n  return fShadow;\n}\n\n\n#endif // HAS_SPOT_LIGHT || HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT\n#if defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n\n\n#if SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING==1\n\n// adjust view-distance based on raster positions\ninline float DitherOffset( float fViewDist)\n{\n  // determine screen offset\n  float2 vScreenPos = GetRasterPos();\n  float fDitherOffset = 0.0f;\n\n#define DITHER_METHOD 2\n\n  // ordered 2x2\n#if DITHER_METHOD == 1\n\n  float2 fXY = frac( vScreenPos *0.5f);\n  fDitherOffset = (fXY.x*1.5f) + (fXY.y*1.0f) - (fXY.x*fXY.y*4.0f);\n\n  // ordered 4x4\n#elif DITHER_METHOD == 2\n\n  // (original)\n//float2 fXY0 = frac( vScreenPos*0.5f) *2;\n//float2 fXY1 = frac( vScreenPos*0.25f - fXY0*0.25f) *2;\n//fDitherOffset = (fXY1.x*3 + fXY1.y*2 - fXY1.x*fXY1.y*4 + (fXY0.x*3 + fXY0.y*2 - fXY0.x*fXY0.y*4) *4) /16;\n\n  // (optimized)\n  float4 fFrac;  float3 fFrc2;\n  fFrac.xy = frac( vScreenPos *0.5f);\n  fFrac.zw = frac( vScreenPos *0.25f -fFrac.xy*0.5f);\n  fFrc2.xy = fFrac.xz * fFrac.yw;\n//fDitherOffset = fFrac.z*(6/16.0f) + fFrac.w*(4/16.0f) - fFrc2.y*(16/16.0f) + fFrac.x*(6/4.0f) + fFrac.y*(4/4.0f) - fFrc2.x*(16/4.0f);\n  fFrc2.z  = dot( fFrac, float4( 6.0f/4.0f, 4.0f/4.0f, 6.0f/16.0f, 4.0f/16.0f));\n  fDitherOffset = dot( fFrc2, float3( -16.0f/4.0f, -16.0f/16.0f, 1.0f));\n\n  // less random (fast?)\n#elif DITHER_METHOD == 3\n  \n  float fOfs1 = dot( vScreenPos, float2(1051,1061)) /13.0f;\n  float fOfs2 = dot( vScreenPos, float2(19,17)) /13.0f;\n  fDitherOffset = frac( fOfs1) * frac( fOfs2);\n\n  // more random (slow?)\n#elif DITHER_METHOD == 4\n\n  fDitherOffset = dot( vScreenPos, float2( 12.9898f,78.233f));\n  fDitherOffset = sin( fDitherOffset);\n  fDitherOffset = frac( fDitherOffset *43758.5453f);\n\n#elif DITHER_METHOD == 5\n\n  static const float3 vMagic = float3( 0.06711056f, 0.00583715f, 52.9829189f);\n  fDitherOffset = frac( vMagic.z * frac( dot( vScreenPos, vMagic.xy)));\n\n#endif // DITHER_METHOD\n\n  // apply dithered offset\n  fViewDist *= 1.0f+ fDitherOffset *c_ssi_fTrilinearSpan;\n\n#undef DITHER_METHOD\n\n  // done\n  return fViewDist;\n}\n\n#endif // SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING==1\n\n\n// returns pixel coordinates in cascaded shadow buffer texture based on distance\ninline float4 ChooseCascade( in float3 vPixPosLit, float fViewDist) \n{\n#if SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING==1\n\n  // apply dithering (if any!) to view distance\n  fViewDist = DitherOffset( fViewDist);\n#endif\n\n  // macro used to choose one of four values based on current cascade\n  // (it has to be a macro because it operates on different types of values)\n#define CHOOSE( res, v0, v1, v2, v3, v4, v5) \\\n  res = (fViewDist<c_ssi_vCascadeStep5.x) ? v1 : v0;  \\\n  res = (fViewDist<c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.w) ? v2 : res; \\\n  res = (fViewDist<c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.z) ? v3 : res; \\\n  res = (fViewDist<c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.y) ? v4 : res; \\\n  res = (fViewDist<c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.x) ? v5 : res;\n\n  // find X,Y scale and offset\n  float4 vPixPosLitOfs;\n  CHOOSE( vPixPosLitOfs,\n    c_ssi_avCascadeBias0, c_ssi_avCascadeBias1,\n    c_ssi_avCascadeBias2, c_ssi_avCascadeBias3,\n    c_ssi_avCascadeBias4, c_ssi_avCascadeBias5);\n  float fSlice;\n  CHOOSE( fSlice, 0.0f, 1.0f, 2.0f, 3.0f, 4.0f, 5.0f);\n\n  // (no more need for cascade-choice macro)\n#undef CHOOSE\n\n  // calculate final coord offset in shadow buffer\n  vPixPosLit.xy = vPixPosLit.xy *vPixPosLitOfs.xy +vPixPosLitOfs.zw;\n\n  // apply Z range inversion\n  vPixPosLit.z = saturate( vPixPosLit.z *c_ssi_vMAddZ.x +c_ssi_vMAddZ.y);\n  return float4( vPixPosLit.xy, fSlice, vPixPosLit.z);\n}\n\n\n// returns two sets of pixel coordinates in cascaded shadow buffer texture based on distance and ratio between them\ninline float ChooseCascade2( in float3 vPixPosLit, float fViewDist, out float4 vPixPosLit0, out float4 vPixPosLit1) \n{\n  // find X, Y scale and offset of cascaded shadow quad\n  float4 vPixPosLitOfs0, vPixPosLitOfs1;\n  float2 vSliceDistRatio;\n  float3 vRatio;\n\n  if( fViewDist < c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.x) {\n    // inside 1st cascade\n    vPixPosLitOfs0 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias5;\n    vPixPosLitOfs1 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias4;\n    vSliceDistRatio.x = saturate( fViewDist / c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.x);\n    vSliceDistRatio.y = 5.0f;\n  } else if( fViewDist < c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.y) {\n    // inside 2nd cascade\n    vPixPosLitOfs0 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias4;\n    vPixPosLitOfs1 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias3;\n    vSliceDistRatio.x = saturate( (fViewDist-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.x) / (c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.y-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.x));\n    vSliceDistRatio.y = 4.0f;\n  } else if( fViewDist < c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.z) {\n    // inside 3rd cascade\n    vPixPosLitOfs0 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias3;\n    vPixPosLitOfs1 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias2;\n    vSliceDistRatio.x = saturate( (fViewDist-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.y) / (c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.z-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.y));\n    vSliceDistRatio.y = 3.0f;\n  } else if( fViewDist < c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.w) {\n    // inside 4th cascade\n    vPixPosLitOfs0 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias2;\n    vPixPosLitOfs1 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias1;\n    vSliceDistRatio.x = saturate( (fViewDist-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.z) / (c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.w-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.z));\n    vSliceDistRatio.y = 2.0f;\n  } else if( fViewDist < c_ssi_vCascadeStep5.x) {\n    // inside 5th cascade (last near cascade)\n    vPixPosLitOfs0 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias1;\n    vPixPosLitOfs1 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias0;\n    vSliceDistRatio.x = saturate( (fViewDist-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.w) / (c_ssi_vCascadeStep5.x-c_ssi_vCascadeSteps.w));\n    vSliceDistRatio.y = 1.0f;\n  } else {\n    // inside far cascade (last cascade)\n    vPixPosLitOfs0 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias0;\n    vPixPosLitOfs1 = c_ssi_avCascadeBias0;\n    vSliceDistRatio.x = 0.0f;\n    vSliceDistRatio.y = 0.0f;\n  } \n  // 1st trilinear - calculate final coord offset in shadow buffer\n  vPixPosLit0.xy = vPixPosLit.xy *vPixPosLitOfs0.xy +vPixPosLitOfs0.zw;\n  // 2nd trilinear - calculate final coord offset in shadow buffer\n  vPixPosLit1.xy = vPixPosLit.xy *vPixPosLitOfs1.xy +vPixPosLitOfs1.zw;\n\n  // apply Z range inversion\n  vPixPosLit0.w = saturate( vPixPosLit.z *c_ssi_vMAddZ.x +c_ssi_vMAddZ.y);\n  vPixPosLit1.w = vPixPosLit0.w;\n\n  // return slices indexes\n  vPixPosLit0.z = vSliceDistRatio.y;\n  vPixPosLit1.z = max( vPixPosLit0.z-1, 0);\n\n  // return trilinear filtering ratio (adjusted by span)\n  vSliceDistRatio.x = (vSliceDistRatio.x-1.0f) *c_ssi_f1oTrilinSpan +1.0f;\n  return saturate( vSliceDistRatio.x);\n}\n\n\n// ortho planar projector for cascaded shadow\ninline float3 SampleOrthoProjector( in float2 vPixPosLit, float fViewDist2)\n{\n  // sample projector texture\n  vPixPosLit = vPixPosLit *0.5f +0.5f;\n  vPixPosLit = vPixPosLit *c_ssi_vProjectorStretch +c_ssi_vProjectorOffset;\n  float3 vcolProj = shbTexSample2D( t_sCascadeProj, s_tCascadeProj, vPixPosLit).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( vcolProj);\n\n  // and attenuate by squared distance\n  float fProjectorAtt = saturate( fViewDist2 *c_ssi_f1oProjectorMaxDist2);\n  return lerp( vcolProj, _tcast(float3,1), fProjectorAtt);\n}\n\n\n// cascaded planar shadow\ninline float3 CascadedPlanarShadow( const float4 vPixPosAbs, out float fOutLightSourceShadowCasterDistance)\n{\n  // calculate view distance^2 from \"shadow\" viewer position (in absolute space)\n  float3 vViewDist = c_ssi_vShadowViewerPos.xyz - vPixPosAbs.xyz;\n  float fViewDist2 = dot( vViewDist, vViewDist);\n\n  // transform pixel with cascaded matrix from abs to light texture space\n  float3 vPixPosLit = mulM43F( vPixPosAbs, c_ssi_mLightViewOrtho);\n\n  // and sample projector texture (attenuated by squared distance)\n  g_vShadowFactor = SampleOrthoProjector( vPixPosLit.xy, fViewDist2);\n\n  // calculate viewer distance\n  float fViewDist = sqrt( fViewDist2);\n  float fShadowFactor;\n\n  // calculate dithering offset\n  float2 vDitherOffset = step( frac( GetRasterPos().xy *0.5f), _tcast(float2,0.25f));  // (\"modulo\")\n  vDitherOffset.y += vDitherOffset.x;  // (y ^= x in floating point)\n  vDitherOffset.y = (vDitherOffset.y>1.1f) ? 0.0f : vDitherOffset.y;\n  vDitherOffset-= 0.5f;\n  vDitherOffset = vDitherOffset *c_ssi_fDitherRadius *c_ssi_f1oShadowMapSize;\n\n  // if using proper trilinear filtering (w/o dithering!)\n  #if SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING == 2\n\n    // choose 2 cascade buffer samples \n    float4 vPixPosLit0, vPixPosLit1;\n    float fDistRatio = ChooseCascade2( vPixPosLit, fViewDist, vPixPosLit0, vPixPosLit1);\n\n    // apply dithering and sample two shadow map samples there\n    vPixPosLit0.xy += vDitherOffset.xy;\n    vPixPosLit1.xy += vDitherOffset.xy;\n    // distances from light source to shadow caster in cascaded shadow map\n#if defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n    float fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance0;\n    float fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance1;\n    float fFactor0 = SampleCascadeShadow( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, vPixPosLit0, fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance0);\n    float fFactor1 = SampleCascadeShadow( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, vPixPosLit1, fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance1);\n    float fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance = lerp( fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance0, fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance1, fDistRatio);\n#else\n    float fFactor0 = SampleCascadeShadow( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, vPixPosLit0);\n    float fFactor1 = SampleCascadeShadow( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, vPixPosLit1);\n#endif\n    // and lerp by distance between those two shadow samples \n    fShadowFactor = lerp( fFactor0, fFactor1, fDistRatio);\n\n  // if no trilinear filtering\n  #else \n\n    // choose cascade buffer\n    float4 vPixPosCascade = ChooseCascade( vPixPosLit, fViewDist);\n\n    // apply dithering and sample shadow map there\n    vPixPosCascade.xy += vDitherOffset;\n#if defined(HAS_DISTANT_LIGHT)\n    float fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance;\n    fShadowFactor = SampleCascadeShadow( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, vPixPosCascade, fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance);\n#else\n    fShadowFactor = SampleCascadeShadow( t_sCascadeShd, s_tCascadeShd, vPixPosCascade);\n#endif\n\n  #endif // TRILINEAR\n\n  // distance between shadow caster and shadow receiver (current pixel)\n  fOutLightSourceShadowCasterDistance = fLightSourceShadowCasterDistance;\n\n  // colorize cascades (if needed)\n  #ifdef COLORIZE_CASCADED_SHADOWS\n\n    const float3 avColors[6] = {\n      float3( 1,1,0), float3( 1,0,1), float3( 0,1,1),\n      float3( 0,0,1), float3( 0,1,0), float3( 1,0,0) };\n    #if SHADOW_TRILINEAR_FILTERING == 2\n      int2 ivCascades = int2( vPixPosLit0.z, vPixPosLit1.z);\n      float3 vColor0 = avColors[ ivCascades.x];\n      float3 vColor1 = avColors[ ivCascades.y];\n      g_vShadowFactor = lerp( vColor0, vColor1, fDistRatio);\n    #else\n      int iCascade = int( vPixPosCascade.z);\n      g_vShadowFactor = avColors[ iCascade];\n    #endif\n\n  #else\n\n    // apply shadow factor\n    g_vShadowFactor *= fShadowFactor;\n\n  #endif\n\n  // return eventual shadow with or w/o projector\n  return g_vShadowFactor;\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(HAS_SPOT_LIGHT)\n\n\n// planar shadow\ninline float3 PlanarShadow( const float4 vPixPosAbs)\n{\n  // transform pixel position from absolute to light space\n  float4 vPixPosLit = mul( vPixPosAbs, c_ssi_mLightViewProj);\n\n  // adjust Z coordinate by depth offset\n  vPixPosLit.z += c_ssi_vMAddZ.y;\n\n  // X & Y coords to projective space\n  // (Z is in normalized meters)\n  vPixPosLit.xyz /= vPixPosLit.w;\n  // normalize to texture coord (0-1 range)\n  vPixPosLit.xy = vPixPosLit.xy *0.5f +0.5f;\n\n  // sample projector texture\n  float2 vProjCoord = vPixPosLit.xy * c_ssi_vProjectorStretch + c_ssi_vProjectorOffset;\n  g_vShadowFactor = shbTexSample2D( t_sPlanarProj, s_tPlanarProj, vProjCoord).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( g_vShadowFactor);\n\n  // calculate dithering offset\n  float2 vDitherOffset = step( frac( GetRasterPos().xy *0.5f), _tcast(float2,0.25f));  // (\"modulo\")\n  vDitherOffset.y += vDitherOffset.x;  // (y ^= x in floating point)\n  vDitherOffset.y = (vDitherOffset.y>1.1f) ? 0.0f : vDitherOffset.y;\n  vDitherOffset-= 0.5f;\n  vDitherOffset = vDitherOffset *c_ssi_fDitherRadius *c_ssi_f1oShadowMapSize;\n\n  vPixPosLit.xy += vDitherOffset;\n  float fShadowFactor = SamplePlanarShadow( t_sPlanarShd, s_tPlanarShd, vPixPosLit.xyz);\n\n  // apply shadow to projector\n  g_vShadowFactor *= fShadowFactor;\n\n  // return eventual shadow with or w/o projector\n  return g_vShadowFactor;\n}\n\n\n#elif defined(HAS_OMNI_LIGHT)\n\n\n// cube shadow calculation\ninline float3 CubeShadow( const float3 vPixDist)\n{\n  // tranform distant vector from abs to light cube-texture space\n  float3 vPixDistLit = mul( vPixDist, c_ssi_mLightView);\n  // and sample projector texture\n  g_vShadowFactor = shbTexSampleCube( t_sCubeProj, s_tCubeProj, vPixDistLit).rgb;\n  LinearSpace( g_vShadowFactor);\n  \n  // calc pixel distance from shadow cube center\n  float3 vDistAbs = abs( vPixDistLit);\n  float fDepthMax = max( max( vDistAbs.x, vDistAbs.y), vDistAbs.z);\n\n  // normalize depth by falloff distance\n\n  /* ORIGINAL:\n\n//fC = -(fFar+fNear)     /fn;\n//fD = -(2.0f*fFar*fNear)/fn;\n\n  float fNear= 0.01f;\n  float fFar = 1.0f / c_ssi_fNormalizedDistance;\n  float fDepth = (fFar+fNear) / (fFar-fNear) - (2*fFar*fNear)/(fFar-fNear)/fDepthMax;\n  fDepth = fDepth *0.5f +0.5f;\n  /*/\n  // OPTIMIZED:\n\n//_CregF( float2, c_ssi_fOmniDistFactors, 39);  // .x=(fFar+fNear)/(fFar-fNear)*0.5+0.5, .y=(fFar*fNear)/(fFar-fNear)\n  float fDepth = c_ssi_fOmniDistFactors.x - c_ssi_fOmniDistFactors.y/fDepthMax;\n  //*/\n  fDepth = saturate( fDepth *c_ssi_vMAddZ.x +c_ssi_vMAddZ.y);\n  float fShadowFactor;\n\n#if !SOFT_SHADOWS\n\n  fShadowFactor = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vPixDistLit, fDepth);\n\n#else\n\n  float3 vProjCoord = vPixDistLit / (fDepthMax*c_ssi_f1oShadowMapSize) *0.5f; // (0.5 for better filtering?)\n  float3 vWeights = frac( vProjCoord.xyz +0.5f);  // (0.5 for adjusting pixel center for bilinear)\n  vProjCoord.xyz -= vWeights; // floor()\n\n  float4 vShadows0, vShadows1;\n  vShadows0.x = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.y  += 1.0f;            // +float3(0,0,0)\n  vShadows0.y = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.xy += float2(1,-1);    // +float3(0,1,0)\n  vShadows0.z = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.y  += 1.0f;            // +float3(1,0,0)\n  vShadows0.w = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.xyz+= float3(-1,-1,1); // +float3(1,1,0)\n  vShadows1.x = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.y  += 1.0f;            // +float3(0,0,1)\n  vShadows1.y = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.xy += float2(1,-1);    // +float3(0,1,1)\n  vShadows1.z = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);  vProjCoord.y  += 1.0f;            // +float3(1,0,1)\n  vShadows1.w = texShadowCube( t_sCubeShd, s_tCubeShd, vProjCoord, fDepth);                                    // +float3(1,1,1)\n  // interpolate by Z\n  vShadows0.x = lerp( vShadows0.x, vShadows1.x, vWeights.z);\n  vShadows0.y = lerp( vShadows0.y, vShadows1.y, vWeights.z);\n  vShadows0.z = lerp( vShadows0.z, vShadows1.z, vWeights.z);\n  vShadows0.w = lerp( vShadows0.w, vShadows1.w, vWeights.z);\n  // interpolate by Y\n  vShadows0.x = lerp( vShadows0.x, vShadows0.y, vWeights.y);\n  vShadows0.y = lerp( vShadows0.z, vShadows0.w, vWeights.y);\n  // interpolate by X\n  fShadowFactor = lerp( vShadows0.x, vShadows0.y, vWeights.x);\n\n#endif // SOFT_SHADOWS\n\n  // modulate projector by shadow\n  g_vShadowFactor *= fShadowFactor;\n\n  // return eventual shadow with or w/o projector\n  return g_vShadowFactor;\n}\n\n\n#endif // (LIGHT TYPE)\n\n// #endif // PS_VER\n\n\n#if 0 // Receiver Plane Depth Bias\n\n\n// Packing derivatives of u,v, and distance to light source w.r.t. screen space x, and y\nduvdist_dx = ddx(projCoords);\nduvdist_dy = ddy(projCoords);\n\n// Invert texture Jacobian and use chain rule to compute ddist/du and ddist/dv\n//  |ddist/du| = |du/dx du/dy|-T * |ddist/dx|\n//  |ddist/dv| |dv/dx dv/dy| |ddist/dy|\n// Multiply ddist/dx and ddist/dy by inverse transpose of Jacobian\nfloat invDet = 1 / ((duvdist_dx.x * duvdist_dy.y) - (duvdist_dx.y * duvdist_dy.x) );\n\n// Top row of 2x2\nddist_duv.x = duvdist_dy.y * duvdist_dx.w ; // invJtrans[0][0] * ddist_dx\nddist_duv.x -= duvdist_dx.y * duvdist_dy.w ; // invJtrans[0][1] * ddist_dy\n// Bottom row of 2x2\nddist_duv.y = duvdist_dx.x * duvdist_dy.w ; // invJtrans[1][1] * ddist_dy\nddist_duv.y -= duvdist_dy.x * duvdist_dx.w ; // invJtrans[1][0] * ddist_dx\n\nddist_duv *= invDet;\n\n// compute depth offset and PCF taps 4 at a time\nfor(int i=0; i<9; i++)\n{\n  // offset of texel quad in texture coordinates;\n  texCoordOffset = (g_vFullTexelOffset * quadOffsets[i] );\n\n  // shadow map values\n  shadowMapVals = tex2D(ShadowSampler, projCoords.xy + texCoordOffset.xy );\n\n  // Apply receiver plane depth offset\n  dist = projCoords.w + (ddist_duv.x * texCoordOffset.x) + (ddist_duv.y * texCoordOffset.y);\n  inLight = ( dist < shadowMapVals );\n  percentInLight += dot(inLight, invNumTaps);\n}\n\n\n// simple and fast jitter \"rotation\"\n\nfloat2 jitterFactor = frac( inp.mShadowTexCoords.xy * float2( 18428.4f, 23614.3f)) * 2.0f - 1.0f;\n\n\n//This produces a simple 2d (or 3D, if you need it) pseudo-random value in the range -1..+1. We than scale this value by the size of the sample disc and use it as a simple vector multiplicator to scale the actual sample offset values.\n\n\nfloat2 offsetFactor = jitterFactor * gSizeOfYourSampleDisc;\n\nfloat shadowDepth0 = tex2D( TexShadow, input.mShadowTexCoords + gShadowSampleOffset[0] * offsetFactor);\nfloat shadowDepth1 = tex2D( TexShadow, input.mShadowTexCoords + gShadowSampleOffset[1] * offsetFactor);\nfloat shadowDepth2 = tex2D( TexShadow, input.mShadowTexCoords + gShadowSampleOffset[2] * offsetFactor);\n// and so on\n\n#endif // 0\n\n#endif // SHADOWBUFFER_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SHOCKWAVE EFFECT (vertex transformation)\n\n// used constant registers: c50-c82\n\n// (works only for vertex shader!)\n#if VS_VER\n\n#ifndef SHOCKWAVE_HS\n#define SHOCKWAVE_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// maximum number of shockwaves allowed\n#define MAX_SHOCKWAVES 32\n\n// shockwave structure\nstruct ShockwaveInfo\n{\n  // impact position\n  float4 swi_vImpactPos;\n  // time and envelope (in .xy!)\n  float4 swi_vTimeEnvelope;\n  // frequency, wavelength, hotspot, falloff\n  float4 swi_vWaveData;\n};\n\n#if _HLSL\n\n// shockwave effect data\nconst uniform ShockwaveInfo c_aswShockwaves[ MAX_SHOCKWAVES] : register(c50);\n\n// get one shockwave data\nstatic inline ShockwaveInfo _getShockwave( const int iIndex)\n{\n  // (simple as that)\n  return c_aswShockwaves[ iIndex];\n}\n#elif _GLSL\n\n// get one matrix for skinning\nstatic inline ShockwaveInfo _getShockwave( const int iIndex)\n{\n  // (need to construct shockwave info structure)\n  return ShockwaveInfo( c_avVexUniformsF[ 50+iIndex*3], c_avVexUniformsF[ 51+iIndex*3], c_avVexUniformsF[ 52+iIndex*3]);\n}\n#endif // API\n\n\n\n// calculate the effect of a shockwave\nstatic inline float3 DoShockwave( in float3 vVexPos, const float3 vPivotPos, in float3 vImpactPos,\n                                  in float2 vTimeEnvelope, in float4 vWaveData, const float fElasticity,\n                                  const float fSway, const float fShockwaveStrength)\n{\n  // name shockwave data\n  #define tmFromImpact vTimeEnvelope.x\n  #define fEnvelope    vTimeEnvelope.y\n  #define fFrequency   vWaveData.x \n  #define fWavelength  vWaveData.y\n  #define fHotSpot     vWaveData.z\n  #define fFallOff     vWaveData.w\n  \n  // calculate direction and distance from current point of impact\n  float3 vImpactDir = vPivotPos - vImpactPos;\n  float fImpactDistance = length( vImpactDir);\n  vImpactDir /= fImpactDistance;  // == normalize()\n  \n  // project current impact direction to Y plane\n  float3 vImpactDirXZ = float3( vImpactDir.x, 0.0f, vImpactDir.z);\n  // calculate length of projected impact vector\n  float fImpactDirProjLen = 0.001f+ length( vImpactDirXZ);\n  \n  // calculate velocity and angular frequency\n  float fVelocity = fFrequency * fWavelength;\n  float fAngularFrequency = 2.0f*PI * fFrequency;\n\n  // calculate distance fall-off from current point of impact\n  float fDistanceRatio = saturate( (fFallOff-fImpactDistance) / (fFallOff-fHotSpot));\n  // (quadratic looks better)\n  fDistanceRatio *= fDistanceRatio;\n \n  // calculate sway amplitude and phase\n  float fSwayAmplitude = fSway *10.0f +1.0f;\n  float fSwayPhase = fSway * fDistanceRatio;\n \n  // calculate current offset for given vertex\n  float fTime = tmFromImpact-fSwayPhase - fImpactDistance/fVelocity ;\n  float fDisplacement = fSwayAmplitude * sin( fAngularFrequency * fTime);\n  \n  // determine how much rotation should be applied (elasticity faking)\n  // (vertices closer to pivot's height rotate less, with linear fall off)  \n  float fRotationRatio = saturate( (vVexPos.y-vPivotPos.y) *fElasticity); \n  // (quadratic looks better)\n  fRotationRatio *= fRotationRatio;\n  \n  // determine total angular displacement using the following steps:\n  // 1. modulate displacement given by wave equation by distance falloff from initial impact point\n  // 2. add a slanting offset (max PI/2 rad, linear falloff with distance from current point of impact)\n  // 3. modulate total angular displacement by rotation ratio (elasticity faking) and envelope value (damping)\n  float fTotalDisplacement = fShockwaveStrength*fEnvelope *fRotationRatio*fDistanceRatio* (fDisplacement-0.5f*PI);\n  \n  // determine slanting axis\n  float3 vSlantingAxis = -vImpactDirXZ / fImpactDirProjLen;\n\n  // determine slanting amount\n  float fTan = tan( fTotalDisplacement);\n  // determine distance from pivot to vertex\n  float fDistanceFromPivot = length( vVexPos - vPivotPos);\n\n  // slant the vertex\n  vVexPos += vSlantingAxis *fTan *fDistanceFromPivot;\n  // but preserve original distance from pivot\n  return vPivotPos+ normalize( vVexPos-vPivotPos) *fDistanceFromPivot;\n  \n  // unname shockwave data\n  #undef fFallOff\n  #undef fHotSpot\n  #undef fWavelength\n  #undef fFrequency\n  #undef fEnvelope\n  #undef tmFromImpact\n}\n\n\n// apply one shockwave effect in absolute space\nstatic inline float3 ApplyOneShockwaveAbs( const int iIndex, float3 vVexPosAbs, const float3 vPivotPosAbs, \n                                           const float fElasticity, const float fSway, const float fShockwaveStrength)\n{\n  // get shockwave from array of shockwaves\n  ShockwaveInfo swi = _getShockwave( iIndex);\n  // and apply it to vertex position in absolute space\n  return DoShockwave( vVexPosAbs, vPivotPosAbs, swi.swi_vImpactPos.xyz,\n    swi.swi_vTimeEnvelope.xy, swi.swi_vWaveData, fElasticity, fSway, fShockwaveStrength);\n}\n\n\n// apply loaded shockwaves in absolute space\nvoid ApplyShockwavesAbs( in float fShockwavesCt, inout float3 vVexPosAbs, const float3 vPivotPosAbs, \n                         const float fElasticity, const float fSway, const float fShockwaveStrength)\n{\n  // loop thru shockwaves\n  int iSW = 0;\n  while( fShockwavesCt > 0.0f) {\n\n    // and apply one by one\n    vVexPosAbs = ApplyOneShockwaveAbs( iSW, vVexPosAbs, vPivotPosAbs, fElasticity, fSway, fShockwaveStrength);\n    fShockwavesCt -= 1.0f;\n    iSW++;\n  }\n}\n\n#endif // SHOCKWAVE_HS\n\n#endif // VS_VER\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// SPHERICAL HARMONICS\n\n// used constant registers: c14-c24\n\n#ifndef SPHERICALHARMONICS_HS\n#define SPHERICALHARMONICS_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n#if _HLSL\n\n  // spherical harmonics coefficients \n  const uniform float3 c_avSHCs[9] : register(c14);\n  // and theirs fetching function\n  static inline float3 _getSHC( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avSHCs[ iIndex];\n  }\n#elif _GLSL\n\n  // spherical harmonics coefficients fetching function\n  static inline float3 _getSHC( int iIndex) {\n    return c_avUniformsF[ iIndex+14].xyz;\n  }\n#endif // API\n\n\n// calculate spherical harmonics lighting\nfloat3 CalcSHLight( float3 vNorAbs)\n{\n  // use ambient component\n  float3 vSH = _getSHC(0); \n\n  // calc normal factors\n  float3 vNorSqr = vNorAbs.xyz * vNorAbs.xyz;\n  float3 vNorMix = vNorAbs.xzy * vNorAbs.zyx;\n  // and apply spherical harmonics lighting\n  vSH += _getSHC(1) * vNorAbs.x;\n  vSH += _getSHC(2) * vNorAbs.y;\n  vSH += _getSHC(3) * vNorAbs.z;\n  vSH += _getSHC(4) * vNorMix.x;\n  vSH += _getSHC(5) * vNorMix.y;\n  vSH += _getSHC(6) * vNorMix.z;\n  vSH += _getSHC(7) *(vNorSqr.z *3.0f -1.0f);\n  vSH += _getSHC(8) *(vNorSqr.x - vNorSqr.y);\n  // (SH can end up negative, so clamping is needed)\n  vSH = max( vSH, _tcast(float3,0));\n\n  // return ambient (and diffuse) light\n  return vSH;\n}\n\n#endif // SPHERICALHARMONICS_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// used constant registers: -\n\n#ifndef BASICTRANSFORMATIONS_HS\n#define BASICTRANSFORMATIONS_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// stretch tangent to object space transformation matrix by factor\ninline float3x3 StretchTanToObjMatrix( const float3x3 mTanToObj, const float4x2 mStretch)\n{\n  float3x3 mTanRot;\n  mTanRot[2] = float3( 0,0,1);\n#if _GLSL\n  mTanRot[0] = mStretch[0].xyz;\n  mTanRot[1] = mStretch[1].xyz;\n  return mul( mTanToObj, mTanRot);\n#elif _HLSL\n  mTanRot[0] = mStretch._m00_m10_m20;\n  mTanRot[1] = mStretch._m01_m11_m21;\n  return mul( mTanRot, mTanToObj);\n#endif\n}\n\n\n// construct tangent to object space transformation matrix\ninline float3x3 MakeTanToObjMatrix( const float3 vNor, const float4 vTan)\n{\n  // construct tangent-space transformation matrix\n  float3 vBin = cross( vNor*vTan.w, vTan.xyz);\n  return float3x3( vTan.xyz, vBin, vNor);\n}\n\n\n// construct tangent to absolute space plane transformation matrix\n// (if plane==0, it's X-plane, otherwise it's Y or Z-plane)\ninline float3x3 MakeTanToAbsPlaneMatrix( in float3 vNorAbs, float fPlane)\n{\n  // store normal\n  float3x3 mTanToAbs;\n  // (re)normalized\n  vNorAbs = normalize( vNorAbs);\n  mTanToAbs[2] = vNorAbs;\n\n  // apply sign to normal (-1 for Y&Z-plane mapping, +1 for X-plane)\n  vNorAbs *= fPlane;\n\n  // make tangent vector out of plane sign (1,0,0 for Y&Z-plane, 0,1,0 for X-plane)\n  fPlane = fPlane *0.5f +0.5f;\n  mTanToAbs[0] = float3( 1.0f-fPlane, fPlane, 0);\n\n  // complete tangent to object space transformation matrix\n  mTanToAbs[1] = cross( vNorAbs, mTanToAbs[0]);\n  mTanToAbs[0] = cross( mTanToAbs[1], vNorAbs);\n  return mTanToAbs;\n}\n\n\n// apply mapping mask (should original UV be used from UV-map or from X,Y or Z-plane)\n// (vMask: .xy=Y-coord mask, does it go to U, V or neither; .z=XZ-coords mask, use XZ or original UV)\ninline float2 SelectUV( in float2 vUV, const float3 vPosAbs, const float3 vMask)\n{\n  float4 vPosAbsAdj = vPosAbs.xyzz *float4(1,-1,-1,1) +0.5f;\n#if _HLSL\n  // take UV or XY\n  vUV = (vMask.zz>=0.0f) ? vPosAbsAdj.xy : vUV;\n  // put Z to U, V or nothing\n  vUV = (vMask.xy>=0.0f) ? vPosAbsAdj.zw : vUV;\n#else\n  // take UV or XY\n  vUV.x = (vMask.z>=0.0f) ? vPosAbsAdj.x : vUV.x;\n  vUV.y = (vMask.z>=0.0f) ? vPosAbsAdj.y : vUV.y;\n  // put Z to U, V or nothing\n  vUV.x = (vMask.x>=0.0f) ? vPosAbsAdj.z : vUV.x;\n  vUV.y = (vMask.y>=0.0f) ? vPosAbsAdj.w : vUV.y;\n#endif\n  return vUV;\n}\n\n// apply mask and return float4 (x,y,0,1)\ninline float4 SelectUV4( in float2 vUV, const float3 vPosAbs, const float3 vMask)\n{\n  float2 vRes = SelectUV( vUV, vPosAbs, vMask);\n  return float4( vRes, 0.0f, 1.0f);\n}\n\n\n\n// fix stretch factor of rotation matrix\n// (instead of it being stretched as transformation matrix, it should be stretched in oposite way;\n//  that way normals will fit to stretched surfaces, but this still doesn't work for tangents!)\ninline void FixRotationStretch( inout float3x3 mRot)\n{\n#if _GLSL\n  float3 v1oLen2 = 1.0f / (mRot[0]*mRot[0] + mRot[1]*mRot[1] + mRot[2]*mRot[2]);\n  mRot[0] *= v1oLen2;\n  mRot[1] *= v1oLen2;\n  mRot[2] *= v1oLen2;\n#else\n  float3 v1oLen2 = 1.0f / float3( dot( mRot[0], mRot[0]), dot( mRot[1], mRot[1]), dot( mRot[2], mRot[2]));\n  mRot[0] *= v1oLen2.xxx;\n  mRot[1] *= v1oLen2.yyy;\n  mRot[2] *= v1oLen2.zzz;\n#endif\n}\n\n\n// normalize rotation rotation matrix\ninline float3x3 NormalizeRotation( const float3x3 mRot)\n{\n  return float3x3( normalize( mRot[0]), normalize( mRot[1]), normalize( mRot[2]));\n}\n\n\n#endif // BASICTRANSFORMATIONS_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// used constant registers: -\n\n#ifndef BUMPNORMAL_HS\n#define BUMPNORMAL_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// normal vector that points up from surface (in tangent space)\nstatic const float3 gc_vNormalTanUp = float3(0,0,1);\n\n\n// calc normal's Z component from X and Y\ninline float CalcNormalZ( const float2 vNormal)\n{\n  // Z = 1 - sqrt( x^2 + y^2 )\n  // (extra .0001 to avoid compiler screaming about \"div by zero\")\n  float fZ = 1.0001f- dot( vNormal.xy, vNormal.xy);\n  return sqrt( saturate( fZ));\n}\n\n\n// bias normal by some amount\n// (0-2 are preffered values here)\ninline float3 BiasNormal( const float3 vNormalTan, const float fBias)\n{\n  // lerp to up-vector and renormalize\n  return normalize( lerp( gc_vNormalTanUp, vNormalTan, _tcast(float3,fBias)));\n}\n\n// TerrainCrumbsShaders.sh samples normal map in vertex shader, hence this check was removed\n//#if PS_VER\n\n\n// unpack unsigned normal X,Y\n#define nor2Du( nor) (nor.b>=0.001f ? nor.ga : nor.rg)\n\n\n// sphere map transform as used by Crytek, see this link (slide 13):\n// http://www.crytek.com/sites/default/files/A_bit_more_deferred_-_CryEngine3.ppt\n\n#define NRA_Crytek 1\n\ninline float4 norPack(in float3 vNor)\n{\n#if NRA_Old\n  return float4(vNormal.xy*0.5f + 0.5f, 0.0f, 0.0f);\n#endif\n\n#if NRA_Crytek\n  // store flipped normal because +Z is singularity (and most texels in most normaps are just slight deviations from 0,0,1)\n  vNor = -vNor;\n\n  // pack normal\n  float fNorXYLen = length(vNor.xy);\n  float2 vNor2 = vNor.xy * (sqrt(vNor.z*0.5f + 0.5f) / max(fNorXYLen, 0.0001f));\n  vNor2 = vNor2 * 0.5f + float2(0.5f, 0.5f);\n  return float4(vNor2, 0.0f, 0.0f);\n#endif\n}\n\n// unpack signed normal X,Y\ninline float2 nor2D( const float4 vNor4)\n{\n#if NRA_Old\n  // unpack normal\n  float2 vOutNor2 = nor2Du( vNor4);\n  // return signed\n  return vOutNor2.xy *2.0f -1.0f;\n#endif\n\n#if NRA_Crytek\n  // unpack normal\n  float2 vG = nor2Du(vNor4);  \n  vG = vG * 2.0f - 1.0f;  \n  float fA = saturate(dot(vG, vG));\n  float fB = sqrt(1.0f - fA) * 2.0f;\n  float2 vOutNor2 = vG * fB;\n  // normal was stored flipped to avoid singularity at +Z, so we reverse the flip\n  return -vOutNor2;\n#endif\n}\n\n\n// unpack normal X,Y and generate Z\ninline float3 nor3D( const float4 vNor4)\n{\n#if NRA_Old\n  // sample and unpack\n  float3 vOutNor3;\n  vOutNor3.xy = nor2D( vNor4);  \n  // generate Z\n  vOutNor3.z = CalcNormalZ( vOutNor3.xy);\n  return vOutNor3;\n#endif\n\n#if NRA_Crytek\n  // unpack normal\n  float2 vG = nor2Du(vNor4);  \n  vG = vG * 2.0f - 1.0f;\n  float fA = saturate(dot(vG, vG));\n  float fB = sqrt(1.0f - fA) * 2.0f;\n  float3 vOutNor3;\n  vOutNor3.xy = vG * fB;\n  vOutNor3.z = fA * 2.0f - 1.0f;\n  // normal was stored flipped to avoid singularity at +Z, so we reverse the flip\n  vOutNor3 = -vOutNor3;\n  return vOutNor3;\n#endif\n}\n\ninline float3 norAttenuate(const float3 vNor, const float fAtt)\n{\n  //return lerp(float3(0.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f), vNor, fAtt);\n  return float3(vNor.xy * fAtt, vNor.z);  \n}\n\n\n// See this link for details on various normal map blending algorithms:\n// http://blog.selfshadow.com/publications/blending-in-detail/\n\n#define NBA_Reoriented_Normal_Mapping 1\n\n// Blend two normals and return the result.\ninline float3 norBlend(const float3 vNor1, const float3 vNor2)\n{\n  // output normal\n  float3 vOutNor;\n\n#if NBA_Old\n  vOutNor.xy = vNor1.xy + vNor2.xy;\n  vOutNor.z = CalcNormalZ(vOutNor.xy);\n#endif\n\n#if NBA_Whiteout\n  vOutNor = float3(vNor1.xy + vNor2.xy, vNor1.z * vNor2.z);  \n#endif\n\n#if NBA_Unreal\n  vOutNor = float3(vNor1.xy + vNor2.xy, vNor1.z);\n#endif\n\n#if NDBA_Partial_Derivative_Blending\n  vOutNor = float3(vNor1.xy/vNor1.z + vNor2.xy/vNor2.z, 1.0f);\n#endif\n\n#if NBA_Reoriented_Normal_Mapping\n  float3 vT = float3(vNor1.x, vNor1.y, vNor1.z + 1.0f);\n  float3 vU = float3(-vNor2.x, -vNor2.y, vNor2.z);\n  vOutNor = vT * dot(vT, vU) - vU * vT.z;   \n#endif\n\n  return vOutNor;\n}\n\n#endif // BUMPNORMAL_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// used constant registers: c14-c17\n\n#ifndef ATMOSPHERICS_HS\n#define ATMOSPHERICS_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n// atmospheric scattering constants\n//===============================================================================\n// camera data\n_CregF( float4, c_vSunDirection0, 14);\nstatic float3 c_vSunDirection = c_vSunDirection0.xyz;\n\n_CregF( float4, c_vSunStrengthKm, 15);\nstatic float3 c_vSunStrength = c_vSunStrengthKm.xyz; // sun color and intensity, default [25,25,25]\nstatic float c_fKm = c_vSunStrengthKm.w; // Mie scattering coefficient, default [21e-6]\n\n_CregF( float4, c_KrHr, 16);\nstatic float3 c_vKr = c_KrHr.xyz; // Rayleigh scattering coefficients, default [5.5e-6, 13.0e-6, 22.4e-6]\nstatic float c_fHr = c_KrHr.w; // Rayleigh scale height, default [8000]\n\n_CregF( float3, c_HmGBlendFactor, 17);\nstatic float c_fHm = c_HmGBlendFactor.x; // Mie scale height, default [1200]\nstatic float c_fG = c_HmGBlendFactor.y; // Mie asymmetry factor, default [0.995], valid range [0-1]\nstatic float c_fBlendFactor = c_HmGBlendFactor.z; // Vertical blend factor, default [0.3], valid range [0-1]\n\n// #define DEFINE_USE_NOISE_FOR_CLOUDS\n\n#ifdef DEFINE_USE_NOISE_FOR_CLOUDS\nfloat CloudDensity(in float3 p) {\n  // this should be chnaged with procedural cloud function\n  // function should return 1.0f in places where cloud density\n  // is high and 0.0f where there are no clouds.\n  return 1.0f;\n}\n#endif\n\n// calculates ray-sphere intersection, returns near/far values\nfloat2 IntersectSphere( float3 vRayOrigin, float3 rd, float sr )\n{\n  float a = dot( rd, rd );\n  float b = 2.0f * dot( rd, vRayOrigin );\n  float c = dot( vRayOrigin, vRayOrigin ) - ( sr * sr );\n  float d = ( b * b ) - 4.0f * a * c;\n  if( d < 0.0f ) return float2( 1e5f, -1e5f );\n  return float2(\n    (-b - sqrt( d ) ) / ( 2.0f * a ),\n    (-b + sqrt( d ) ) / ( 2.0f * a ) );\n}\n\nvoid AtmosphericScattering( float3 vRayOrigin, float3 vRayDirection, out float3 vColor, out float3 vAttenuation, const in float fMaxDistance, const in float fAtmosphereAlpha )\n{\n  vColor = float3( 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f );\n  vAttenuation = float3( 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f );\n\n  float fPlanetRadius = 6371000.0f; // radius of the planet in meters\n  float fAtmosphereRadius = 6471000.0f; // radius of the atmosphere in meters\n  vRayOrigin.y += fPlanetRadius + 1000.0f;\n\n  const int dSkyScatteringRaySamples = fAtmosphereAlpha < 0.001f ? 1 : 10;\n  const int dSkyScatteringLightSamples = fAtmosphereAlpha < 0.001f ? 1 : 4;\n\n  const int iScatteringRaySamples = fMaxDistance < 0.0f ? dSkyScatteringRaySamples : 3;\n  const int iScatteringLightSamples = fMaxDistance < 0.0f ? dSkyScatteringLightSamples : 3;\n  const float fScatteringLightSamplesInv = 1.0f / _tcast(float,iScatteringLightSamples);\n\n  // calculate ray step size, different calculations if ray hits the\n  // terrain or atmosphere\n  float fRayStepSize = fMaxDistance / iScatteringRaySamples;\n  if( fRayStepSize < 0.0f ) {\n    float2 p = IntersectSphere( vRayOrigin, vRayDirection, fAtmosphereRadius );\n    if( p.x > p.y ) return;\n    fRayStepSize = p.y / iScatteringRaySamples;\n  }\n\n  float fRayDistance = 0.0f;\n\n  // total rayleigh and mie scattering\n  float3 vSumR = float3( 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f );\n  float3 vSumM = float3( 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f );\n\n  // optical depth\n  float fROpticalDepth = 0.0f;\n  float fMOpticalDepth = 0.0f;\n\n  for( int i = 0; i < iScatteringRaySamples; i++ )\n  {\n    float3 vPos = vRayOrigin + vRayDirection * ( fRayDistance + fRayStepSize * 0.5f );\n\n    // sample height\n    float fSampleHeight = length( vPos ) - fPlanetRadius;\n    if( fSampleHeight < 1000.1f ) fSampleHeight = 1000.1f;\n\n  #ifdef DEFINE_USE_NOISE_FOR_CLOUDS\n\n    float fCloudAttenuation = 0.0f;\n    const float fTime = 1.0f;\n    const float fCloudLowerHeight = 3000.0f;\n    const float fCloudUpperHeight = 7000.0f;\n    const float fCloudScale = 1.0f;\n    if( fSampleHeight >= fCloudLowerHeight && fSampleHeight < fCloudUpperHeight ) {\n      fCloudAttenuation = CloudDensity( ( vPos + float3( 23175.7f, 0.0f, -fTime*3e3f ) ) * fCloudScale );\n      fCloudAttenuation *= saturate( sin( 3.1415f * ( fSampleHeight - fCloudLowerHeight ) / ( fCloudUpperHeight - fCloudLowerHeight ) ) );\n    }\n    const float fCloudRayleighMultiplier = 3.0f;\n    const float fCloudMieMultiplier = 3.0f;\n\n    // optical depth\n    float fStepROpticalDepth = ( exp( -fSampleHeight / c_fHr ) + fCloudAttenuation * fCloudRayleighMultiplier ) * fRayStepSize;\n    float fStepMOpticalDepth = ( exp( -fSampleHeight / c_fHm ) + fCloudAttenuation * fCloudMieMultiplier ) * fRayStepSize;\n\n  #else // DEFINE_USE_NOISE_FOR_CLOUDS\n\n    // optical depth\n    float fStepROpticalDepth = exp( -fSampleHeight / c_fHr ) * fRayStepSize;\n    float fStepMOpticalDepth = exp( -fSampleHeight / c_fHm ) * fRayStepSize;\n\n  #endif\n\n    // increases optical depth\n    fROpticalDepth += fStepROpticalDepth;\n    fMOpticalDepth += fStepMOpticalDepth;\n\n    // light integration step\n    float fLightStepSize = IntersectSphere( vPos, c_vSunDirection, fAtmosphereRadius ).y * fScatteringLightSamplesInv;\n\n    float fLightRayDistance = iScatteringLightSamples * fLightStepSize - fLightStepSize * 0.5;\n    float fLightROpticalDepth = 0.0f;\n    float fLightMOpticalDepth = 0.0f;\n\n    for( int j = 0; j < iScatteringLightSamples; j++ )\n    {\n      // calculate height of the sample along light ray\n      float fHeightLight = length( vPos + c_vSunDirection * ( fLightRayDistance + fLightStepSize * 0.5 ) ) - fPlanetRadius;\n      if( fHeightLight < 10.1f ) fHeightLight = 10.1f;\n\n    #ifdef DEFINE_USE_NOISE_FOR_CLOUDS\n\n      if( fHeightLight >= fCloudLowerHeight && fHeightLight < fCloudUpperHeight ) {\n        fCloudAttenuation = CloudDensity( ( vPos + float3( 23175.7f, 0.0f, -fTime*3e3f ) ) * fCloudScale );\n        fCloudAttenuation *= saturate( sin( 3.1415f * ( fHeightLight - fCloudLowerHeight ) / ( fCloudUpperHeight - fCloudLowerHeight ) ) );\n      }\n      fLightROpticalDepth += ( exp( -fHeightLight / c_fHr ) + fCloudAttenuation * fCloudRayleighMultiplier ) * fLightStepSize;\n      fLightMOpticalDepth += ( exp( -fHeightLight / c_fHm ) + fCloudAttenuation * fCloudMieMultiplier ) * fLightStepSize;\n\n    #else\n\n      fLightROpticalDepth += exp( -fHeightLight / c_fHr ) * fLightStepSize;\n      fLightMOpticalDepth += exp( -fHeightLight / c_fHm ) * fLightStepSize;\n\n    #endif  \n\n      fLightRayDistance -= fLightStepSize;\n    }\n\n    // calculate attenuation\n    vAttenuation = exp( -( c_fKm * ( fMOpticalDepth + fLightMOpticalDepth ) + c_vKr * ( fROpticalDepth + fLightROpticalDepth ) ) );\n\n    // accumulate scattering\n    vSumR += fStepROpticalDepth * vAttenuation;\n    vSumM += fStepMOpticalDepth * vAttenuation;\n\n    fRayDistance += fRayStepSize;\n  }\n\n  // rayleigh and mie phases\n  float fMu = dot( vRayDirection, c_vSunDirection );\n  float fMuMu = fMu * fMu;\n  float fG2 = c_fG * c_fG;\n  float fRayleighPhase = 3.0f / ( 16.0f * PI ) * ( 1.0f + fMuMu );\n  float fMiePhase = 3.0f / ( 8.0f * PI ) * ( ( 1.0f - fG2 ) * ( fMuMu + 1.0f ) ) / ( pow( 1.0f + fG2 - 2.0f * fMu * c_fG, 1.5f ) * ( 2.0f + fG2 ) );\n\n  // inscattering color\n  vColor = c_vSunStrength * c_vKr * vSumR * fRayleighPhase;\n  \n  if( fMaxDistance < 0 )\n  {\n    vAttenuation = c_vSunStrength * c_fKm * vSumM * fMiePhase;\n\n    if( vRayDirection.y < -0.15f ) {\n      vColor = float3(0,0,0);\n      vAttenuation = float3(1,1,1);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n#endif // ATMOSPHERICS_HS\n""
""/* Copyright (c) 2002-2018 Croteam Ltd. All rights reserved. */\n\n// used constant registers: c8\n\n#ifndef BUMPMAPPING_HS\n#define BUMPMAPPING_HS 1\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n\n\n// bump and detail strenghts\n_CregF( float2, c_vBumpStrengths, 8);\n// static float c_fNormalBias = c_vBumpStrengths.x;\n// static float c_fDetailBias = c_vBumpStrengths.y;\n\n\n// get surface normal (in tangent space!) from normal and detail-map\n// (vNorDetBias.x=all bumps attenuation, .y=only detail bump attenuation)\ninline float3 GetBumpedNormal( sampler2D tNormalMap, SamplerState sNormalMap, sampler2D tDetailMap,\n                               SamplerState sDetailMap, const float4 vNorDetUVMap, in float2 vNorDetBias,\n                               out float4 vRawNorDet)\n{\n  // if using bump mapping\n#ifdef HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n  // sample base and detail normals\n  float3 vBaseNormal = nor3D( texSample2D( tNormalMap, sNormalMap, vNorDetUVMap.xy));\n  float3 vDetailNormal = nor3D( texSample2D( tDetailMap, sDetailMap, vNorDetUVMap.zw));\n\n  // attenuate normals\n  vNorDetBias*= c_vBumpStrengths;\n  vBaseNormal = norAttenuate(vBaseNormal, vNorDetBias.x);\n  vDetailNormal = norAttenuate(vDetailNormal, vNorDetBias.y);\n\n  // output XY parts of both base and detail normal (used later for fake bump mapping)\n  vRawNorDet.xy = vBaseNormal.xy;\n  vRawNorDet.zw = vDetailNormal.xy;\n\n  // return blended normal\n  return norBlend(vBaseNormal, vDetailNormal);\n\n  // if not using bump mapping\n#else \n\n  // just return up-vector Z-normal\n  return float3( 0,0,1);\n\n#endif // HAS_NORMAL_MAP\n}\n\n#endif // BUMPMAPPING_HS\n""

""\n#define _GLSL 1 \n#define _GLSL_METAL 0 \n#define _HLSL 0 \n#define _PSSL 0 \n#define PLATFORM_WIN 1 \n#define PLATFORM_LINUX 1 \n#define PLATFORM_ANDROID 1 \n#define PLATFORM_ORBIS 0 \n#define PLATFORM_OSX 0 \n\n""

""\n#if _HLSL==1 && !_PSSL\n\n/*\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*\n* Trade secret of Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.\n* Copyright (c) 2015 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. (unpublished)\n*\n* All rights reserved.  This notice is intended as a precaution against inadvertent publication and\n* does not imply publication or any waiver of confidentiality.  The year included in the foregoing\n* notice is the year of creation of the work.\n*\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\n\n/**\n*************************************************************************************************************\n* @File  amddxextshaderintrinsics.hlsl\n*\n* @brief\n*    AMD D3D Shader Intrinsics API hlsl file.\n*    This include file contains the shader intrinsics definitions (structures, enums, constant)\n*    and HLSL shader intrinsics functions.\n*\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\n\n#ifndef _AMDDXEXTSHADERINTRINSICS_HLSL_\n#define _AMDDXEXTSHADERINTRINSICS_HLSL_\n\n/**\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*   Definitions to construct the intrinsic instruction composed of an opcode and optional immediate data.\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_MagicCodeShift   28\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_MagicCodeMask    0xf\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_OpcodePhaseShift 24\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_OpcodePhaseMask  0x3\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_DataShift        8\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_DataMask         0xffff\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_OpcodeShift      0\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_OpcodeMask       0xff\n\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_MagicCode        0x5\n\n\n/**\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*   Intrinsic opcodes.\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsOpCode_ViewportIndex  0x10\n\n\n/**\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*   Resource and sampler slots for intrinsics using sample_l.\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\n//*\n#ifndef AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsResSlot\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsResSlot       t127\n#endif\nTexture3D<float4> AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsResource : register (AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsResSlot);\n//*/\n/*\n#ifndef AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsSamplerSlot\n#define AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsSamplerSlot   s15\n#endif\nSamplerState AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsSamplerState : register (AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsSamplerSlot);\n//*/\n\n/**\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*   MakeAmdShaderIntrinsicsInstruction\n*\n*   Creates instruction from supplied opcode and immediate data.\n*   NOTE: This is an internal function and should not be called by the source HLSL shader directly.\n*\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\nuint MakeAmdShaderIntrinsicsInstruction(uint opcode, uint opcodePhase, uint immediateData)\n{\n    return ((AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_MagicCode << AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_MagicCodeShift) |\n            (immediateData << AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_DataShift) |\n            (opcodePhase << AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_OpcodePhaseShift) |\n            (opcode << AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_OpcodeShift));\n}\n\n/**\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*   AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_GetViewportIndex\n*\n*   Returns current viewport index for replicated draws when MultiView extension is enabled (broadcast masks\n*   are set).\n*\n*   Available if CheckSupport(AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsSupport_MultiViewIndices) returned S_OK.\n*\n*   Only available in vertex/geometry/domain shader stages.\n*\n*************************************************************************************************************\n*/\n//*\nSamplerState MyLittleSampler\n{\n   // sampler state\n   Filter = MIN_MAG_MIP_LINEAR;\n   AddressU = MIRROR;\n   AddressV = MIRROR;\n\n   // sampler comparison state\n   ComparisonFunc = LESS;\n};\n//*/\nuint AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsics_GetViewportIndex()\n{\n    uint retVal;\n    uint instruction = MakeAmdShaderIntrinsicsInstruction(AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsOpCode_ViewportIndex, 0, 0);\n\n    retVal = asuint(AmdDxExtShaderIntrinsicsResource.SampleLevel(MyLittleSampler, float3(0, 0, 0), asfloat(instruction)).x);\n    return retVal;\n}\n\n\n#endif // AMD_HLSL_EXTENSION\n\n#endif // _HLSL==1 && !_PSSL\n""

""\n// FXAAShader.psh\n\n// (essential macros for parsing HLSL and GLSL!)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Macros.hs>\n// (various includes)\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/Misc.hs>\n#include <Engine/Graphics/Shader/Include/VREye.hs>\n\n// source texture to be AAed\n_Sreg2D( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, 0);\n\n// pixel size in source texture\n_CregF( float4, c_vCanvasPixSize, 0);\n_CregF( float4, c_vCoordsClamp, 1);\n_CregF( float4, c_vConsoleRcpFrameOpt , 2);\n_CregF( float4, c_vConsoleRcpFrameOpt2, 3);\n#define c_vConsoleConstDir c_vCanvasPixSize\n\n\n// color component weights be used for luminance calculations (in RGB order)\nstatic const float3 LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS = float3( 0.299f, 0.587f, 0.114f);\n\n// rectantle VS output = this PS input\nPS_IN_BEGIN\n  // (this must match by name and type output of rectangle vertex shader!)\n  _inReg( float4, vTexCoords, 0);  // source (.xy)\n  PS_IN_VR_REGS\nPS_IN_END\n\n\n/*============================================================================\n\n                    NVIDIA FXAA 3.11 by TIMOTHY LOTTES\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nCOPYRIGHT (C) 2010, 2011 NVIDIA CORPORATION. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nTO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED\n*AS IS* AND NVIDIA AND ITS SUPPLIERS DISCLAIM ALL WARRANTIES, EITHER EXPRESS\nOR IMPLIED, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF\nMERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. IN NO EVENT SHALL NVIDIA\nOR ITS SUPPLIERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY SPECIAL, INCIDENTAL, INDIRECT, OR\nCONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES WHATSOEVER (INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, DAMAGES FOR\nLOSS OF BUSINESS PROFITS, BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, LOSS OF BUSINESS INFORMATION,\nOR ANY OTHER PECUNIARY LOSS) ARISING OUT OF THE USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE\nTHIS SOFTWARE, EVEN IF NVIDIA HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH\nDAMAGES.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                           INTEGRATION CHECKLIST\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n(1.)\nIn the shader source, setup defines for the desired configuration.\nWhen providing multiple shaders (for different presets),\nsimply setup the defines differently in multiple files.\nExample,\n\n  #define FXAA_PC 1\n  #define FXAA_HLSL_5 1\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET 12\n\nOr,\n\n  #define FXAA_360 1\n  \nOr,\n\n  #define FXAA_PS3 1\n  \nEtc.\n\n(2.)\nThen include this file,\n\n  \"fxaa3_11.h\"\n\n(3.)\nThen call the FXAA pixel shader from within your desired shader.\nLook at the FXAA Quality fxaaPixelShader() for docs on inputs.\nAs for FXAA 3.11 all inputs for all shaders are the same \nto enable easy porting between platforms.\n\n  return fxaaPixelShader(...);\n\n(4.)\nInsure pass prior to FXAA outputs RGBL (see next section).\nOr use,\n\n  #define FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA 1\n\n(5.)\nSetup engine to provide the following constants\nwhich are used in the fxaaPixelShader() inputs,\n\n  float2 fxaaQualityRcpFrame,\n  float4 fxaaConsoleRcpFrameOpt,\n  float4 fxaaConsoleRcpFrameOpt2,\n  float4 fxaaConsole360RcpFrameOpt2,\n  float fxaaQualitySubpix,\n  float fxaaQualityEdgeThreshold,\n  float fxaaQualityEdgeThresholdMin,\n  float fxaaConsoleEdgeSharpness,\n  float fxaaConsoleEdgeThreshold,\n  float fxaaConsoleEdgeThresholdMin,\n  float4 fxaaConsole360ConstDir\n\nLook at the FXAA Quality fxaaPixelShader() for docs on inputs.\n\n(6.)\nHave FXAA vertex shader run as a full screen triangle,\nand output \"pos\" and \"fxaaConsolePosPos\" \nsuch that inputs in the pixel shader provide,\n\n  // {xy} = center of pixel\n  float2 pos,\n\n  // {xy__} = upper left of pixel\n  // {__zw} = lower right of pixel\n  float4 fxaaConsolePosPos,\n\n(7.)\nInsure the texture sampler(s) used by FXAA are set to bilinear filtering.\n\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                    INTEGRATION - RGBL AND COLORSPACE\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nFXAA3 requires RGBL as input unless the following is set, \n\n  #define FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA 1\n\nIn which case the engine uses green in place of luma,\nand requires RGB input is in a non-linear colorspace.\n\nRGB should be LDR (low dynamic range).\nSpecifically do FXAA after tonemapping.\n\nRGB data as returned by a texture fetch can be non-linear,\nor linear when FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA is not set.\nNote an \"sRGB format\" texture counts as linear,\nbecause the result of a texture fetch is linear data.\nRegular \"RGBA8\" textures in the sRGB colorspace are non-linear.\n\nIf FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA is not set,\nluma must be stored in the alpha channel prior to running FXAA.\nThis luma should be in a perceptual space (could be gamma 2.0).\nExample pass before FXAA where output is gamma 2.0 encoded,\n\n  color.rgb = ToneMap(color.rgb); // linear color output\n  color.rgb = sqrt(color.rgb);    // gamma 2.0 color output\n  return color;\n\nTo use FXAA,\n\n  color.rgb = ToneMap(color.rgb);  // linear color output\n  color.rgb = sqrt(color.rgb);     // gamma 2.0 color output\n  color.a = dot(color.rgb, float3(0.299, 0.587, 0.114)); // compute luma\n  return color;\n\nAnother example where output is linear encoded,\nsay for instance writing to an sRGB formated render target,\nwhere the render target does the conversion back to sRGB after blending,\n\n  color.rgb = ToneMap(color.rgb); // linear color output\n  return color;\n\nTo use FXAA,\n\n  color.rgb = ToneMap(color.rgb); // linear color output\n  color.a = sqrt(dot(color.rgb, float3(0.299, 0.587, 0.114))); // compute luma\n  return color;\n\nGetting luma correct is required for the algorithm to work correctly.\n\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                          BEING LINEARLY CORRECT?\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nApplying FXAA to a framebuffer with linear RGB color will look worse.\nThis is very counter intuitive, but happends to be true in this case.\nThe reason is because dithering artifacts will be more visiable \nin a linear colorspace.\n\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                             COMPLEX INTEGRATION\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nQ. What if the engine is blending into RGB before wanting to run FXAA?\n\nA. In the last opaque pass prior to FXAA,\n   have the pass write out luma into alpha.\n   Then blend into RGB only.\n   FXAA should be able to run ok\n   assuming the blending pass did not any add aliasing.\n   This should be the common case for particles and common blending passes.\n\nA. Or use FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA.\n\n============================================================================*/\n\n/*============================================================================\n\n                             INTEGRATION KNOBS\n\n/*==========================================================================*/\n#ifndef FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA\n  //\n  // For those using non-linear color,\n  // and either not able to get luma in alpha, or not wanting to,\n  // this enables FXAA to run using green as a proxy for luma.\n  //\n  // This will turn off AA on anything which lacks some amount of green.\n  // Pure red and blue or combination of only R and B, will get no AA.\n  //\n  // Might want to lower the settings for both,\n  //    fxaaConsoleEdgeThresholdMin\n  //    fxaaQualityEdgeThresholdMin\n  // In order to insure AA does not get turned off on colors \n  // which contain a minor amount of green.\n  //\n  // 1 = On.\n  // 0 = Off.\n  //\n  #define FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA 1\n#endif\n\n/*============================================================================\n                        FXAA QUALITY - TUNING KNOBS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nNOTE the other tuning knobs are now in the shader function inputs!\n============================================================================*/\n\n#ifndef FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET\n  //\n  // Choose the quality preset.\n  // This needs to be compiled into the shader as it effects code.\n  // Best option to include multiple presets is to \n  // in each shader define the preset, then include this file.\n  // \n  // OPTIONS\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 10 to 15 - default medium dither (10=fastest, 15=highest quality)\n  // 20 to 29 - less dither, more expensive (20=fastest, 29=highest quality)\n  // 39       - no dither, very expensive \n  //\n  // NOTES\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 12 = slightly faster then FXAA 3.9 and higher edge quality (default)\n  // 13 = about same speed as FXAA 3.9 and better than 12\n  // 23 = closest to FXAA 3.9 visually and performance wise\n  //  _ = the lowest digit is directly related to performance\n  // _  = the highest digit is directly related to style\n  // \n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET 23\n#endif\n\n\n/*============================================================================\n\n                           FXAA QUALITY - PRESETS\n\n============================================================================*/\n\n/*============================================================================\n                     FXAA QUALITY - MEDIUM DITHER PRESETS\n============================================================================*/\n#if (FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET == 10)\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_PS 3\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_P0 1.5f\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_P1 3.0f\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_P2 12.0f\n#endif\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n#if (FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET == 11)\n 12.0f\n#endif\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n#if (FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET == 12)\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_PS 5\n  #define FXAA_QUALITY_P0 1.0f\n  #define 8.0f\n#endif\n\n/*============================================================================\n                     FXAA QUALITY - EXTREME QUALITY\n============================================================================*/\n#if (FXAA_QUALITY_PRESET == 39)\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_PS 12\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P0 1.0f\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P1 1.0f\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P2 1.0f\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P3 1.0f\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P4 1.0f\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P5 1.5f\n    #define FXAA_QUALITY_P6 2.0f\n mipmap from texture\n#define fxaaTexTop( t,s, p)     texLod2D( t,s, MultiviewUV(p), 0.0f)\n#define fxaaTexOff( t,s, p,o,r) texLod2D( t,s, MultiviewUV(p+(o*r)), 0.0f)\n\n\n/*============================================================================\n                   GREEN AS LUMA OPTION SUPPORT FUNCTION\n============================================================================*/\n#if FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA == 0\n  static inline float fxaaLuma( float4 rgba) { return dot( rgba.rgb, LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS); }\n#else\n  static inline float fxaaLuma( float4 rgba) { return rgba.y; }\n#endif    \n\n\n/*============================================================================\n                             FXAA3 QUALITY\n============================================================================*/\n\n\nPS_ENTRY( fxaaPS)\n{    \n  PS_VR_INIT;\n  // get input coords \n  float2 posM = PS_IN( vTexCoords.xy);\n  // and clamp them to be inside (sub-)drawport\n  posM = clamp( posM, c_vCoordsClamp.xy, c_vCoordsClamp.zw);\n  //\n  // Only used on FXAA Quality.\n  // This used to be the FXAA_QUALITY_SUBPIX define.\n  // It is here now to allow easier tuning.\n  // Choose the amount of sub-pixel aliasing removal.\n  // This can effect sharpness.\n  //   1.00 - upper limit (softer)\n  //   0.75 - default amount of filtering\n  //   0.50 - lower limit (sharper, less sub-pixel aliasing removal)\n  //   0.25 - almost off\n  //   0.00 - completely off\n  const float fxaaQualitySubpix = 0.25f;\n  //\n  // Only used on FXAA Quality.\n  // This used to be the FXAA_QUALITY_EDGE_THRESHOLD define.\n  // It is here now to allow easier tuning.\n  // The minimum amount of local contrast required to apply algorithm.\n  //   0.333 - too little (faster)\n  //   0.250 - low quality\n  //   0.166 - default\n  //   0.125 - high quality \n  //   0.063 - overkill (slower)\n  const float fxaaQualityEdgeThreshold = 0.166f;\n  //\n  // Only used on FXAA Quality.\n  // This used to be the FXAA_QUALITY_EDGE_THRESHOLD_MIN define.\n  // It is here now to allow easier tuning.\n  // Trims the algorithm from processing darks.\n  //   0.0833 - upper limit (default, the start of visible unfiltered edges)\n  //   0.0625 - high quality (faster)\n  //   0.0312 - visible limit (slower)\n  // Special notes when using FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA,\n  //   Likely want to set this to zero.\n  //   As colors that are mostly not-green\n  //   will appear very dark in the green channel!\n  //   Tune by looking at mostly non-green content,\n  //   then start at zero and increase until aliasing is a problem.\n  const float fxaaQualityEdgeThresholdMin = 0.0833f;\n\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float4 rgbyM = fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM);\n  float lumaM;\n#if FXAA_GREEN_AS_LUMA == 0\n  lumaM = dot( rgbyM.rgb, LUMINANCE_WEIGHTS); // rgbyM.w\n#else\n  lumaM = rgbyM.y;\n#endif\n  float lumaS = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2( 0, 1), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n  float lumaE = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2( 1, 0), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n  float lumaN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2( 0,-1), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n  float lumaW = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2(-1, 0), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float maxSM = max(lumaS, lumaM);\n  float minSM = min(lumaS, lumaM);\n  float maxESM = max(lumaE, maxSM);\n  float minESM = min(lumaE, minSM);\n  float maxWN = max(lumaN, lumaW);\n  float minWN = min(lumaN, lumaW);\n  float rangeMax = max(maxWN, maxESM);\n  float rangeMin = min(minWN, minESM);\n  float rangeMaxScaled = rangeMax * fxaaQualityEdgeThreshold;\n  float range = rangeMax - rangeMin;\n  float rangeMaxClamped = max(fxaaQualityEdgeThresholdMin, rangeMaxScaled);\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  if( range < rangeMaxClamped) { PS_OUT( rgbyM); }\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float lumaNW = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2(-1,-1), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n  float lumaSE = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2( 1, 1), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n  float lumaNE = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2( 1,-1), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n  float lumaSW = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexOff( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posM, float2(-1, 1), c_vCanvasPixSize.xy));\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float lumaNS = lumaN + lumaS;\n  float lumaWE = lumaW + lumaE;\n  float subpixRcpRange = 1.0f/range;\n  float subpixNSWE = lumaNS + lumaWE;\n  float edgeHorz1 = (-2.0f * lumaM) + lumaNS;\n  float edgeVert1 = (-2.0f * lumaM) + lumaWE;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float lumaNESE = lumaNE + lumaSE;\n  float lumaNWNE = lumaNW + lumaNE;\n  float edgeHorz2 = (-2.0f * lumaE) + lumaNESE;\n  float edgeVert2 = (-2.0f * lumaN) + lumaNWNE;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float lumaNWSW = lumaNW + lumaSW;\n  float lumaSWSE = lumaSW + lumaSE;\n  float edgeHorz4 = (abs(edgeHorz1) * 2.0f) + abs(edgeHorz2);\n  float edgeVert4 = (abs(edgeVert1) * 2.0f) + abs(edgeVert2);\n  float edgeHorz3 = (-2.0f * lumaW) + lumaNWSW;\n  float edgeVert3 = (-2.0f * lumaS) + lumaSWSE;\n  float edgeHorz = abs(edgeHorz3) + edgeHorz4;\n  float edgeVert = abs(edgeVert3) + edgeVert4;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float subpixNWSWNESE = lumaNWSW + lumaNESE;\n  float lengthSign = c_vCanvasPixSize.x;\n  bool horzSpan = edgeHorz >= edgeVert;\n  float subpixA = subpixNSWE * 2.0f + subpixNWSWNESE;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  if(!horzSpan) lumaN = lumaW;\n  if(!horzSpan) lumaS = lumaE;\n  if( horzSpan) lengthSign = c_vCanvasPixSize.y;\n  float subpixB = (subpixA * (1.0f/12.0)) - lumaM;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float gradientN = lumaN - lumaM;\n  float gradientS = lumaS - lumaM;\n  float lumaNN = lumaN + lumaM;\n  float lumaSS = lumaS + lumaM;\n  bool pairN = abs(gradientN) >= abs(gradientS);\n  float gradient = max(abs(gradientN), abs(gradientS));\n  if(pairN) lengthSign = -lengthSign;\n  float subpixC = saturate(abs(subpixB) * subpixRcpRange);\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float2 posB = posM;\n  float2 offNP;\n  offNP.x = (!horzSpan) ? 0.0f : c_vCanvasPixSize.x;\n  offNP.y = ( horzSpan) ? 0.0f : c_vCanvasPixSize.y;\n  if(!horzSpan) posB.x += lengthSign * 0.5f;\n  if( horzSpan) posB.y += lengthSign * 0.5f;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  float2 posN = posB - offNP * FXAA_QUALITY_P0;\n  float2 posP = posB + offNP * FXAA_QUALITY_P0;\n  float subpixD = ((-2.0f)*subpixC) + 3.0;\n  float lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN));\n  float subpixE = subpixC * subpixC;\n  float lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP));\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  if(!pairN) lumaNN = lumaSS;\n  float gradientScaled = gradient * 1.0f/4.0;\n  float lumaMM = lumaM - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n  float subpixF = subpixD * subpixE;\n  bool lumaMLTZero = lumaMM < 0.0f;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  lumaEndN -= lumaNN * 0.5f;\n  lumaEndP -= lumaNN * 0.5f;\n  bool doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n  bool doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n  if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P1;\n  bool doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n  if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P1;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  if(doneNP) {\n    if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n    if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n    if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n    if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n    doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n    doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n    if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P2;\n    doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n    if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P2;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n  #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 3)\n    if(doneNP) {\n      if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n      if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n      if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n      if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n      doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n      doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n      if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P3;\n      doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n      if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P3;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n    #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 4)\n      if(doneNP) {\n        if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n        if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n        if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n        if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n        doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n        doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n        if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P4;\n        doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n        if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P4;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n      #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 5)\n        if(doneNP) {\n          if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n          if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n          if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n          if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n          doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n          doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n          if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P5;\n          doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n          if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P5;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n        #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 6)\n          if(doneNP) {\n            if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n            if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n            if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n            if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n            doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n            doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n            if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P6;\n            doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n            if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P6;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n          #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 7)\n            if(doneNP) {\n              if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n              if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n              if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n              if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n              doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n              doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n              if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P7;\n              doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n              if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P7;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n            #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 8)\n              if(doneNP) {\n                if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n                if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n                if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n                if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n                doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n                doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n                if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P8;\n                doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n                if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P8;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n              #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 9)\n                if(doneNP) {\n                  if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n                  if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n                  if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n                  if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n                  doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n                  doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n                  if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P9;\n                  doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n                  if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P9;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n                #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 10)\n                  if(doneNP) {\n                    if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n                    if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n                    if(!doneN) lumaEndN = lumaEndN - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n                    if(!doneP) lumaEndP = lumaEndP - lumaNN * 0.5f;\n                    doneN = abs(lumaEndN) >= gradientScaled;\n                    doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n                    if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P10;\n                    doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n                    if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P10;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n                  #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 11)\n                    if(doneNP) {\n                      if(!doneN) lumaEndN = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posN.xy));\n                      if(!doneP) lumaEndP = fxaaLuma( fxaaTexTop( t_sSrc, s_tSrc, posP.xy));\n      doneP = abs(lumaEndP) >= gradientScaled;\n                      if(!doneN) posN.xy -= offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P11;\n                      doneNP = (!doneN) || (!doneP);\n                      if(!doneP) posP.xy += offNP.xy * FXAA_QUALITY_P11;\n/*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\n                    #if (FXAA_QUALITY_PS > 12)\n
